century Irish history. \n 她是19世纪爱尔兰历史方面的国际权威。 \n]\n','2020-03-05',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uka/ukaur/ukauror027.mp3'),('autistic','自闭症','uk :ɔːˈtɪs.tɪk, us :ɑːˈtɪs.tɪk','[ne child in 5,000 is autistic.\n, The story is told from the viewpoint of an autistic child.\n, She was diagnosed as autistic at 18 months.\n]\n','2020-01-20',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english/uk_pron/u/uka/ukaut/ukautis002.mp3'),('automate','使自动化','uk :ˈɔː.tə.meɪt, us :ˈɑː.t̬ə-','[Massive investment is needed to automate the production process. \n 要实现生产过程的自动化需要大量的投资。 \n]\n','2019-10-03',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uka/ukaut/ukautis021.mp3'),('autonomy','自治，自治权自主，自主权','uk :ɔːˈtɒn.ə.mi, us :ɑːˈtɑː.nə.mi','[Demonstrators demanded immediate autonomy for their region. \n 游行示威者要求立即实现该地区的自治。 \n, The universities want to preserve their autonomy from central government. \n 大学都希望维护其自主办学权，不受中央政府的控制。 \n]\n','2019-10-07',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uka/ukaut/ukauton002.mp3'),('averse','反对的；嫌恶的；不愿意的','uk :əˈvɜːs, us :əˈvɝːs','[Few people are averse to the idea of a free holiday. \n 几乎没有人会反对免费假期这个主意。 \n, I\'m not averse to (= I like) the occasional glass of champagne myself. \n 我乐得偶尔自己来杯香槟酒。 \n]\n','2019-10-08',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uka/ukaut/ukauton027.mp3'),('avert','防止，避免转移（目光、想法等）；把…转（向别处）','uk :əˈvɜːt, us :əˈvɝːt',NULL,'2021-03-11',8,10,1,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uka/ukaut/ukauton029.mp3'),('avocado','鳄梨','uk :ˌæv.əˈkɑː.dəʊ, us :ˌæv.əˈkɑː.doʊ','[]\n','2019-12-26',0,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukcld/ukcld00050.mp3'),('awareness','意识','uk :əˈweə.nəs, us :əˈwer.nəs','[Public awareness of the problem will make politicians take it seriously. \n 一旦公众意识到这个问题，政客们就会严肃对待它了。 \n, Environmental awareness has increased dramatically over the past decade. \n 在过去的10年中，环保意识明显增强。 \n]\n','2020-01-23',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uka/ukavi/ukaviat026.mp3'),('awkward','难用的；棘手的；难处理的，难对付的令人尴尬的；使人难堪的尴尬的；局促不安的；为难的难相处的；不合作的；故意为难的笨拙的；别扭的；不灵活的；难看的','uk :ˈɔː.kwəd, us :ˈɑː.kwɚd','[It s an awkward corner, so take it slowly. \n 这个转弯不好过，开慢点儿。 \n, Some of the questions were rather awkward. \n 有些问题很难回答。 \n, It was an awkward ascent, but we reached the top eventually. \n 那段上坡路很难走，但最后我们还是爬到了山顶。 \n, [ + to infinitive ] \n My car s quite awkward to drive. \n 我的车很难开。 \n, He s an awkward customer (= a difficult person to deal with). \n 他是个很难应付的顾客。 \n, an awkward position/situation \n 令人尴尬的位置／局面 \n, There followed an awkward silence while we all tried to think of something to say. \n 然后是一段令人尴尬的沉默，我们都绞尽脑汁地想说点儿什么。 \n, They d chosen an awkward time to call as I d just got into the bath. \n 他们偏偏在我刚开始洗澡的时候来电话，真不是时候。 \n, The police asked some awkward questions about where the money had come from. \n 警方围绕钱的来源问了一些让人很难作答的问题。 \n, I always feel awkward when I m with Chris - he s so difficult to talk to. \n 我跟克里斯在一起总感到别扭——与他这人交谈太费劲儿。 \n, He seemed a little awkward when I first met him. \n 我第一次见他的时候，他有点儿放不开。 \n, Just stop being so awkward and help me push the car, will you! \n 别再跟我闹别扭了，快帮我推推车，好不好！ \n, His movements were slow and awkward. \n 他的动作迟缓笨拙。 \n]\n','2020-01-21',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uka/ukawe/ukawein010.mp3'),('awry','离开预期方向（的）；出错（的）曲（的）；歪（的）；斜（的）','uk :əˈraɪ, us :əˈraɪ','[Anything that goes awry (= goes wrong) in the office is blamed on Pete. \n 办公室什么事情出了岔子都会怪罪到皮特头上。 \n, The strike has sent the plans for investment seriously awry. \n 罢工严重打乱了投资计划。 \n, She rushed in, her face red and sweaty and her hat awry. \n 她冲了进来，满脸通红、一头大汗，帽子都歪了。 \n]\n','2020-03-05',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uka/ukawe/ukawein017.mp3'),('axis','轴（线）；中心线参考轴线，基准线，坐标线枢椎，第二颈椎轴心（指政府或从政者之间的联盟）（第二次世界大战中的）轴心国','uk :ˈæk.sɪs, us :ˈæk.sɪs','[The earth revolves around the axis that joins the North and South Poles. \n 地球围绕贯穿南北两极的地轴自转。 \n, The diameter of a circle is also an axis. \n 一个圆的直径也是一条轴线。 \n, Plot distance on the vertical y-axis against time on the horizontal x-axis. \n 用纵坐标Y轴表示距离，用横坐标X轴表示时间。 \n, the Franco-German axis \n 法德轴心 \n, the Axis powers/nations \n 轴心国 \n]\n','2020-03-19',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uka/ukawe/ukawein024.mp3'),('bachelor','独身男子，单身汉','uk :ˈbætʃ.əl.ər, us :ˈbætʃ.əl.ɚ','[He remained a bachelor until he was well into his 40s. \n 他一直到四十好几还是单身。 \n, Sam is a confirmed bachelor (= he is unlikely ever to want to get married). \n 西蒙是个信守独身主义的人。 \n]\n','2020-03-18',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uka/ukazt/ukazt__021.mp3'),('backstab','背刺','null','null\n','2020-01-09',0,0,0,'null'),('backstop','（英国圆场棒球运动中的）接手（棒球）接手（catcher的非正式说法）（棒球场上的）挡球网','uk :ˈbæk.stɒp, us :ˈbæk.stɑːp',NULL,'2021-03-08',3,8,1,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukb/ukbac/ukbackc030.mp3'),('bald','秃头的全秃的简单的；不加赘述的；不加详述的光滑的；磨平的','uk :bɔːld, us :bɑːld','[At 20 he was already going bald. \n 他20岁就开始谢顶了。 \n, When he took off his hat, we saw that he was as bald as a coot! \n 他脱帽后，我们发现他头全秃了！ \n, There was just this bald statement of resignation - no explanation or anything. \n 只有简单的辞职声明——没有解释之类的东西。 \n, The tyre was completely bald. \n 轮胎完全磨平了。 \n]\n','2020-02-21',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukb/ukbal/ukbalal005.mp3'),('bandit','土匪；盗贼；暴徒','uk :ˈbæn.dɪt, us :ˈbæn.dɪt','[]\n','2019-12-19',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukb/ukbal/ukballs027.mp3'),('banter','开玩笑，逗乐（善意地）取笑，逗弄','uk :ˈbæn.tər, us :ˈbæn.t̬ɚ','[He considered himself a master of witty banter. \n 他认为自己是风趣幽默的玩笑大王。 \n, He stood around bantering with his colleagues. \n 他转来转去，与同事们打趣逗乐。 \n]\n','2020-01-09',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukb/ukban/ukbanqu005.mp3'),('barely','仅；刚好；几乎没有','uk :ˈbeə.li, us :ˈber.li','[They have barely enough (= no more than what is needed) to pay the rent this month. \n 他们本月差点就付不起房租。 \n, She was barely (= only just) 15 when she won her first championship. \n 她首次获得冠军时刚刚15岁。 \n]\n','2020-03-11',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukb/ukbar/ukbareb005.mp3'),('barrage','掩护炮火，阻击火网连珠炮一样的（投诉、批评或质问），接二连三的…堰；拦河坝；拦潮坝','uk :ˈbær.ɑːʒ, us :bəˈrɑːʒ','[an artillery barrage \n 炮火掩护 \n, The TV station has received a barrage of complaints about the amount of violence in the series. \n 电视台接到了一连串的投诉，批评电视剧中的暴力镜头太多。 \n, He faced a barrage of questions over his handling of the problem. \n 就该问题的处理方式，他受到了接二连三的质问。 \n, The proposed tidal barrage would generate enough electricity to supply 80,000 homes. \n 提议修筑的拦潮坝发电量将足够8万户家庭使用。 \n]\n','2019-10-07',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukb/ukbar/ukbaroq007.mp3'),('barrel','桶桶（一桶石油相当于159升）枪管飞驰','uk :ˈbær.əl, us :ˈber.əl','[They drank a whole barrel of beer (= the contents of a barrel) at the party. \n 聚会上他们喝了整整一桶啤酒。 \n, We were barrelling along the autobahn at 180 kph. \n 我们以每小时180公里的速度在高速路上飞驰。 \n]\n','2019-12-26',0,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukb/ukbar/ukbaroq009.mp3'),('barricade','（尤指迅速设置的）障碍物，路障设路障于某物的对面、周围或前面','uk :ˈbær.ɪ.keɪd, us :ˈber.ə.keɪd','[Inmates erected a barricade between themselves and the prison guards. \n 囚犯们设置了路障把狱警和他们自己隔开。 \n, Barricade the doors! \n 堵住门！ \n, [ + adv/prep ] \n Terrified villagers have barricaded themselves into their houses. \n 惊恐不安的村民们把自己关在家里不出来。 \n]\n','2020-03-12',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukb/ukbar/ukbaroq011.mp3'),('bash','猛撞；猛击严厉批评，猛烈抨击聚会猛击；痛打试试看','uk :bæʃ, us :bæʃ','[He bashed his arm against a shelf. \n 他的胳膊猛地撞在了架子上。 \n, K \n I could hear her bashing away on the computer (= hitting the keys loudly). \n 我能听见她重重地敲击计算机键盘的声音。 \n, He kept bashing local government officials. \n 他不停地抨击当地政府官员。 \n, He had a big bash for his 18th birthday. \n 他举办了盛大的聚会庆祝自己的18岁生日。 \n, a bash on the head \n 猛击头部 \n, I ve never been skiing before, but I m prepared to have a bash (at it). \n 我以前从来没有滑过雪，但是我准备试试。 \n]\n','2020-01-10',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukb/ukbar/ukbaroq029.mp3'),('bastion','堡垒棱堡（城堡和堡垒的突出部分）','uk :ˈbæs.ti.ən, us :ˈbæs.ti.ən','[British public schools are regarded as one of the last bastions of upper-class privilege. \n 英国公学被视为上流阶级特权的最后堡垒之一。 \n]\n','2019-12-11',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukb/ukbas/ukbashf029.mp3'),('bat','球棒；球拍；球板蝙蝠（尤指女子）眨眼（以引起注意）用球棒（或球拍）击（球）','uk :bæt, us :bæt','[a baseball/cricket/rounders/table tennis bat \n 棒球球棒／板球球板／跑柱式棒球球棒／乒乓球球拍 \n, She smiled and batted her eyelashes at him. \n 她微笑着向他眨了眨眼睛。 \n, He batted the ball high into the air. \n 他放了一个高球。 \n, Jones will be the first to bat. \n 琼斯将是第一个击球的。 \n]\n','2020-03-11',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukb/ukbas/ukbashf030.mp3'),('batter','连续猛打（尤指妇女、儿童）（用面粉、鸡蛋和牛奶调成的）面糊（棒球等的）击球员','uk :ˈbæt.ər, us :ˈbæt̬.ɚ',NULL,'2021-03-08',6,8,1,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukb/ukbat/ukbatch021.mp3'),('beam','光线；光束；光柱（定向发出的）射束，粒子流（尤指支撑建筑物或其他结构的）梁，桁架，栋梁（女子体操运动中的）平衡木高兴的微笑，眉开眼笑辐射；发光；闪光；发射电波；播送','uk :biːm, us :biːm','[We could just pick out the trail in the weak beam of the flashlight. \n 我们借着手电筒微弱的光仅能勉强认清路。 \n, The rabbit stopped, mesmerized by the beam of the car s headlights. \n 兔子被汽车前灯射出的光束迷住了眼，停了下来。 \n, a laser beam \n 激光束 \n, an electron beam \n 电子波 \n, The sitting room had exposed wooden beams. \n 客厅顶上有裸露的木梁。 \n, She beamed with delight/pleasure at his remarks. \n 听完他的话她高兴得眉开眼笑。 \n, The child beamed at his teacher as he received the award. \n 那个孩子在领奖时对他的老师报以微笑。 \n, [ + speech ] \n  I m so pleased to see you,  he beamed (= said as he smiled). \n “见到你很高兴，”他微笑着说。 \n, The sun beamed (= shone brightly) down on the boat as it drifted along. \n 阳光照在缓缓漂动的船上。 \n, The concert was beamed (= broadcast) by satellite all over the world. \n 音乐会经卫星播送到世界各地。 \n]\n','2020-01-03',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukb/ukbat/ukbattl030.mp3'),('beckon',':ˈbek.ən,','uk','[The customs official beckoned the woman to his counter. \n 海关官员示意那个妇女到他桌前来。 \n, \"Hey you!\" she called, beckoning me over with her finger. \n “嘿，叫你呢！”她喊道，并用手指示意我过去。 \n, He beckoned to me, as if he wanted to speak to me. \n 他给我打手势，好像是要跟我说什么。 \n, For many young people, the bright lights of the city beckon, though a lot of them end up sleeping on the streets. \n 城市璀璨的灯火吸引了许多年轻人，然而其中许多人却最终落得露宿街头。 \n, She\'s an excellent student, for whom a wonderful future beckons. \n 她是个优秀的学生，美妙的前程向她召唤。 \n]','2019-10-09',0,1,0,'null'),('behalf','代表…，作为…的代表；代替…因为，为了…的利益','uk :bɪˈhɑːf, us :bɪˈhæf','[On behalf of the entire company, I would like to thank you for all your work. \n 我代表全公司对你的工作表示感谢。 \n, Unfortunately, George cannot be with us today so I am pleased to accept this award on his behalf. \n 遗憾的是乔治今天不能亲临，因此我很荣幸能替他领这个奖。 \n, She wasn t able to be present, so I signed the letter in her behalf. \n 她不能前来，所以我替她在信上署名。 \n, Please don t leave on my behalf. \n 请不要因为我而离开。 \n]\n','2020-03-19',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukb/ukbeg/ukbegui005.mp3'),('belie','给人以假象；掩饰（感情等）','uk :bɪˈlaɪ, us :bɪˈlaɪ','[Her calm face belied the terror she was feeling. \n 她平静的表情掩盖了内心的恐惧。 \n]\n','2020-01-09',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukb/ukbel/ukbelda006.mp3'),('bent','（bent 的过去式及过去分词）弯曲的；不直的；不平的（尤指当权者）不诚实的（尤指男性）同性恋的天赋','uk :bent, us :bent',NULL,'2021-03-08',3,8,1,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukb/ukben/ukbenev012.mp3'),('bestow','赠予；给予','uk :bɪˈstəʊ, us :bɪˈstoʊ','[The George Cross is a decoration that is bestowed upon/on British civilians for acts of great bravery. \n 乔治十字勋章是为了表彰英国平民的英勇行为而颁发的。 \n]\n','2019-12-13',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukb/ukbes/ukbesid017.mp3'),('bewildered','使迷惑，使糊涂；难住','uk :bɪˈwɪl.dər, us :bɪˈwɪl.dɚ','[The instructions completely bewildered me. \n 说明书把我完全弄糊涂了。 \n]\n','2020-02-28',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukb/ukbet/ukbetid023.mp3'),('beyond','更远；远于（范围）超出…；超过…太…而难以置信（无法修复，难以辨认等）（案件或罪行）证据确凿的，确实的令…无法理解；非…所能及','uk :biˈjɒnd, us :biˈjɑːnd','[In the distance, beyond the river, was a small town. \n 在河对岸的远处有一座小镇。 \n, From the top of the hill we could see our house and the woods beyond. \n 站在这个小山顶，能看到我们的房子和远处的森林。 \n, Few people live beyond the age of a hundred. \n 很少有人活过100岁。 \n, We cannot allow the work to continue beyond the end of the year. \n 我们不能允许这项工作延续到下一年。 \n, I ve got nothing to tell you beyond (= in addition to) what I told you earlier. \n 除了先前告诉你的以外，我没有别的可说了。 \n, The repercussions will be felt throughout the industry and beyond (= in other areas). \n 影响将波及整个产业及其他领域。 \n, Tonight s performance has been cancelled due to circumstances beyond our control (= events that we are unable to deal with). \n 由于出现了一些我们无法控制的情况，今晚的演出取消了。 \n, She has always lived beyond her means (= spent more than she has earned). \n 她生活总是入不敷出。 \n, His thoughtlessness is beyond belief. \n 他的轻率令人不可思议。 \n, He survived the accident, but his car was damaged beyond repair. \n 在车祸中他幸存了下来，但他的车却彻底报废了。 \n, Her guilt was established beyond reasonable doubt. \n 她的罪行确凿无疑。 \n, Physics is completely beyond me. \n 恐怕我根本就学不会物理。 \n]\n','2020-01-20',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/