:ˈboʊ.vaɪn','[a bovine virus \n 牛（痘）病毒 \n, He had a gentle, slightly bovine expression. \n 他表情温和，略显木讷。 \n]\n','2020-01-24',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukb/ukbou/ukbount009.mp3'),('bowl','碗；钵（物体的）碗状部分圆形运动场；圆形露天剧场草地滚木球戏（草地滚木球戏中所用的）木球；（保龄球运动中所用的）圆球（美国）美式橄榄球季后赛（在游戏中）滚动球把（球）投给击球员，投（球）','uk :bəʊl, us :boʊl','[a soup/cereal/salad/sugar bowl \n 汤碗／麦片粥碗／色拉钵／糖钵 \n, a bowl of soup/rice/porridge \n 一碗汤／米饭／粥 \n, She eats a bowl (= the contents of a bowl) of cereal every morning. \n 她每天早上吃一碗麦片粥。 \n, Sift the flour and baking powder into a mixing bowl. \n 将面粉和发酵粉筛进搅拌钵里。 \n, K \n Just put the dirty dishes in the washing-up bowl, and I ll do them later. \n 将脏碟子放进洗碗盆好了，我一会儿再洗。 \n, The toilet bowl was cracked and stained, and the walls were covered in mould. \n 抽水马桶破裂了，污迹斑斑，四周墙上到处都是霉点。 \n, the Hollywood Bowl \n 好莱坞露天剧场 \n, Bowls is one of the most popular sports in the UK . \n 草地滚球是英国最流行的运动之一。 \n, Pringle was tired after bowling for an hour. \n 投了一小时球后普林格尔累了。 \n]\n','2019-12-23',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukb/ukboe/ukboer_020.mp3'),('brawl','（乱哄哄的）斗殴，闹事斗殴，大打出手','uk :brɔːl, us :brɑːl','[a drunken brawl \n 醉酒斗殴 \n, The young men had nothing better to do than brawl in the streets. \n 这些年轻人除了在大街上打架斗殴做不出什么好事。 \n]\n','2020-01-10',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukb/ukbra/ukbraw_002.mp3'),('brawling','（乱哄哄的）斗殴，闹事斗殴，大打出手','uk :brɔːl, us :brɑːl','[a drunken brawl \n 醉酒斗殴 \n, The young men had nothing better to do than brawl in the streets. \n 这些年轻人除了在大街上打架斗殴做不出什么好事。 \n]\n','2020-02-21',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukb/ukbra/ukbraw_002.mp3'),('breach','破坏，违犯；违反，不履行扰乱治安（行为）违反（法律或规章）（攻击墙或防御工事时打出的）缺口破坏，违犯；违反，不履行（尤指为从背后突袭）在…上打开缺口','uk :briːtʃ, us :briːtʃ','[They felt that our discussions with other companies constituted a breach of/in our agreement. \n 他们认为我们与别的公司谈判违反了我们之间的协定。 \n, He was sued for breach of contract. \n 他因为违反合同而被起诉。 \n, There have been serious security breaches (= breaks in our security system). \n 安全体系出了大问题。 \n, The theatre was in breach of the safety laws for having no fire doors. \n 由于没有消防门，这家剧院违反了安全法规。 \n, A cannon ball had made a breach in their castle walls. \n 一颗炮弹在他们城堡的墙上打出了一个缺口。 \n, They breached the agreement they had made with their employer. \n 他们违反了曾与雇主达成的协议。 \n, Their defences were easily breached. \n 他们的防线轻而易举就被突破了。 \n]\n','2019-10-09',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukb/ukbra/ukbraw_013.mp3'),('brew','酿（啤酒）泡（茶）；煮（咖啡）；（茶）冲泡；（咖啡）煮（坏事或暴风雨）即将来临，酝酿（尤指某地或某个时间酿造的）啤酒一杯茶；一份啤酒混合物','uk :bruː, us :bruː','[[ + two objects ] \n He brewed us some coffee./He brewed some coffee for us. \n 他给我们煮了些咖啡。 \n, It was too quiet - I felt that trouble was brewing. \n 太安静了——我觉得要出事了。 \n, A storm was brewing in the distance. \n 远处一场暴风雨即将来临。 \n, Make us a brew, Bren. \n 布伦，给我们泡杯茶吧。 \n, They gave her a strange brew to drink. \n 他们让她喝一种奇怪的混合饮料。 \n, War, with its fear, its deprivation, its excitement and violence makes for a very heady brew (= powerful combination). \n 战争是恐惧、剥夺、刺激和暴力诸因素的混合体，给人以强烈震撼。 \n]\n','2020-01-03',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukb/ukbre/ukbrew_001.mp3'),('briefly','短暂地；简短地简言之，一言以蔽之','uk :ˈbriːf.li, us :ˈbriːf.li','[We chatted briefly about the weather. \n 我们聊了几句天气。 \n, Briefly, the company needs to cut its expenditure. \n 简言之，公司需要缩减开支。 \n]\n','2019-12-26',0,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukb/ukbre/ukbrew_028.mp3'),('bronchiolitis','毛细支气管炎','bräŋ-kē-ō-ˈlī-təs','null\n','2020-01-23',0,0,0,'null'),('bronchitis','支气管炎','uk :brɒŋˈkaɪ.tɪs, us :brɑːŋˈkaɪ.t̬əs','[]\n','2020-01-23',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uka/ukad5/ukad5080.mp3'),('bronze','青铜古铜色，青铜色青铜塑像铜牌古铜色的，青铜色的','uk :brɒnz, us :brɑːnz','[The church bells are made of bronze. \n 教堂大钟是青铜制成的。 \n, He got a bronze in the high jump. \n 他跳高得了铜牌。 \n]\n','2020-01-09',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukb/ukbro/ukbroke014.mp3'),('brow','额头山顶；悬崖边缘；峭壁顶端','uk :braʊ, us :braʊ','[She wrinkled her brow as she thought. \n 她思考时皱起眉头。 \n, He paused at the top of the hill and mopped his brow (= rubbed the sweat away). \n 他在山顶停了会儿，擦去额头上的汗。 \n, the brow of the hill \n 山顶 \n]\n','2020-02-28',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukb/ukbro/ukbroug003.mp3'),('brown','棕色（的），褐色（的）（把食物）炒成褐色','uk :braʊn, us :braʊn','[dark/light brown \n 深褐色／浅褐色 \n, Lightly brown the onion before adding the tomatoes. \n 加西红柿之前先把洋葱炒至略呈褐色。 \n, Allow the meat to brown before adding the vegetables. \n 把肉炒成褐色再加蔬菜。 \n]\n','2020-02-27',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukb/ukbro/ukbroug006.mp3'),('brute','残忍的人（尤指大个的）野兽；牲畜强力，极大的力量','uk :bruːt, us :bruːt','[[ as form of address ] \n Take your hands off me, you brute! \n 把手松开，你这畜牲！ \n, Your dog s an ugly brute, isn t it? \n 你那条狗是个丑陋的家伙，对吧？ \n, The oldest elephant was lame, poor brute. \n 那头最老的大象腿跛了，可怜的家伙。 \n, In the end she used brute force to push him out. \n 最后她使出吃奶的力气将他推了出去。 \n]\n','2020-01-17',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukb/ukbro/ukbroug017.mp3'),('bucket','（有提梁的）桶','uk :ˈbʌk.ɪt, us :ˈbʌk.ɪt','[Armed with a bucket and a mop, I started washing the floor. \n 提着桶和拖把，我开始拖地板。 \n, K \n I took my two-year-old nephew down to the beach with his bucket and spade. \n 我带两岁的小外甥去海滩，拿着他的小桶和铲子。 \n]\n','2019-10-03',0,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukb/ukbru/ukbrusq022.mp3'),('burglarize','入室盗窃','uk :ˈbɜː.ɡəl, us :ˈbɝː.ɡəl','[When they got back from their holiday they found that their home had been burgled. \n 他们度假回来时发现家中被盗了。 \n]\n','2020-01-03',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukb/ukbun/ukbunny025.mp3'),('bust','（女子的）胸部，胸围半身像逮捕；搜捕击碎；打破；弄坏逮捕；突击搜查（建筑物等）并逮捕疑犯坏的，损坏的破产','uk :bʌst, us :bʌst','[I couldn t find any blouses in my bust size. \n 我找不到适合我胸围的衬衫。 \n, There was a bust of Mahler on his desk. \n 他书桌上有一尊马勒的半身像。 \n, In their latest drugs bust police entered a warehouse where cocaine dealers were meeting. \n 在最近的毒品搜捕行动中，警方突袭了一个可卡因毒贩正在进行交易的仓库。 \n, Oh no! I bust his MP3 player. \n 噢，不好！我弄坏了他的MP3播放机。 \n, The police busted him because they think he s involved with a terrorist group. \n 警方认为他与恐怖团伙有牵连而逮捕了他。 \n, I think my watch is bust. \n 我想我的表坏了。 \n, More than 20 companies in the district went bust during the last three months. \n 过去的3个月里这一地区有超过20家公司破产。 \n]\n','2019-12-23',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukb/ukbus/ukbushr012.mp3'),('cabbie','出租车司机，计程车司机','uk :ˈkæb.i, us :ˈkæb.i','[]\n','2019-12-26',0,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukb/ukbys/ukbysta013.mp3'),('cabinet','内阁贮藏柜；陈列柜；橱柜','uk :ˈkæb.ɪ.nət, us :ˈkæb.ən.ət','[The Cabinet meet/meets every Thursday. \n 内阁成员每周四开会。 \n, The President is completing the selection of his new Cabinet. \n 首相已宣布新内阁名单。 \n, a cabinet post \n 内阁大臣 \n, K \n a cabinet reshuffle (= changes in the Cabinet). \n 内阁改组 \n, K \n a cabinet minister \n 内阁部长 \n, Valuable pieces of china were on display in a glass-fronted cabinet. \n 贵重瓷器陈列在正面是玻璃的柜子里。 \n, a bathroom/filing cabinet \n 浴室／文件柜 \n]\n','2019-12-26',0,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukb/ukbys/ukbysta017.mp3'),('cache','隐藏物；隐藏所（计算机的）高速缓冲存储器','uk :kæʃ, us :kæʃ','[an arms cache \n 武器隐藏地 \n, a cache of explosives/weapons/drugs \n 一批隐藏的炸药／武器／毒品 \n, 256 Kb secondary cache \n 256千字节二级高速缓冲存储器 \n]\n','2019-12-27',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukb/ukbys/ukbysta022.mp3'),('cadre','（军队、政治或商业组织的）骨干队伍，干部队伍干部','uk :ˈkɑː.dər, us :ˈkɑː.dɚ','[]\n','2020-03-05',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukcad/ukcad__012.mp3'),('calamity','灾难；灾祸','uk :kəˈlæm.ə.ti, us :kəˈlæm.ə.t̬i','[A series of calamities ruined them - floods, a failed harvest, and the death of a son. \n 一连串的灾难击垮了他们——洪水、歉收、丧子。 \n]\n','2020-02-28',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukcaj/ukcajun009.mp3'),('campus','（大学）校园，校区','uk :ˈkæm.pəs, us :ˈkæm.pəs','[There s accommodation for about five hundred students on campus. \n 校区内可供约500名学生住宿。 \n]\n','2019-12-26',0,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukcam/ukcambo029.mp3'),('cancer','癌，癌症（迅速蔓延的）弊病，恶习巨蟹宫（黄道第4宫）；出生于巨蟹宫时段（即在6月22日至7月22日之间）的人','uk :ˈkæn.sər, us :ˈkæn.sɚ','[He died of liver cancer. \n 他死于肝癌。 \n, cancer of the cervix/stomach \n 子宫颈／胃癌 \n, breast/bowel/lung cancer \n 乳腺／肠／肺癌 \n, cancer cells \n 癌细胞 \n, a cancer patient \n 癌症患者 \n, It was a secondary cancer. \n 这是继发癌症。 \n, Drug abuse is a cancer that is destroying our society. \n 滥用毒品是正在毁灭我们社会的毒瘤。 \n]\n','2020-02-21',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukcam/ukcamsh013.mp3'),('capacity','容积，容量；生产能力；（尤指某人或某组织的）办事能力职位；工作；角色','uk :kəˈpæs.ə.ti, us :kəˈpæs.ə.t̬i','[The stadium has a seating capacity of 50,000. \n 这个体育场能容纳5万人。 \n, The game was watched by a capacity crowd/audience of 50,000 (= the place was completely full). \n 比赛场座无虚席，5万观众观看了比赛。 \n, She has a great capacity for hard work. \n 她特别能吃苦耐劳。 \n, The purchase of 500 tanks is part of a strategy to increase military capacity by 25 percent over the next five years. \n 购买500辆坦克是在今后5年里将军事力量增加25%的战略计划的一部分。 \n, [ + to infinitive ] \n It seems to be beyond his capacity to (= he seems to be unable to) follow simple instructions. \n 他好像连简单的指令也听不懂。 \n, Do you think it s within his capacity to (= do you think he ll be able to) do the job without making a mess of it? \n 你认为他有能力完成这项工作而不把它搞砸吗？ \n, The generators each have a capacity of (= can produce) 1,000 kilowatts. \n 每台发电机都有1000千瓦的发电能力。 \n, The larger cars have bigger capacity engines (= the engines are bigger and more powerful). \n 大轿车引擎功率也比较大。 \n, All our factories are working at (full) capacity (= are producing goods as fast as possible). \n 我们所有的工厂都在满负荷运行。 \n, We are running below capacity (= not producing as many goods as we are able to) because of cancelled orders. \n 因为订单取消，我们的工厂开工不足。 \n, He suffered a stroke in 2008, which left him unable to speak, but his mental capacity (= his ability to think and remember) wasn t affected. \n 2008年他得了中风，不能说话了，但是思维能力没有受影响。 \n, She guides tourists at the Martin Luther King Jr. Birth Home in her capacity as a National Park Service ranger. \n 作为国家公园管理局的管理员，她陪同游客参观马丁·路德·金的出生地。 \n, She was speaking in her capacity as a novelist, rather than as a television presenter. \n 她是作为小说家而不是电视节目主持人在发言。 \n]\n','2020-01-23',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukcan/ukcant_021.mp3'),('capital market','资本市场','Zīběn shìchǎng','\n','2019-10-07',0,1,0,'https://translate.google.cn/translate_tts?ie=UTF-8&q=capital market&tl=ja&tk=508598.128706&client=webapp&prev=input'),('capricious','反复无常的','uk :kəˈprɪʃ.əs, us :kəˈprɪʃ.əs','[a capricious child \n 任性的小孩 \n, He was a cruel and capricious tyrant. \n 他是个残忍而又反复无常的暴君。 \n]\n','2019-12-20',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukcap/ukcapit010.mp3'),('caption','（图书、杂志或报纸图片的）说明文字图片说明','uk :ˈkæp.ʃən, us :ˈkæp.ʃən','[The picture was captioned  Catherine Deneuve in Belle du Jour . \n 照片说明写道“凯瑟琳·德纳芙在《白日美人》中”。 \n, a captioned photograph \n 一幅带有文字说明的照片 \n]\n','2020-04-01',5,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukcap/ukcapit020.mp3'),('cardinal','（罗马天主教会的）红衣主教，枢机主教基数红衣凤头鸟（见于北美，雄鸟有鲜红色的羽毛）极重要的；基本的；主要的','uk :ˈkɑː.dɪ.nəl, us :ˈkɑːr.dɪ.nəl','[Cardinals elect and advise the Pope. \n 红衣主教们推选教皇并担当教皇的顾问。 \n, a cardinal rule/error/sin \n 基本规则／根本错误／严重错误 \n]\n','2020-01-20',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukcar/ukcarap027.mp3'),('carnage','屠杀','Túshā','\n','2019-10-28',0,0,0,'https://translate.google.cn/translate_tts?ie=UTF-8&q=carnage &tl=ja&tk=460853.80961&client=webapp&prev=input'),('carve','（尤指在石头或木头上）雕刻把（熟肉）切成小片','uk :kɑːv, us :kɑːrv','[This totem pole is carved from/out of a single tree trunk. \n 这根图腾柱是由一整根树干雕刻而成的。 \n, He carved her name on a tree. \n 他将她的名字刻在了树上。 \n, Some of the tunnels in the cliff are natural, some were carved out (= cut into the rock) by soldiers for defensive purposes. \n 峭壁中的一些隧道是天然形成的，一些是士兵们在石头上开凿出来用于防御的。 \n, Would you like me to carve (the chicken)? \n 您要我（把鸡肉）切成小块吗？ \n]\n','2019-12-11',0,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukcal/ukcalip022.mp3'),('casual','（衣服）休闲的；便装的不在意的；不放在心上的；漫不经心的不固定的；不定期的；临时的不经意的，随意的；碰巧的','uk :ˈkæʒ.u.əl, us :ˈkæʒ.u.əl','[casual clothes \n 休闲服 \n, The psychologist s attitude seemed far too casual, even brutal. \n 那个心理学家的态度似乎太过冷淡了，甚至有些冷酷。 \n, Security around the conference hotel seemed almost casual. \n 举行会议的酒店周围的安全措施似乎不太严格。 \n, Although close to tears, she tried to make her voice sound casual. \n 尽管都快掉眼泪了，可她还是尽力使自己的声音听上去满不在乎。 \n, casual labour/labourers/workers \n 零工／临时工 \n, casual sex \n 随便的性关系 \n, It was just a casual comment, I didn t mean it to be taken so seriously. \n 我只是随便说说而已，不是当真的。 \n, To a casual observer, everything might appear normal. \n 对于一个漫不经心的人来说，也许看上去一切正常。 \n]\n','2020-02-28',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukcas/ukcaste007.mp3'),('catalyst','催化剂促成变化的人；引发变化的事件','uk :ˈkæt.əl.ɪst, us :ˈkæt̬.əl.ɪst','[The high suicide rate acted as a catalyst for change in the prison system. \n 高自杀率促成了监狱系统的改革。 \n]\n','2020-03-17',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukcas/ukcaste019.mp3'),('catastrophic','严重的破坏','uk :ˌkæt.əˈstrɒf.ɪk, us :ˌkæt̬.əˈstrɑː.fɪk','[n unchecked increase in the use of fossil fuels could have catastrophic results for the planet.\n, A catastrophic storm made landfall on US soil.\n, he had to put her catastrophic Olympic performance out of her mind.\n]\n','2019-10-08',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukcas/ukcaste026.mp3'),('cathartic','解气','uk :kəˈθɑː.tɪk, us :kəˈθɑːr.tɪk','[ cathartic experience\n, I find it very cathartic to dance. \n]\n','2019-12-19',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukcat/ukcatch021.mp3'),('cathedral','（一个教区内的）总教堂，大教堂','uk :kəˈθiː.drəl, us :kəˈθiː.drəl','[Salisbury Cathedral \n 索尔兹伯里大教堂 \n]\n','2020-03-25',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukcat/ukcatch022.mp3'),('cattle','牛','uk :ˈkæt.əl, us :ˈkæt̬.əl','[beef/dairy cattle \n 肉／奶牛 \n]\n','2020-01-24',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukcat/ukcatsu005.mp3'),('caution','谨慎，小心，慎重（警察对违法者的）口头警告告诫；警告，提醒（足球比赛中，裁判出示黄牌作出的）警告（警察）正式警告告诫；提醒（足球比赛中，裁判出示黄牌）警告','uk :ˈkɔː.ʃən, us :ˈkɑː.ʃən','[We need to proceed with/exercise caution (= be careful in taking action, making decisions, etc.) \n 我们必须谨慎行事。 \n, They treated the story of his escape with (some/great/extreme) caution (= thought that it might not be true). \n 他们对他逃跑的报道有些／相当／极为怀疑。 \n, As it was her first offence, she was only given a caution. \n 由于是初犯，所以只给了她一个口头警告。 \n, Just a word of caution - the cheaper models probably aren t worth buying. \n 只是提醒一句——更为便宜的型号很可能不值得购买。 \n, The newspaper cautioned its readers against buying shares without getting good advice first. \n 报纸告诫读者事先没有获得好的建议，不要购买股票。 \n]\n','2020-03-31',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukcat/ukcatsu024.mp3'),('cellar','（通常用于储物的）地窖，地下室','uk :ˈsel.ər, us :ˈsel.ɚ','[]\n','2020-03-11',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukcel/ukceleb013.mp3'),('certificate','证书；证明成绩合格证书；毕业证书','uk :səˈtɪf.ɪ.kət, us :sɚˈtɪf.ə.kət','[a birth/marriage/death certificate \n 出生／结婚／死亡证明 \n, a doctor s/medical certificate \n 医生／医疗证明 \n, She has a Certificate in Drama Education. \n 她有戏剧教育资格证书。 \n]\n','2020-03-05',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukcer/ukcereb016.mp3'),('cervical','子宫颈的颈椎的','uk :səˈvaɪ.kəl, us :ˈsɝː.vɪ.kəl','[cervical cancer \n 宫颈癌 \n, cervical screening \n 宫颈癌筛查 \n, cervical compression \n 颈椎压迫 \n]\n','2020-02-19',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/c/ces/cespu/cespuk000203.mp3'),('chancellor','','uk :ˈtʃɑːn.səl.ər, us :ˈtʃæn.səl.ɚ','[Helmut Kohl became the first Chancellor of a united Germany in 1990. \n 赫尔穆特‧科尔于1990年成为德国统一后的首任总理。 \n, A former politician has been appointed Chancellor of the university. \n 一位昔日的政治人物被委任为大学校长。 \n]\n','2021-03-26',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukcha/ukchamo011.mp3'),('channel','电视台；电视频道（水或其他液体流通的）管道，渠道；航道英吉利海峡（交流的）途径，渠道（提供产品、信息等的）渠道，方法（机场或港口检查旅客行李的）通道引导；把…导入，将…引入模仿（某人的举止等）','uk :ˈtʃæn.əl, us :ˈtʃæn.əl','[a cable/terrestrial/satellite channel \n 有线／地面／卫星频道 \n, a music/movie/news/shopping/sports channel \n 音乐／电影／新闻／购物／体育频道 \n, the news on Channel 4 \n 四频道的新闻 \n, She switched/turned to another channel to watch football. \n 她换到另一个频道看足球赛。 \n, There are drainage/irrigation channels all over this flat agricultural land. \n 在这片平坦的农田上遍布着排水／灌溉渠。 \n, The boats all have to pass through this narrow channel. \n 所有船只都必须通过这条狭窄的航道。 \n, We re going to have a day-trip across the Channel. \n 我们将进行一次横渡英吉利海峡的一日游。 \n, We took the car to France overnight on a (cross-)channel ferry. \n 我们用横渡英吉利海峡的渡船把汽车运到了法国。 \n, We must open the channels of communication between the two countries. \n 我们必须打开两国之间的交流渠道。 \n, The government pursued every diplomatic/official channel to free the hostages. \n 政府寻求一切外交／官方渠道以使人质获释。 \n, Complaints should be made through the proper/usual channels. \n 应当通过适当的／正常的渠道进行投诉。 \n, The insurer sells its products through a variety of distribution channels, including banks. \n 保险公司通过包括银行在内的各种渠道销售其产品。 \n, If you have nothing to declare, go through the green channel. \n 如果你没有东西要申报，就走绿色通道。 \n, Goods to declare - use the red channel. \n 有商品要报税——走红色通道。 \n, Ditches were constructed to channel water away from the buildings. \n 修造了沟渠把水引离建筑物。 \n, If she could only channel all that energy into something useful. \n 要是她能把那些精力都倾注到有用的事情上就好了。 \n, A lot of money has been channelled into research in that particular field. \n 大笔经费投入到了那个领域的研究中。 \n, The band were dressed in 1960s outfits and seemed to be channelling the Beatles. \n 这支乐队身着60年代的服装，似乎是在模仿甲壳虫乐队。 \n]\n','2020-01-10',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukcha/ukchamo023.mp3'),('chant','重复地说（或唱）；反复吟唱；反复念诵反复地（用简单的调子）颂唱祷文反复说（或吟唱）的词语','uk :tʃɑːnt, us :tʃænt','[The crowd were chanting the team s name. \n 人群正反复呼唤着自己足球队的名字。 \n, Demonstrators chanted anti-government slogans in the square. \n 示威者在广场上呼喊反政府口号。 \n, We could hear the monks chanting. \n 我们能听到和尚们在念经。 \n, The fans started to sing the familiar football chant,  Here we go, here we go, here we go!  \n 球迷们开始反复唱那支熟悉的足球歌：Here we go，here we go，here we go！ \n]\n','2020-03-05',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukcha/ukchamo024.mp3'),('chaperone','（尤指旧时在公共场所陪伴未婚少女的）年长女伴陪检护士（陪女病人接受男医生检查的女护士）；监护警察（在公共场所保护受害者）（青年社交活动中在场监护的）年长者；行为监督人（在拍摄过程中照顾儿童演员的）监护人（尤指旧时在公共场所为未婚少女）陪伴，陪同（青年社交活动中成年人在场）监督，陪同','uk :ˈʃæp.ə.rəʊn, us :ˈʃæp.ɚ.oʊn','[umorous \n She asked me to go to the cinema with her and Andrew, I think as a sort of chaperone. \n 她要我跟她和安德鲁去看电影，我想是让我去做年长女伴。 \n, Several parents acted as chaperones for the school dance. \n 有几位家长在学校的舞会做行为监督人。 \n, Her mother and sister acted as chaperones during filming. \n 在电影拍摄过程中，她的妈妈和姐姐作为监护人照顾她。 \n, Do you trust him on your own or do you want me to chaperone you? \n 你是信任跟他单独去呢，还是想让我陪你去？ \n, Several parents volunteered to chaperone class field trips. \n 班级的实地考察活动有几位家长自愿陪同。 \n]\n','2020-03-13',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukcha/ukchaot010.mp3'),('characteristic','特色，特点，特征特有的，典型的','uk :ˌkær.ək.təˈrɪs.tɪk, us :ˌker.ək.təˈrɪs.tɪk','[Unfortunately a big nose is a family characteristic. \n 不幸的是，大鼻子是家族特征。 \n, Sentimentality seems a characteristic of all the writers of that period. \n 多愁善感似乎是那个时期所有作家的特征。 \n, The male bird displays (= has) several characteristics which distinguish him from the female. \n 雄鸟有几个有别于雌鸟的特征。 \n, With the hospitality so characteristic of these people, they opened their house to over 50 guests. \n 这些人生性好客，他们敞开家门接待了五十多位客人。 \n, She behaved with characteristic dignity. \n 她表现出自己特有的尊严。 \n, The creamy richness is characteristic of the cheese from this region. \n 奶味浓郁是该地区出产的奶酪的特色。 \n]\n','2019-10-07',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukcha/ukchaot022.mp3'),('charity','慈善事业；慈善组织，慈善机构仁慈，宽容，友善','uk :ˈtʃær.ə.ti, us :ˈtʃer.ə.t̬i','[She does a lot of work for charity. \n 她做了很多慈善工作。 \n, People tend to give to (= give money to) charity at Christmas time. \n 人们往往在圣诞节向慈善组织捐钱。 \n, Proceeds from the sale of these cards will go to (= be given to) local charities. \n 卖这些贺卡所得的收益将捐献给地方慈善组织。 \n, UNICEF is an international charity. \n 联合国儿童基金会是国际性慈善组织。 \n, They did a charity performance on the first night, to raise money for AIDS research. \n 他们的首晚演出是慈善义演，为艾滋病研究募集资金。 \n]\n','2020-02-13',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukcha/ukcharg012.mp3'),('chart','图表；示意图；曲线图海图；航图（每周唱片销量）排行榜用图表表示；标示仔细观察；详细记录制定（行动计划）（音乐）进榜，上榜','uk :tʃɑːt, us :tʃɑːrt','[There is a chart on the classroom wall showing the relative heights of all the children. \n 教室墙上有一张图表，显示出所有孩子的相对身高。 \n, The sales chart shows a distinct decline in the past few months. \n 销售图表明在过去几个月里销售量明显下降。 \n, the TV weather chart \n 电视气象图 \n, a naval chart \n 海军航图 \n, the dance charts \n 舞曲排行榜 \n, It s been number one in the charts for six weeks. \n 它占据排行榜之首已达6周之久。 \n, We need some sort of graph on which we can chart our progress. \n 我们需要那种可以在上面标出我们进展的图表。 \n, The map charts the course of the river where it splits into two. \n 地图在这条河分成两条支流处标出了水流流向。 \n, A global study has just been started to chart the effects of climate change. \n 一项观察记录气候变化后果的全球性研究才刚刚起步。 \n, The local branch of the party is meeting to chart their election campaign. \n 该政党的地方分部正开会制定他们的选举活动计划。 \n, Their first record didn t even chart. \n 他们的首张唱片连排行榜都没有进。 \n]\n','2020-03-25',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukcha/ukcharg025.mp3'),('chewing','咀嚼；嚼碎（尤指为品尝味道而）嚼，咬嚼，咀嚼咀嚼物（越嚼越软的）硬糖；口香糖','uk :tʃuː, us :tʃuː','[This meat is difficult to chew. \n 这肉很难嚼。 \n, You don t chew your food enough - that s why you get indigestion. \n 你没把食物嚼烂——这就是你消化不良的原因。 \n, Would you like some gum to chew? \n 你想吃口香糖吗？ \n, She gave the children some sweets to chew (on) during the long car journey. \n 在漫长的汽车旅行途中，她给了孩子们些糖果嚼着吃。 \n, She sat in the dentist s waiting room, nervously chewing (at) (= biting) her nails. \n 她坐在牙医的候诊室里，紧张地咬着指甲。 \n, dog chews \n 狗咬胶 \n]\n','2019-12-26',0,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukche/ukchess007.mp3'),('chick','雏鸟，幼鸟；（尤指）小鸡（冒犯性用语）女孩；少女；小妞儿','uk :tʃɪk, us :tʃɪk','[]\n','2019-12-26',0,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukche/ukchess017.mp3'),('chlorine','氯，氯气','uk :ˈklɔː.riːn, us :ˈklɔːr.iːn','[The chlorine in the pool makes my eyes sore. \n 游泳池里的氯气刺得我眼睛发疼。 \n]\n','2020-01-03',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukchi/ukchirp021.mp3'),('choke','（使）窒息；（使）哽噎；（使）呼吸困难（掐住喉咙）使停止呼吸，使窒息堵塞，阻塞；塞满（通常指在运动中关键时刻因丧失信心而）失败；怯场（机动车上的）阻风门，阻塞门','uk :tʃəʊk, us :tʃoʊk','[She choked to death on a fish bone. \n 她被鱼刺卡住后窒息而亡。 \n, Children can choke on peanuts. \n 小孩子吃花生会噎住的。 \n, Peanuts can choke a small child. \n 花生会噎住小孩。 \n, At lunchtime the streets were choked with traffic. \n 午餐时大街上塞车了。 \n, He could score points at will during the qualifying matches, but in the final he completely choked. \n 他在预选赛中总能随心所欲地得分，可到了决赛发挥就完全失常了。 \n]\n','2020-03-19',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukcho/ukchock009.mp3'),('chore','日常琐事；杂务；乏味的例行工作','uk :tʃɔːr, us :tʃɔːr','[I\'ll go shopping when I\'ve done my chores (= done the jobs in or around the house). \n 我把家务琐事干完后要去购物。 \n, I find writing reports a real chore (= very boring). \n 我觉得写报告真是件烦人的事。 \n]\n','2019-10-07',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukcho/ukchora003.mp3'),('chorus','（通常在歌曲每一节后的）副歌，合唱部分；合唱曲合唱曲合唱团，歌咏队歌舞队；伴舞；伴唱（古希腊戏剧中解释剧情的）歌队，合唱队异口同声齐声说；异口同声地说','uk :ˈkɔː.rəs, us :ˈkɔːr.əs','[I ll sing the verses and I d like you all to join in the chorus. \n 我唱独唱部分，我希望你们都加入合唱。 \n, They burst into a chorus of (= they sang the song) Happy Birthday. \n 他们突然开始齐唱“祝你生日快乐”。 \n, The choir will be performing the Hallelujah Chorus at the concert. \n 唱诗班将在音乐会上演唱《哈利路亚大合唱》。 \n, He sings with the Los Angeles Gay Men s Chorus. \n 他在洛杉矶男同性恋合唱团演唱。 \n, She quickly left the chorus for a starring role. \n 她很快离开歌舞队去出演一个主要角色。 \n, a chorus girl \n 歌舞队女演员 \n, The newcomers added their voices to the chorus expressing delight at the result. \n 新来的人和大家一起为这个结果欢呼雀跃。 \n, There was a chorus of disapproval/complaint/condemnation at his words (= everyone complained together). \n 大家一致反对／抱怨／谴责他说的话。 \n,  Not now,  the children chorused in unison,  we re watching TV.  \n “现在不要，”孩子们齐声嚷道，“我们正在看电视。” \n]\n','2020-03-18',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukcho/ukchora009.mp3'),('chronicle','编年史；年代记；大事记（报纸名称）…新闻，…记事报记述，记录（大事）；把…载入编年史','uk :ˈkrɒn.ɪ.kəl, us :ˈkrɑː.nɪ.kəl','[the Anglo-Saxon Chronicle \n 《盎格鲁-撒克逊人编年史》 \n, a chronicle of the French Revolution \n 法国大革命编年史 \n, the Hampshire Chronicle \n 《汉普郡记事报》 \n, The book chronicles the writer s coming to terms with his illness. \n 这本书记述了作者慢慢学会忍受自己病痛的前后过程。 \n]\n','2020-02-21',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukchr/ukchron001.mp3'),('circumstance','条件，情况；情形，形势无法控制的因素；客观环境；命运经济状况','uk :ˈsɜː.kəm.stɑːns, us :ˈsɝː.kəm.stæns','[I think she coped very well under the circumstances. \n 我觉得在那种情况下她处理得很不错。 \n, Obviously we can\'t deal with the problem until we know all the circumstances. \n 显然，我们只有了解全部情况后才能处理这问题。 \n, She died in suspicious circumstances. \n 她死得很蹊跷。 \n, We oppose capital punishment in/under any circumstances. \n 无论在什么情况下，我们都不赞成死刑。 \n, Under no circumstances should you (= you should not) approach the man. \n 你无论如何都不应该联系那个男人。 \n, The meeting has been cancelled due to circumstances beyond our control. \n 会议因不可控情况的出现而被取消了。 \n, They were victims of circumstance. \n 他们是客观环境的牺牲品。 \n, We were obliged to go by force of circumstance. \n 形势所迫，我们不得不走。 \n, Grants are available depending on your circumstances. \n 视经济状况，符合条件可获得助学金。 \n, By now she was alone and living in reduced circumstances (= with little money). \n 现在她孤单一人，生活拮据。 \n]\n','2019-10-08',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukcin/ukcinna026.mp3'),('circumstances','条件，情况；情形，形势无法控制的因素；客观环境；命运经济状况','uk :ˈsɜː.kəm.stɑːns, us :ˈsɝː.kəm.stæns','[I think she coped very well under the circumstances. \n 我觉得在那种情况下她处理得很不错。 \n, Obviously we can t deal with the problem until we know all the circumstances. \n 显然，我们只有了解全部情况后才能处理这问题。 \n, She died in suspicious circumstances. \n 她死得很蹊跷。 \n, We oppose capital punishment in/under any circumstances. \n 无论在什么情况下，我们都不赞成死刑。 \n, Under no circumstances should you (= you should not) approach the man. \n 你无论如何都不应该联系那个男人。 \n, The meeting has been cancelled due to circumstances beyond our control. \n 会议因不可控情况的出现而被取消了。 \n, They were victims of circumstance. \n 他们是客观环境的牺牲品。 \n, We were obliged to go by force of circumstance. \n 形势所迫，我们不得不走。 \n, Grants are available depending on your circumstances. \n 视经济状况，符合条件可获得助学金。 \n, By now she was alone and living in reduced circumstances (= with little money). \n 现在她孤单一人，生活拮据。 \n]\n','2020-04-03',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukcin/ukcinna026.mp3'),('cite','举例，引证引用，引述援引；传唤，传讯（军队中公开）嘉奖，表彰，表扬','uk :saɪt, us :saɪt','[She cited three reasons why people get into debt. \n 她举出了人们为何负债的3个原因。 \n, The company cited a 13 percent decline in new orders as evidence that overall demand for its products was falling. \n 公司举出新订单减少13%这一事实，以此来证明对其产品的总需求在下降。 \n, She cites both T.S. Eliot and Virginia Woolf in her article. \n 她在文章中引用了T.S.艾略特和弗吉尼娅•吴尔夫的作品。 \n, The lawyer cited two similar cases. \n 律师援引了两个类似的案例。 \n, He has been cited as the co-respondent in the divorce case. \n 他作为这起离婚案的共同被告被传讯。 \n, He was cited for bravery. \n 他因为勇敢而受到嘉奖。 \n]\n','2020-02-13',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukcir/ukcirrh008.mp3'),('civil','文职的；民用的；平民的，国民的民事的有礼貌的；文明的；客气的','uk :ˈsɪv.əl, us :ˈsɪv.əl','[Helicopters are mainly used for military rather than civil use. \n 直升机主要用于军事而非民用。 \n, After ten years of military dictatorship, the country now has a civil government. \n 经历了10年军事专制统治后，该国现在有了一个文官政府。 \n, We weren t married in church, but we had a civil ceremony in a registry office. \n 我们没在教堂结婚，不过在婚姻登记处举行了个世俗仪式。 \n, The matter would be better dealt with in the civil court rather than by an expensive criminal proceeding. \n 这事最好在民事法庭处理，而不要进行昂贵的刑事诉讼。 \n, His manner was civil, though not particularly friendly. \n 他的态度很客气，尽管不是特别友好。 \n]\n','2020-02-13',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukcir/ukcirrh021.mp3'),('claimant','要求者；索赔人；认领人','uk :ˈkleɪ.mənt, us :ˈkleɪ.mənt','[]\n','2020-03-05',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukciv/ukcivvy009.mp3'),('clandestine','（尤指从事不被官方允许的活动）秘密的，暗中的，私下的','uk :klænˈdes.tɪn, us :klænˈdes.tɪn','[The group held weekly clandestine meetings in a church. \n 这个团体每星期都在教堂举行秘密集会。 \n, He has been having a clandestine affair with his secretary for three years. \n 他和秘书私通已有3年了。 \n, She undertook several clandestine operations for the CIA. \n 她执行过中央情报局的好几次秘密行动。 \n]\n','2020-03-05',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukciv/ukcivvy022.mp3'),('classier','流行的；时髦的；豪华的','uk :ˈklɑː.si, us :ˈklæs.i','[That s one classy vehicle you ve got there. \n 你那辆车真是太气派了。 \n]\n','2020-03-25',2,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukcla/ukclass004.mp3'),('clatter','（使）发出响亮的撞击声；（使）哐啷作响','uk :ˈklæt.ər, us :ˈklæt̬.ɚ','[Don t clatter the dishes - you ll wake the baby up. \n 别把碗碟碰得叮当响——会把宝宝吵醒的。 \n, He was clattering away at his keyboard. \n 他在键盘上咔嗒咔嗒打东西。 \n]\n','2020-04-01',4,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukcla/ukclass005.mp3'),('clinical','门诊的，临床的冷漠的；无动于衷的；无感情的无特色的；冷冰冰的；朴素的','uk :ˈklɪn.ɪ.kəl, us :ˈklɪn.ɪ.kəl','[clinical tests/training \n 临床试验／实习 \n, the Department of Clinical Medicine \n 临床医学部 \n, Clinical trials of the new drug may take five years. \n 这种新药的临床试验可能需要5年时间。 \n, She seems to have a very clinical attitude towards her children. \n 她好像对子女们态度很冷漠。 \n, We were going to paint our kitchen white, but we decided that would look too clinical. \n 我们打算把厨房漆成白色，可是又觉得那样会看起来太冷冰冰了。 \n]\n','2020-01-23',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukcli/ukclima018.mp3'),('clink','（使）发出叮当声，（使）叮当作响叮当声监狱，大牢','uk :klɪŋk, us :klɪŋk','[The ice clinked as she dropped it into the glass. \n 她把冰块丢入玻璃杯，冰块叮当作响。 \n, We all clinked our glasses together and drank to a happy new year. \n 我们大家一起碰杯，祝贺新年快乐。 \n, I could hear the clink of coins in his pocket. \n 我能听到他口袋里的硬币叮当作响。 \n, Everyone always said Joe would end up in (the) clink. \n 大家都说乔总有一天要坐牢。 \n]\n','2019-12-27',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukcli/ukclima021.mp3'),('closet','（尤指放衣服的）壁橱，壁柜，储藏室关，藏，封闭私下的，秘密的，不公开的','uk :ˈklɒz.ɪt, us :ˈklɑː.zət','[a bedroom/linen/storage closet \n 卧室壁橱／家庭日用织品柜橱／储藏室 \n, Two weeks before my exams I closeted myself (away) in my room with my books and I didn t speak to anyone. \n 考试前两星期，我把自己关在房里读书，不跟任何人说话。 \n, The president has been closeted with (= having a private meeting with) his advisers for several hours. \n 总统与顾问们已经密谈了好几个小时了。 \n, a closet alcoholic/smoker \n 不愿承认的酗酒者/吸烟者 \n, Dole portrayed the president in campaign speeches as a  closet liberal . \n 多尔在竞选演讲中将总统描绘为“藏而不露的自由主义者”。 \n]\n','2020-02-27',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukcli/ukclipp030.mp3'),('clown','丑角，小丑（常指故意）出洋相的人；愚蠢可笑的人扮小丑；出洋相；逗笑','uk :klaʊn, us :klaʊn','[Left alone, the class threw books, pulled faces, and generally clowned around. \n 由于没有人管，班上的学生扔书本，扮鬼脸，简直胡闹成一片。 \n]\n','2019-12-26',0,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukclo/ukclosu015.mp3'),('clue','线索；迹象；提示','uk :kluː, us :kluː','[Police are still looking for clues in their search for the missing girl. \n 警方仍在寻找失踪女孩的线索。 \n, I m never going to guess the answer if you don t give me a clue. \n 要是你不给我一点提示，我永远也猜不到答案。 \n]\n','2020-02-28',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukclo/ukclosu021.mp3'),('cocoon','茧；卵袋安全宁静的地方；避风港给…加上保护层，将…裹住','uk :kəˈkuːn, us :kəˈkuːn','[the warm, safe cocoon of childhood \n 童年生活的温馨安逸、备受呵护 \n, As a student you re cocooned against/from the real world. \n 作为一名学生，你处在与现实世界隔离的环境之中。 \n]\n','2020-02-21',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukcoc/ukcocke014.mp3'),('coffin','棺材；灵柩','uk :ˈkɒf.ɪn, us :ˈkɑː.fɪn','[]\n','2019-12-27',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukcoe/ukcoedu014.mp3'),('coinage','货币系统，货币制度新造的词（语）；新词语的创造','uk :ˈkɔɪ.nɪdʒ, us :ˈkɔɪ.nɪdʒ','[decimal coinage \n 十进位币制 \n, The expression  boy band  is a 1990s coinage. \n boy band（男孩乐队）是20世纪90年代的新词语。 \n]\n','2020-04-01',3,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukcoh/ukcohab016.mp3'),('colonist','殖民地居民；殖民地移民；殖民地开拓者','uk :ˈkɒl.ə.nist, us :ˈkɑː.lə.nist','[]\n','2019-11-08',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukcld/ukcld01677.mp3'),('colony','殖民地殖民地定居者群体（具有共同爱好或工作的）聚居人群，群体（动物、昆虫或植物的）群，群落；生物群（有篱笆或围墙环绕的）住宅区','uk :ˈkɒl.ə.ni, us :ˈkɑː.lə.ni','[Australia and New Zealand are former British colonies. \n 澳大利亚和新西兰从前是英国的殖民地。 \n, an artists  colony \n 聚居在一起的艺术家 \n, a nudist colony \n 群居的裸体主义者 \n, a colony of ants/termites/bacteria \n 蚁群／白蚁群／菌落 \n]\n','2020-03-13',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukcol/ukcolle028.mp3'),('colossal','巨大的，庞大的','uk :kəˈlɒs.əl, us :kəˈlɑː.səl','[In the centre of the hall stood a colossal wooden statue, decorated in ivory and gold. \n 大厅中央矗立着一尊用象牙和金子装饰的木质巨型雕像。 \n, They were asking a colossal amount of money for the house. \n 他们对这房子漫天要价。 \n]\n','2019-12-13',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukcol/ukcolor003.mp3'),('commanding height','制高点','Zhǐlìng gāodù','\n','2019-10-07',0,1,0,'https://translate.google.cn/translate_tts?ie=UTF-8&q= commanding height&tl=ja&tk=509866.127966&client=webapp&prev=input'),('commencement','','uk :kəˈmens.mənt, us :kəˈmens.mənt','[Would passengers please turn off their mobile phones before the commencement of the flight. \n 请乘客们在飞机起飞前关闭手机。 \n]\n','2021-03-26',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukcom/ukcomma013.mp3'),('commercial','商业的；商务的；贸易的（唱片、电影、书等）商业化的，以营利为目的的（产品）商品化的（广播或电视）商业性的，靠广告收入维持的（电视或广播里的）商业广告','uk :kəˈmɜː.ʃəl, us :kəˈmɝː.ʃəl','[a commercial organization/venture/success \n 商业组织／企业／成功 \n, commercial law \n 商法 \n, The commercial future of the company looks very promising. \n 这家公司的商业前景看起来非常光明。 \n, a commercial break \n 插播广告 \n]\n','2019-10-08',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukcom/ukcomma024.mp3'),('commission','（正式地）安排…做，委托…做委任（或任命）…为军官（负责调查问题真相或原因的）委员会佣金；提成；回扣委托；请求犯罪军官的职务（或职权）','uk :kəˈmɪʃ.ən, us :kəˈmɪʃ.ən','[The newspaper commissioned a series of articles on the worst excesses of the fashion industry. \n 报社请人撰写了一系列针砭时装业极端倾向的文章。 \n, She\'s commissioned an artist to paint her portrait. \n 她请了一位艺术家为她画肖像。 \n, Grandfather was commissioned as Group Captain in the RAF just before the war. \n 就在战争爆发前夕祖父被任命为皇家空军上校。 \n, a commission on alcohol abuse/racial tension \n 酗酒问题／种族间紧张关系调查委员会 \n, The government has set up/established a commission to investigate the problem of inner city violence. \n 政府设立了专门委员会来调查市中心区的暴力问题。 \n, Is she paid a regular wage or is it on/by commission only? \n 她拿正式工资还是只拿提成？ \n, She gets a 15 percent commission on every machine she sells. \n 她每卖出一台机器就拿15%的提成。 \n, [ + to infinitive ] \n She\'s just got a commission to paint Sir Ellis Pike\'s wife. \n 她刚刚受托为埃利斯‧帕克爵士的夫人画像。 \n, Do you do/take commissions? \n 你接受委托吗？ \n, the commission of the crime/offence/murder \n 犯罪／犯法／犯杀人罪 \n]\n','2019-10-08',0,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukcom/ukcommi006.mp3'),('commitment','忠诚；投入；奉献；承诺，保证，诺言必须做（或处理）的事情','uk :kəˈmɪt.mənt, us :kəˈmɪt.mənt','[Players must make a commitment to play for a full season. \n 队员必须保证参加整个赛季的比赛 \n, her commitment to left-wing politics/the cause of feminism/the company \n 她对左翼政治／女权主义事业／公司的奉献 \n, She is known chiefly for her commitment to nuclear disarmament. \n 她主要以全力支持核裁军运动而出名。 \n, I d like to thank the staff for having shown such commitment. \n 我要对全体员工作出的巨大奉献表示感谢。 \n, Try the product out in the comfort of your own home with absolutely no commitment to buy! \n 可在家随意试用本产品且根本无须承诺购买！ \n, family/work commitments \n 家庭义务／工作任务 \n, I ve got too many commitments at the moment to do an evening class. \n 我眼下要做的事情太多，没时间晚上上课。 \n, Children are such a commitment. \n 照管孩子真费精力。 \n]\n','2020-01-15',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukcom/ukcommi010.mp3'),('commonplace','平常的；常见的；普通的；普遍的陈词滥调；寒暄客套；老生常谈','uk :ˈkɒm.ən.pleɪs, us :ˈkɑː.mən.pleɪs','[Electric cars are increasingly commonplace. \n 电动汽车越来越普及了。 \n, We exchanged commonplaces about the weather over cups of tea. \n 我们喝了几杯茶，就天气方面的话题寒暄了几句。 \n]\n','2020-02-21',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukcom/ukcommi022.mp3'),('companion','同伴；伙伴；伴侣陪护（旧时受雇陪伴老太太或女性病人旅行的年轻女子）（成对物件中的）一件（用于书名）指南，手册','uk :kəmˈpæn.jən, us :kəmˈpæn.jən','[The dog has been her constant companion these past ten years. \n 在过去的这10年里，这条狗一直与她形影不离。 \n, a travelling companion \n 旅伴 \n, I ve still got one of the candlesticks but I ve lost its companion. \n 我还拥有一个烛台，却把配对的另一个给弄丢了。 \n, the Music Lover s Companion \n 《音乐爱好者指南》 \n]\n','2020-01-15',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukcom/ukcommu022.mp3'),('comparison','比较，对照，对比相提并论，认为…和…相似','uk :kəmˈpær.ɪ.sən, us :kəmˈper.ɪ.sən','[They made a comparison of different countries  eating habits. \n 他们对不同国家的饮食习惯作了一番比较。 \n, By/In comparison with the French, the British eat far less fish. \n 与法国人相比，英国人吃鱼要少得多。 \n, She drew a comparison between life in the army and life in prison. \n 她把军队生活比作坐牢。 \n, To my mind there s no comparison between the two restaurants (= one is much better than the other). \n 在我心目中，这两家饭店根本不能相比。 \n, He s a good writer but he doesn t bear/stand comparison with Shakespeare (= he is not nearly as good as Shakespeare). \n 他是位好作家，但无法与莎士比亚相提并论。 \n]\n','2020-02-13',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukcom/ukcompa001.mp3'),('compartment','（车辆的）分隔厢，舱；（尤指火车的）隔间，包厢（家具、设备或容器的）隔间，格（身体内的）隔间，隔室','uk :kəmˈpɑːt.mənt, us :kəmˈpɑːrt.mənt','[a first-class compartment \n 头等包厢 \n, a fridge with a small freezer compartment \n 带有小冷冻室的冰箱 \n, the sleeping/inner compartment in a tent \n 帐篷里的睡间／内间 \n, The knee joint is composed of three compartments and ligaments that stabilize the joint. \n 膝关节由三个隔间和起稳定作用的韧带组成。 \n]\n','2020-01-03',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukcom/ukcompa002.mp3'),('compassion','同情，怜悯，恻隐之心','uk :kəmˈpæʃ.ən, us :kəmˈpæʃ.ən','[I was hoping she might show a little compassion. \n 我当时想她或许会表现出一点点同情心。 \n]\n','2020-03-05',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukcom/ukcompa006.mp3'),('compensate','赔偿；补偿弥补，补偿','uk :ˈkɒm.pən.seɪt, us :ˈkɑːm.pən.seɪt','[Victims of the crash will be compensated for their injuries. \n 车祸的受害者会得到伤害赔偿。 \n, Nothing will ever compensate for his lost childhood. \n 什么也不能弥补他失去的童年。 \n, His enthusiasm more than compensates for his lack of experience. \n 他的热情大大弥补了经验的不足。 \n, I took her swimming to compensate for having missed out on the cinema. \n 为弥补她错过了电影，我带她去游泳。 \n, We were late and I was driving fast to compensate. \n 我们迟到了，所以我开快车来赶时间。 \n]\n','2020-01-15',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukcom/ukcompa019.mp3'),('competitive edge','竞争优势','Jìngzhēng yōushì','\n','2019-10-07',0,1,0,'https://translate.google.cn/translate_tts?ie=UTF-8&q=competitive edge&tl=ja&tk=177902.295578&client=webapp&prev=input'),('compound','化合物复合物；混合物（语法中的）复合词（围起来的）场地，楼群，院落使加重，使加剧，使恶化使混合；使复合复合的（利息）以复利计算的','uk :ˈkɒm.paʊnd, us :ˈkɑːm-','[Salt is a compound of sodium and chlorine. \n 盐是钠和氯的化合物。 \n, Many fertilizers contain nitrogen compounds. \n 许多化学肥料都含有氮化合物。 \n, Then there was his manner, a curious compound of humour and severity. \n 还有他的态度，那是一种幽默与严厉的奇异混合。 \n,  Bodyguard  and  floppy disk  are two examples of compounds. \n bodyguard 和 floppy disk 是两个复合词。 \n, The gates opened and the troops marched into their compound. \n 大门开了，部队进入他们的大院。 \n, The embassy compound has been closed to the public because of a bomb threat. \n 因受到炸弹威胁，使馆区停止对公众开放。 \n, Her terror was compounded by the feeling that she was being watched. \n 她有种被人监视的感觉，这加剧了她的恐惧感。 \n, His financial problems were compounded when he unexpectedly lost his job. \n 他意外地失去了工作，这使他手头更紧了。 \n, Severe drought has compounded food shortages in the region. \n 严重的干旱加剧了该地区的食品短缺问题。 \n, Most tyres are made of rubber compounded with other chemicals and materials. \n 大多数轮胎都是用橡胶和其他化学制品、材料混合制成的。 \n, compound interest \n 复利 \n, The investment fund has achieved annual compound returns of 18.2 percent. \n 投资得到了18.2%的复利年回报率。 \n]\n','2020-01-24',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukcom/ukcompl019.mp3'),('con','骗，诈骗，哄骗（通常指钱财）骗局；圈套；花招不利条件；弊病已决犯，既决犯；（服刑中的）囚犯（同 convict）共；与同保守党（Conservativel的缩写）','uk :kɒn, us :kɑːn','[She felt she had been conned into buying the car. \n 她觉得自己上当受骗买下了这辆车。 \n, Thieves conned him out of his life savings. \n 小偷骗走了他一辈子的积蓄。 \n, He managed to con £20 out of them (= get that amount from them by deceiving them). \n 他从他们那里骗得20英镑。 \n, It s a con - you get half the food for twice the price! \n 这是个圈套——你花两倍的钱才买到一半的食物！ \n, a con trick \n 骗局 \n, One of the cons of buying a bigger car is that it costs more to run. \n 买辆大一点的汽车的缺点是跑起来更费油。 \n, You have to weigh up all the pros and cons of the matter before you make a decision. \n 作决定之前，你要权衡问题的利弊。 \n, conspiracy \n 共谋 \n, consortium \n 财团 \n]\n','2020-03-11',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukcom/ukcompr021.mp3'),('conceal','隐藏；隐匿；隐瞒；隐蔽','uk :kənˈsiːl, us :','[The listening device was concealed in a pen. \n 窃听装置藏在了笔里。 \n, I tried to conceal my surprise when she told me her age. \n 她告诉我她的年龄时，我尽力掩饰自己的惊讶。 \n, It was said that the police concealed vital evidence. \n 据说警方隐瞒了关键的证据。 \n, Is there something you re concealing from me? \n 你是不是有事瞒着我？ \n]\n','2020-03-18',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukcom/ukcompr024.mp3'),('conceive','想象；想出；构想构想，想出，设想出（计划或主意）怀孕；受孕；怀（胎）','uk :kənˈsiːv, us :kənˈsiːv','[I think my uncle still conceives of me as a four-year-old. \n 我觉得我叔叔仍然把我看成是4岁的小孩。 \n, He couldn t conceive of a time when he would have no job. \n 他不能想象有一天他会没有工作。 \n, [ + question word ] \n I can t conceive (= it is too shocking to imagine) how anyone could behave so cruelly. \n 我不能想象有人竟然能做出如此残酷的事情。 \n, [ + that ] \n I find it hard to conceive (= it is too shocking to imagine) that people are still treated so badly. \n 我觉得难以想象人们竟然还受着那样的虐待。 \n, He conceived the plot for this film while he was still a student. \n 他还是个学生的时候就已经构想出了这部影片的情节。 \n, The exhibition was conceived by the museum s director. \n 这次展览是由博物馆馆长构思设计的。 \n, Do you know exactly when you conceived? \n 你知道自己怀孕的确切时间吗？ \n, The baby was conceived in March, so will be born in December. \n 这孩子是3月份怀上的，所以会在12月出生。 \n]\n','2020-03-05',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukcon/ukconce002.mp3'),('concept','原则；概念；观念；想法对…一无所知','uk :ˈkɒn.sept, us :ˈkɑːn.sept','[The concept of free speech is unknown to them. \n 他们没有言论自由的概念。 \n, It is very difficult to define the concept of beauty. \n 很难给美这个概念下一个定义。 \n, I failed to grasp the film s central concept. \n 我没理解这部电影的中心思想。 \n, Kleenbrite is a whole new concept in toothpaste! \n Kleenbrite 是牙膏生产领域的一个全新概念！ \n, I don t think you have any concept of the pain you have caused her. \n 我觉得你对自己给她造成的痛苦根本就一无所知。 \n]\n','2020-01-10',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukcon/ukconce011.mp3'),('concrete','混凝土用混凝土覆盖确定的，确实的；具体的，有形的，实在的','uk :ˈkɒŋ.kriːt, us :ˈkɑːn.kriːt','[reinforced concrete \n 钢筋混凝土 \n, a concrete floor/path \n 混凝土地面／道路 \n, a grey concrete building \n 灰色的混凝土建筑物 \n, Why did you concrete over that nice garden? \n 你为什么把那个漂亮的花园铺上混凝土？ \n, They think she killed her husband, but they have no concrete evidence. \n 他们认为她杀死了自己的丈夫，但是没有确凿的证据。 \n, We have a general idea of what we want, but nothing concrete at the moment. \n 我们对需要什么有个大致的想法，可是具体的东西目前还没有想好。 \n]\n','2020-03-19',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukcon/ukconci022.mp3'),('condemnation','谴责，指责，声讨','uk :ˌkɒn.dəmˈneɪ.ʃən, us :ˌkɑːn.dəmˈneɪ.ʃən','[The shooting of the police officer has received universal condemnation. \n 枪杀警察事件受到了大众的一致谴责。 \n]\n','2020-03-18',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukcon/ukconde002.mp3'),('condescend','屈尊做…，俯就做…，降格做…','uk :ˌkɒn.dɪˈsend, us :ˌkɑːn.dəˈsend','[I wonder if Michael will condescend to visit us? \n 我不知道迈克尔是否会屈尊造访我们？ \n]\n','2020-03-06',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukcon/ukconde009.mp3'),('conduct','组织；实施；进行；处理（尤指在公共或正式场合中）举止，表现；为人引导；带领；指引；给…带路为…导游，带（游客）游览指挥（合唱团、乐队等）传导（电或热）行为，举止；表现；为人组织方式；实施方式','uk :kənˈdʌkt, us :kənˈdʌkt','[We are conducting a survey to find out what our customers think of their local bus service. \n 我们正在进行一项调查，了解顾客对当地公交服务系统的看法。 \n, The experiments were conducted by scientists in New York. \n 这些实验是科学家在纽约做的。 \n, How you choose to conduct your private life is your own business! \n 你选择怎么过你的私生活是你自己的事！ \n, How should I conduct myself at these dinners? I know nothing about etiquette. \n 我在这类晚宴上该怎样做到举止得体呢？对于礼仪我可是一窍不通。 \n, May I conduct you to your table, sir, or would you prefer to have a drink at the bar first? \n 先生，我带您去餐桌呢，还是您先在吧台喝上一杯？ \n, The protesters were conducted from the courtroom by two police officers. \n 抗议者被两名警察带出了法庭。 \n, A guide conducts tours of the cathedral every afternoon at 2.00. \n 每天下午2点一位导游会带游客参观大教堂。 \n, a conducted tour of the palace \n 有导游陪同的宫殿游 \n, The orchestra was conducted by Mira Shapur. \n 管弦乐队由米拉‧沙普尔指挥。 \n, Who\'s conducting at tonight\'s concert? \n 今晚的音乐会谁担任指挥？ \n, Copper conducts electricity, but plastic does not. \n 铜导电，但塑料不导电。 \n, bad/excellent/disgraceful conduct \n 糟糕的／得体的／丢脸的举止 \n, The club has a strict code (= set of rules) of conduct. \n 该俱乐部有严格的行为准则。 \n, He was criticized for his conduct of the inquiry. \n 他组织这次调查的方式受到了批评。 \n]\n','2019-10-03',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukcon/ukconde029.mp3'),('confirmatory','确切的','uk :kənˈfɜː.mə.tər.i, us :kənˈfɜ˞ː.mə.tɔːr.i','[nyone who tests positive with a rapid test must get a confirmatory blood test.\n]\n','2019-10-09',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english/uk_pron/c/cdo/cdo03/cdo0318ukconf0346.mp3'),('confiscate','（通常指作为惩罚）没收，把…充公','uk :ˈkɒn.fɪ.skeɪt, us :ˈkɑːn.fə.skeɪt','[Miss Edwards confiscated my phone! \n 爱德华小姐没收了我的电话！ \n, His passport was confiscated by the police to prevent him from leaving the country. \n 警方没收了他的护照，以防他出境。 \n]\n','2020-03-06',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukcon/ukconfi010.mp3'),('conflagration','大火，大火灾冲突；灾祸；战火','uk :ˌkɒn.fləˈɡreɪ.ʃən, us :ˌkɑːn.fləˈɡreɪ.ʃən','[The government has turned a minor local problem into a full-blown regional conflagration. \n 政府把一个地方性的小问题演变为一场全面的地区冲突。 \n]\n','2020-03-06',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukcon/ukconfi013.mp3'),('confront','面对，面临；遭遇；直面，正视','uk :kənˈfrʌnt, us :kənˈfrʌnt','[As she left the court, she was confronted by angry crowds who tried to block her way. \n 她离开法庭时，愤怒的人群试图拦住她的去路。 \n, It s an issue we ll have to confront at some point, no matter how unpleasant it is. \n 不管它有多讨厌，我们终究要面对这个问题。 \n, I thought I would stay calm, but when I was confronted with/by the TV camera, I got very nervous. \n 我以为我会保持镇静，可是面对电视镜头，我却变得紧张万分。 \n]\n','2020-02-28',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukcon/ukconfi025.mp3'),('confrontation','对抗；冲突；对峙；争论','uk :ˌkɒn.frʌnˈteɪ.ʃən, us :ˌkɑːn.frənˈteɪ.ʃən','[Some couples seem to like confrontation, but Josh and I hardly ever argue. \n 有的夫妻似乎很喜欢争吵，我跟乔希却几乎没有吵过嘴。 \n, There were violent confrontations between police and demonstrators. \n 警察和示威者之间发生了激烈的冲突。 \n]\n','2019-10-09',0,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukcon/ukconfi026.mp3'),('confrontational','對抗性的','uk :ˌkɒn.frʌnˈteɪ.ʃən.əl, us :ˌkɑːn.frənˈteɪ.ʃən.əl','[e has a very aggressive, confrontational way of talking to people.\n, The opposition has adopted a more confrontational approach in recent months.\n, nion leaders said they were disappointed by the rhetoric used by the management, and dismayed by their confrontational approach.\n, You should try to be less confrontational if you want to work well in a team.\n]\n','2020-01-09',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukcon/ukconfi027.mp3'),('congregate','聚集，集合','uk :ˈkɒŋ.ɡrɪ.ɡeɪt, us :ˈkɑːŋ.ɡrə.ɡeɪt','[A crowd congregated around the entrance to the theatre, hoping to catch a glimpse of the stars of the show. \n 一群人聚集在戏院门口，希望能看一眼演出的明星。 \n]\n','2019-12-20',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukcon/ukconfu019.mp3'),('conjure','变戏法；用魔法变出；像变魔术般变出','uk :ˈkʌn.dʒər, us :ˈkʌn.dʒɚ','[In an instant, the magician had conjured (up) a dove from his hat. \n 魔术师眨眼间便从他的帽子里变出了一只鸽子。 \n]\n','2020-01-20',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukcon/ukconje009.mp3'),('connoisseur','（艺术品、食品、饮料等的）鉴赏家，鉴定家，行家','uk :ˌkɒn.əˈsɜːr, us :ˌkɑː.nəˈsɝː','[a wine/art connoisseur \n 葡萄酒／艺术鉴赏家 \n, a connoisseur of ballet/cigars \n 芭蕾舞／雪茄行家 \n]\n','2020-02-21',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukcon/ukconje024.mp3'),('conscientious','认真的；尽心尽责的；一丝不苟的','uk :ˌkɒn.ʃiˈen.ʃəs, us :ˌkɑːn.ʃiˈen.ʃəs','[a conscientious student \n 认真的学生 \n]\n','2020-02-27',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukcon/ukconsc002.mp3'),('consciousness','意识；感觉；觉悟有意识的；神志清醒的；有知觉的','uk :ˈkɒn.ʃəs.nəs, us :ˈkɑːn.ʃəs.nəs','[[ + that ] \n Her consciousness that she s different makes her feel uneasy. \n 意识到自已与众不同，她感到很不自在。 \n, Working in an unemployment office had helped to raise his political consciousness. \n 在失业救济办公室工作帮助他提高了政治意识。 \n, He lost consciousness after his accident and never recovered/regained it. \n 事故发生后他便失去了知觉，再也没有苏醒过来。 \n]\n','2020-02-19',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukcon/ukconsc007.mp3'),('consecrate','使圣化；把…奉为神圣；给…祝圣宣布…任主教','uk :ˈkɒn.sɪ.kreɪt, us :ˈkɑːn.sə.kreɪt','[The new cathedral was completed and consecrated in 2002. \n 新的大教堂于2002年竣工并祝圣。 \n]\n','2020-01-17',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukcon/ukconsc011.mp3'),('consequent','作为结果的；随之而来的；由此引起的','uk :ˈkɒn.sɪ.kwənt, us :ˈkɑːn.sə.kwənt','[Our use of harmful chemicals and the consequent damage to the environment is a very serious matter. \n 我们使用有害化学物品且因此对环境造成了破坏，这是件非常严重的事情。 \n]\n','2019-10-08',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukcon/ukconsc020.mp3'),('considerable','相当大的；相当多的；非常可观的；相当重要的','uk :kənˈsɪd.ər.ə.bəl, us :kənˈsɪd.ɚ.ə.bəl','[The fire caused considerable damage to the church. \n 那场火灾给教堂造成了重大损失。 \n]\n','2020-03-05',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukcon/ukconse003.mp3'),('consist','在于，存在于','uk :kənˈsɪst, us :kənˈsɪst','[The beauty of air travel consists in its speed and ease. \n 乘飞机旅行的好处在于快捷、舒适。 \n, [ + -ing verb ] \n For her, happiness consists in watching television and reading magazines. \n 对她来说，幸福就是看电视和读杂志。 \n]\n','2019-12-27',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukcld/ukcld00265.mp3'),('constitution','宪法；章程体质，体格组成；构成；结构；构造','uk :ˌkɒn.stɪˈtʃuː.ʃən, us :ˌkɑːn.stəˈtuː.ʃən',NULL,'2021-03-08',7,9,1,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukcon/ukconsp021.mp3'),('constitutional','宪法（或章程）允许的，符合宪法（或章程）的体质的，体格的健身散步','uk :ˌkɒn.stɪˈtʃuː.ʃən.əl, us :ˌkɑːn.stəˈtuː.ʃən.əl',NULL,'2021-03-08',5,8,1,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukcon/ukconsp022.mp3'),('contagious','（疾病）接触性传染的（人）患传染病的，带传染源的（情感）具有感染力的，蔓延的','uk :kənˈteɪ.dʒəs, us :kənˈteɪ.dʒəs','[The infection is highly contagious, so don t let anyone else use your towel. \n 这种传染病极易传染，所以不要让别人用你的毛巾。 \n, Keep him out of school until he s not contagious anymore. \n 在他不再传染前，别让他上学了。 \n, Fear is contagious. \n 恐惧是会传染的。 \n]\n','2020-03-26',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukcon/ukconst030.mp3'),('contaminate','污染；弄脏；毒害','uk :kənˈtæm.ɪ.neɪt, us :kənˈtæm.ə.neɪt','[Much of the coast has been contaminated by nuclear waste. \n 大部分海岸已受到核废料污染。 \n, The food which had been contaminated was destroyed. \n 受污染的食物已被销毁了。 \n]\n','2020-01-23',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukcon/ukconta006.mp3'),('contemplate','盘算；沉思，冥想','uk :ˈkɒn.təm.pleɪt, us :ˈkɑːn.t̬əm.pleɪt','[[ + -ing verb ] \n I m contemplating going abroad for a year. \n 我打算出国一年。 \n, They were contemplating a move to California. \n 他们打算搬到加利福尼亚去。 \n, It s too awful/horrific/dangerous to contemplate. \n 这件事太糟糕／可怕／危险，简直不敢想。 \n]\n','2020-01-24',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukcon/ukconta010.mp3'),('content','满意的；满足的；知足的（杂志或书的）目录（文章、演讲、电影等的）内容所含之物；容纳的东西；内容含量使满意，使满足','uk :kənˈtent, us :kənˈtent','[He seems fairly content with (his) life. \n 他好像对生活相当满足。 \n, [ + to infinitive ] \n They re content to socialize with a very small circle of people. \n 他们满足于只和一小群人交往。 \n, the table of (= list of) contents \n 目录 \n, the contents page \n 目录页 \n, It s a very stylish and beautiful film, but it lacks content. \n 这部电影很新潮而且画面美丽，但内容空洞。 \n, We ve discussed the unusual form of the book - now, what about the content? \n 我们已经讨论了这本书与众不同的形式——现在，谈谈它的内容怎么样？ \n, The contents of his bag spilled all over the floor. \n 他包里的东西掉了一地。 \n, He didn t need to open the letter because he already knew the contents. \n 他不用拆那封信，因为他已经知道内容了。 \n, Chocolate has a high fat content. \n 巧克力脂肪含量很高。 \n, You re quite easily contented, aren t you? \n 你很容易满足，是不是？ \n, My explanation seemed to content him. \n 我的解释似乎让他很满意。 \n]\n','2020-01-15',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukcon/ukconta026.mp3'),('contingency','可能发生的事；意外事件，不测事件','uk :kənˈtɪn.dʒən.si, us :kənˈtɪn.dʒən.si','[You must be able to deal with all possible contingencies. \n 你必须能应付一切可能发生的意外事件。 \n, Have you made any contingency plans? \n 你们制订应急方案了吗？ \n]\n','2019-10-08',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukcon/ukconte020.mp3'),('contrary','相反；反面；对立面；相反事物正相反，恰恰相反正相反的，恰恰相反的相反的，对立的；完全不同的与大多数人的看法不同乖戾的；故意作对的；执拗的','uk :ˈkɒn.trə.ri, us :ˈkɑːn.tre.ri','[I was worried that it might be too hard for me but it turned out the contrary was true. \n 我原来担心那可能对我来说太难了，可是我发现恰恰相反。 \n,  I thought you said the film was exciting?   On the contrary, I nearly fell asleep half way through it!  \n “你不觉得这部电影很精彩吗？”“正相反，看到一半我差点睡着！” \n, For a long time it was thought to be a harmless substance, but we now have proof/evidence to the contrary. \n 长期以来这种物质被认为是无害的，但最近我们有了相反的证据。 \n, a contrary point of view \n 相反的观点 \n, Contrary to all our expectations, he found a well-paid job and a nice girlfriend. \n 出乎我们的意料，他找到了一份报酬不菲的工作和一个漂亮的女友。 \n, Contrary to popular opinion, I don t dye my hair! \n 与大多数人的想法不同，我不染头发！ \n, He doesn t really mean it - he s just being contrary. \n 这不是他的本意——他只是在故意作对。 \n]\n','2020-02-21',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukcon/ukcontr003.mp3'),('contrast','差别，差异；对照，对比对照，对比形成对照；显出明显的差异','uk :ˈkɒn.trɑːst, us :ˈkɑːn.træst','[I like the contrast of the white trousers with the black jacket. \n 我喜欢白色长裤与黑色夹克形成的反差。 \n, The antique furnishing provides an unusual contrast to the modernity of the building. \n 这座建筑物的古典装饰与它自身的现代风格形成了不同寻常的反差。 \n, There s a marked contrast between his character and hers. \n 他的性格与她形成了鲜明对比。 \n, Their economy has expanded, while ours, by/in contrast, has declined. \n 他们的经济快速增长，相比之下，我们的经济则滑坡了。 \n, The amount spent on defence is in stark/sharp (= in very noticeable) contrast to that spent on housing and health. \n 国防支出与住房及医疗保健的支出形成了鲜明的对照。 \n, I love his use of contrast (= strong differences between light and darkness) in his later photographs. \n 我喜欢他后期摄影作品中光暗对比的运用。 \n, If you contrast some of her early writing with her later work, you can see just how much she improved. \n 如果你对比一下她的早期作品和后期的作品，就会看出她进步有多大。 \n, The styles of the two film makers contrast quite dramatically. \n 两位电影导演风格迥异。 \n, The tartness of the lemons contrasts with the sweetness of the honey. \n 柠檬的酸味和蜂蜜的甜味形成鲜明的对比。 \n]\n','2020-02-28',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukcon/ukcontr005.mp3'),('controversial','有争议的；引起争议的','uk :ˌkɒn.trəˈvɜː.ʃəl, us :ˌkɑːn.trəˈvɝː.ʃəl','[a controversial issue/decision/speech/figure \n 有争议的问题／决议／讲话／数字 \n, The book was very controversial. \n 这本书很有争议。 \n]\n','2020-01-23',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukcon/ukcontr023.mp3'),('controversy','争议；争论；争辩','uk :ˈkɒn.trə.vɜː.si, us :ˈkɑːn.trə.vɝː.si','[There was a big controversy surrounding/over the use of drugs in athletics. \n 体育界对使用违禁药物争议很大。 \n, The policy has caused fierce/heated controversy ever since it was introduced. \n 这项政策自推行以来已引起了激烈的争论。 \n]\n','2020-03-12',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukcon/ukcontr025.mp3'),('convey','表达，传达（思想、感情或想法）运送，运输','uk :kənˈveɪ, us :kənˈveɪ','[His poetry conveys a great sense of religious devotion. \n 他的诗歌表达了献身宗教的强烈感情。 \n, Please convey our condolences to the family. \n 请向家人转达我们的哀思。 \n, [ + question word ] \n I tried to convey in my speech how grateful we all were for his help. \n 在发言中，我竭力地表达我们大家对他所给予帮助的感激之情。 \n, You don t want to convey the impression that we re not interested. \n 你不想给人留下我们不感兴趣的印象吧。 \n, The goods are usually conveyed by rail. \n 这种货物通常通过铁路运输。 \n, Could you convey a message to Mr Merrick for me, please? \n 你能替我给梅里克先生传个口信吗？ \n]\n','2019-12-19',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukcon/ukconve003.mp3'),('convicted','（在法庭上）宣判…有罪，证明…有罪已决犯，既决犯；（服刑中的）囚犯','uk :kənˈvɪkt, us :kənˈvɪkt','[He has twice been convicted of robbery/arson. \n 他两次被判犯有抢劫罪／纵火罪。 \n, an escaped convict \n 逃犯 \n]\n','2020-01-09',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukcon/ukconve009.mp3'),('convince','说服；使相信；使信服','uk :kənˈvɪns, us :kənˈvɪns','[He managed to convince the jury of his innocence. \n 他使陪审团相信他是无辜的。 \n, [ + (that) ] \n It s useless trying to convince her (that) she doesn t need to lose any weight. \n 要让她相信她无需减肥是徒劳的。 \n, [ + to infinitive ] \n I hope this will convince you to change your mind. \n 我希望这会说服你改变主意。 \n]\n','2020-01-09',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukcon/ukconve011.mp3'),('convincing','令人信服的；有说服力的令人心悦诚服的胜利，大比分获胜','uk :kənˈvɪn.sɪŋ, us :kənˈvɪn.sɪŋ','[a convincing argument/explanation \n 令人信服的论据／解释 \n, convincing evidence \n 确凿的证据 \n, The end of the book wasn\'t very convincing. \n 这本书的结局难以令人信服。 \n, They won a convincing victory. \n 他们大比分获胜。 \n]\n','2019-10-08',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukcon/ukconve013.mp3'),('cope','（成功地）对付，应付，处理','uk :kəʊp, us :koʊp','[It must be really hard to cope with three young children and a job. \n 要照顾3个小孩还要工作肯定不容易。 \n, It s only been a year since he died - how s she coping? \n 他过世刚一年时间——她的情况怎么样？ \n, He had so much pressure on him in his job that eventually he just couldn t cope. \n 他工作压力太大，最后便扛不住了。 \n]\n','2020-03-17',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukcop/ukcop__002.mp3'),('cord','（一段）绳，索，线电线灯芯绒灯芯绒裤子（体内的）带，索','uk :kɔːd, us :kɔːrd','[Where s the cord that ties back the curtains? \n 系窗帘的绳子在哪儿？ \n, an extension cord \n 延长线 \n, a cord shirt/jacket \n 灯芯绒衬衫／外套 \n, the umbilical cord \n 脐带 \n]\n','2020-02-19',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukcho/ukchora002.mp3'),('corny','（尤指笑话、电影、故事等）陈腐的，老套的；平淡的，乏味的','uk :ˈkɔː.ni, us :ˈkɔːr.ni','[corny jokes \n 老掉牙的笑话 \n, I couldn t watch the whole movie - it was just too corny. \n 我无法看完整部电影——简直太老套了。 \n]\n','2020-02-27',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukcor/ukcorne014.mp3'),('coronavirus','冠状病毒','uk :kəˈrəʊ.nəˌvaɪə.rəs, us :kəˈroʊ.nəˌvaɪ.rəs','[]\n','2020-01-23',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english/uk_pron/c/cdo/cdo03/cdo0317corouk0920.mp3'),('corpse','（通常指人的）尸体','uk :kɔːps, us :kɔːrps','[]\n','2020-01-03',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukcor/ukcorps001.mp3'),('corrode','（使）腐蚀；侵蚀','uk :kəˈrəʊd, us :kəˈroʊd','[Steel tends to corrode faster in a salty atmosphere. \n 在盐分高的环境里，钢往往腐蚀得更快。 \n]\n','2020-01-15',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukcor/ukcorps027.mp3'),('cotton','棉，棉花棉线；棉布（通常用于清洁皮肤的）药棉，脱脂棉','uk :ˈkɒt.ən, us :ˈkɑː.t̬ən','[a bale of cotton \n 一大包棉花 \n, a shirt made of pure cotton \n 纯棉衬衫 \n, She looked pretty in a simple cotton dress. \n 她穿着朴素的棉布连衣裙，看上去很漂亮。 \n, K \n a reel of cotton (= thread) \n 一卷棉线 \n, cotton pads \n 化妆棉 \n]\n','2019-10-07',0,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukcos/ukcossa021.mp3'),('counterfeit','伪造的；仿造的；假冒的','uk :ˈkaʊn.tə.fɪt, us :ˈkaʊn.t̬ɚ.fɪt','[counterfeit jewellery/passports/coins \n 假珠宝／护照／钱币 \n]\n','2020-03-11',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukcou/ukcounc019.mp3'),('counterpart','（与不同地方或组织的人或物）作用相同者，相对应者','uk :ˈkaʊn.tə.pɑːt, us :ˈkaʊn.t̬ɚ.pɑːrt','[The prime minister is to meet his European counterparts to discuss the war against drugs. \n 首相将会见欧洲各国首脑就打击毒品犯罪进行商讨。 \n]\n','2020-01-10',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukcou/ukcounc029.mp3'),('coup','意想不到的成功政变；（尤指）军事政变','uk :kuː, us :kuː','[It was a tremendous coup for the local paper to get an exclusive interview with Prince Charles. \n 当地报纸能独家采访到查尔斯王子是破天荒的成功。 \n, I got him to come to a party, which was something of a coup. \n 我说服了他来参加聚会，实属意外之得。 \n, a military coup \n 军事政变 \n]\n','2020-03-11',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukcon/ukconve025.mp3'),('courier','（递送重要书信或文件的）信使，递送员旅游团领队，导游通过递送员递送','uk :ˈkʊr.i.ər, us :ˈkʊr.i.ɚ','[I want to have this package delivered by motorcycle courier. \n 我想找摩托递送员送这个包裹。 \n, I ll courier the relevant documents to you this afternoon. \n 我今天下午请递送员把相关文件送给你。 \n]\n','2020-01-10',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukcou/ukcouri001.mp3'),('coward','胆小鬼，懦夫','uk :ˈkaʊ.əd, us :ˈkaʊ.ɚd','[They branded her a coward for informing on her colleagues during the interrogation. \n 她在审讯中告发了同事，因此被视为懦夫。 \n]\n','2019-12-19',0,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukcov/ukcover012.mp3'),('creep','（通常指为避免注意而）缓慢行进，悄悄移动，潜行谄媚者，奴颜婢膝者，阿谀奉承者讨厌鬼，令人恶心的人（尤指男人）使…毛骨悚然；使…紧张害怕','uk :kriːp, us :kriːp','[She turned off the light and crept through the door. \n 她关上灯，悄悄溜出门。 \n, Someone was creeping around outside my window. \n 有人在我的窗户外蹑手蹑脚地走动。 \n, The spider crept up the wall. \n 蜘蛛缓缓地爬上墙。 \n, The traffic was creeping along at a snail s pace. \n 车辆如蜗牛般缓慢移动。 \n, Making coffee for the boss again? You creep! \n 又在给老板冲咖啡？你这个马屁精！ \n, He was such a creep - he was always staring at me in the canteen. \n 他真是个讨厌鬼——在饭厅里他老盯着我看。 \n, [ as form of address ] \n Leave me alone, creep! \n 让我一个人呆一会儿，你这个讨厌鬼！ \n, Living next to a graveyard would give me the creeps. \n 住在墓地旁边会令我毛骨悚然。 \n]\n','2019-12-19',0,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukcre/ukcreed002.mp3'),('crippling','手臂残废者；瘸子，跛子感情残废者，感情有缺陷的人使受伤致残；使跛严重损坏；严重削弱残疾的，伤残的严重的；造成严重后果的','uk :ˈkrɪp.əl, us :ˈkrɪp.əl','[a country crippled by war \n 因战争而元气大伤的国家 \n, Will she be crippled for life? \n 她会终生残疾吗？ \n, A crippling attack of malaria kept him in bed for months. \n 一场严重的疟疾让他好几个月卧床不起。 \n, crippling debts \n 使人破产的债务 \n]\n','2020-01-09',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukcre/ukcrew_028.mp3'),('crisis','危机，极其困难的时期紧要关头，危急时刻（疾病的）危险期，关键期信任危机','uk :ˈkraɪ.sɪs, us :ˈkraɪ.sɪs',NULL,'2021-03-08',9,11,1,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukcri/ukcripp003.mp3'),('crisp','脆的；易碎的（糕点、饼干等食物）酥脆的（蔬果）新鲜爽脆的，脆生生的（纸或布）挺括的，平展的（声音或形象）清晰明了的（说话、写作或行为）干脆利落的，利索的，明快的（天气）干冷的，晴冷的（空气）清爽的，凉爽的油炸薯片酥皮水果甜点心','uk :krɪsp, us :krɪsp','[a crisp apple \n 脆生生的苹果 \n, a crisp new £5 note/a crisp white tablecloth \n 平展簇新的5英镑钞票／平展的白色桌布 \n, The sound from the new speakers is very crisp. \n 新扬声器的声音非常清晰。 \n, a crisp reply \n 干脆利落的回答 \n, a crisp, efficient manner \n 举止利落干练 \n, a wonderful crisp spring morning \n 一个晴爽的春日清晨 \n, I breathed in deeply the crisp mountain air. \n 我深深地吸了口山间清爽的空气。 \n, a packet of salt and vinegar crisps \n 一袋盐醋薯片 \n, apple crisp \n 酥皮苹果甜点 \n]\n','2021-03-23',5,7,1,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukcri/ukcripp004.mp3'),('criteria','（作出评判、决定或处理的）标准，准则','uk :kraɪˈtɪə.ri.ən, us :kraɪˈtɪr.i.ən','[The Health Service should not be judged by financial criteria alone. \n 公共医疗卫生服务不应仅仅以财务状况的好坏为标准来评判。 \n]\n','2020-02-20',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukcri/ukcripp012.mp3'),('critique','评论文章，评论（常指否定的评论）评论（书、戏剧、电影等）','uk :krɪˈtiːk, us :krɪˈtiːk','[a Marxist critique of neo-liberal policy \n 以马克思主义观点评论新自由政策的文章 \n, Students take turns critiquing each others  work.  \n 学生们轮流评论彼此的作品。 \n]\n','2020-02-28',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukcri/ukcripp018.mp3'),('crook','骗子；无赖；（尤指）诈骗犯臂弯（尤指牧羊人或主教用的）曲柄手杖不好的，坏的；有病的使（手指或手臂）弯曲','uk :krʊk, us :krʊk','[These politicians are just a bunch of crooks. \n 这些政客不过是一帮骗子。 \n, I m a bit crook at the moment. \n 我目前身体不太好。 \n, She delicately crooked her little finger as she picked up her cup. \n 她端茶杯时优雅地翘起小指。 \n]\n','2020-02-27',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukcro/ukcrocu009.mp3'),('crop','庄稼，作物；收成，收获量（同时涌现的）一批，一帮（人或事物）平头发型（鸟的）嗉囊短马鞭修剪；剪短（羊、马等）啃食（草或其他植物）的顶部剪裁（照片）（植物）结果，开花，收成，收获种植（庄稼）','uk :krɒp, us :krɑːp','[The main crops grown for export are coffee and rice. \n 主要的出口作物是咖啡和大米。 \n, a bumper (= very good) potato crop \n 土豆大丰收 \n, The judges will select the best from this year s crop of first novels. \n 评委们将从今年的一批处女作小说中选出最出色的一部。 \n, Her hair was cut in a short crop. \n 她留着很短的平头。 \n, He had his hair cropped when he went into the army. \n 他参军时把头发剪短了。 \n, He cropped the photo so that only the face remained. \n 他把照片剪到只剩下脸。 \n, The carrots have cropped (= grown) well this year. \n 今年的胡萝卜收成很好。 \n, The land is intensively cropped. \n 这片地庄稼种得很密。 \n]\n','2020-02-13',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukcro/ukcrocu014.mp3'),('crop-up','提及','','null\n','2020-02-13',0,0,0,'null'),('crossword','纵横填字游戏','uk :ˈkrɒs.wɜːd, us :ˈkrɑːs.wɝːd','[I do the Times crossword every morning. \n 我每天早上都要做《泰晤士报》上的填字游戏。 \n]\n','2019-12-20',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukcro/ukcross018.mp3'),('crowd','>人群；群众>（有共同爱好的）一帮朋友，一伙人，一群人>挤；靠近；盯着','uk :>kraʊd, us :>kraʊd',NULL,'2021-03-26',0,8,1,NULL),('crucial','至关重要的；关键的；决定性的','uk :ˈkruː.ʃəl, us :ˈkruː.ʃəl','[a crucial decision/question \n 至关重要的决定／问题 \n, Her work has been crucial to the project\'s success. \n 她的工作对于这个项目的成功至关重要。 \n, [ + that ] \n It is crucial that the problem is tackled immediately. \n 关键是要马上着手处理这一问题。 \n]\n','2019-10-08',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukcro/ukcrowe004.mp3'),('crude','粗糙的；简陋的；粗制的；未加修饰的粗俗的；粗野的；无礼的原油','uk :kruːd, us :kruːd','[a crude device/weapon \n 简陋的装置／粗制的武器 \n, a crude remark/comment \n 粗俗的话／评论 \n]\n','2020-01-09',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukcro/ukcrowe013.mp3'),('cruel','残忍的；残酷的；刻毒伤人的令人痛苦的残酷地；残忍地','uk :ˈkruː.əl, us :ˈkruː.əl','[Don t tease him about his weight - it s cruel. \n 别拿他的体重开玩笑——这样太刻薄了。 \n, Children can be very cruel to each other. \n 小孩相互之间会很残忍。 \n, His death was a cruel blow. \n 他的死是个无情的打击。 \n]\n','2020-01-17',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukcro/ukcrowe018.mp3'),('cunning','狡猾的，狡诈的吸引人的，迷人的狡诈；狡猾；机灵','uk :ˈkʌn.ɪŋ, us :ˈkʌn.ɪŋ','[a cunning plan/ploy \n 诡诈的计划／花招 \n, He s a very cunning man. \n 他为人十分狡猾。 \n, a cunning little child/puppy/kitten \n 逗人喜爱的小孩／小狗／小猫 \n, We need to show some cunning if we want to defeat the enemy. \n 要想骗过敌人，我们得想点计策。 \n]\n','2020-01-09',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukcul/ukcull_029.mp3'),('cunt','讨厌鬼；蠢人，笨蛋（冒犯性用语）女人的阴部；阴道','uk :kʌnt, us :kʌnt','[You stupid cunt! \n 你这个蠢货！ \n]\n','2020-03-19',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukcun/ukcunt_001.mp3'),('curator','（博物馆、图书馆等的）馆长','uk :kjʊˈreɪ.tər, us :kjɝːˈeɪ.t̬ɚ',NULL,'2021-03-08',8,10,1,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukcun/ukcunt_019.mp3'),('currency','货币，通货流行；流通；通用','uk :ˈkʌr.ən.si, us :ˈkɝː.ən.si','[foreign currency \n 外币 \n, His ideas enjoyed wide currency during the last century. \n 他的思想在上个世纪广为流传。 \n, Many informal expressions are gaining currency in serious newspapers. \n 许多非正式表达方法正在为严肃报刊所接受。 \n]\n','2020-02-27',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukcur/ukcurio014.mp3'),('custodian','监护人；监管人；看护人；保管人（思想或原则的）捍卫者看门人，门房；房屋看管人','uk :kʌsˈtəʊ.di.ən, us :kʌsˈtoʊ.di.ən','[the custodian of a museum/castle \n 博物馆／城堡的看护人 \n, She sees herself as a custodian of the public s morals. \n 她视自己为公共道德的捍卫者。 \n]\n','2020-02-27',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukcur/ukcurta022.mp3'),('customs-union','关税同盟','null','null\n','2020-04-01',0,5,0,'null'),('cynical','愤世嫉俗的；怀疑人之真诚的；认为人皆自私的利用他人感情的；损人利己的','uk :ˈsɪn.ɪ.kəl, us :ˈsɪn.ɪ.kəl','[She has a pretty cynical view of men. \n 她对男人的态度太过偏激。 \n, I ve always been deeply cynical about politicians. \n 我对政客们总是嗤之以鼻。 \n, She works in that most cynical of industries - advertising. \n 她供职于最具煽惑性的行业——广告行业。 \n, He praises my cooking but it s just a cynical ploy to get me to make him dinner. \n 他夸我烧一手好菜只不过是在耍花招，哄我给他做饭。 \n]\n','2020-01-09',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukcyb/ukcyber023.mp3'),('dame','女人（童话剧中通常由男人扮演的）老年女丑角，滑稽老太婆（英国授予有贡献的女性的荣誉称号）女爵士；有女爵士头衔的女性','uk :deɪm, us :deɪm','[Dame Judy Dench \n 朱迪‧登奇女爵士 \n]\n','2019-12-23',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukd/ukdag/ukdagoe026.mp3'),('dapper','（男子）穿着考究的，衣冠楚楚的','uk :ˈdæp.ər, us :ˈdæp.ɚ','[Hercule Poirot is the dapper detective of the Agatha Christie novels. \n 赫尔克里‧波洛就是阿加莎‧克里斯蒂小说中那位衣冠楚楚的侦探。 \n]\n','2021-03-26',5,5,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukd/ukdam/ukdamne030.mp3'),('datum','（一条）信息，数据','uk :ˈdeɪ.təm, us :ˈdeɪ.t̬əm','[]\n','2020-02-28',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/e/epd/epd07/epd07880.mp3'),('dean','','uk :diːn, us :diːn','[She is the new dean of the Faculty of Social Sciences. \n 她是社会科学院的新任院长。 \n, the Dean of Medicine \n 医学系系主任 \n, Parsons is the dean of the TV news correspondents at Channel Nine. \n 帕森斯是9频道电视新闻记者中的元老。 \n]\n','2021-03-26',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukd/ukddt/ukddt__025.mp3'),('debate','谈论，讨论；争论，辩论讨论；争论斟酌；考虑','uk :dɪˈbeɪt, us :dɪˈbeɪt','[Education is the current focus of public debate. \n 教育是目前大众谈论的焦点。 \n, How we proceed from here is a matter for debate. \n 我们下一步怎样做还需要讨论。 \n, Over the year we have had several debates about future policy. \n 一年来，我们就未来的政策进行了几次讨论。 \n, In Parliament today, MPs debated the Finance Bill. \n 今天在议会上议员们讨论了财政法案。 \n, They had been debating for several hours without reaching a conclusion. \n 他们已经争论了好几个小时，仍然没有得出一个结论。 \n, [ + question word ] \n The authorities debated whether to build a new car park. \n 政府有关部门就是否要修建一座新停车场进行了讨论。 \n, [ + question word ] \n We debated whether to take the earlier train. \n 我们考虑到底要不要乘早一点的那次列车。 \n, I m still debating what colour to paint the walls. \n 我还在考虑要把墙刷成什么颜色。 \n]\n','2020-01-15',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukd/ukdea/ukdeath012.mp3'),('debris','碎片，残片','uk :ˈdeb.riː, us :dəˈbriː','[Debris from the aircraft was scattered over a large area. \n 飞机残片散落在一片很大的区域。 \n]\n','2020-03-05',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukd/ukdea/ukdeath022.mp3'),('debt','借款，欠款；债务','uk :det, us :det','[He managed to pay off his debts in two years. \n 他设法在两年内还清了债务。 \n, The company ran up huge debts. \n 公司很快就负债累累。 \n, They are in debt to (= owe money to) the bank. \n 他们欠银行的钱。 \n, He got into debt (= borrowed money) after he lost his job. \n 他失业后开始举债。 \n, The company is deep in debt (= owes a lot of money). \n 公司已经债台高筑。 \n]\n','2019-10-07',0,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukd/ukdea/ukdeath023.mp3'),('decade','十年；年代','uk :ˈdek.eɪd, us :ˈdek.eɪd','[]\n','2019-10-07',0,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukd/ukdea/ukdeath030.mp3'),('decay','腐蚀；（使）衰败，（使）衰弱腐蚀；衰败，衰弱','uk :dɪˈkeɪ, us :dɪˈkeɪ','[Sugar makes your teeth decay. \n 糖能引起蛀牙。 \n, The role of the extended family has been decaying for some time. \n 大家庭的作用开始减弱已经有一段时间了。 \n, Pollution has decayed the surface of the stonework on the front of the cathedral. \n 大教堂前部的石刻表面已经因为污染受到了侵蚀。 \n, the smell of decaying meat \n 腐肉气味 \n, environmental/industrial/moral/urban decay \n 环境恶化／工业衰退／道德沦丧／城市衰落 \n, dental/tooth decay \n 蛀牙 \n, The buildings had started to fall into decay. \n 那些建筑已经开始破败了。 \n, This industry has been in decay for some time. \n 这个行业早就开始衰退了。 \n]\n','2020-01-20',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukd/ukdec/ukdecad014.mp3'),('deceive','欺骗，蒙骗；隐瞒自欺欺人，欺骗自己骗子','uk :dɪˈsiːv, us :dɪˈsiːv','[The company deceived customers by selling old computers as new ones. \n 该公司用旧计算机冒充新机器欺骗顾客。 \n, The sound of the door closing deceived me into thinking they had gone out. \n 关门声让我以为他们已经出门了。 \n, She thinks he ll come back, but she s deceiving herself. \n 她认为他会回来，实际上她是在自欺欺人。 \n]\n','2020-02-21',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukd/ukdec/ukdecad021.mp3'),('decimal','十进位的小数；十进小数','uk :ˈdes.ɪ.məl, us :ˈdes.ə.məl','[If you calculate the result to two decimal places (= give two numbers after the decimal point, as in 3.65), that should minimize any possible errors. \n 如果将计算结果保留两位小数，就会最大限度地减小可能的误差。 \n, Three fifths expressed as a decimal is 0.6. \n 3/5用小数表示就是0.6。 \n]\n','2020-03-12',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukd/ukdec/ukdecep010.mp3'),('decorate','装饰，装点，打扮粉刷；（给…）贴壁纸（尤指授予奖章以）嘉奖，表彰','uk :ˈdek.ə.reɪt, us :ˈdek.ər.eɪt','[They decorated the wedding car with ribbons and flowers. \n 他们用彩带和鲜花装点婚车。 \n, We re going to decorate the kitchen next week. \n 我们下周要粉刷厨房。 \n, I hate the smell of paint when I m decorating. \n 我刷墙时很讨厌油漆味儿。 \n, They were decorated for their part in the rescue. \n 他们因在此次救援行动中的表现而受到嘉奖。 \n]\n','2020-03-25',2,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukd/ukdec/ukdecod014.mp3'),('dedicate','奉献，献出（全部精力、时间等）（把书籍、戏剧、演出等）献给为（尤指宗教建筑）举行奉献典礼；为…举行落成仪式','uk :ˈded.ɪ.keɪt, us :ˈded.ə.keɪt','[He has dedicated his life to scientific research. \n 他把自己的一生都献给了科学研究工作。 \n, The new president said she would dedicate herself to protecting the rights of the sick and the homeless. \n 新任总统说她将致力于保护病人和无家可归者的权利。 \n, The book is dedicated to the author s husband. \n 作者将此书献给自己的丈夫。 \n, The church was dedicated on 1 March 1805 to the local Saint Jude. \n 教堂于1805年3月1日落成以纪念当地的圣裘德。 \n]\n','2020-03-06',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukd/ukdec/ukdecry002.mp3'),('deed','（尤指很坏或很好的）事情，行为（土地或建筑的）契约，所有权证书','uk :diːd, us :diːd','[It seems to me that a lot of evil deeds are done in the name of religion. \n 在我看来，很多坏事都是打着宗教的幌子干的。 \n, She s always helping people and doing good deeds. \n 她总是帮助别人，经常做好事。 \n]\n','2020-03-06',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukd/ukdec/ukdecry011.mp3'),('defect','缺点；缺陷；瑕疵生理缺陷；生理障碍（尤指为加入敌对国家、政党等）脱离，退出，叛逃','uk :ˈdiː.fekt, us :ˈdiː.fekt',NULL,'2021-03-08',4,9,1,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukd/ukdef/ukdefec001.mp3'),('deliberate','（常指坏事）有意的，故意的，蓄意的慢吞吞的；小心谨慎的；沉稳的慎重考虑；仔细讨论','uk :dɪˈlɪb.ər.ət, us :dɪˈlɪb.ɚ.ət','[a deliberate attack/insult/lie \n 蓄意攻击／侮辱／说谎 \n, We made a deliberate decision to live apart for a while. \n 经过慎重考虑，我们决定分开住一段时间。 \n, From her slow, deliberate speech I guessed she must be drunk. \n 她说话慢吞吞的，我猜她肯定喝醉了。 \n, The jury took five days to deliberate on the case. \n 陪审团花了5天时间对此案进行了慎重讨论。 \n, The committee has deliberated the question at great length. \n 委员会已经仔细讨论过这个问题了。 \n, [ + question word ] \n He s deliberating whether or not to accept the new job that he s been offered. \n 他正在慎重考虑是否接受提供给他的这份新工作。 \n]\n','2020-02-21',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukd/ukdej/ukdejur018.mp3'),('deliberately','故意地不慌不忙地，从容地','uk :dɪˈlɪb.ər.ət.li, us :dɪˈlɪb.ɚ.ət.li','[I m sure he says these things deliberately to annoy me. \n 我敢肯定他是故意说这些来气我的。 \n, Calmly and deliberately, she cut up his suits one by one. \n 她平静从容地把他的西服一件一件剪成碎片。 \n]\n','2020-02-21',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukd/ukdej/ukdejur020.mp3'),('delicate','脆弱的；娇嫩的需要小心处理的微妙的形势（问题，时刻等）精细的，精密的柔和的；轻柔的；清淡的纤细的，细长的','uk :ˈdel.ɪ.kət, us :ˈdel.ə.kət','[Peaches have delicate skins which are easily bruised. \n 桃子的表皮很娇嫩，容易碰伤。 \n, Delicate plants need to be kept in a greenhouse during the winter. \n 娇贵的植物需要在温室里过冬。 \n, delicate china \n 易碎的瓷器 \n, Molly s health has always been delicate (= she gets sick easily). \n 莫莉的身体一直都很娇弱。 \n, Repairing damaged nerves is a very delicate operation/process. \n 修复受损神经的手术／过程需要非常小心谨慎。 \n, I need to speak to you about a delicate matter. \n 我要跟你谈一件很棘手的事情。 \n, The pay negotiations have reached a delicate point/stage. \n 工资谈判已经到了微妙的关头／阶段。 \n, Teachers need to strike a delicate (= carefully achieved) balance between instructing their students and letting them discover things for themselves. \n 教师需要在向学生传授知识和引导学生自己去探索之间找到一个微妙的平衡点。 \n, Weather-forecasters have extremely delicate equipment which helps them predict what the weather is going to be like. \n 气象预报人员使用非常精密的设备来帮助他们预测天气变化。 \n, a rose with a delicate scent \n 散发清香的玫瑰 \n, a delicate shade of pink \n 柔和的粉色 \n, We chose a delicate floral pattern for our bedroom curtains. \n 我们为卧室选了一种花色图案非常淡雅的窗帘。 \n, She folded her delicate hands on the table. \n 她纤纤十指交叉着放在桌上。 \n]\n','2019-12-13',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukd/ukdej/ukdejur023.mp3'),('delta','三角洲（希腊语字母表的第四个字母）','uk :ˈdel.tə, us :ˈdel.t̬ə','[the Mississippi delta \n 密西西比河三角洲 \n, the delta of the Nile \n 尼罗河三角洲 \n]\n','2019-12-11',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukd/ukdel/ukdelig020.mp3'),('delude','欺骗，蒙骗','uk :dɪˈluːd, us :dɪˈluːd','[He s deluding himself if he thinks he s going to be promoted this year. \n 如果他认为今年将获得晋升，那他是在自己骗自己。 \n]\n','2020-02-21',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukd/ukdel/ukdelig021.mp3'),('demerit','缺陷；劣势（尤指学校给学生的）记过，过失分','uk :ˌdiːˈmer.ɪt, us :ˌdiːˈmer.ɪt','[We need to consider the merits and demerits of the plan. \n 我们需要考虑该计划的优缺点。 \n, She got three demerits for lateness on this term s report. \n 她因迟到在本学期总评中被记过3次。 \n]\n','2019-12-19',0,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukd/ukdem/ukdemag017.mp3'),('democracy','民主；民主思想；民主政体民主国家','uk :dɪˈmɒk.rə.si, us :-ˈmɑː.krə-','[The government has promised to uphold the principles of democracy. \n 政府承诺将坚持民主的原则。 \n, The early 1990s saw the spread of democracy in Eastern Europe. \n 20世纪90年代初，民主思想在东欧迅速传播。 \n, Few of the Western democracies still have a royal family. \n 西方民主国家鲜有保留皇室者。 \n]\n','2020-03-31',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukd/ukdem/ukdemag028.mp3'),('demonstrate','显示；表明展示，演示表达；表露；表现；显露示威，游行','uk :ˈdem.ən.streɪt, us :ˈdem.ən.streɪt','[These numbers clearly demonstrate the size of the economic problem facing the country. \n 这些数字清楚表明了该国经济问题的严重程度。 \n, [ + that ] \n Research has demonstrated that babies can recognize their mother s voice very soon after birth. \n 研究表明，婴儿出生后很快就能辨识母亲的声音。 \n, These problems demonstrate the importance of strategic planning. \n 这些问题显示出了战略规划的重要性。 \n, He got a job demonstrating kitchen equipment in a department store. \n 他找到一份在百货店演示厨房设备的工作。 \n, [ + question word ] \n The teacher demonstrated how to use the equipment. \n 老师演示了如何使用这种设备。 \n, He has demonstrated a genuine interest in the project. \n 他对该项目表现出了极大的兴趣。 \n, His answer demonstrated a complete lack of understanding of the question. \n 他的回答表明他完全没有理解这个问题。 \n, Thousands of people gathered to demonstrate against the new proposals. \n 数千人聚集在一起示威，抗议这些新提案。 \n]\n','2020-02-28',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukd/ukdem/ukdemoc021.mp3'),('demonstration','演示，示范游行，示威表示；表达；表现；表明','uk :ˌdem.ənˈstreɪ.ʃən, us :ˌdem.ənˈstreɪ.ʃən','[This disaster is a clear demonstration of the need for tighter controls. \n 这场灾难清楚表明需要进一步加强控制。 \n, Let me give you a demonstration of how the camera works. \n 让我来给你演示一下照相机的工作原理。 \n, She told us how easy it was to use the software, then by way of demonstration produced a beautiful graph with a few clicks of the mouse. \n 她告诉我们使用这个软件非常容易，然后点击了几下鼠标就画出了一张好看的图表给我们作了示范。 \n, We re going to a cookery demonstration tonight. \n 今天晚上我们要去看烹饪表演。 \n, The students are holding a demonstration against the proposed changes. \n 学生们举行游行示威，抗议提议中要进行的改变。 \n, Protesters staged an anti-war demonstration. \n 抗议者举行反战示威活动。 \n, Huge crowds followed the funeral procession in a public demonstration of grief. \n 大批群众跟在葬礼队伍的后面，公开表达他们的悲痛。 \n, There has been little demonstration of support for the proposal so far. \n 到目前为止，很少有人对这个提案表示支持。 \n]\n','2020-02-28',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukd/ukdem/ukdemoc022.mp3'),('demonstrator','展示者，演示者，示范者示威者，游行者','uk :ˈdem.ən.streɪ.tər, us :ˈdem.ən.streɪ.t̬ɚ','[A demonstrator was showing customers how the food processor worked. \n 一个人在向顾客演示如何使用食品加工器。 \n, Police arrested several of the demonstrators. \n 警察逮捕了数名示威者。 \n]\n','2019-12-13',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukd/ukdem/ukdemoc026.mp3'),('derivative','缺乏独创性的；模仿的衍生物，派生物；派生词金融衍生产品','uk :dɪˈrɪv.ə.tɪv, us :dɪˈrɪv.ə.t̬ɪv','[His painting/style is very derivative. \n 他的油画／风格有很重的模仿痕迹。 \n,  Detestable  is a derivative of  detest . \n detestable 这个词是从 detest 派生而来的。 \n]\n','2019-10-07',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukd/ukder/ukdereg011.mp3'),('derive','从…中得到，从…中获得','uk :dɪˈraɪv, us :dɪˈraɪv','[The institute derives all its money from foreign investments. \n 该机构的资金均来自于国外投资。 \n, She derives great pleasure/satisfaction from playing the violin. \n 拉小提琴能让她获得极大的乐趣／满足。 \n]\n','2021-03-08',5,7,1,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukd/ukder/ukdereg013.mp3'),('derriere','臀部','uk :ˈder.i.eər, us :ˈder.iˈer','[]\n','2020-03-06',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/e/epd/epd08/epd08320.mp3'),('deserve','值得；应得','uk :dɪˈzɜːv, us :dɪˈzɝːv','[After all that hard work, you deserve a holiday. \n 干了那么多活儿，你该休假了。 \n, Chris deserves our special thanks for all his efforts. \n 我们应该特别感谢克里斯所付出的心血。 \n, I hope they get the punishment they deserve. \n 我希望他们受到应有的惩罚。 \n, [ + to infinitive ] \n They certainly deserved to win that game. \n 他们当然应该赢得那场比赛。 \n]\n','2020-01-24',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukd/ukdes/ukdescr017.mp3'),('desperation','破釜沉舟，拼死一搏急需；渴求','uk :ˌdes.pəˈreɪ.ʃən, us :ˌdes.pəˈreɪ.ʃən','[There was a note of desperation in his voice. \n 他的声音里透出破釜沉舟的决心。 \n, In desperation, they jumped out of the window to escape the fire. \n 情急之下，他们跳出窗户躲避大火。 \n, an act of desperation \n 破釜沉舟之举 \n, his desperation to survive \n 他强烈的求生欲望 \n]\n','2020-01-09',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukd/ukdes/ukdesir023.mp3'),('desultory','漫无目的的，随意的；无计划的','uk :ˈdes.əl.tər.i, us :ˈdes.əl.tɔːr.i','[She made a desultory attempt at conversation. \n 她只是随意聊聊而已。 \n, He wandered around, cleaning up in a desultory way. \n 他四下走走，心不在焉地收拾收拾。 \n]\n','2020-03-05',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukd/ukdes/ukdespo026.mp3'),('detective','侦探警探（用于某些级别的警察头衔）','uk :dɪˈtek.tɪv, us :dɪˈtek.tɪv','[a private detective \n 私家侦探 \n, detective stories \n 侦探故事 \n, Detective Sergeant Lewis \n 刘易斯探长 \n]\n','2019-12-20',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukd/ukdet/ukdetai008.mp3'),('deterioration','恶化','uk :dɪˌtɪə.ri.əˈreɪ.ʃən, us :dɪˌtɪr.i.əˈreɪ.ʃən','[e\'ve seen a deterioration in relations between the countries.\n, When we arrived, we were appalled at her deterioration.\n, e cannot allow continued deterioration of our production standards.\n, A deterioration in retail sales in the second quarter has resulted in a poor forecast.\n]\n','2020-02-19',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english/uk_pron/u/ukd/ukdet/ukdetai015.mp3'),('detest','憎恨；厌恶，讨厌','uk :dɪˈtest, us :dɪˈtest','[I detest any kind of cruelty. \n 我厌恶任何形式的残暴。 \n, [ + -ing verb ] \n I detest having to get up when it\'s dark outside. \n 我讨厌天不亮就得起床。 \n, her detested older brother \n 她那令人讨厌的哥哥 \n]\n','2019-10-07',0,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukd/ukdet/ukdetai023.mp3'),('devastate','摧毁；毁灭使极为震惊；使极为烦乱','uk :ˈdev.ə.steɪt, us :ˈdev.ə.steɪt',NULL,'2021-03-08',7,9,1,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukd/ukdet/ukdetou015.mp3'),('devotee','（狂热的）崇拜者，爱好者','uk :ˌdev.əˈtiː, us :ˌdev.əˈtiː','[He is a great devotee of the prime minister. \n 他是首相的狂热崇拜者。 \n, devotees of golf \n 高尔夫球爱好者 \n]\n','2019-10-07',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukd/ukdev/ukdevil015.mp3'),('diagnose','诊断（病症）；查出（问题）','uk :ˈdaɪ.əɡ.nəʊz, us :ˌdaɪ.əɡˈnoʊz','[The specialist diagnosed cancer. \n 那位专家作出的诊断是癌症。 \n, His condition was diagnosed as some type of blood disorder. \n 他的病被诊断为某种血液病。 \n, She was diagnosed with/as having diabetes. \n 她被查出患有糖尿病。 \n, The electrician has diagnosed a fault in the wiring. \n 电工查出了一处线路故障。 \n]\n','2020-01-20',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukd/ukdex/ukdextr010.mp3'),('dial','拨号，按号码表盘，仪表盘旋钮，调节器（老式电话机的）拨号盘','uk :ˈdaɪ.əl, us :ˈdaɪ.əl','[Can I dial this number direct, or do I have to go through the operator? \n 我可以直接拨这个号码还是需要通过话务员接转？ \n, Dial 0 for the switchboard. \n 总机拨0。 \n, Can you read what it says on the dial? \n 你能读出仪表盘上的读数吗？ \n, The dial of/on his watch had a picture of Mickey Mouse on it. \n 他手表的表盘上有一个米老鼠的图案。 \n, You turn this dial to find a different radio station. \n 转动这个旋钮可选择不同的广播电台。 \n]\n','2019-12-23',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukd/ukdex/ukdextr019.mp3'),('diameter','直径','uk :daɪˈæm.ɪ.tər, us :daɪˈæm.ə.t̬ɚ','[The diameter measures twice the radius. \n 直径是半径的两倍。 \n, The pond is six feet in diameter. \n 这个池塘的直径为6英尺。 \n]\n','2020-03-31',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukd/ukdex/ukdextr026.mp3'),('diarrhea','腹泻','uk :ˌdaɪ.əˈriː.ə, us :ˌdaɪ.əˈriː.ə','[diarrhoea and sickness \n 腹泻恶心 \n, an attack of diarrhoea \n 腹泻发作 \n]\n','2020-01-23',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukd/ukdia/ukdiaph004.mp3'),('digestive','消化的（全麦）消化饼干','uk :daɪˈdʒes.tɪv, us :daɪˈdʒes.tɪv','[the digestive process \n 消化过程 \n]\n','2020-01-23',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukd/ukdif/ukdiffi016.mp3'),('dimly','昏暗的','uk :ˈdɪm.li, us :ˈdɪm.li','[he room was dimly lit.\n, The February sun shone dimly.\n,  dimly remembered reading the book a few years before.\n, They were only dimly aware of the telephone ringing.\n]\n','2021-03-26',3,6,1,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english/uk_pron/u/ukd/ukdig/ukdigs_029.mp3'),('dimmer','亮度调节器','uk :ˈdɪm.ər, us :ˈdɪm.ɚ','[]\n','2019-12-26',0,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uka/uka32/uka32549.mp3'),('disarming','缴…的械,解除…的武装；交出武器,裁军（尤指出乎意料地）使产生好感','uk :dɪˈsɑːm, us :dɪˈsɑːrm','[With one movement, she disarmed the man and pinned him against the wall. \n 她一下子就缴了那男子的械，并把他按到墙上。 \n, Many politicians argued that this was no time to disarm (= give up the country s weapons and army). \n 很多政治家争辩说现在不是交出国家的武器和军队的时候。 \n, Experts successfully managed to disarm the bomb (= stop it from exploding). \n 专家们成功地拆除了炸弹的引信。 \n, His frankness completely disarmed her. \n 他的坦率彻底征服了她。 \n]\n','2020-01-20',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukd/ukdis/ukdisap003.mp3'),('disc','圆盘，盘状物椎间盘唱盘；光盘','uk :dɪsk, us :dɪsk','[The dog s name was engraved on a little metal disc attached to its collar. \n 狗的名字刻在项圈上吊着的一块金属小圆盘上。 \n]\n','2020-02-19',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukd/ukdis/ukdisap021.mp3'),('discourse','对话；交流演讲，演说；论文，文章','uk :ˈdɪs.kɔːs, us :ˈdɪs.kɔːrs','[a discourse on/upon the nature of life after death \n 关于来世之实质的文章 \n]\n','2020-04-03',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukd/ukdis/ukdisco012.mp3'),('discrepancy','不一致，出入，差异','uk :dɪˈskrep.ən.si, us :dɪˈskrep.ən.si','[There is some discrepancy between the two accounts. \n 这两份账单之间有一些出入。 \n, The committee is reportedly unhappy about the discrepancy in numbers. \n 据说委员会对数字不一致很不满。 \n]\n','2020-02-13',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukd/ukdis/ukdisco024.mp3'),('discrimination','歧视；区别对待区分能力，辨别能力','uk :dɪˌskrɪm.ɪˈneɪ.ʃən, us :dɪˌskrɪm.əˈneɪ.ʃən','[racial/sex/age discrimination \n 种族／性别／年龄歧视 \n, Until 1986 most companies would not even allow women to take the exams, but such blatant discrimination is now disappearing. \n 直至1986年大多数公司甚至还不允许女性参加这种考试，但目前这种明目张胆的歧视做法正在消失。 \n]\n','2020-02-14',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukd/ukdis/ukdisco030.mp3'),('disgruntled','不满的；不悦的','uk :dɪsˈɡrʌn.təld, us :dɪsˈɡrʌn.t̬əld','[A disgruntled former employee is being blamed for the explosion. \n 一名心怀不满的前员工被认为是此次爆炸的罪魁祸首。 \n, The players were disgruntled with the umpire. \n 运动员们对裁判不满。 \n]\n','2020-03-19',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukd/ukdis/ukdiscr030.mp3'),('disguise','给…化装，给…乔装打扮；将…伪装起来掩饰，隐藏（观点、感受等）化装用具（服饰）；用于伪装的东西伪装，化装','uk :dɪsˈɡaɪz, us :dɪsˈɡaɪz','[He disguised himself by wearing a false beard. \n 他粘上假胡须伪装自己。 \n, Minor skin imperfections can usually be disguised with a spot of make-up. \n 微小的皮肤瑕疵通常可以用化妆品来掩盖。 \n, We tried to disguise the fact that it was just a school hall by putting up coloured lights and balloons. \n 我们挂上彩灯和气球，不想让人看出这里实际上只是一个学校礼堂。 \n, I couldn t disguise my disappointment. \n 我无法掩饰自己的失望。 \n, He put on a large hat and glasses as a disguise and hoped no one would recognize him. \n 他戴上大帽子和眼镜来伪装自己，希望没人会认出他来。 \n, She usually goes out in disguise to avoid being bothered by the public. \n 她外出时通常都要化装，以免受到公众的打扰。 \n, He claims that most Western aid to the Third World is just colonialism in disguise. \n 他说西方给第三世界提供的援助大多只是变相的殖民主义行为。 \n]\n','2020-03-25',2,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukd/ukdis/ukdisgu001.mp3'),('disinfection','消毒','uk :ˌdɪs.ɪnˈfek.ʃən, us :ˌdɪs.ɪnˈfek.ʃən','[horough cleaning and disinfection of all surfaces is essential.\n, water disinfection products\n]\n','2020-01-23',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english/uk_pron/u/ukb/ukb00/ukb00443.mp3'),('dispose','使对…产生某种感觉','uk :dɪˈspəʊz, us :dɪˈspoʊz','[His rudeness when we first met didn t dispose me very kindlyto/towards him. \n 我们首次会面时他粗暴的态度使我对他没产生什么好感。 \n]\n','2020-01-23',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukd/ukdis/ukdispl010.mp3'),('dispose-of','摆脱','摆脱','null\n','2020-01-23',0,0,0,'null'),('disproportionate','不成比例的；不相称的；太大（或太小）的','uk :ˌdɪs.prəˈpɔː.ʃən.ət, us :ˌdɪs.prəˈpɔːr.ʃən.ət','[There are a disproportionate number of girls in the class. \n 这个班里女孩的人数特别多。 \n, The country s great influence in the world is disproportionate to its relatively small size. \n 该国在世界上的巨大影响力与其相对较小的面积有些不成比例。 \n]\n','2020-03-05',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukd/ukdis/ukdispl017.mp3'),('disregard','忽视，漠视，无视忽视，无视，不理会','uk :ˌdɪs.rɪˈɡɑːd, us :ˌdɪs.rɪˈɡɑːrd','[What amazes me is her complete disregard for anyone else s opinion. \n 让我吃惊的是，她完全无视他人的意见。 \n, He told us to disregard everything we d learned so far and start again. \n 他告诉我们不要考虑所学过的东西，一切要重新开始。 \n]\n','2020-03-18',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukd/ukdis/ukdispl030.mp3'),('disruption','分裂','uk :dɪsˈrʌpʃən, us :','[t would cause a tremendous disruption to our work schedule to install a different computer system.\n, A crackdown on illegal-immigrant hiring could create widespread workplace disruptions.\n]\n','2019-10-08',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english/uk_pron/u/ukd/ukdis/ukdisre010.mp3'),('dissent','（尤指对正式建议、计划或普遍看法的）不同意，异议不服裁判不同意，持有异议','uk :dɪˈsent, us :dɪˈsent',NULL,'2021-03-11',15,17,1,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukd/ukder/ukdereg029.mp3'),('dissertation','专题论文；学位论文','uk :ˌdɪs.əˈteɪ.ʃən, us :ˌdɪs.ɚˈteɪ.ʃən','[Ann did her dissertation on Baudelaire. \n 安的论文写的是波德莱尔。 \n]\n','2020-04-01',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukd/ukdis/ukdisre024.mp3'),('dissolution','（官方组织的）解散；（法律合约的）解除','uk :ˌdɪs.əˈluː.ʃən, us :ˌdɪs.əˈluː.ʃən',NULL,'2021-03-08',6,8,1,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukd/ukdis/ukdissi007.mp3'),('distemper','（尤指过去刷墙用的）水胶混合涂料（动物感染的）瘟热；（尤指）犬瘟热','uk :dɪˈstem.pər, us :dɪˈstem.pɚ','[]\n','2020-02-27',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukd/ukdis/ukdissi019.mp3'),('distinction','区别，差别，不同优秀，卓越（学生作业的）优，优等特质，特性','uk :dɪˈstɪŋk.ʃən, us :dɪˈstɪŋk.ʃən','[There s a clear distinction between the dialects spoken in the two regions. \n 这两个地区的方言有着明显的不同。 \n, This company makes no distinction between the sexes. \n 这家公司男女平等。 \n, a writer/scientist/wine of distinction \n 一流的作家／科学家／葡萄酒 \n, She has the distinction of being one of the few people to have an honorary degree conferred on her by the university this year. \n 今年只有几个人被授予了大学荣誉学位，她有幸成为其中之一。 \n]\n','2020-03-05',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukd/ukdis/ukdissi027.mp3'),('distinguishable','易分辨的','uk :dɪˈstɪŋ.ɡwɪ.ʃə.bəl, us :dɪˈstɪŋ.ɡwɪ.ʃə.bəl','[here are at least 20 distinguishable dialects of the language just on the south island.\n, His days were barely distinguishable from one another. \n,  few words were distinguishable among the slurred muttering.\n]\n','2019-12-13',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english/uk_pron/u/ukd/ukdis/ukdisti002.mp3'),('distress','忧虑；悲伤；痛苦受苦；遇难；遇险使烦乱，使焦虑，使忧虑','uk :dɪˈstres, us :dɪˈstres','[She claimed that the way she had been treated at work had caused her extreme emotional and psychological distress. \n 她说自己在工作中受到的待遇让她在情感和心理上都感到非常痛苦。 \n, Many of the horses were showing signs of distress at the end of the race. \n 比赛接近尾声时，许多马匹都表现出非常痛苦的样子。 \n, Six people were rescued by helicopter from a fishing boat in distress off the coast. \n 直升机从海岸附近的一艘遇险渔船上救出了6个人。 \n, a distress signal \n 求救信号 \n, I hope I haven t distressed you with all these personal questions. \n 我希望我问的这些私人问题没有让你心烦。 \n]\n','2020-02-13',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukd/ukdis/ukdisti014.mp3'),('district','区，区域','uk :ˈdɪs.trɪkt, us :ˈdɪs.trɪkt','[the business district of New York \n 纽约的商业区 \n, the Lake District/the Peak District \n 湖区／峰区 \n, S \n the City of Malden School District \n 马尔登市学区 \n, K \n South Cambridgeshire District Council \n 剑桥郡南区议会 \n]\n','2020-01-09',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukd/ukdis/ukdisti022.mp3'),('distrust','不信任，不相信，怀疑不信任，不相信，怀疑','uk :dɪˈstrʌst, us :dɪˈstrʌst','[The two groups have existed in a state of mutual distrust for centuries. \n 几个世纪以来这两个群体一直处于互不信任的状态之中。 \n, She has a (deep) distrust of the media. \n 她对媒体（非常）不信任。 \n, Many politicians are deeply distrusted by the electorate. \n 很多政治人物非常不受选民信任。 \n]\n','2020-01-10',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukd/ukdis/ukdisti023.mp3'),('disturbed','有精神障碍的，精神不正常的，精神受刺激的','uk :dɪˈstɜːbd, us :dɪˈstɝːbd','[a centre for emotionally/mentally disturbed teenagers \n 情感／精神障碍少年康复中心 \n]\n','2020-02-27',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukd/ukdis/ukdisti027.mp3'),('dithering','犹豫，踌躇对…感到紧张（或激动、困惑等）','uk :ˈdɪð.ər, us :ˈdɪð.ɚ','[Stop dithering and choose which one you want! \n 别犹豫了，赶快决定你想要哪个！ \n, She\'s still dithering over whether to accept the job she\'s just been offered. \n 她还在犹豫要不要接受刚刚给她的那份工作。 \n, Gideon is in a bit of a dither about what to wear for the interview. \n 吉迪恩紧张得有些不知穿什么衣服去参加面试才好。 \n]\n','2019-10-08',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukd/ukdis/ukdisun006.mp3'),('ditto','也是如此，亦然（表示赞同或避免重复时用）表示“同上”或“同前”的符号（\"）','uk :ˈdɪt.əʊ, us :ˈdɪt̬.oʊ','[ I hate reality TV shows   Ditto.  \n “我讨厌这些真人秀电视节目。”“我也是。” \n, Local residents are opposed to the proposal. Ditto many members of the city council (= they are also opposed). \n 当地居民反对这个提案，很多市议会议员也是如此。 \n]\n','2020-01-14',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukd/ukdis/ukdisun010.mp3'),('diversion','绕行路线改变目的地；改变用途转移注意力的事物；分心的事物消遣，娱乐','uk :daɪˈvɜː.ʃən, us :dɪˈvɝː.ʃən','[Traffic diversions will be kept to a minimum throughout the festival. \n 在节日期间，尽量少实行交通禁行措施。 \n, the diversion of money to other projects \n 将资金转用于其他项目 \n, Shoplifters often work in pairs, with one creating a diversion to distract the staff while the other steals the goods. \n 商店窃贼通常结伙作案，一人转移店员的注意力，另一人则偷盗货物。 \n, Reading is a pleasant diversion. \n 阅读是一种愉快的消遣。 \n]\n','2020-04-03',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukd/ukdis/ukdisun028.mp3'),('diversity','多样性，多样化差异，不同点；差异性','uk :daɪˈvɜː.sə.ti, us :dɪˈvɝː.sə.t̬i','[Does television adequately reflect the ethnic and cultural diversity of the country? \n 电视节目能充分反映出这个国家民族和文化的多样性吗？ \n, There is a wide diversity of opinion on the question of unilateral disarmament. \n 对于单方面裁军问题，人们的看法各不相同。 \n]\n','2020-04-01',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukd/ukdis/ukdisun030.mp3'),('doctrine','（尤指政治或宗教的）信条，教义，学说','uk :ˈdɒk.trɪn, us :ˈdɑːk.trɪn','[Christian doctrine \n 基督教教义 \n, The president said he would not go against sound military doctrine. \n 总统说他不会反对行之有效的军事学说。 \n]\n','2020-01-09',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukd/ukdiz/ukdizzi030.mp3'),('dodgy','不诚实的，不怀好意的不可靠的；有风险的可能要断的；可能会痛苦的','uk :ˈdɒdʒ.i, us :ˈdɑː.dʒi','[a dodgy deal \n 不诚实的交易 \n, They got involved with a dodgy businessman and lost all their savings. \n 他们遇到了一个奸商，结果把所有积蓄都赔进去了。 \n, The weather might be a bit dodgy at this time of year. \n 每年的这个时候天气都可能有些变化无常。 \n, I can t come in to work today - I ve got a bit of a dodgy stomach. \n 我今天不能来上班了——我的肚子有些不舒服。 \n, It was a dodgy situation. \n 当时局面并不稳定。 \n, Careful - that chair s a bit dodgy. \n 小心——那把椅子有些不稳。 \n, Ever since the accident I ve had this dodgy leg. \n 自从那次事故以后，我的腿就总是作痛。 \n]\n','2020-03-19',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukd/ukdoc/ukdocud013.mp3'),('domestic','本国的，国内的家庭的佣人，保姆','uk :dəˈmes.tɪk, us :dəˈmes.tɪk','[domestic airlines/flights \n 国内航空公司／航班 \n, Domestic opinion had turned against the war. \n 国内舆论已转而反对战争。 \n, domestic chores/duties/arrangements \n 家务琐事／家庭责任／家务安排 \n]\n','2020-02-13',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukd/ukdol/ukdolph006.mp3'),('dorm','（尤指寄宿学校或大学的）宿舍（学院或大学的）学生宿舍楼','uk :dɔːm, us :dɔːrm','[The hostel has single-sex dorms.\n, Smoking is not permitted in college dorms.\n, My mom and I were buying things 