nk you . \n 我们从小就被反复告知总要记着说“请”和“谢谢”。 \n, He drilled the children in what they should say. \n 他一遍又一遍地告诉孩子们应该说什么话。 \n]\n','2020-01-03',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukd/ukdre/ukdress017.mp3'),('droplet','小滴','uk :ˈdrɒp.lət, us :ˈdrɑːp.lət','[]\n','2020-01-24',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukd/ukdri/ukdrive017.mp3'),('drowning','溺死，淹死','uk :ˈdraʊn.ɪŋ, us :ˈdraʊn.ɪŋ','[There were three drownings in the lake last year. \n 去年这个湖里发生过3起溺水身亡事件。 \n, death by drowning \n 溺亡 \n]\n','2020-02-27',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/c/ca2/ca2uk/ca2uk036.mp3'),('dual','两部分的；二元的；双重的（教练汽车的）双重控制，复式操纵双重国籍','uk :ˈdʒuː.əl, us :ˈduː.əl','[This room has a dual purpose, serving as both a study and a dining room. \n 这个房间有两个用途，既作书房又当餐厅。 \n, the dual role of chairman and chief executive \n 董事长和首席执行官的双重角色 \n, She has dual British and American nationality. \n 她有英美双重国籍。 \n]\n','2020-01-14',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukd/ukdru/ukdrubb026.mp3'),('dubious','半信半疑的，可疑的；不确定的；不可信的怀疑的；无把握的','uk :ˈdʒuː.bi.əs, us :ˈduː.bi.əs','[These claims are dubious and not scientifically proven. \n 这些说法未经科学证实，有些可疑。 \n, He has been associated with some dubious characters. \n 他曾经与一些可疑人物有交往。 \n, Ruth Ellis has the dubious (= bad) distinction of being the last woman to be hanged in Britain. \n 露丝‧埃利斯背负着英国最后一个被绞死的女人这样一个恶名。 \n, I m dubious about his promises to change his ways. \n 他承诺将改变行事方式，我对此有些怀疑。 \n]\n','2020-03-05',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukd/ukdub/ukdubio001.mp3'),('dumb','哑的；说不出话的愚蠢的','uk :dʌm, us :dʌm','[He s been deaf and dumb since birth. \n 他生下来就又聋又哑。 \n, She was struck dumb by what she had seen. \n 她被自己看到的惊得说不出话来。 \n, Are they brave or just dumb? \n 他们是勇敢还是愚蠢而已？ \n, What a dumb idea! \n 这想法太蠢了！ \n]\n','2019-12-27',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukd/ukdul/ukdull_007.mp3'),('dutch','荷兰的；荷兰人的；荷兰语的荷兰语','uk :dʌtʃ, us :dʌtʃ','[]\n','2020-02-13',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukd/ukdus/ukdusts003.mp3'),('dutiful','尽责的，尽职的','uk :ˈdʒuː.tɪ.fəl, us :ˈduː.t̬ɪ.fəl','[a dutiful son/husband \n 孝顺的儿子／有责任感的丈夫 \n]\n','2020-01-09',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukd/ukdus/ukdusts006.mp3'),('dysfunction','功体失调；机能不良','uk :dɪsˈfʌŋk.ʃən, us :dɪsˈfʌŋk.ʃən','[There appears to be a dysfunction in the patient s respiratory system. \n 患者的呼吸系统似乎出现功能失调。 \n]\n','2020-01-23',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukd/ukdyn/ukdynam005.mp3'),('easter','复活节（基督教纪念耶稣复活的节日）','uk :ˈiː.stər, us :ˈiː.stɚ','[I get two weeks off school at Easter. \n 复活节我们学校放假两周。 \n]\n','2020-01-10',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uke/ukeas/ukeasil006.mp3'),('eccentric','怪异的，古怪的；异乎寻常的不正圆的行为古怪的人','uk :ɪkˈsen.trɪk, us :ɪkˈsen.trɪk','[eccentric behaviour \n 怪异的行为 \n, eccentric clothes \n 奇装异服 \n, My mother is something of an eccentric. \n 我妈妈有点古怪。 \n]\n','2020-03-24',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uke/ukec_/ukec___004.mp3'),('ego','自我评价；自我中心；自负；自尊心（心理分析上的）自我','uk :ˈiː.ɡəʊ, us :ˈiː.ɡoʊ','[That man has such an enormous ego - I ve never known anyone so full of themselves! \n 那个人自负得要命——我从来没有见过这么自以为是的人。 \n, I m glad she got the job - she needed something to boost/bolster her ego (= give her confidence). \n 我很高兴她得到了这份工作——她太需要点什么来增强她的信心了。 \n]\n','2020-02-21',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uke/ukeff/ukeffor014.mp3'),('elaborate','精心计划（或制作）的；详尽的；复杂的详尽说明；阐述','uk :iˈlæb.ər.ət, us :iˈlæb.ɚ.ət','[You want a plain blouse to go with that skirt - nothing too elaborate. \n 你应该用一件样式简单的衬衫来配那条裙子，不要样式太复杂的。 \n, They re making the most elaborate preparations for the wedding. \n 他们正为婚礼做极为精心周到的准备。 \n, He came out with such an elaborate excuse that I didn t quite believe him. \n 他突然说了那么一大套理由，我不太相信他。 \n, The congresswoman said she was resigning, but refused to elaborate on her reasons for doing so. \n 这位国会女议员说她要辞职，但拒绝说明辞职的原因。 \n]\n','2019-12-20',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uke/ukeig/ukeight014.mp3'),('elbow','肘；（衣服的）肘部用肘推；用肘挤开（为让某人注意或提醒某事而）用肘碰','uk :ˈel.bəʊ, us :ˈel.boʊ','[Her arm was bandaged from the elbow to the fingers. \n 她的胳膊从肘部一直到手指全缠上了绷带。 \n, The sleeve of his shirt was torn at the elbow. \n 他的衬衫的肘部被撕了个口子。 \n, He elbowed his way to the front of the crowd. \n 他挤到了人群的前边。 \n, They elbowed the onlookers aside. \n 他们把旁观者推到一边。 \n, She elbowed me in the ribs before I could say anything. \n 我还没开口呢，她就用胳膊肘在我肋部碰了一下。 \n]\n','2019-12-26',0,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uke/ukeig/ukeight030.mp3'),('elementary','基本的初级的；基础的','uk :ˌel.ɪˈmen.tər.i, us :ˌel.əˈmen.t̬ɚ.i','[I have an elementary knowledge of physics. \n 我懂一些基本的物理知识。 \n, They made some elementary mistakes. \n 他们犯了一些很基础的错误。 \n, Millions of travellers fail to take even the most elementary of precautions. \n 上百万的旅行者甚至没有采取最基本的预防措施。 \n, This book contains a series of elementary exercises for learners. \n 本书含有为学习者设计的一系列基础练习。 \n]\n','2020-03-06',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uke/ukele/ukelect014.mp3'),('elevation','立面图；立视图海拔；高度丘；高地，高处提拔；晋升；提升','uk :ˌel.ɪˈveɪ.ʃən, us :ˌel.əˈveɪ.ʃən','[This plan shows the front, side, and back elevations of the new supermarket. \n 该示意图展示的是新超市的正、侧、后三面的立视图。 \n, Atmospheric pressure varies with elevation and temperature. \n 气压随海拔和气温的变化而变化。 \n, The crop is not grown at high elevations/above an elevation of 1,000 metres. \n 这种作物不宜在海拔高的／海拔高于1000米的地区种植。 \n, The flagpole stands on a small elevation in front of the building. \n 旗杆矗立在楼前的一小块高地上。 \n, His elevation to the presidency of the new republic was generally popular. \n 总的来说，他被推举为新共和国的总统是众望所归。 \n]\n','2020-01-10',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uke/ukele/ukelect020.mp3'),('elite','（社会）上层集团；掌权人物；出类拔萃的人，精英（社会）上层集团的；掌权人物的；精英的','uk :iˈliːt, us :iˈliːt','[the country\'s educated elite \n 这个国家受过良好教育的精英 \n, a member of the elite \n 上层集团的一员 \n, isapproving \n A powerful and corrupt elite has bled this country dry. \n 该国专权腐败的权贵阶层榨干了人民的血汗。 \n, Elite troops were airlifted to the trouble zone. \n 精锐部队被空运到骚乱地区。 \n]\n','2019-10-07',0,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uke/ukeli/ukelimi005.mp3'),('elysium','极其美好；天堂','uk :iˈlɪz.i.əm, us :iˈlɪz.i.əm','[Everything was perfect. She was in Elysium. \n 对她来说一切都是那么完美，就好像在天堂一样。 \n]\n','2020-01-20',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uke/ukelu/ukeluci008.mp3'),('emaciated','（通常由于疾病或极度饥饿）消瘦的，憔悴的，虚弱的','uk :iˈmeɪ.si.eɪ.tɪd, us :iˈmeɪ.si.eɪ.t̬ɪd','[There were pictures of emaciated children on the cover of the magazine. \n 杂志封面上是几幅骨瘦如柴的儿童的照片。 \n]\n','2020-01-03',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uke/ukelu/ukeluci010.mp3'),('emanate','表现；显示','uk :ˈem.ə.neɪt, us :ˈem.ə.neɪt','[Her face emanated sadness. \n 她脸上露出伤心的表情。 \n]\n','2020-03-05',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uke/ukelu/ukeluci013.mp3'),('emblem','象征；标志；符号；徽章','uk :ˈem.bləm, us :ˈem.bləm','[A rose is the national emblem of England. \n 玫瑰是英格兰的标志。 \n]\n','2020-01-10',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uke/ukemb/ukembar015.mp3'),('emerge','出现，浮现；露出（从困境中）摆脱出来，存活下来（尤指经过审查或讯问后）被知晓，显露，暴露','uk :ɪˈmɜːdʒ, us :ɪˈmɝːdʒ','[She emerged from the sea, blue with cold. \n 她浮出了海面，浑身冻得发青。 \n, The Prince emerged unscathed from the scandal. \n 王子安然走出了丑闻。 \n, The facts behind the scandal are sure to emerge eventually. \n 丑闻背后的真相最终一定会水落石出。 \n, [ + that ] \n It has emerged that secret talks had been going on between the two companies before the takeover was announced. \n 现在已经真相大白，原来在接管计划宣布之前，两家公司一直在进行秘密会谈。 \n, She s the most exciting British singer to emerge on the pop scene for a decade. \n 她是10年来在流行乐坛中崭露头角的最为令人兴奋的英国歌手。 \n]\n','2020-02-21',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uke/ukemb/ukembry007.mp3'),('eminent','显赫的；卓越的；著名的','uk :ˈem.ɪ.nənt, us :ˈem.ə.nənt',NULL,'2021-03-08',6,9,1,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uke/ukemb/ukembry021.mp3'),('emission','（气体、热量、光线等的）排放，散发，射出排放物；散发物','uk :iˈmɪʃ.ən, us :iˈmɪʃ.ən','[Environmental groups want a substantial reduction in the emission of greenhouse gases. \n 环保组织要求切实减少温室气体的排放量。 \n, carbon dioxide emissions \n 二氧化碳的排放 \n]\n','2020-01-15',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uke/ukemb/ukembry027.mp3'),('emphasize','强调；重视使突出；使明显','uk :ˈem.fə.saɪz, us :ˈem.fə.saɪz','[[ + question word ] \n I d just like to emphasize how important it is for people to learn foreign languages. \n 我只是想强调一下学习外语的重要性。 \n, [ + that ] \n He emphasized that all the people taking part in the research were volunteers. \n 他着重指出所有参加这项研究的人都是志愿者。 \n, You can use italics or capitals to emphasize a word in a piece of writing. \n 你可以用斜体或者大写来强调文章中的某个词。 \n, Tight jeans will only emphasize any extra weight that you are carrying. \n 紧身牛仔裤只会使你身上的赘肉更明显。 \n]\n','2020-02-28',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uke/ukemo/ukemolu017.mp3'),('enchant','使陶醉；使入迷对…施魔法','uk :ɪnˈtʃɑːnt, us :ɪnˈtʃænt','[The audience was clearly enchanted by her performance. \n 观众显然陶醉于她的演出中。 \n]\n','2020-01-15',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uke/ukenc/ukencas002.mp3'),('encrust','cover or decorate (something) with a hard surface layer','/ɪnˈkrʌst,ɛnˈkrʌst/','null\n','2020-04-01',5,0,0,'null'),('encyclopedias','百科全书；（某一学科的）专科全书，大全','uk :ɪnˌsaɪ.kləˈpiː.di.ə, us :ɪnˌsaɪ.kləˈpiː.di.ə','[The Cambridge Encyclopedia of Language \n 剑桥语言百科全书 \n]\n','2020-02-21',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uke/ukenc/ukencum002.mp3'),('encyclopedic','信息量大的；知识渊博的百科全书似的；包罗万象的；博学的','uk :ɪnˌsaɪ.kləˈpiː.dɪk, us :ɪnˌsaɪ.kləˈpiː.dɪk','[her encyclopedic knowledge of France \n 她关于法国的广博知识 \n]\n','2020-03-11',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uke/ukenc/ukencum003.mp3'),('endurance','忍耐力，耐受力','uk :ɪnˈdʒʊə.rəns, us :ɪnˈdʊr.əns','[Running a marathon is a test of human endurance. \n 马拉松长跑是对人耐力的考验。 \n, The pain was bad beyond endurance. \n 疼痛剧烈，令人难以忍受。 \n]\n','2020-01-17',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uke/ukenc/ukencum028.mp3'),('engage','雇用；聘用吸引住，使感兴趣（使）（机器）啮合，接合，衔接进攻；（与…）交战，（与…）开战教（儿童）；使忙于，使参加（尤指作家、音乐家、艺术家等）积极介入政治的','uk :ɪnˈɡeɪdʒ, us :ɪnˈɡeɪdʒ','[[ + to infinitive ] \n I have engaged a secretary to deal with all my paperwork. \n 我雇用了一名秘书来处理我全部的文书工作。 \n, We re engaging the services of a professional administrator. \n 我们将聘用专业管理人员为我们服务。 \n, The debate about food safety has engaged the whole nation. \n 关于食品安全的争论引起了全国关注。 \n, If a book doesn t engage my interest in the first few pages, I don t usually continue reading it. \n 如果一本书的前几页不能引起我的兴趣，通常我就不再往下读了。 \n, When the large gear wheel engages (with the smaller one), the mill stone will start to go round. \n 当大齿轮（与小齿轮）啮合时，石磨就开始转动。 \n, Enemy planes engaged the troops as they advanced into the mountains. \n 部队进山的时候，敌机开始对他们发起攻击。 \n]\n','2020-02-28',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uke/ukend/ukendwa022.mp3'),('enrollment','入学登记','uk :ˌəʊ.pən ədˈmɪʃ.ənz, us :ˌoʊ.pən ədˈmɪʃ.ənz','null\n','2021-03-26',0,0,0,'null'),('entail','使必要；牵涉','uk :ɪnˈteɪl, us :ɪnˈteɪl','[Such a large investment inevitably entails some risk. \n 这样的巨额投资必然会有一定的风险。 \n, [ + -ing verb ] \n Repairing the roof will entail spending a lot of money. \n 修房顶免不了要花好多钱。 \n]\n','2019-10-08',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uke/ukens/ukensla007.mp3'),('enterocolitis','小肠结肠炎','ˌentərōkəˈlītis','null\n','2020-01-23',0,0,0,'null'),('entrenched','牢固确立的；根深蒂固的；积重难返的','uk :ɪnˈtrentʃt, us :ɪnˈtrentʃt','[It s very difficult to change attitudes that have become so deeply entrenched over the years. \n 改变多年以来形成的根深蒂固的旧看法是很困难的。 \n, The organization was often criticized for being too entrenched in its views. \n 这个组织死守着自己的观点不变，因此常常受到批评。 \n]\n','2020-02-28',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uke/ukent/ukentic026.mp3'),('entwined','缠绕；盘绕；使交错紧密结合的；不可分离的','uk :ɪnˈtwaɪn, us :ɪnˈtwaɪn','[The picture captures the two lovers with their arms entwined. \n 这张照片拍摄到的是紧紧拥抱在一起的一对恋人。 \n, The fates of both countries seem somehow entwined. \n 这两个国家的命运似乎是紧密相连的。 \n]\n','2020-02-21',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uke/ukent/ukentre008.mp3'),('enveloped','覆盖；包住；围绕；笼罩','uk :ɪnˈvel.əp, us :ɪnˈvel.əp','[The graveyard looked ghostly, enveloped in mist. \n 墓地笼罩在薄雾中，显得阴森森的。 \n]\n','2020-01-23',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uke/ukent/ukentre012.mp3'),('enviably','令人羡慕的','uk :ˈen.vi.ə.bli, us :ˈen.vi.ə.bli','[espite her problems, she has an enviably positive attitude.\n, They share an enviably happy life.\n]\n','2020-03-11',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english/uk_pron/u/uke/ukent/ukentre015.mp3'),('enzyme','酶','uk :ˈen.zaɪm, us :ˈen.zaɪm','[An enzyme in the saliva of the mouth starts the process of breaking down the food. \n 由于唾液中酶的作用，食物进入口腔时就开始了分解过程。 \n]\n','2020-01-24',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uke/ukent/ukentre029.mp3'),('epidemic','（疾病的）流行，传染泛滥；蔓延流行的；盛行的；肆虐的','uk :ˌep.ɪˈdem.ɪk, us :ˌep.əˈdem.ɪk','[a flu epidemic \n 流感的传播 \n, a crime/unemployment epidemic \n 犯罪频发／大范围失业 \n, Poverty in this country has reached epidemic proportions . \n 这个国家很多人处于贫困之中。 \n, Crime and poverty are epidemic in the city. \n 犯罪和贫穷如瘟疫一般在这个城市肆虐。 \n]\n','2020-01-23',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uke/ukepe/ukepee_010.mp3'),('epidemiology','流行病学的','uk :ˌep.ɪ.diː.miˈɒl.ə.dʒi, us :ˌep.ə.diːmiˈɑː.lə.dʒi','[]\n','2020-01-23',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/e/epd/epd10/epd10065.mp3'),('episode','事件；（相关的）一连串事件；一段经历（尤指电视或广播节目的）一集，一节，片断','uk :ˈep.ɪ.səʊd, us :ˈep.ə.soʊd','[This latest episode in the fraud scandal has shocked a lot of people. \n 诈骗丑闻最新爆出的这一事件让很多人瞠目结舌。 \n, The drugs, the divorce, and the depression - it s an episode in his life that he wants to forget. \n 吸毒、离婚和消沉——这是他人生中不堪回首的一段经历。 \n]\n','2019-12-13',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uke/ukepe/ukepee_023.mp3'),('equity','（公司的）股本，股票值；股票资产净值公平；公正（英语国家的一种司法制度，允许在现存法律不适用时对案件作出公正判决的）衡平法','uk :ˈek.wɪ.ti, us :ˈek.wə.t̬i','[He sold his equity in the company last year. \n 他去年卖掉了这家公司的股票。 \n, The rights give holders the opportunity to purchase additional equity interests in the company at a big discount. \n 这些权利使得股票持有者有机会以很优惠的折扣价额外购买该公司股份。 \n, a society based on equity and social justice \n 建立在公平公正和社会正义基础之上的社会 \n]\n','2019-10-07',0,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uke/ukequ/ukequip004.mp3'),('errand','（短程）差事；跑腿','uk :ˈer.ənd, us :ˈer.ənd','[I ll meet you at six, I ve got some errands to do/run first. \n 我会在6点和你见面，我得先去办些事情。 \n]\n','2020-01-03',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uke/ukero/ukeroge008.mp3'),('escalation','扩大，恶化','uk :ˌes.kəˈleɪ.ʃən, us :ˌes.kəˈleɪ.ʃən','[t\'s difficult to explain the recent escalation in/of violent crime.\n, Price escalations for building materials caused the project to be cancelled.\n,  U ] \n the escalation of costs\n, [ C ] \n military escalation\n]\n','2020-02-19',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english/uk_pron/u/uke/ukero/ukeroge027.mp3'),('establishment','企业；机构；单位（尤指支持维持现状的）当权派，统治集团，权势集团建立；创立','uk :ɪˈstæb.lɪʃ.mənt, us :ɪˈstæb.lɪʃ.mənt',NULL,'2020-03-19',1,5,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uke/ukesq/ukesq__010.mp3'),('estate','（位于乡村的）大片私有土地，庄园，种植园（个人死后留下的全部）财产，遗产（按规划建造的）住宅区，工业区旅游汽车；客货两用轿车状况；状态','uk :ɪˈsteɪt, us :ɪˈsteɪt','[It s a typical country estate with a large house for the owner, farm buildings, and estate workers  houses. \n 这是一个典型的乡村庄园，建有主人的大宅子、许多农舍以及庄园工人的住处。 \n, She left her entire estate to her niece. \n 她把所有的遗产都留给了自己的侄女。 \n, a housing estate \n 住宅区 \n, an industrial estate (= a group of factories) \n 工业区 \n, the holy estate of marriage \n 婚姻的神圣性 \n]\n','2020-02-14',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uke/ukesq/ukesq__011.mp3'),('estimate','估计；估算；估价估计；估算；估价','uk :ˈes.tɪ.meɪt, us :ˈes.tə.meɪt','[Government sources estimate a long-term 50 percent increase in rail fares. \n 政府消息人士估计火车票价将有一个涨幅达50%的长期上调。 \n, [ + (that) ] \n They estimate (that) the journey will take at least two weeks. \n 他们估计这次行程至少需要两周时间。 \n, [ + question word ] \n It was difficult to estimate how many trees had been destroyed. \n 很难估计有多少树被毁。 \n, The number of people who applied for the course was 120 compared with an initial estimate of between 50 and 100. \n 最初估计申请选修这门课程的学生也就是50到100人，可实际上报名的有120人。 \n, We ll accept the lowest of three estimates for the building work. \n 在对这项建筑工程的3个投标中，我们将采纳报价最低的那个。 \n, a conservative (= low) estimate \n 保守估计 \n, a rough (= not exact) estimate \n 粗略估计 \n]\n','2020-03-05',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uke/ukesq/ukesq__014.mp3'),('ethereal','轻飘的，缥缈的；优雅的；（尤指）超凡的','uk :iˈθɪə.ri.əl, us :iˈθɪr.i.əl','[an ethereal being \n 精灵 \n, ethereal beauty \n 超凡的美 \n]\n','2020-01-20',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uke/ukete/uketern005.mp3'),('evade','逃脱，躲开；回避，逃避回避议题／问题（等等）','uk :ɪˈveɪd, us :ɪˈveɪd','[The police have assured the public that the escaped prisoners will not evade recapture for long. \n 警方向公众保证，逃犯很快就会再次落网。 \n, She leaned forward to kiss him but he evaded her by pretending to sneeze. \n 她身子前倾想要吻他，可他假装打喷嚏躲开了。 \n, An Olympic gold medal is the only thing that has evaded her in her remarkable career. \n 在其辉煌的运动生涯中，唯一没有得到的荣誉就是奥运会金牌。 \n, [ + -ing verb ] \n He can t evade doing military service forever. \n 他不可能永远逃避服兵役。 \n, Just give me an answer and stop evading the question! \n 直截了当地回答我，不要再回避问题！ \n]\n','2020-01-10',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uke/ukeur/ukeuro_013.mp3'),('evaluate','评估，评价；估值','uk :ɪˈvæl.ju.eɪt, us :ɪˈvæl.ju.eɪt','[It s impossible to evaluate these results without knowing more about the research methods employed. \n 如不能对使用的研究方法有更多了解，就无法对其结果作出评价。 \n, [ + question word ] \n We shall need to evaluate how the new material stands up to wear and tear. \n 我们需要对新材料的耐磨损度作出鉴定。 \n]\n','2020-01-23',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uke/ukeur/ukeuro_014.mp3'),('exaggerated','夸张；夸大；对…言过其实','uk :ɪɡˈzædʒ.ə.reɪt, us :ɪɡˈzædʒ.ə.reɪt','[The threat of attack has been greatly exaggerated. \n 遭受袭击的威胁被过分夸大了。 \n, Don t exaggerate - it wasn t that expensive. \n 不要言过其实——没有那么贵。 \n, I m not exaggerating - it was the worst meal I ve ever eaten in my life. \n 我不是在夸大其词——那是我这辈子吃到的最难以下咽的饭了。 \n]\n','2020-02-28',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uke/ukevi/ukevil_022.mp3'),('excavate','发掘；挖出（尤指用机器）开凿，挖（洞），挖空','uk :ˈek.skə.veɪt, us :ˈek.skə.veɪt','[Ice age bones are being excavated in the caves. \n 冰河时期的遗骸正从岩洞中发掘出来。 \n, In tin mining today, workers excavate tunnels horizontally from a vertical shaft. \n 如今开采锡矿，工人们从竖井中横向开挖隧道。 \n]\n','2020-02-28',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uke/ukexa/ukexami012.mp3'),('excess','过分；过量；过度过分的行为；越轨行为；暴行（保险的）免赔款，自负款过多的；多余的，额外的','uk :ɪkˈses, us :ɪkˈses','[An excess of enthusiasm is not always a good thing. \n 过分热情不见得总是件好事情。 \n, They both eat to excess (= too much). \n 他们两个都吃得太多了。 \n, There will be an increase in tax for those earning in excess of (= more than) twice the national average wage. \n 对于那些收入超过全国平均工资一倍以上的人，税收额将要增加。 \n, For many years people were trying to escape the excesses (= cruel actions) of the junta. \n 在过去很多年里，人们一直都在想方设法逃离胡作非为的军政府统治。 \n, As for shoes, her excesses (= the large number she owned) were well known. \n 说到鞋，众所周知她的鞋多得离谱。 \n, She has an excess of £200 on her home insurance policy. \n 她的房屋保险免赔款金额是200镑。 \n, Cut off any excess pastry and put it to one side. \n 切掉多余的馅饼皮，放在一边。 \n]\n','2020-04-03',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uke/ukexa/ukexami030.mp3'),('excessive','过分的；过度的；过多的','uk :ekˈses.ɪv, us :ekˈses.ɪv','[Excessive exercise can sometimes cause health problems. \n 体育锻炼过度有时也会导致健康问题。 \n, Any more pudding would simply be excessive. \n 一口布丁也不能吃了，再吃就吃多了。 \n]\n','2020-02-21',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uke/ukexc/ukexces002.mp3'),('exclude','阻止…进入；把…排斥在外（有意地）不包括排除…；不考虑…；认为…不可能','uk :ɪkˈskluːd, us :ɪkˈskluːd','[Women are still excluded from the club. \n 这家俱乐部仍然把女性拒之门外。 \n, Microbes must, as far as possible, be excluded from the room during an operation. \n 在手术过程中，要尽可能防止细菌进入手术室。 \n, Tom has been excluded from school (= he is not allowed to go to school) for bad behaviour. \n 汤姆因为行为不端被学校开除了。 \n, The price excludes local taxes. \n 这个价格不包括地方税。 \n, We can t exclude the possibility that he is dead. \n 我们不能排除他已经死亡的可能性。 \n]\n','2020-01-14',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uke/ukexc/ukexces020.mp3'),('exemption','免税','uk :ɪɡˈzemp.ʃən, us :ɪɡˈzemp.ʃən','[andidates with a qualification in chemistry have exemption from this course.\n, Organizations may qualify for exemption from income tax if they operate exclusively as charities.\n,  U ] \n He was granted exemption from military service during World War II.\n,  C ] \n a tax exemption\n, xemption from sth \n Formula One was granted an exemption from a ban on tobacco advertising.\n, xemption from doing sth \n Can the parent company claim exemption from preparing a cash flow statement?\n]\n','2019-10-03',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english/uk_pron/u/uke/ukexc/ukexcre028.mp3'),('exert','运用；行使（权威、权力等）；施加（影响等）用力；尽力；努力','uk :ɪɡˈzɜːt, us :ɪɡˈzɝːt','[If you were to exert your influence they might change their decision. \n 如果你能施加你的影响，他们或许会改变决定。 \n, Some managers exert considerable pressure on their staff to work extra hours without being paid. \n 一些老板向员工施加巨大的压力迫使他们无偿加班。 \n, I was too tired to exert myself. \n 我太累了，心有余而力不足。 \n]\n','2019-10-07',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uke/ukexe/ukexert001.mp3'),('exhausted','极其疲惫的；精疲力竭的','uk :ɪɡˈzɔː.stɪd, us :ɪɡˈzɑː.stɪd','[Exhausted, they fell asleep. \n 他们精疲力尽，倒头就睡。 \n, By the time they reached the summit they were exhausted. \n 他们登到山顶时，已经精疲力竭了。 \n]\n','2020-01-17',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uke/ukexe/ukexert010.mp3'),('exhibit','展出，展览；展示展品；展出物；陈列品（一批）展品，展览（法庭上出示的）证据，物证','uk :ɪɡˈzɪb.ɪt, us :ɪɡˈzɪb.ɪt','[He frequently exhibits at the art gallery. \n 他经常在艺术馆展出作品。 \n, In the summer the academy will exhibit several prints that are rarely seen. \n 该学会将于今年夏天对外展出几幅罕见的版画作品。 \n, He exhibited great self-control considering her rudeness. \n 她那么无礼，他表现出如此的克制力已很不错了。 \n, The museum has a fascinating collection of exhibits ranging from Iron Age pottery to Inuit clothing. \n 这个博物馆收藏的展品，从铁器时代的陶器，到因纽特人的衣物，丰富多彩，令人称奇。 \n, Let\'s go see the new dinosaur exhibit. \n 我们去看这个有关恐龙的新展览吧。 \n, Is exhibit C the weapon that you say was used? \n 物证C是不是你说的所使用的武器？ \n]\n','2019-10-07',0,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uke/ukexe/ukexert016.mp3'),('exigent','紧急的，急迫的；苛求的','uk :ˈek.sɪ.dʒənt, us :ˈek.sə.dʒənt','[an exigent problem \n 亟待解决的问题 \n, an exigent manager \n 苛刻的经理 \n]\n','2020-03-13',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uke/ukexe/ukexert029.mp3'),('existence','存在；实有生活；生活方式','uk :ɪɡˈzɪs.təns, us :ɪɡˈzɪs.təns','[Many people question the existence of God. \n 很多人怀疑上帝是否真的存在。 \n, Modern cosmology believes the universe to have come into existence about 15 billion years ago. \n 现代宇宙论认为，宇宙大约在150亿年前就已经形成了。 \n, The theatre company that they started is still in existence today. \n 他们创建的剧团时至今日仍在演出。 \n, She has a miserable existence living with him. \n 和他生活在一起，她的日子苦不堪言。 \n]\n','2020-03-06',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uke/ukexi/ukexist002.mp3'),('existential','存在的','uk :ˌeɡ.zɪˈsten.ʃəl, us :ˌeɡ.zɪˈsten.ʃəl','[n existential argument/philosopher\n, a novel of existential dread\n, he biggest existential threat to humans is probably still nuclear war.\n, This remote part of Western Australia represents a serious existential challenge.\n]\n','2020-02-28',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english/uk_pron/u/uke/ukexi/ukexist004.mp3'),('expend','花费，消费，耗费（尤指时间、精力或钱）','uk :ɪkˈspend, us :ɪkˈspend','[You expend so much effort for so little return. \n 你费了那么大劲儿，回报却如此微不足道。 \n, Governments expend a lot of resources on war. \n 各国政府在战争上消耗了大量资源。 \n]\n','2020-03-12',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uke/ukexp/ukexpat021.mp3'),('expire','到期，期满；结束逝世，亡故','uk :ɪkˈspaɪər, us :ɪkˈspaɪr','[My passport expires next month. \n 我的护照下个月过期。 \n, The contract between the two companies will expire at the end of the year. \n 两公司之间的合同将在年底到期。 \n]\n','2019-12-13',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uke/ukexp/ukexper014.mp3'),('explicable','可解释的；可说明的；可理解的','uk :ekˈsplɪk.ə.bəl, us :ekˈsplɪk.ə.bəl','[Under the circumstances, what happened was quite explicable . \n 在那种情形下，所发生的事情是完全可以理解的。 \n]\n','2020-02-27',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uke/ukexp/ukexper021.mp3'),('exploit','利用；开发；发挥（出于私利）利用；剥削不寻常的行为；英勇的行为；奇遇','uk :ɪkˈsplɔɪt, us :ɪkˈsplɔɪt','[We need to make sure that we exploit our resources as fully as possible. \n 我们需要确保尽可能充分利用资源。 \n, Laws exist to stop companies exploiting their employees. \n 法律规定禁止公司剥削其员工。 \n, She was telling me about her exploits while travelling around Africa. \n 她跟我讲述了她在非洲各地旅游时的奇遇。 \n]\n','2019-10-07',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uke/ukexp/ukexper030.mp3'),('exponential','（增长率）越来越快的，呈几何数（增长）的含有指数的','uk :ˌek.spəˈnen.ʃəl, us :ˌek.spoʊˈnen.ʃəl','[We are looking for exponential growth in our investment. \n 我们希望投资能够呈几何数增长。 \n, There has been an exponential increase in the world population this century. \n 本世纪世界人口一直呈几何数增长。 \n, 64 is an exponential expression. \n 64是一个指数式。 \n]\n','2020-03-18',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uke/ukexp/ukexplo016.mp3'),('extraordinary','非凡的；特别的；意想不到的；令人惊奇的特别会议','uk :ɪkˈstrɔː.dɪn.ər.i, us :ɪkˈstrɔːr.dən.er.i','[He told the extraordinary story of his escape. \n 他讲述了他离奇的逃亡经历。 \n, Her voice had an extraordinary hypnotic quality. \n 她的嗓音有一种奇特的催眠效果。 \n, an extraordinary coincidence \n 令人吃惊的巧合 \n]\n','2020-03-23',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uke/ukext/ukextra014.mp3'),('extreme','极大的；极度的；极端的极严厉的；严重的；极糟的（信仰或政党）偏激的，过激的，极端的末端的，尽头的；（尤指）离中心最远的极度；极端（用于强调）极其，非常，极度极端；极端不同的事物','uk :ɪkˈstriːm, us :ɪkˈstriːm',NULL,'2021-03-26',2,6,1,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uke/ukext/ukextra024.mp3'),('extremity','末端，尽头；（尤指）离中心最远之处（身体的）末端，末梢（如手指、脚趾、鼻子等）','uk :ɪkˈstrem.ə.ti, us :ɪkˈstrem.ə.t̬i','[The wood lies on the southern extremity of the estate. \n 树林位于庄园的最南端。 \n]\n','2020-02-19',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uke/ukext/ukextra029.mp3'),('exude','明显地流露，充分显露（爱、自信、痛苦等）散发；渗出，流出','uk :ɪɡˈzjuːd, us :ɪɡˈzuːd','[She just exudes confidence. \n 她显得信心十足。 \n, Some trees exude from their bark a sap that repels insect parasites. \n 一些树的树皮会分泌出一种汁液来驱除寄生在树上的昆虫。 \n]\n','2020-01-17',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uke/ukext/ukextri008.mp3'),('fabulous','极好的；绝佳的虚构的，想象的，虚幻的','uk :ˈfæb.jə.ləs, us :ˈfæb.jə.ləs','[She looked absolutely fabulous in her dress. \n 她穿着这身连衣裙看起来漂亮极了。 \n, They ve got a fabulous apartment in the centre of Paris. \n 他们在巴黎市中心有一套极佳的公寓。 \n, We had a fabulous time at the party. \n 我们在聚会上玩得很痛快。 \n, The unicorn is a fabulous creature. \n 独角兽是一种实际上并不存在的动物。 \n]\n','2020-02-21',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uke/ukeye/ukeyeto014.mp3'),('facial','面部的，脸上的面部美容护理','uk :ˈfeɪ.ʃəl, us :ˈfeɪ.ʃəl','[facial hair \n 脸部汗毛 \n, facial cleansers and moisturizers \n 面部清洁和保湿用品 \n, facial expressions \n 面部表情 \n, Beauty treatments range from an eyelash tint at £8 to a deep cleansing facial costing £80. \n 美容护理项目包括从收费8英镑的染睫毛到收费80英镑的面部深层清洁 \n]\n','2020-01-10',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uke/ukeye/ukeyeto025.mp3'),('fad','一时的风尚；短暂的狂热','uk :fæd, us :fæd','[the latest health fad \n 最新健康时尚 \n, K \n There was a fad for wearing ripped jeans a few years ago. \n 几年前有一阵子流行穿有洞的牛仔裤。 \n]\n','2019-12-23',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukf/ukfac/ukfacin016.mp3'),('fade','（使）褪色；（使）变暗；（使）衰弱','uk :feɪd, us :feɪd','[If you hang your clothes out in the bright sun, they will fade. \n 衣服挂在光线强的地方晾晒会褪色。 \n, My suntan is already fading. \n 我晒黑的肤色已经开始变浅了。 \n, They arrived home just as the light was fading (= as it was getting dark). \n 天色变暗时，他们到家了。 \n, The sun had faded the blue walls. \n 太阳把蓝色的墙晒褪了色。 \n]\n','2019-12-11',0,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukf/ukfac/ukfacin025.mp3'),('faint','微弱的；不清晰的；微小的根本不知道虚弱无力；感到眩晕；快要晕倒似的昏厥；晕倒昏厥；晕倒','uk :feɪnt, us :feɪnt','[a faint sound/noise/smell \n 微弱的声音／隐约的响声／淡淡的气味 \n, The lamp gave out a faint glow. \n 灯发出微弱的光。 \n, She gave me a faint smile of recognition. \n 她认出了我，冲我淡淡一笑。 \n, There s not the faintest hope of ever finding him. \n 没有丝毫找到他的希望。 \n, She bears a faint resemblance to my sister. \n 她和我姐姐长得有点儿像。 \n, I have a faint suspicion that you may be right! \n 我隐约觉得你可能是对的！ \n,  Is she going to stay?   I haven t the faintest idea.  \n “她要留下来吗？我一点儿也不知道。” \n, I don t have the faintest idea what you re talking about! \n 我根本不知道你在说什么！ \n, She felt faint with hunger. \n 她饿得头昏眼花。 \n, He faints at the sight of blood. \n 他一见血就晕。 \n, I nearly fainted in the heat. \n 我差点热晕过去。 \n, She took one look at the hypodermic needle and fainted (dead) away (= became unconscious immediately). \n 她一眼看到注射针头就昏了过去。 \n, On receiving the news, she fell into a dead faint. \n 听到消息，她昏死过去。 \n]\n','2021-03-26',9,10,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukf/ukfag/ukfagge009.mp3'),('faith','信任；信心（某一）宗教宗教信仰','uk :feɪθ, us :feɪθ','[She has no faith in modern medicine. \n 她对现代医学没有信心。 \n, You ll cope - I have great faith in you. \n 你能应付得了——我对你很有信心。 \n, After the trial, his family said they had lost all faith in the judicial system. \n 审判之后，他的家人说，他们对司法体系已完全丧失信心。 \n, Politicians must start keeping their promises if they want to restore the people s faith in government. \n 如果政治人物想恢复人们对政府的信任，他们必须开始信守承诺。 \n, the Muslim/Christian/Jewish/Buddhist faith \n 伊斯兰教／基督教／犹太教／佛教 \n, They were persecuted for their faith. \n 他们因宗教信仰而遭受迫害。 \n, He was forced to practise his faith in secret. \n 他被迫对自己的宗教信仰保密。 \n, a multi-faith society \n 宗教信仰多元化的社会 \n, They were brought up in the true faith (= the religion which the speaker believes is the only true one). \n 他们在正统的宗教熏陶下长大。 \n, Even in the bad times she never lost her faith. \n 即使在困难时期，她也从未丧失信仰。 \n, Her faith in God was shattered when her baby died. \n 她的孩子死后，她对上帝的信仰破灭了。 \n, It s my faith that keeps me going. \n 是我的信仰在推动我前进。 \n]\n','2020-01-20',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukf/ukfag/ukfagge021.mp3'),('fame','名声，名气；声誉，名望','uk :feɪm, us :feɪm','[She first rose to fame as a singer at the age of 16. \n 她16岁时便作为歌手一举成名。 \n, She moved to London in search of fame and fortune. \n 为了追逐名利她移居伦敦。 \n, The town s fame rests on its beautiful cathedral. \n 这个镇因美丽的修道院而闻名。 \n]\n','2020-04-01',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukf/ukfal/ukfalsi006.mp3'),('fanciest','想要；想做爱慕，喜欢自认为是；自命不凡想象；认为（表示惊讶）真想不到！装饰的；花哨的；繁复的昂贵的；豪华的一时的兴趣（或爱好）喜欢上，爱上吸引…，中…的意想象（力）','uk :ˈfæn.si, us :ˈfæn.si','[Do you fancy a drink this evening? \n 你今晚想喝一杯吗？ \n, [ + -ing verb ] \n I didn t fancy swimming in that water. \n 我不想在那水里游泳。 \n, He could tell she fancied him. \n 他看得出她喜欢他。 \n, That Dave really fancies himself, doesn t he? \n 那个戴夫挺自命不凡的，是吧？ \n, He fancies himself as a bit of a singer. \n 他认为自己多少是个歌手。 \n, [ + to infinitive ] \n Who do you fancy to win the Cup this year? \n 你认为今年谁会赢得杯赛？ \n, [ + (that) ] \n literary \n I fancied (that) I saw something moving in the corner. \n 我觉得看见角落里有东西在动。 \n, ld-fashioned \n This isn t the first time this has happened, I fancy. \n 我想，这不是第一次发生这种事了。 \n, Fancy seeing you here! \n 没想到在这里遇见你！ \n,  They have eight children.   Fancy that (= how surprising)!  \n “他们有8个孩子。”“真想不到啊！” \n, I wanted a simple black dress, nothing fancy. \n 我想要一件简洁的黑色礼服，不要花哨的东西。 \n, The decorations were a little too fancy for my tastes. \n 这种装饰风格过于繁复，不合我的喜好。 \n, fancy cakes \n 花式蛋糕 \n, We stayed in a fancy hotel near the Champs-Élysées. \n 我们住在香榭丽舍大街附近一家豪华的酒店里。 