ncial affairs \n 金融事务 \n]\n','2019-10-07',0,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukf/ukfin/ukfinan003.mp3'),('firm','结实的；坚固的牢固的；稳固的坚决的；坚定的强有力的；紧紧的，牢牢的确定的；坚定不移的严格的，强硬的公司；商号使（土）变硬；使（土）坚实稳定下来；保持不变','uk :fɜːm, us :fɝːm','[I d rather sleep on a firm mattress than a soft one. \n 我宁愿睡硬床垫，也不要软的。 \n, These pears are still too firm to eat. \n 这些梨还太硬，没法吃。 \n, The bridge provided a firm platform for the bungee jumpers. \n 这座桥为蹦极者提供了稳固的平台。 \n, The government remains firm in its opposition to tax reform. \n 政府仍坚决反对税收改革。 \n, a firm handshake \n 强有力的握手 \n, Keep a firm hold of the handrail as you go down. \n 下去时要牢牢抓住扶手。 \n, igurative \n No one seems to have a firm grip on the company at the moment. \n 目前似乎没有人能牢牢掌控公司。 \n, igurative \n You need a firm grasp of mathematics to become an astronaut. \n 要成为宇航员，数学知识必须非常扎实。 \n, He is a firm believer in traditional family values. \n 他坚信应遵循传统的家庭价值观念。 \n, Some people still claim that there is no firm evidence linking smoking with lung cancer. \n 有人仍声称没有确凿的证据表明吸烟与肺癌有关。 \n, I was always very firm with my children - they knew the rules and I made sure they followed them. \n 我对孩子们总是很严格——他们知道规矩，我则监督他们守规矩。 \n, He works for a law firm called Neil and Vigliano. \n 他在一家名为尼尔和维利亚诺的律师事务所供职。 \n, He s just started working for an accountancy firm/a firm of accountants in Cambridge. \n 他刚刚开始在剑桥的一家会计师事务所工作。 \n, Firm the soil around the cuttings and water them in. \n 把插条四周的土压实，再浇上水。 \n, After a turbulent week on the markets, share prices firmed today. \n 经过一周的市场动荡，股票价格今天稳定下来了。 \n]\n','2019-12-23',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukf/ukfir/ukfirew004.mp3'),('fission','（核）裂变，分裂细胞分裂；裂殖','uk :ˈfɪʃ.ən, us :ˈfɪʃ.ən','[nuclear fission \n 核裂变 \n, The fission of the cell could be inhibited with certain chemicals. \n 细胞裂殖可以靠某些化学制品加以抑制。 \n]\n','2020-03-12',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukf/ukfir/ukfirew028.mp3'),('fizzy','嘶嘶的，起泡的','uk :ˈfɪz.i, us :ˈfɪz.i','[fizzy orange/mineral water \n 起泡橘子水／矿泉水 \n]\n','2020-01-24',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukf/ukfis/ukfistf026.mp3'),('flagpole','旗杆','uk :ˈflæɡ.pəʊl, us :ˈflæɡ.poʊl','[]\n','2020-03-25',1,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukf/ukfla/ukflacc009.mp3'),('flatfoot','條子','','null\n','2020-01-03',0,0,0,'null'),('fling','猛扔，猛投，猛掷迅猛移动；猛地做…气呼呼地说，愤怒地说短暂的欢乐时光','uk :flɪŋ, us :flɪŋ','[He crumpled up the letter and flung it into the fire. \n 他把信揉成一团，猛地扔进火中。 \n,  And you can take your ring back too!  she cried, flinging it down on the table. \n “你可以把你的戒指也拿走！”她喊道，猛地把戒指摔到桌子上。 \n, K informal \n Could you fling the paper over here (= give me the paper)? \n 你能把报纸丢过来吗？ \n, She flung her arms around his neck. \n 她猛地搂住他的脖子。 \n, The door was flung open by the wind. \n 风把门猛地吹开了。 \n, Sergei flung himself down on the sofa. \n 谢尔盖猛地扑倒在沙发上。 \n, K informal \n Let me just fling (= quickly put) a few things into my bag, and I ll be right with you. \n 让我往包里塞几样东西，马上就跟你去。 \n, K informal \n They were flung (= quickly put) in prison. \n 他们很快被投入监狱。 \n, They were flinging bitter accusations at each other. \n 他们彼此破口大骂。 \n, [ + speech ] \n  I don t care what you think , she flung (back) at him. \n “我不在乎你怎么想，”她气呼呼地回敬他道。 \n, The girls are going to the beach for one last fling before the end of summer. \n 姑娘们要去海滩享受夏季结束前最后一段短暂的欢乐时光。 \n]\n','2019-12-11',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukf/ukfli/ukflick017.mp3'),('flip','（使）快速翻转；迅速翻动翻烤（食物）迅速转售（稍作装修后的房子）以获取利润翻动，翻转（flippant的非正式说法）“不！”（感叹词，表示愠怒）','uk :flɪp, us :flɪp','[I flipped the book (over) to look at the back cover. \n 我很快地把书翻过去看了看封底。 \n, I lost my place in my book when the pages flipped over in the wind. \n 风把书页吹乱了，我找不到正在看的那个地方了。 \n, You turn the machine on by flipping (= operating) the switch on the side. \n 把边上的开关按一下，机器就启动了。 \n, The captains flipped a coin into the air (= made it turn over in the air to see which side it landed on) to decide which side would bat first. \n 两队队长向空中抛出一枚硬币，决定哪一方先击球。 \n, I don t want to spend the rest of my life flipping burgers. \n 我可不想一辈子都翻烤汉堡。 \n, I am going to take three weeks  vacation and flip this house. \n 我要休假三个星期，稍微装修一下这个房子然后卖掉。 \n, a flip of a coin \n 抛硬币 \n, The acrobats were doing somersaults and flips (= jumping and turning their bodies over in the air). \n 杂技演员们正在翻筋斗和空翻。 \n, Oh, flip, I ve missed the bus. \n 哦不！我错过公交车了。 \n]\n','2019-12-23',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukf/ukfli/ukflick020.mp3'),('flock','>羊群；鸟群；人群>（特定类型的）一群人>（充填垫子等的）软填料；（在墙纸或窗帘上制作凸起图案用的）短绒，绒屑>聚集；蜂拥>用软材料覆盖表面装饰','uk :>flɒk, us :>flɑːk',NULL,'2021-03-08',6,11,1,NULL),('flout','公然藐视，无视，违背（规定、法律或习俗）','uk :flaʊt, us :flaʊt','[Many motorcyclists flout the law by not wearing helmets. \n 许多骑摩托车的人无视法律，不戴头盔。 \n, The orchestra decided to flout convention/tradition, and wear their everyday clothes for the concert. \n 管弦乐队决定一改传统，在音乐会上穿日常服装。 \n]\n','2019-10-07',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukf/ukflo/ukflori020.mp3'),('fluent','（指人说某种语言）流利的（语言）讲得流利的','uk :ˈfluː.ənt, us :','[She s fluent in French. \n 她的法语很流利。 \n, He s a fluent Russian speaker. \n 他的俄语讲得很流利。 \n, He speaks fluent Chinese. \n 他汉语讲得很流利。 \n]\n','2019-12-19',0,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukf/ukflu/ukfluct004.mp3'),('fluid','液体；流质流畅的（情况、想法或计划）不固定的，易变的','uk :ˈfluː.ɪd, us :ˈfluː.ɪd','[If you have a fever you should drink plenty of fluids. \n 如果发烧，应多喝流质。 \n, power steering fluid \n 助力转向液 \n, The virus is contracted through exchange of bodily fluids (= liquids, such as blood, that come from the human body). \n 这种病毒通过体液感染。 \n, fluid movements \n 流畅的动作 \n, The military situation is still very fluid. \n 军事局势依然很不稳定。 \n]\n','2020-01-03',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukf/ukflu/ukfluct009.mp3'),('flustered','心烦意乱的；慌张的；紧张的','uk :ˈflʌs.təd, us :ˈflʌs.tɚd','[She seemed a little flustered. \n 她似乎有点儿紧张。 \n, If I look flustered it s because I m trying to do so many things at once. \n 如果我看上去很慌乱，那是因为我正试图同时做很多件事情。 \n]\n','2019-12-20',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukf/ukflu/ukflush003.mp3'),('flutter','（使）飘动，挥动，颤动；拍（翅）；鼓（翼）（心）怦怦乱跳；（胃）颤动一阵兴奋（或激动）（尤指赛马中的）小赌注振动；颤动；忽闪','uk :ˈflʌt.ər, us :ˈflʌt̬.ɚ','[Brightly coloured flags were fluttering in the breeze. \n 鲜艳的彩旗在微风中飘扬。 \n, Leaves fluttered down onto the path. \n 树叶飘落到小径上。 \n, Butterflies fluttered about in the sunshine. \n 蝴蝶在阳光下翩翩飞舞。 \n, A white bird poised on a wire and fluttered its wings. \n 一只白鸟立在电线上，扑打着翅膀。 \n, Every time I think about my exams my stomach flutters! \n 每次一想到考试，我心里就不舒服！ \n, The publication of her first novel last spring caused a flutter of excitement. \n 去年秋天她的第一部小说出版后引起一阵轰动。 \n, Auntie Paula likes to have a bit of a flutter on the horses. \n 葆拉姨妈喜欢在赛马上下一点儿小赌注。 \n]\n','2020-04-01',5,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukf/ukflu/ukflush007.mp3'),('flux','不断的变动，不停的变化（助）熔剂','uk :flʌks, us :flʌks','[Our plans are in a state of flux at the moment. \n 我们的计划目前处在不断变化之中。 \n]\n','2019-12-16',0,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukf/ukflu/ukflush009.mp3'),('foe','敌人地球之友（一个国际环保组织，Friends of the Earth的缩写）','uk :fəʊ, us :foʊ','[The two countries have united against their common foe. \n 两国联合起来对抗共同的敌人。 \n, They were bitter foes for many years. \n 他们结仇多年。 \n, Foes of the government will be delighting in its current difficulties. \n 政府的敌人会对政府目前的困难处境幸灾乐祸。 \n]\n','2019-12-16',0,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukf/ukfob/ukfob__009.mp3'),('foldaway','可折叠的；折叠式的','uk :ˈfəʊld.ə.weɪ, us :ˈfoʊld.ə.weɪ','[a foldaway bed \n 折叠床 \n]\n','2020-03-25',2,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukf/ukfob/ukfob__021.mp3'),('folly','愚蠢；愚蠢的行为（或念头等）装饰性建筑（尤指见于英国花园或公园内的小型城堡、殿堂等）','uk :ˈfɒl.i, us :ˈfɑː.li','[She said that the idea was folly. \n 她说这是个愚蠢的主意。 \n, [ + to infinitive ] \n It would be folly for the country to become involved in the war. \n 那个国家要是参战的话实属愚蠢之举。 \n, a Gothic garden folly \n 一个歌特式的花园建筑 \n]\n','2020-02-28',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukf/ukfol/ukfolks006.mp3'),('foremost','最重要的；最佳的；领先的','uk :ˈfɔː.məʊst, us :ˈfɔːr.moʊst','[This is one of the country s foremost arts centres. \n 这是全国最重要的艺术中心之一。 \n, She s one of the foremost experts on child psychology. \n 她是儿童心理学领域最顶尖的专家之一。 \n]\n','2020-01-09',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukf/ukfor/ukforef019.mp3'),('foreshadowing','是…的预兆，预示','uk :fɔːˈʃæd.əʊ, us :fɔːrˈʃæd.oʊ','[The recent outbreak of violence was foreshadowed by isolated incidents in the city earlier this year. \n 今年早些时候城里发生的几起孤立事件是近来爆发的暴力事件的预兆。 \n]\n','2020-03-19',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukf/ukfor/ukforef029.mp3'),('formula','惯例；配方；处方公式，方程式分子式（婴儿）配方奶','uk :ˈfɔː.mjə.lə, us :ˈfɔːr.mjə.lə',NULL,'2020-03-25',1,4,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukf/ukfor/ukforgi030.mp3'),('fortified','（尤指为防御而）加强，增强','uk :ˈfɔː.tɪ.faɪ, us :ˈfɔːr.t̬ə.faɪ','[a fortified town \n 设防的城镇 \n, They hurriedly fortified the village with barricades of carts. \n 他们匆忙用马车搭起路障，加强村子的防御。 \n, The argument had fortified her resolve to prove she was right. \n 这番争论增强了她证明自己正确的决心。 \n, He fortified himself with a drink and a sandwich before driving on. \n 继续开车之前，他喝了杯饮料吃了块三明治来增强体力。 \n, a fruit drink fortified with vitamin C (= with vitamin C added) \n 添加了维生素C的果汁饮料 \n]\n','2019-10-08',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukf/ukfor/ukformu028.mp3'),('forum','（尤指讨论与公共利益相关的问题的）论坛，讨论会（