g a language. \n 掌握一些语法对学习一种语言来说很重要。 \n]\n','2020-01-23',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukf/ukfum/ukfumes013.mp3'),('funeral','葬礼，丧礼','uk :ˈfjuː.nər.əl, us :ˈfjuː.nɚ.əl','[The funeral will be held next Friday. \n 葬礼将在下周五举行。 \n, Over 300 mourners attended the funeral. \n 300多名哀悼者参加了葬礼。 \n, a funeral procession \n 送葬的队伍 \n]\n','2019-12-27',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukf/ukfum/ukfumes020.mp3'),('furious','极其生气的，怒不可遏的强烈的；激烈的暴怒；狂怒','uk :ˈfjʊə.ri.əs, us :ˈfʊr.i.əs','[I was late and he was furious with me. \n 我迟到了，他冲我大发脾气。 \n, He s furious about/at the way he s been treated. \n 他因自己受到这样的对待而大发雷霆。 \n, We had a furious debate about the death penalty. \n 我们就死刑问题吵了个天翻地覆。 \n, There is a furious struggle going on between the two presidential candidates. \n 两位总统竞选人之间进行着激烈的争斗。 \n, He set off running at a furious pace. \n 他出发时猛跑了一阵。 \n]\n','2020-02-28',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukf/ukfun/ukfunk_007.mp3'),('furnace','熔炉暖气炉','uk :ˈfɜː.nɪs, us :ˈfɝː.nɪs','[People who work with furnaces in a steel factory need to wear protective clothing. \n 钢厂里在熔炉边工作的人都需要穿防护服。 \n, This room s like a furnace (= is very hot)! \n 这个房间热得像熔炉！ \n, It s cold in here - should I turn on the furnace? \n 这里很冷——要不要我把暖气炉打开？ \n]\n','2020-03-06',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukf/ukfun/ukfunk_012.mp3'),('gastrointestinal','胃肠（里）的；与肠胃相关的','uk :ˌɡæs.trəʊˌɪn.tesˈtaɪ.nəl, us :ˌɡæs.troʊ.ɪnˈtes.tən.əl','[the gastrointestinal tract \n 胃肠道 \n, gastrointestinal bleeding \n 胃肠出血 \n]\n','2020-01-23',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/e/epd/epd12/epd12072.mp3'),('genre','（尤指艺术的）风格，类型，体裁属于某类型的；按某种风格创作的','uk :ˈʒɑ̃ː.rə, us :ˈʒɑːn.rə','[What genre does the book fall into - comedy or tragedy? \n 这本书属于什么体裁——喜剧还是悲剧？ \n, a literary/musical/film genre \n 文学体裁／音乐风格／电影类型 \n, a genre movie \n 类型电影 \n, genre fiction \n 类型小说 \n]\n','2020-01-10',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukg/ukgen/ukgenit008.mp3'),('geographic','地理的；地理学的','uk :ˌdʒi.əˈɡræf.ɪ.kəl, us :ˌdʒi.əˈɡræf.ɪ.kəl','[a geographical region \n 地理区域 \n, geographical features \n 地理特征 \n]\n','2019-10-08',0,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukg/ukgeo/ukgeogr002.mp3'),('gerbil','沙鼠','uk :ˈdʒɜː.bəl, us :ˈdʒɝː.bəl','[]\n','2020-02-27',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukg/ukgeo/ukgeogr023.mp3'),('gist','要旨，要点；大意','uk :dʒɪst, us :dʒɪst','[That was the gist of what he said. \n 那就是他的话的大意。 \n, I think I got (= understood) the gist of what she was saying. \n 我想我明白她说的话的大意了。 \n]\n','2019-12-11',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukg/ukgir/ukgiraf020.mp3'),('glamour','吸引力；魅力；诱惑力','uk :ˈɡlæm.ər, us :ˈɡlæm.ɚ','[Who can resist the glamour of Hollywood? \n 谁能抗拒得了好莱坞的诱惑？ \n]\n','2020-04-03',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukg/ukgla/ukglaci021.mp3'),('glance','瞥一眼，迅速地看一眼，扫视闪耀，闪光，闪烁瞥一眼，迅速地看一眼，扫视立刻乍看之下，最初看到时','uk :ɡlɑːns, us :ɡlæns','[She glanced around/round the room to see who was there. \n 她扫视了一眼房间，看看谁在里面。 \n, He glanced up from his book as I passed. \n 我走过的时候，正埋头读书的他抬头瞥了我一眼。 \n, Could you glance over/through this letter and see if it s alright? \n 你能不能看一下这封信，看看写得行不行？ \n, The sunlight glanced on the lake. \n 湖面上波光粼粼。 \n, She took/cast a glance at her watch. \n 她看了一下手表。 \n, He could tell at a glance that something was wrong. \n 他一眼就看出问题了。 \n, At first glance I thought it was a dog (but I was mistaken). \n 乍一看我还以为是一条狗呢（但是我看走眼了）。 \n]\n','2020-01-03',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukg/ukgla/ukglaci023.mp3'),('glare','（长久的）怒视，瞪眼刺眼的光发出刺眼的光怒视，瞪眼','uk :ɡleər, us :ɡler','[She gave me a fierce glare. \n 她恶狠狠地瞪了我一眼。 \n, Tinted windows will reduce the glare/the sun s glare. \n 有色玻璃窗会遮挡刺眼的阳光。 \n, This screen gives off a lot of glare. \n 这种屏幕发出的光太刺眼。 \n, The sun was glaring right in my eyes. \n 强烈的阳光直刺我的眼睛。 \n, She glared angrily at everyone and stormed out of the room. \n 她横眉怒目地瞪了大家一眼，气呼呼地冲出房间。 \n]\n','2019-12-11',0,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukg/ukgla/ukglaci027.mp3'),('glimmer','发出微弱的光；隐约闪烁闪烁的微光；微弱的亮光微弱的（好）迹象；一丝，一线','uk :ˈɡlɪm.ər, us :ˈɡlɪm.ɚ','[The lights of the village were glimmering in the distance. \n 远处村庄微弱的灯光时隐时现。 \n, The sky glimmered with stars. \n 天空闪烁着点点星光。 \n, a glimmering candle \n 暗淡摇曳的烛光 \n, We saw a glimmer of light in the distance. \n 我们看到远处有一线微光。 \n, This month s sales figures offer a glimmer of hope for the depressed economy. \n 这个月的销售额给萧条的经济带来一丝希望。 \n, She s never shown a glimmer of interest in classical music. \n 她对古典音乐从没有表现出过一丁点儿兴趣。 \n, The first glimmer of light (= sign of development or understanding) has appeared in the peace talks. \n 和平会谈首次出现了一丝转机。 \n]\n','2019-12-26',0,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukg/ukgla/ukglass026.mp3'),('glove-compartment','（汽車前排座位前面放小物件的）雜物箱','','null\n','2020-01-03',0,0,0,'null'),('gnawing','折磨人的；令人苦恼的；使人痛苦的','uk :ˈnɔː.ɪŋ, us :ˈnɑː.ɪŋ','[I ve had gnawing doubts about this project for some time. \n 一段时间以来，我对这个项目一直怀有重重疑虑。 \n, After three days, we felt an agonizing, gnawing hunger. \n 三天后，我们开始感觉到饥饿的煎熬和折磨。 \n]\n','2020-03-19',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukg/ukglu/ukglutt016.mp3'),('goggling','（由于惊奇）瞪大眼睛看','uk :ˈɡɒɡ.əl, us :ˈɡɑː.ɡəl','[The cathedral was full of goggling tourists. \n 大教堂里挤满了游客，一个个瞪大眼睛，惊奇地看着。 \n]\n','2020-03-25',2,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukg/ukgod/ukgodpa009.mp3'),('goon','（受人雇用的）打手，杀手，暴徒傻瓜，蠢人','uk :ɡuːn, us :ɡuːn','[]\n','2019-12-27',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukg/ukgon/ukgonad026.mp3'),('gossip','（有关别人隐私的）流言蜚语，闲言碎语，闲聊爱说长道短的人；喜欢散布流言蜚语的人（对别人的隐私）说长道短，传播流言蜚语','uk :ˈɡɒs.ɪp, us :ˈɡɑː.səp','[Her letter was full of gossip. \n 她信里讲的都是些闲言碎语。 \n, I don t like all this idle gossip. \n 我讨厌这些无聊的流言蜚语。 \n, I ve got some juicy gossip for you. \n 我有些特别有趣的小道消息告诉你。 \n, Have you heard the (latest) gossip? \n 你听到（最近流传的）那些闲言碎语了吗？ \n, K \n Jane and Lyn sat in the kitchen having a good gossip about their friends. \n 简和琳恩坐在厨房里大聊特聊自己的那帮朋友。 \n, She s a terrible gossip. \n 她是个很要命的长舌妇。 \n, Stop gossiping and do your work. \n 别再闲扯了，继续干点活去。 \n, People have started to gossip about us. \n 人们已经开始说我们的闲话了。 \n]\n','2020-03-06',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukg/ukgoo/ukgoose021.mp3'),('gown','（尤指正式场合穿的）女式礼服（特定场合穿的）长袍，罩衣，长外衣','uk :ɡaʊn, us :ɡaʊn','[a ball gown \n 舞会礼服 \n, a hospital gown \n 病号服 \n]\n','2020-02-27',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukg/ukgou/ukgourd016.mp3'),('grace','优美，优雅，雍容文雅；通情达理，体面风度（尤指上帝赐予人类的）恩典，恩宠承蒙上帝的恩典，上帝开恩（基督徒的）饭前感恩祷告宽限期，延缓期使优美，为…增色，使增辉光临…而使之蓬筚生辉；莅临而为（某人）增光大人，阁下，夫人（对公爵、公爵夫人、女公爵或大主教的尊称）','uk :ɡreɪs, us :ɡreɪs','[Joanna has natural grace and elegance. \n 乔安娜举止自然优雅。 \n, They accepted their defeat with good grace. \n 他们很有风度地认输了。 \n, Ken is sadly lacking in social graces. \n 糟糕的是，肯在社交场合很没有风度。 \n, Betty believed that it was through divine grace that her husband had recovered from his illness. \n 贝蒂认为全靠上天开恩她的丈夫才得以痊愈。 \n, By the grace of God, the pilot managed to land the damaged plane safely. \n 蒙上帝开恩，飞行员成功地将受损的飞机安全降落。 \n, The children always say grace at dinnertime. \n 孩子们在用餐前总是要做感恩祷告。 \n, The exams have been postponed, so the students have a few days  grace before they start. \n 考试推迟了，所以学生们得以晚几天进考场。 \n, Her face has graced the covers of magazines across the world. \n 她的面孔出现在全世界各种杂志的封面上，使之赫然生辉。 \n, We are delighted that the mayor will be gracing us with his presence at our annual dinner. \n 市长将光临我们每年一度的宴会，我们感到万分荣幸。 \n, umorous \n So you ve finally decided to grace us with your presence, have you? (= You are late.) \n 你看，你终于肯光临寒舍了，大驾难起啊，是吗？（幽默地表示“你迟到了”这个意思） \n]\n','2020-03-18',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukg/ukgou/ukgourd021.mp3'),('grandiose','夸大的，不切实际的；华而不实的','uk :ˈɡræn.di.əʊs, us :ˈɡræn.di.oʊs','[grandiose schemes/designs/ideas for making money \n 不切实际的赚钱计划／方案／想法 \n]\n','2020-02-28',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukg/ukgra/ukgrand013.mp3'),('grant','（尤指政府为特殊目的给予个人或组织的）拨款，补助金（通常指官方）同意，准予，授予（常指在表达相反的意见之前表示让步）承认，同意认为…是理所当然的视…为理所当然（而不去表示感激）；（认为理所当然而）不去重视…因为','uk :ɡrɑːnt, us :ɡrænt','[a student/research grant \n 助学金／研究拨款 \n, a local authority/government grant \n 当地行政机构／政府拨款 \n, [ + to infinitive ] \n They gave/awarded her a grant to study abroad for one year. \n 他们给／授予她一笔奖学金供她出国留学1年。 \n, [ + two objects ] \n They granted her an entry visa. \n 他们发给她入境签证。 \n, He was granted asylum. \n 他的避难请求被接受了。 \n, ormal \n She granted their request/wish. \n 她答应了他们的请求／满足了他们的愿望。 \n, I grant that it must have been upsetting but even so I think she overreacted. \n 我承认这事肯定很让人心烦，但即使是这样，我觉得她也有点小题大做。 \n, I grant you (= it is true that), it s a difficult situation but I feel sure he could have handled it more sensitively. \n 不错，这种局面是很棘手，但是我确实觉得他本可以更加理智地来处理。 \n, I didn t realize that Melanie hadn t been to college - I suppose I just took it for granted. \n 我不知道梅拉妮没上大学——我只是想当然地认为她上过了。 \n, One of the problems with relationships is that after a while you just take each other for granted. \n 恋爱中会遇到的一个问题是，相处一段时间后，双方就都把对方为自己所做的一切当成理所当然。 \n, Granted (that) the story s true, there s not a lot you can do about it. \n 因为这件事情是真的，你实在没有办法做什么。 \n]\n','2019-12-19',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukg/ukgra/ukgrand029.mp3'),('grapple','（尤指为了得到某物而）扭打，搏斗','uk :ˈɡræp.əl, us :ˈɡræp.əl','[The children grappled for the ball. \n 孩子们为了争球打成一团。 \n]\n','2019-10-07',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukg/ukgra/ukgranu019.mp3'),('grasp','抓紧，握紧急忙抓住，毫不犹豫地把握住（机会）理解，领悟，明白（尤指费解之事）紧抓，紧握，抓牢力所能及；掌握，把握理解','uk :ɡrɑːsp, us :ɡræsp','[Rosie suddenly grasped my hand. \n 罗茜突然抓住了我的手。 \n, We must grasp every opportunity to strengthen economic ties with other countries. \n 我们必须把握住一切机会加强与其他国家的经济联系。 \n, I think I managed to grasp the main points of the lecture. \n 我觉得我还是理解了演讲的要点。 \n, The government has acknowledged that homelessness is a problem but it has failed to grasp the scale of the problem. \n 政府已经承认很多人无家可归是个问题，但还没有意识到问题的严重性。 \n, He shook my hand with a very firm grasp. \n 他非常有力地和我握了握手。 \n, The presidency at last looked within her grasp (= it looked possible that she might become president). \n 终于，总裁的职位对她来说似乎伸手可及。 \n, Why is success always beyond my grasp (= impossible to get)? \n 为什么我总是功败垂成？ \n, The gold medal slipped from his grasp (= he was unable to get it) in the last moments of the race. \n 在比赛最后一刻他与金牌失之交臂。 \n, I sometimes think that he s losing his grasp on reality (= his ability to judge what is real and what is not). \n 有时我觉得他认不清现实。 \n, He has a good grasp of the issues. \n 他对这些问题非常了解。 \n]\n','2020-03-05',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukg/ukgra/ukgranu020.mp3'),('gratification','满足','uk :ˌɡræt.ɪ.fɪˈkeɪ.ʃən, us :ˌɡræt̬.ə.fəˈkeɪ.ʃən','[exual gratification\n, Some people expect instant gratification (= to get what they want immediately).\n]\n','2020-02-21',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english/uk_pron/u/ukg/ukgra/ukgrate005.mp3'),('gratify','使高兴；使满意；满足（某人的愿望、需求等）','uk :ˈɡræt.ɪ.faɪ, us :ˈɡræt̬.ə.faɪ','[We were gratified by the response to our appeal. \n 呼吁得到积极响应，我们感到非常欣慰。 \n, [ + to infinitive ] \n He was gratified to see how well his students had done. \n 看到学生们成绩如此出众，他非常高兴。 \n]\n','2020-03-18',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukg/ukgra/ukgrate006.mp3'),('greenback','美钞','uk :ˈɡriːn.bæk, us :ˈɡriːn.bæk','[]\n','2019-12-20',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukg/ukgra/ukgravi026.mp3'),('grind','碾碎，磨碎，把…磨成粉磨，把…磨锋利，把…磨光把牙齿咬得嘎嘎响；出声地磨牙令人厌倦的苦事，苦差事只会读书的无趣之人，书呆子','uk :ɡraɪnd, us :ɡraɪnd','[to grind coffee \n 磨咖啡豆 \n, Shall I grind a little black pepper over your salad? \n 要不要我磨一点黑胡椒粉给你撒在色拉上？ \n, They grind the grain into flour (= make flour by crushing grain) between two large stones. \n 他们把谷子放在两块大石头之间磨成粉。 \n, She has a set of chef s knives that she grinds every week. \n 她有一套厨房用刀具，每个星期都磨一次。 \n, He ground down the sharp metal edges to make them smooth. \n 他把尖利的金属边缘打磨平。 \n, The car engine was making a strange grinding noise. \n 汽车发动机发出一种奇怪的摩擦声音。 \n, She grinds her teeth in her sleep. \n 她睡觉磨牙。 \n, Having to type up my handwritten work was a real grind. \n 还得把手写的作业打出来，这让我叫苦不迭。 \n, The daily grind of taking care of three children was wearing her down. \n 每天照顾3个孩子，这个苦差事把她快累垮了。 \n]\n','2020-03-17',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukg/ukgre/ukgrena028.mp3'),('grip','紧握，握紧，紧抓（住）使入迷，吸引…的注意力（感情等）强烈地控制；对…产生强烈影响控制，支配紧握，握紧，紧抓（住）旅行袋，（旅行用）手提包','uk :ɡrɪp, us :ɡrɪp','[The baby gripped my finger with her tiny hand. \n 婴儿的小手紧紧握住我的手指。 \n, Old tyres won t grip (= stay on the surface of the road) in the rain very well. \n 在雨天，旧轮胎在路面上防滑性能不是太好。 \n, This trial has gripped the whole nation. \n 这场审判引起了全国的关注。 \n, I was gripped throughout the entire two hours of the film. \n 整整两个小时我都沉浸在这部电影里。 \n, Then he turned towards me, and I was suddenly gripped by fear. \n 然后，他转过身对着我，我突然惊恐万状。 \n, Rebels have tightened their grip on the city. \n 叛军已经加强了他们对这座城市的控制。 \n, He will do anything to keep his grip on power. \n 为了保住权力他什么都会干。 \n, She tightened her grip on my arm. \n 她越来越用力地抓住我的胳膊。 \n, She would not loosen her grip on my arm. \n 她紧抓住我的胳膊不放。 \n]\n','2020-02-28',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukg/ukgri/ukgrind004.mp3'),('grit','砂，沙砾，沙粒勇气，毅力（尤指作为早餐的）粗玉米粉，玉米子（为防滑）在（路面上）撒沙砾','uk :ɡrɪt, us :ɡrɪt','[The road had been covered with grit. \n 以前这条路一直铺满沙砾。 \n, It takes true (= real) grit to stand up to a bully. \n 面对一个恃强凌弱者奋起反抗确实需要勇气。 \n, Council lorries had been out gritting the icy roads the night before. \n 政务委员会在头天夜里派出卡车在结冰的路面上撒了沙砾。 \n]\n','2020-01-03',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukg/ukgri/ukgrind012.mp3'),('grown','成年男子；成年女子','uk :ɡrəʊn, us :ɡroʊn','[I don t like to see a grown man in tears. \n 我讨厌看大男人哭鼻子。 \n]\n','2020-02-27',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukg/ukgri/ukgrind018.mp3'),('guilty','>内疚的，愧疚的，自责的>有过失的，犯了罪的，有罪责的>有过错的一方；犯罪的一方','uk :>ˈɡɪl.ti, us :>ˈɡɪl.ti',NULL,'2021-03-26',1,7,1,NULL),('gulp','大口地吃（或喝）；（因为害怕、吃惊、激动等）倒吸气，喘不过气来大口大口地吸（气）吞，咽','uk :ɡʌlp, us :ɡʌlp','[She gulped down her drink and made a hasty exit. \n 她大口喝下饮料后急匆匆地出去了。 \n, When it was his turn to dive, he gulped and stepped up onto the diving board. \n 轮到他跳水时，他深吸了一口气后走上跳板。 \n, He swallowed his drink in one gulp. \n 他把杯中的酒一饮而尽。 \n, She rose to the surface of the water once every minute to get/take a gulp of air. \n 她每隔一分钟要把头探出水面吸一大口气。 \n]\n','2020-01-03',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukg/ukgui/ukguime016.mp3'),('gum','齿龈，牙龈，牙床树胶，树脂胶，粘合剂口香糖（同 chewing gum）；泡泡糖（同 bubble gum）透明果味糖；胶姆糖；橡皮软糖用胶粘','uk :ɡʌm, us :ɡʌm','[sore gums \n 牙龈疼痛 \n, fruit/wine gums \n 水果胶姆糖／酒胶糖 \n, The labels were already gummed to the envelopes. \n 标签已经粘贴在信封上了。 \n]\n','2019-12-23',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukg/ukgui/ukguime017.mp3'),('gut','消化道；肠道，肠大肚子，肥大的腹部（同 bowels）（尤指旧时用来制作乐器和球拍的）肠线直觉，本能，内心感觉凭直觉，凭感情（决定或判断）勇气，胆量，意志（通常指火灾）彻底损毁（房屋）的内部（通常指为了装修）拆除（房屋）的内部（尤指在烹调前）取出…的内脏','uk :ɡʌt, us :ɡʌt','[Meat stays in the gut longer than vegetable matter. \n 和蔬菜相比，肉类在消化道中停留的时间更长。 \n, He s got a huge beer gut (= large stomach caused by drinking beer). \n 他有个大啤酒肚。 \n, My guts hurt. \n 我五脏六腑都疼。 \n, He got a knife in the guts. \n 他肚子被戳了一刀。 \n, I have a gut feeling that the relationship won t last. \n 我有种直觉，这段关系不会太长久。 \n, My head said that I should go but my gut said I should stay. \n 理智上我该走，但是感觉告诉我该留。 \n, I went with my gut and chose Sarah to lead the team. \n 我听从了直觉，选择莎拉领导队伍。 \n, [ + to infinitive ] \n It takes a lot of guts to admit to so many people that you ve made a mistake. \n 在那么多人面前承认自己犯了错误是需要很大勇气的。 \n, A fire gutted the bookshop last week. \n 上周一场火把书店给烧了个精光。 \n, She gutted the fish and cut off their heads. \n 她取出鱼的内脏并把鱼头切掉。 \n]\n','2020-02-28',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukg/ukgun/ukgunge028.mp3'),('gutted','非常沮丧的；非常失望的；极度伤心的','uk :ˈɡʌt.ɪd, us :ˈɡʌt̬.ɪd','[He was gutted when she finished the relationship. \n 她跟他分手后，他伤心欲绝。 \n]\n','2020-03-05',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukg/ukgut/ukgutsy002.mp3'),('habitually','习惯性地','uk :həˈbɪtʃ.ə.li, us :həˈbɪtʃ.ə.li','[here is something wrong with anyone who is so habitually rude.\n, There were schools where more than half the students were habitually late.\n]\n','2019-12-19',0,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english/uk_pron/u/ukg/ukgyr/ukgyros012.mp3'),('hail','雹，冰雹（同时抛向某人的）一阵招呼，呼喊下冰雹','uk :heɪl, us :heɪl','[a hail of bullets \n 一阵弹雨 \n, The prime minister was greeted with a hail of insults as she arrived at the university. \n 首相来到大学时遭到一阵辱骂。 \n, Shall we hail a taxi? \n 我们要叫出租车吗？ \n, I tried to hail her from across the room. \n 我在屋子的另一端冲她喊。 \n]\n','2019-12-23',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukh/ukhae/ukhaema015.mp3'),('halt','（使）停止，停下停止，停下，中止停止，中止','uk :hɒlt, us :hɑːlt','[ Halt!  called the guard.  You can t go any further without a permit.  \n “站住！”警卫喊道，“没有通行证不能入内。” \n, Production has halted at all of the company s factories because of the pay dispute. \n 由于工资纠纷，这家公司所有工厂都停产了。 \n, Security forces halted the demonstrators by blocking the road. \n 警卫部队用封路的办法来制止示威者前进。 \n, the recent halt in production \n 最近的停产 \n, Severe flooding has brought trains to a halt (= prevented them from moving) on several lines in Scotland. \n 凶猛的洪水使苏格兰几条铁路线上的火车停驶。 \n, The bus came to a halt (= stopped) just in time to avoid hitting the wall. \n 公共汽车正好及时停下，没有撞到墙上。 \n, If traffic increases beyond a certain level, the city grinds to a halt (= stops completely). \n 如果交通流量的增长超过一定限度，城市就会陷于瘫痪状态。 \n, The car screeched to a halt (= stopped suddenly and noisily) just as the lights turned red. \n 这辆车就在信号灯变红时嘎吱一声刹住了车。 \n, How many more people will have to die before they call a halt to the fighting? \n 还要死多少人他们才会停战？ \n]\n','2020-01-24',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukh/ukhal/ukhallw006.mp3'),('handbill','传单，小广告','uk :ˈhænd.bɪl, us :ˈhænd.bɪl','[]\n','2019-12-27',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/e/epd/epd13/epd13378.mp3'),('handmaid','女仆，侍女起辅助（或支持）作用的事物，基础','uk :ˈhændˌmeɪ.dən, us :ˈhændˌmeɪ.dən','[Technique is the handmaiden of art. \n 技巧乃艺术之基础。 \n]\n','2020-02-27',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukh/ukhan/ukhandb029.mp3'),('harass','骚扰；使烦恼，打扰','uk :ˈhær.əs, us :həˈræs','[Stop harassing me! \n 别烦我！ \n]\n','2019-12-13',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukh/ukhap/ukhapha013.mp3'),('harpsichord','羽管键琴，古键琴','uk :ˈhɑːp.sɪ.kɔːd, us :ˈhɑːrp.sɪ.kɔːrd','[]\n','2019-12-16',0,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukh/ukhar/ukharne005.mp3'),('hatred','憎恨，憎恶','uk :ˈheɪ.trɪd, us :ˈheɪ.trɪd','[What is very clear in these letters is Clark s passionate hatred of his father. \n 这些信非常清楚地表明了克拉克对他父亲的深切痛恨。 \n, The motive for this shocking attack seems to be racial hatred. \n 看起来这起令人震惊的攻击事件的动机像是种族仇恨。 \n]\n','2020-03-19',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukh/ukhas/ukhasty015.mp3'),('haunting','（因一种令人忧伤的美丽而）让人难忘的，萦绕心头的','uk :ˈhɔːn.tɪŋ, us :ˈhɑːn.t̬ɪŋ','[a haunting melody \n 难忘的旋律 \n, the haunting beauty of Africa \n 非洲令人难忘的美丽 \n]\n','2019-12-19',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukh/ukhas/ukhasty027.mp3'),('hearse','灵车，柩车','uk :hɜːs, us :hɝːs','[]\n','2019-12-27',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukh/ukhea/ukheads026.mp3'),('hedge','（尤指花园、田块或马路边缘的）树篱保护（或控制、限制）手段让表述内容的严重程度降低的单词（或词组）严格限制避免答复，拐弯抹角，回避','uk :hedʒ, us :hedʒ','[a privet hedge \n 女贞树篱 \n, She\'d made some overseas investments as a hedge against rising inflation in this country. \n 在海外有一些投资，可以抵消该国不断上升的通货膨胀所带来的损失。 \n, We\'ve got permission, but it\'s hedged about/around with strict conditions. \n 我们得到了许可，但却有严格的限制条件。 \n, Stop hedging and tell me what you really think. \n 别再拐弯抹角了，告诉我你的真实想法。 \n]\n','2019-10-07',0,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukh/ukhea/ukheave019.mp3'),('hedge fund','对冲基金','Duìchōng jījīn','\n','2019-10-07',0,1,0,'https://translate.google.cn/translate_tts?ie=UTF-8&q=hedge fund&tl=ja&tk=889337.763277&client=webapp&prev=input'),('hence','因此，所以从此，从现在起','uk :hens, us :hens','[His mother was Italian, hence his name - Luca. \n 他母亲是意大利人，所以他的名字叫——卢卡。 \n, The project will be completed at the end of the decade, two years hence. \n 本项目将于这个10年期结束时完成，从现在算起还有两年时间。 \n]\n','2019-10-07',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukh/ukhel/ukhellu022.mp3'),('heptagon','七边形','uk :ˈhep.tə.ɡən, us :-ɡɑːn','[]\n','2020-01-10',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukh/ukhen/ukhenpe004.mp3'),('herald','预示…的开始；（尤指通过庆祝或赞扬）宣布（常指好事）预兆，前兆（旧时的）传令官','uk :ˈher.əld, us :ˈher.əld','[The president s speech heralds a new era in foreign policy. \n 总统的演说预示着一个外交政策新时代的开始。 \n, This drug has been heralded as a major breakthrough in the fight against breast cancer. \n 据称这种药是在对抗乳腺癌方面取得的一个重大突破。 \n, If this first opera of the season is a herald (= sign) of what is to come, we can expect great things. \n 如果本季的这第一部歌剧是一个信号，那么我们可以期待接下来的剧目会非常精彩。 \n]\n','2020-02-28',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukh/ukhen/ukhenpe009.mp3'),('herb','（用作调味品或药材的）香草，药草','uk :hɜːb, us :ɝːb','[dried/fresh herbs \n 干／新鲜药草 \n, Basil, oregano, thyme, and rosemary are all herbs. \n 罗勒、牛至、百里香和迷迭香都是香草。 \n, A large range of herbs and spices are used in South Asian cooking. \n 印度烹饪中使用多种药草和香料。 \n]\n','2020-02-27',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukh/ukhen/ukhenpe012.mp3'),('heterosexual','异性恋者','uk :ˌhet.ər.əˈsek.ʃu.əl, us :ˌhet̬.ə.roʊˈsek.ʃu.əl','[]\n','2020-02-13',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukh/ukher/ukherse017.mp3'),('highball','高杯酒（用威士忌和水或汽水混合制成）','uk :ˈhaɪ.bɔːl, us :ˈhaɪ.bɑːl','[]\n','2020-01-03',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/c/cal/cald4/cald4uk0731.mp3'),('hillbilly','（住在山区的）乡巴佬，土包子','uk :ˈhɪlˌbɪl.i, us :ˈhɪlˌbɪl.i','[]\n','2020-01-03',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/c/cal/cald4/cald4uk0741.mp3'),('hippopotamus','河马','uk :ˌhɪp.əˈpɒt.ə.məs, us :ˌhɪp.əˈpɑː.t̬ə.məs','[]\n','2019-10-07',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukh/ukhim/ukhimal028.mp3'),('hooch','烈酒；（尤指）烈性威士忌','uk :huːtʃ, us :huːtʃ','[]\n','2020-01-03',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/c/cal/cald4/cald4uk0768.mp3'),('horn','角；角质（车辆的）喇叭（乐器）号','uk :hɔːn, us :hɔːrn','[The driver blew/sounded (informal honked) her horn. \n 那个司机按了喇叭。 \n]\n','2020-01-03',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukh/ukhoo/ukhoove019.mp3'),('hostility','敌意，不友好不同意，不喜欢战斗；战争行为','uk :hɒsˈtɪl.ə.ti, us :hɑːˈstɪl.ə.t̬i',NULL,'2021-03-11',12,14,1,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukh/ukhor/ukhorsi024.mp3'),('hotspot','多事之地；热点地区；可能发生战争（或骚乱）的地方热闹场所（可接上无线宽带上网的）热点','uk :ˈhɒt.spɒt, us :ˈhɑːt.spɑːt','[The border has become a major hotspot. \n 边境地区已经变成了主要的热点。 \n, The Manhattan is one of the best hotspots in town. \n 曼哈顿是城里最热闹的地方之一。 \n, There are wi-fi hotspots in all our cafés. \n 我们所有的咖啡馆里都有上网热点。 \n]\n','2019-12-26',0,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uka/uka33/uka33350.mp3'),('hum','发出连续低沉的声音，嗡嗡作响哼（曲子）忙乱，忙碌；嘈杂持续低沉的噪音；嗡嗡声','uk :hʌm, us :hʌm','[The computers were humming in the background. \n 计算机在背景中嗡嗡作响。 \n, What\'s that strange humming sound? \n 那种奇怪的嗡嗡声是什么？ \n, She hummed to herself as she walked to school. \n 她在上学的路上边走边哼曲子。 \n, I\'ve forgotten how that song goes - could you hum it for me? \n 我忘了那个调子怎么唱了——你能给我哼一下吗？ \n, The bar was really humming last night. \n 昨晚酒吧里一片乱哄哄的。 \n, Our house is on a main road, so we can hear the constant hum of traffic. \n 我们的房子在大路旁，所以能听见持续不断的交通噪声。 \n, There\'s an annoying hum on this computer. \n 这台计算机总是发出一种让人心烦的嗡嗡声。 \n]\n','2019-10-07',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukh/ukhuf/ukhuffi018.mp3'),('humdrum','乏味的，单调的，令人厌倦的','uk :ˈhʌm.drʌm, us :ˈhʌm.drʌm','[We lead such a humdrum life/existence. \n 我们的生活／日子过得真是乏味。 \n, Most of the work is fairly humdrum. \n 这工作大部分都相当单调。 \n]\n','2019-10-07',0,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukh/ukhum/ukhuman007.mp3'),('humidity','湿润，潮湿湿度','uk :hjuːˈmɪd.ə.ti, us :hjuːˈmɪd.ə.t̬i','[I don t like the humidity of this climate. \n 我不喜欢这种潮湿的天气。 \n, The temperature is almost 80 degrees, and the humidity 35%. \n 温度已经接近80度，湿度为30多一点。 \n]\n','2020-01-23',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukh/ukhum/ukhuman013.mp3'),('humiliation','羞辱','uk :hjuːˌmɪl.iˈeɪ.ʃən, us :hjuːˌmɪl.iˈeɪ.ʃən','[fter the humiliation of last week\'s defeat, the Mets were back on form.\n, Imagine the humiliation of having to apologize.\n, I felt a deep humiliation and wanted the ground to swallow me up.\n]\n','2019-10-08',0,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english/uk_pron/u/ukh/ukhum/ukhuman017.mp3'),('humorous','幽默的，滑稽的','uk :ˈhjuː.mə.rəs, us :ˈhjuː.mə.rəs','[Her latest book is a humorous look at teenage life. \n 她的新书是对青少年生活的一种幽默审视。 \n]\n','2020-02-28',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukh/ukhum/ukhuman009.mp3'),('hunch','直觉；预感弓（背），弯腰','uk :hʌntʃ, us :hʌntʃ','[[ + that ] \n I had a hunch that you d be here. \n 直觉告诉我你会来这儿。 \n, Sometimes you have to be prepared to act on/follow a hunch. \n 有时候你得准备好按直觉行事。 \n, We hunched round the fire to keep warm. \n 我们弓着身子围在火边取暖。 \n, Stand up straight and don t hunch your back. \n 站直了，别弯着腰。 \n]\n','2019-12-24',0,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukh/ukhun/ukhunch001.mp3'),('hurl','（通常指愤怒或用力地）抛，扔大声辱骂（某人）','uk :hɜːl, us :hɝːl','[In a fit of temper he hurled the book across the room. \n 他一怒之下把书扔到了房间的另一头。 \n, Youths hurled stones at the soldiers. \n 年轻人向士兵们投掷石块。 \n, I wasn t going to stand there while he hurled abuse at me! \n 我不会站在那儿任他大声辱骂！ \n]\n','2020-01-10',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukh/ukhun/ukhunch030.mp3'),('hybrid','（动物或植物的）杂交种，混合种（两种完全不同的东西的）混合用汽油以及其他形式的能源（通常为电力）一同发动的机动车','uk :ˈhaɪ.brɪd, us :ˈhaɪ.brɪd','[The garden strawberry is a large-fruited hybrid. \n 人工栽培的草莓是一种果实较大的杂交品种。 \n, The animal looks like a hybrid of a zebra and a horse. \n 这只动物看上去像是斑马和马杂交所得。 \n, His work is an interesting hybrid of popular and classical music. \n 他的作品是经典与流行音乐有趣的混合。 \n]\n','2020-01-14',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukh/ukhur/ukhurly027.mp3'),('hypocrisy','虚伪，伪善','uk :hɪˈpɒk.rɪ.si, us :hɪˈpɑː.krə.si','[There s one rule for her and another rule for everyone else and it s sheer hypocrisy. \n 对她是一种标准，而对所有其他人是另一种标准，这是彻头彻尾的虚伪。 \n]\n','2020-03-18',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukh/ukhyp/ukhyper019.mp3'),('hypocrite','伪君子，伪善者','uk :ˈhɪp.ə.krɪt, us :ˈhɪp.ə.krɪt','[He s a hypocrite - he s always lecturing other people on the environment but he drives around in a huge car. \n 他是个伪君子——他总在教导别人要保护环境，可他自己却开着辆大排量的汽车到处转。 \n]\n','2020-01-10',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukh/ukhyp/ukhyper020.mp3'),('iconic','（尤指能代表某种观点或某一时代）非常出名的，受欢迎的','uk :aɪˈkɒn.ɪk, us :aɪˈkɑː.nɪk','[John Lennon gained iconic status following his death. \n 约翰‧列侬死后成了偶像级人物。 \n]\n','2020-04-03',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukh/ukhyp/ukhypot029.mp3'),('illicit','非法的；违禁的；社会不容许的','uk :ɪˈlɪs.ɪt, us :ɪˈlɪs.ɪt','[illicit drugs such as cocaine and cannabis \n 可卡因和大麻之类的违禁药物 \n, the illicit trade in stolen vehicles \n 非法的赃车交易 \n, an illicit love affair \n 不正当的恋情 \n]\n','2019-12-27',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uke/ukele/ukelect027.mp3'),('illuminate','为…照明，照亮阐明，解释','uk :ɪˈluː.mɪ.neɪt, us :ɪˈluː.mə.neɪt','[The streets were illuminated with strings of coloured lights. \n 街道被一串串彩灯照亮了。 \n, an article which illuminates the issues at stake \n 对一些紧要的问题进行阐述的文章 \n]\n','2020-03-25',2,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uki/ukign/ukignor025.mp3'),('illustrate','给（书籍、杂志等）画插图（尤指用例子）说明，阐明','uk :ˈɪl.ə.streɪt, us :ˈɪl.ə.streɪt','[a beautifully illustrated book/old manuscript \n 配有精美插图的书／旧手稿 \n, The lecturer illustrated his point with a diagram on the blackboard. \n 讲师在黑板上用图表来说明自己的观点。 \n, This latest conflict further illustrates the weakness of the UN. \n 最近的这次冲突进一步说明了联合国的软弱。 \n, [ + question word ] \n The exhibition will illustrate how life evolved from water. \n 这次展览将展示生命是如何从水中演化而来的。 \n]\n','2020-03-18',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uki/ukill/ukillus003.mp3'),('illustration','插图；图解，图示例证，实例','uk :ˌɪl.əˈstreɪ.ʃən, us :ˌɪl.əˈstreɪ.ʃən','[a full-page illustration \n 一幅整页的插图 \n, colour/black and white illustrations \n 彩色／黑白插图 \n, This delay is a perfect illustration of why we need a new computer system. \n 这次延误再好不过地说明了我们为什么需要新的电脑系统。 \n, A couple of examples are included, by way of illustration (= to show the meaning more clearly). \n 聊举几例，以兹说明。 \n]\n','2020-03-06',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uki/ukill/ukillus004.mp3'),('immanence','内在','uk :ˈɪm.ə.nəns, us :ˈɪm.ə.nəns','[he immanence of religion is reflected in the music, much of which is based on Buddhist chants.\n, They recorded their daily activities with a peculiar sense of immanence.\n]\n','2020-03-23',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english/uk_pron/u/ukb/ukb00/ukb00606.mp3'),('immoral','不道德的，道德败坏的卖淫所得','uk :ɪˈmɒr.əl, us :ɪˈmɔːr.əl','[an immoral act \n 不道德的举动 \n, immoral behaviour \n 不道德的行为 \n, It s an immoral tax, because the poor will pay relatively more. \n 这是不道德的税收，因为穷人相对要付出更多。 \n, If convicted, she could be jailed for five years for living off immoral earnings. \n 如果被判有罪，她可能会因靠卖淫为生坐5年牢。 \n]\n','2020-03-19',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uki/ukimm/ukimmod005.mp3'),('immune','免疫的不受影响的免除的，豁免的','uk :ɪˈmjuːn, us :ɪˈmjuːn',NULL,'2021-03-08',4,7,1,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uki/ukimm/ukimmod011.mp3'),('immunity','免疫；免除；豁免','uk :ɪˈmjuː.nə.ti, us :ɪˈmjuː.nə.t̬i','[The vaccination gives you immunity against the disease for up to six months. \n 注射这种疫苗会使你对这种疾病有长达6个月的免疫力。 \n, He was granted immunity from prosecution because he confessed the names of the other spies. \n 他因供出了其他间谍的名字而免受起诉。 \n]\n','2020-01-10',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uki/ukimm/ukimmod012.mp3'),('immunosuppression','免疫抑制（通常通过药物有意识地抑制免疫反应，尤其用在阻止或降低机体对移植器官的排斥反应）','uk :ˌɪm.jə.nəʊ.səˈpreʃ.ən, us :ˌɪm.jə.noʊ.səˈpreʃ.ən','[High levels of immunosuppression are needed to prevent rejection of transplanted tissue or organs. \n 需要高强度的免疫抑制来防止对移植器官或组织的排斥。 \n]\n','2020-01-23',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uki/ukimm/ukimmod017.mp3'),('impact','冲击（力）；撞击（力）（尤指新事物的）巨大影响，强大作用（对…）产生影响','uk :ˈɪm.pækt, us :ˈɪm.pækt','[The impact of the crash reduced the car to a third of its original length. \n 撞车时的冲击力使车身变形，仅剩原长的三分之一。 \n, The bullet explodes on impact (= when it hits another object). \n 子弹击中物体时爆炸。 \n, The anti-smoking campaign had had/made quite an impact on young people. \n 禁烟运动对年轻人影响很大。 \n, The new proposals were intended to soften the impact of the reformed tax system. \n 新的提议旨在减轻改革后的税制所造成的影响。 \n, Falling export rates have impacted (on) the country\'s economy quite considerably. \n 出口率的下降对该国的经济造成了相当大的影响。 \n]\n','2019-10-08',0,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uki/ukimm/ukimmod023.mp3'),('impassable','（道路）不能通行的，无法通过的','uk :ɪmˈpɑː.sə.bəl, us :ɪmˈpæs.ə.bəl','[Many roads were flooded and impassable following the storm. \n 暴风雨过后，许多道路被淹，无法通行。 \n]\n','2019-10-08',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uki/ukimp/ukimpar005.mp3'),('implacable','不饶人的；坚定的；无法改变的','uk :ɪmˈplæk.ə.bəl, us :ɪmˈplæk.ə.bəl',NULL,'2021-03-08',5,7,1,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uki/ukimp/ukimpet012.mp3'),('implicate','牵连，涉及','uk :ˈɪm.plɪ.keɪt, us :ˈɪm.plə.keɪt','[Have they any evidence to implicate him in the robbery? \n 他们有证据表明他涉嫌抢劫案吗？ \n]\n','2020-01-23',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uki/ukimp/ukimpet022.mp3'),('imply','暗指，暗示正如…所暗示的必然包含；使成为必需','uk :ɪmˈplaɪ, us :ɪmˈplaɪ','[[ + (that) ] \n Are you implying (that) I\'m fat? \n 你是在暗示我长得胖吗？ \n, I\'m not implying anything about your cooking, but could we eat out tonight? \n 我并不是暗示你做的饭不好吃，只是想提议我们今晚去外面吃，好吗？ \n, I detected an implied criticism of the way he was treated. \n 我觉察到他在含蓄地批评自己受到的待遇。 \n, Variable rate loans, as the name implies, have a variable interest rate. \n 可变利率贷款，正如名字所暗示的，是一种利率可能变化的贷款。 \n, Socialism implies equality. \n 社会主义必然包含平等。 \n]\n','2019-10-09',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uki/ukimp/ukimplo002.mp3'),('impose','推行；强制实行把（尤指信仰或生活方式）强加于勉强；打扰，麻烦','uk :ɪmˈpəʊz, us :ɪmˈpoʊz','[Very high taxes have recently been imposed on cigarettes. \n 最近对香烟开征很高的税。 \n, Judges are imposing increasingly heavy fines for minor driving offences. \n 法官们对轻微的违章驾驶开始处以越来越重的罚款。 \n, The council has imposed a ban on alcohol in the city parks. \n 市政会禁止在城市公园中饮酒。 \n, I don t want them to impose their religious beliefs on my children. \n 我不希望他们把自己的宗教信仰强加给我的孩子们。 \n, We must impose some kind of order on the way this office is run. \n 我们得给这个办公室的管理定出规章来。 \n, Are you sure it s all right for me to come tonight? I don t want to impose. \n 你肯定我今天晚上来没有问题吗？我不想太麻烦你。 \n, She s always imposing on people - asking favours and getting everyone to do things for her. \n 她总是强人所难——要人帮忙做这做那。 \n]\n','2020-01-24',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uki/ukimp/ukimplo017.mp3'),('impressionable','（通常指年轻人）易受影响的','uk :ɪmˈpreʃ.ən.ə.bəl, us :ɪmˈpreʃ.ən.ə.bəl','[He s at that impressionable age when he s very easily led by other children. \n 他正处于那种易受影响的年龄，行为非常容易受其他孩子左右。 \n]\n','2019-12-20',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uki/ukimp/ukimpra012.mp3'),('impunity','（惩罚、坏结果的）免除','uk :ɪmˈpjuː.nə.ti, us :ɪmˈpjuː.ə.t̬i','[Criminal gangs are terrorizing the city with apparent impunity. \n 犯罪集团使市民人心惶惶却显然没有受到惩罚。 \n]\n','2020-01-14',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uki/ukimp/ukimpro014.mp3'),('in force','in large number','null','null\n','2019-10-08',1,0,0,'null'),('inaccurate','不准确的；不精确的','uk :ɪnˈæk.jə.rət, us :ɪnˈæk.jɚ.ət','[Their estimate of the cost of the project was wildly (= extremely) inaccurate. \n 他们对项目费用的估计非常不准确。 \n, an inaccurate device/weapon \n 不精确的设备／武器 \n]\n','2020-03-06',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uki/ukimp/ukimpro025.mp3'),('inadequacy','不够好，劣质（处理事情）信心不足','uk :ɪˈnæd.ɪ.kwə.si, us :ɪˈnæd.ə.kwə.si','[Economic growth is hindered by the inadequacies of the public transport system. \n 经济发展受制于公共交通运输系统的不完善。 \n, The inadequacy of the budget is likely to cause problems. \n 预算的不足有可能会导致问题。 \n, I always suffer from feelings of inadequacy when I m with him. \n 和他在一起时总觉得自己不如他，这让我感到不舒服。 \n]\n','2020-03-05',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uki/ukimp/ukimpro030.mp3'),('incandescent','白炽的，白热的极亮的极度愤怒的；极度高兴的杰出的，卓越的','uk :ˌɪn.kænˈdes.ənt, us :ˌɪn.kænˈdes.ənt','[an incandescent lamp \n 白炽灯 \n, The mountain s snow-white peak was incandescent against the blue sky. \n 雪白的山顶在蓝天的映衬下十分耀眼。 \n, He was incandescent with rage. \n 他大发雷霆。 \n, Her beauty had an incandescent quality to it. \n 她貌美绝伦，光彩照人。 \n, an incandescent performance/career \n 炉火纯青的表演／辉煌的事业 \n]\n','2020-03-25',2,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uki/ukina/ukinaug015.mp3'),('inconvenience','不便，麻烦带来不便，导致麻烦','uk :ˌɪn.kənˈviː.ni.əns, us :ˌɪn.kənˈviːn.jəns','[We apologize for any inconvenience caused by the late arrival of the train. \n 我们对火车晚点所造成的一切不便表示歉意。 \n, We had the inconvenience of being unable to use the kitchen for several weeks. \n 我们有几个星期不能使用厨房，很不方便。 \n, Having to wait for ten minutes was a minor inconvenience. \n 得等上10分钟确实有一点儿麻烦。 \n, The strike inconvenienced many people. \n 罢工给许多人带来了不便。 \n]\n','2020-03-18',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uki/ukinc/ukincon028.mp3'),('incorporate','包含；将…包括在内','uk :ɪnˈkɔː.pər.eɪt, us :ɪnˈkɔːr.pɚ.eɪt','[Suggestions from the survey have been incorporated into/in the final design. \n 调查中取得的建议已被纳入了最终的设计之中。 \n, This aircraft incorporates several new safety features. \n 这种飞机具有几种新的安全特征。 \n]\n','2020-03-11',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uki/ukinc/ukincor001.mp3'),('incubate','孵（卵），孵化（细菌或病毒在体内）潜伏','uk :ˈɪŋ.kjə.beɪt, us :ˈɪŋ.kjə.beɪt','[The female bird incubates the eggs for about 16 days. \n 雌鸟孵卵16天左右。 \n]\n','2020-01-24',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uki/ukinc/ukincor025.mp3'),('incubation','孵化, 疾病, （細菌或病毒在體內）潛伏','uk :ˌɪŋ.kjəˈbeɪ.ʃən, us :ˌɪŋ.kjəˈbeɪ.ʃən','[he incubation period varies depending on the time of year when the eggs were laid.\n, The chemical makes eggshells so thin and porous that they break during incubation. \n, n smallpox, there is an incubation period of 8–18 days between initial infection and first symptoms.\n, After about two weeks of incubation, symptoms begin.\n]\n','2020-01-23',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english/uk_pron/u/uki/ukinc/ukincor026.mp3'),('indice','指数，索引','ˈɪndɪsiːz','null\n','2019-10-07',0,1,0,'null'),('inevitability','必然性','uk :ɪˌnev.ɪ.təˈbɪl.ə.ti, us :ˌɪnˌev.ə.t̬əˈbɪl.ə.t̬i','[he inevitability of change\n, His created a sense of inevitability around his campaign. \n]\n','2020-02-28',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english/uk_pron/u/uki/ukine/ukineff019.mp3'),('inevitable','不可避免的；必然发生的不可避免的情况；逃避不了的事实','uk :ɪˈnev.ɪ.tə.bəl, us :ˌɪnˈev.ə.t̬ə.bəl','[The accident was the inevitable consequence/result/outcome of carelessness. \n 这一事故是粗心导致的必然结果。 \n, Eventually the inevitable happened and he had a heart attack. \n 最终不可避免的情况还是发生了，他心脏病发作。 \n]\n','2020-03-05',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uki/ukine/ukineff020.mp3'),('infant','婴儿幼儿学校的学生幼儿学校（同 infant school）学前班的，幼儿的','uk :ˈɪn.fənt, us :ˈɪn.fənt','[a newborn infant \n 新生儿 \n, Jenny is a top-year infant now. \n 珍妮现在是一所幼儿学校的大班生。 \n, Andrew s still in the infants. \n 安德鲁还在上幼儿学校。 \n, an infant teacher/class \n 幼师／学前班 \n]\n','2020-01-23',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uki/ukine/ukinexp019.mp3'),('infatuated','（通常短期）热恋的，着迷的','uk :ɪnˈfætʃ.u.eɪ.tɪd, us :ɪnˈfætʃ.u.eɪ.t̬ɪd','[She was infatuated with her boss. \n 她对她的老板很着迷。 \n]\n','2020-03-18',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uki/ukine/ukinexp025.mp3'),('infidelity','（夫妇间的）不忠实，不贞行为','uk :ˌɪn.fɪˈdel.ə.ti, us :ˌɪn.fəˈdel.ə.t̬i','[marital/sexual infidelity \n 婚姻／性方面的不忠 \n, She could not forgive his many infidelities. \n 她不能原谅他的诸多不忠行为。 \n]\n','2020-02-13',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uki/ukinf/ukinfec017.mp3'),('informally','非公式','null','null\n','2019-10-08',1,0,0,'null'),('infrastructure','基础设施','uk :ˈɪn.frəˌstrʌk.tʃər, us :ˈɪn.frəˌstrʌk.tʃɚ','[The war has badly damaged the country\'s infrastructure. \n 战争严重破坏了该国的基础设施。 \n]\n','2019-10-09',0,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uki/ukinf/ukinfor009.mp3'),('ingrained','（观念）根深蒂固的（尘土等）深嵌着的，难以去除的','uk :ɪnˈɡreɪnd, us :ɪnˈɡreɪnd','[Such ingrained prejudices cannot be corrected easily. \n 如此根深蒂固的偏见是不容易纠正的。 \n, The belief that you should own your house is deeply ingrained in our society. \n 在我们的社会中，应该拥有自己的住房这一观念根深蒂固。 \n, The oil had become ingrained in his skin. \n 油污已渗入他的皮肤。 \n]\n','2020-03-12',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uki/ukinf/ukinfor029.mp3'),('inhabit','居住于','uk :ɪnˈhæb.ɪt, us :ɪnˈhæb.ɪt','[These remote islands are inhabited only by birds. \n 这些偏僻的岛屿上只有鸟类栖息。 \n]\n','2020-01-09',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uki/uking/ukingra007.mp3'),('inhabitant','（某地的）居民，栖居动物','uk :ɪnˈhæb.ɪ.tənt, us :ɪnˈhæb.ɪ.tənt','[a city of five million inhabitants \n 拥有500万居民的城市 \n]\n','2020-04-03',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uki/uking/ukingra009.mp3'),('inhale','吸气；吸入狼吞虎咽','uk :ɪnˈheɪl, us :ɪnˈheɪl','[She flung open the window and inhaled deeply. \n 她打开窗户，深深地吸了口气。 \n, She became ill shortly after inhaling the fumes. \n 她吸入浓烟后不久就生病了。 \n, Tony inhaled his burger. \n 托尼狼吞虎咽地吃汉堡。 \n]\n','2021-03-11',6,8,1,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uki/uking/ukingra011.mp3'),('inlay','镶嵌图案（或装饰）','uk :ˈɪn.leɪ, us :ˈɪn.leɪ','[The walls of the palace are marble with silver inlay. \n 宫殿的墙壁是镶银大理石的。 \n]\n','2021-03-23',4,7,1,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uki/ukini/ukiniti021.mp3'),('innate','天生的，固有的','uk :ɪˈneɪt, us :ɪˈneɪt','[Cyril s most impressive quality was his innate goodness. \n 西里尔给人印象最深的品质是他天生的善良。 \n]\n','2020-01-10',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uki/ukini/ukiniti027.mp3'),('inoculation','接种','uk :ɪˌnɒk.jəˈleɪ.ʃən, us :ɪˌnɑː.kjəˈleɪ.ʃən','[fter inoculation with the 2nd vaccine the animals\' temperature will go up.\n, He received a cholera inoculation.\n, A doctor visits the clinic monthly to give inoculations.\n]\n','2020-01-23',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english/uk_pron/u/uki/ukinn/ukinnin023.mp3'),('inquire','询问，打听','uk :ɪnˈkwaɪər, us :ɪnˈkwaɪr','[Shall I inquire about the price of tickets? \n 我可以问一下票价吗？ \n, [ + question word ] \n She called to inquire when her car would be ready. \n 她打电话询问她的车何时能准备好。 \n, [ + speech ] \n  Where are we going?  he inquired politely. \n “我们要去哪儿？”他客气地问道。 \n]\n','2020-03-06',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uke/ukenl/ukenliv013.mp3'),('insane','疯癫的，精神失常的疯狂的；荒唐的精神病患者','uk :ɪnˈseɪn, us :ɪnˈseɪn','[For the last ten years of his life he was clinically insane. \n 在生命的最后10年，他处于临床上的精神失常状态。 \n, nformal \n I sometimes think I m going insane (= I feel very confused). \n 我有时觉得自己快要疯了。 \n, It would be insane not to take advantage of this opportunity. \n 如果不抓住这一机会的话那就太荒唐了。 \n, a hospital for the criminally insane \n 为患有精神病的犯人开设的医院 \n]\n','2020-01-14',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uki/ukino/ukinorg016.mp3'),('insanely','疯狂地','uk :ɪnˈseɪn.li, us :ɪnˈseɪn.li','[She gets insanely jealous if he so much as looks at another woman. \n 哪怕他只是看一眼别的女人，她都会妒嫉得发疯。 \n]\n','2020-03-18',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uki/ukino/ukinorg017.mp3'),('insinuate','含沙射影地说，影射','uk :ɪnˈsɪn.ju.eɪt, us :ɪnˈsɪn.ju.eɪt','[[ + (that) ] \n Are you insinuating (that) I m losing my nerve? \n 你是在暗示我胆怯了吗？ \n, What are you insinuating, Daniel? \n 丹尼尔，你究竟在影射什么？ \n]\n','2019-12-19',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uki/ukins/ukinsin003.mp3'),('inspect','检查；审视视察；检阅鉴定，查勘（建筑物）','uk :ɪnˈspekt, us :ɪnˈspekt','[After the crash both drivers got out and inspected their cars for damage. \n 撞车后，两辆车的司机都下来检查各自的车有无损坏。 \n, She held the bank note up to the light and inspected it carefully. \n 她举起钞票，对着光仔细检查。 \n, An official from the Department of Health will be inspecting the restaurant this afternoon. \n 今天下午卫生部的一名官员要来视察这家餐馆。 \n, The King inspected the troops. \n 国王检阅了部队。 \n]\n','2020-03-06',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uki/ukins/ukinsin029.mp3'),('inspection','检查；视察鉴定，查勘（建筑物）','uk :ɪnˈspek.ʃən, us :ɪnˈspek.ʃən','[Her passport seemed legitimate, but on closer inspection, it was found to have been altered. \n 她的护照看似合法，但仔细检查，发现做过手脚。 \n, She arrived to carry out/make a health and safety inspection of the building. \n 她来对大楼进行安全卫生检查。 \n]\n','2019-10-08',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uki/ukins/ukinsin030.mp3'),('instant','立即的，即刻的（食品或饮品）快餐的，方便的，速溶的瞬息，顷刻','uk :ˈɪn.stənt, us :ˈɪn.stənt','[This type of account offers you instant access to your money. \n 这种账户允许随时支取存款。 \n, Contrary to expectations, the film was an instant success. \n 与预期相反，这部电影一上演即获得成功。 \n, instant coffee/soup \n 速溶咖啡／快餐汤 \n, In an instant her mood had changed. \n 顷刻间她的情绪就变了。 \n, The startled boy froze for an instant, then fled. \n 那个受惊的男孩愣了片刻，然后就逃跑了。 \n,  Stop that noise this instant (= now)!  \n 马上把那噪音停下来！ \n, I ll call you the instant (= as soon as) I get home. \n 我一到家就给你打电话。 \n]\n','2020-03-18',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uki/ukins/ukinspe013.mp3'),('instigate','促使发生；发起','uk :ˈɪn.stɪ.ɡeɪt, us :ˈɪn.stə.ɡeɪt','[The government will instigate new measures to combat terrorism. \n 政府将采取新措施打击恐怖主义。 \n, The revolt in the north is believed to have been instigated by a high-ranking general. \n 北方的叛乱据信是由一名高级将领唆使的。 \n]\n','2020-02-13',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uki/ukins/ukinspe019.mp3'),('institute','研究所；学院建立；制定；开始','uk :ˈɪn.stɪ.tʃuːt, us :ˈɪn.stə.tuːt','[the Massachusetts Institute of Technology \n 麻省理工学院 \n, She is threatening to institute legal proceedings against the hospital. \n 她威胁说要对该医院提起诉讼。 \n]\n','2020-03-12',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uki/ukins/ukinspe026.mp3'),('institutional','机构的','uk :ˌɪn.stɪˈtʃuː.ʃən.əl, us :ˌɪn.stəˈtuː.ʃən.əl','[The hospital provides typically awful institutional food. \n 医院供应的是公共机构常见的那种难吃的食物。 \n]\n','2019-10-07',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uki/ukins/ukinspe028.mp3'),('instruction','指示，命令，吩咐用法说明；操作指南教授；指导（某种技能／科目）','uk :ɪnˈstrʌk.ʃən, us :ɪnˈstrʌk.ʃən','[The police who broke into the house were only acting on/under instructions. \n 警察破门而入只是奉命行事。 \n, [ + to infinitive ] \n He gave me strict instructions to get there by eight o clock. \n 他命令我必须在8点以前到达那里。 \n, The cooking instructions say to bake it for half an hour. \n 烹调说明书上说烘烤半个小时。 \n, You obviously didn t read the instructions properly. \n 你显然没有好好看说明书。 \n, They need clear instructions on what to do next. \n 关于下一步该怎么做，他们需要明确的指导。 \n, The video provides instruction on how to operate the computer. \n 这盘录像教人们如何操作计算机。 \n, The course gives you basic instruction in car maintenance. \n 这门课教授汽车维修方面的基本知识。 \n, Have you seen the instruction manual for the washing machine? \n 你看过洗衣机的操作指南吗？ \n]\n','2020-02-27',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uki/ukins/ukinstr002.mp3'),('insufficiency','不够，不足；不充分（器官和身体部分）机能不全，功能不全','uk :ˌɪn.səˈfɪʃ.ən.si, us :ˌɪn.səˈfɪʃ.ən.si','[Sometimes we blame all our problems on an insufficiency of money. \n 有时候我们把所有问题都归咎于钱不够。 \n, Pancreatic insufficiency is associated with excess fat in stool. \n 胰功能不全和粪便中脂肪过多有关联。 \n]\n','2020-01-23',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uki/ukins/ukinstr015.mp3'),('insult','侮辱；辱骂侮辱，辱骂','uk :ˈɪn.sʌlt, us :ˈɪn.sʌlt','[She made several insults about my appearance. \n 她说了几句侮辱我长相的话。 \n, The steelworkers  leader rejected the two percent pay rise saying it was an insult to the profession. \n 钢铁工人的领导者拒绝接受2%的加薪，认为这是对他们职业的侮辱。 \n, The instructions are so easy they are an insult to your intelligence (= they seem to suggest you are not clever if you need to use them). \n 说明如此简单，简直是在侮辱你的智商。 \n, First he drank all my wine and then he insulted all my friends. \n 他先喝光了我的酒，然后又辱骂了我所有的朋友。 \n]\n','2020-03-06',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uki/ukins/ukinstr024.mp3'),('insurance','保险','uk :ɪnˈʃɔː.rəns\nɪnˈʃʊə.rəns, us :ɪnˈʃɜ.r.əns','[life/health/car/travel insurance \n 人寿／健康／汽车／旅行保险 \n, I ll need to take out extra car insurance for another driver. \n 我需要为另一名驾车人购买汽车保险。 \n, The insurance doesn t cover you for (= include) household items. \n 这份保险没有包括你的家用物品。 \n]\n','2020-01-03',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uki/ukins/ukinsur001.mp3'),('insurgent','叛乱者，造反者，暴动者（尤指政党的）反对派','uk :ɪnˈsɜː.dʒənt, us :ɪnˈsɝː.dʒənt','[All approaches to the capital are now under the control of the insurgents. \n 所有通往首都的道路都被叛乱分子控制了。 \n]\n','2020-03-10',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uki/ukins/ukinsur006.mp3'),('intellectual','智力的，脑力的知识分子，脑力劳动者','uk :ˌɪn.təlˈek.tʃu.əl, us :ˌɪn.t̬əlˈek.tʃu.əl',NULL,'2020-03-19',1,5,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uki/ukins/ukinsur020.mp3'),('intellectualism','主知主義者','uk :ˌɪn.təlˈek.tʃu.ə.lɪ.zəm, us :ˌɪn.t̬əlˈek.tʃu.ə.lɪ.zəm','[e wasn\'t intimidated by Kerry\'s intellectualism.\n, She encouraged her father to offset his intellectualism with displays of emotion.\n]\n','2019-12-20',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english/uk_pron/u/uki/ukins/ukinsur021.mp3'),('intense','强烈的，极度的认真的；热切的；有强烈情感的；尖锐的','uk :ɪnˈtens, us :ɪnˈtens','[intense cold/heat/hatred \n 严寒／酷热／痛恨 \n, an intense flavour/colour \n 浓烈的口味／浓重的颜色 \n, He suddenly felt an intense pain in his back. \n 他突然觉得背部一阵剧痛。 \n, an intense young man \n 认真的年轻人 \n]\n','2020-01-20',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uki/ukint/ukintem006.mp3'),('intensify','加强，增强；强化','uk :ɪnˈten.sɪ.faɪ, us :ɪnˈten.sə.faɪ','[Fighting around the capital has intensified in the last few hours. \n 首都周围的战斗在过去的几小时里变得更加激烈。 \n]\n','2020-02-28',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uki/ukint/ukintem010.mp3'),('intent','专心致志的，专注的执意要做；决意要达成意图，目的','uk :ɪnˈtent, us :ɪnˈtent','[an intent stare \n 目不转睛的注视 \n, She had an intent look on her face. \n 她的面部表情非常专注。 \n, I ve tried persuading her not to go but she s intent on it. \n 我试图劝她不要去，但她坚决要去。 \n, He seems intent on upsetting everyone in the room! \n 他看来存心要惹恼屋子里的每个人！ \n, I spent half the morning on the phone, which wasn t really my intent. \n 我半个上午都花在了打电话上，这可不是我真正想做的。 \n, [ + to infinitive ] \n It was not his intent to hurt anyone. \n 他的本意并不是想伤害谁。 \n, She was charged with possessing weapons with intent to endanger life. \n 她被指控以故意伤人为目的持有武器。 \n]\n','2020-02-21',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uki/ukint/ukintem013.mp3'),('interpret','理解，解释，阐释（表演者根据本人对作品的理解）表演，演绎翻译，口译','uk :ɪnˈtɜː.prɪt, us :-ˈtɝː-','[It s difficult to interpret these statistics without knowing how they were obtained. \n 不了解这些统计数字是怎样得来的就难以理解它们。 \n, A jury should not interpret the silence of a defendant as a sign of guilt. \n 陪审团不应该将被告的沉默看作是有罪的表示。 \n, If Shakespeare s plays are to reach a large audience they need to be interpreted in a modern style. \n 要使莎士比亚的戏剧让大量观众去接受，就需要用现代的风格去演绎。 \n, We had to ask our guide to interpret for us. \n 我们不得不请导游为我们翻译。 \n]\n','2020-03-05',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uki/ukint/ukinter220.mp3'),('interpretation','解释，阐释；理解（音乐，戏剧角色等的）演绎；演出；表演','uk :ɪnˌtɜː.prəˈteɪ.ʃən, us :ɪnˌtɝː.prəˈteɪ.ʃən','[The dispute is based on two widely differing interpretations of the law. \n 争论是源于对法律的两种截然不同的解释。 \n, The rules are vague and open to interpretation. \n 规则很含糊，可作各种诠释。 \n, It is difficult for many people to accept a literal interpretation of the Bible. \n 很多人觉得难以接受对圣经的字面诠释。 \n, Her interpretation of Juliet was one of the best performances I have ever seen. \n 她演绎的朱丽叶是我所见到的最出色的表演之一。 \n]\n','2020-01-09',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uki/ukint/ukinter221.mp3'),('interval','间隔；间距（两点之间的）区间（演出的）幕间休息；（体育比赛的）中间休息，中场休息每隔（一定时间或距离）音程','uk :ˈɪn.tə.vəl, us :ˈɪn.t̬ɚ.vəl','[We see each other at regular intervals - usually about once a month. \n 我们定期见面——通常大约是每月一次。 \n, The plants should be spaced at six-inch intervals. \n 这些植物应该以六英尺的间隔栽种。 \n, There will be two 20-minute intervals during the opera. \n 歌剧演出中有两次20分钟的幕间休息。