人好好聊了一番。 \n, He was jawing away to his girlfriend for hours on the phone. \n 他和女朋友煲了几个小时的电话粥。 \n]\n','2020-01-17',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukj/ukjau/ukjaund009.mp3'),('jeopardise','使处于危险境地；危及，损害','uk :ˈdʒep.ə.daɪz, us :ˈdʒep.ɚ.daɪz','[She knew that by failing her finals she could jeopardize her whole future. \n 她知道考试不及格会影响自己的整个前程。 \n]\n','2019-10-08',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukj/ukjeh/ukjehov010.mp3'),('jest','笑话；滑稽事开玩笑地，诙谐地开玩笑','uk :dʒest, us :dʒest','[His proposal was no jest - he was completely sincere. \n 他的建议不是开玩笑，他完全是认真的。 \n, I only said it in jest - you re obviously not fat. \n 我那么说是开玩笑——很显然，你不胖。 \n, Would I jest about something so important? \n 我会拿这么重要的事开玩笑吗？ \n]\n','2020-01-09',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukj/ukjeh/ukjehov024.mp3'),('jewish','犹太教','ˈdʒuː.ɪʃ',NULL,'2020-03-25',1,4,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english/uk_pron/u/ukj/ukjet/ukjetsa012.mp3'),('joint','共有的，共享的；共同的关节使脱臼接头；接缝；结合处一大块烤肉带骨的大块肉（出售廉价饮食的）酒吧（或餐馆）不良场所（声名狼藉的公众娱乐场所）大麻烟卷把（肉）切成大块（供烹制用）','uk :dʒɔɪnt, us :dʒɔɪnt','[a joint bank account \n 共有银行账户 \n, The project was a joint effort between the two schools (= they worked on it together). \n 这一项目是两个学校共同合作的。 \n, The two Russian ice skaters came joint second (= they were both given second prize) in the world championships. \n 两名俄罗斯滑冰运动员在世界锦标赛中并列第二。 \n, In court, the parents were awarded joint custody of their son (= the right to care for him was shared between them). \n 法庭上这对父母获判对他们的儿子共同拥有监护权。 \n, an elbow/hip/knee joint \n 肘／髋／膝关节 \n, As you become older, your joints get stiffer. \n 随着年龄增加，关节就会变僵硬。 \n, I put my shoulder out of joint last weekend lifting heavy boxes. \n 我上周末搬重箱子时肩膀脱臼了。 \n, Damp has penetrated the joints in the wood panelling. \n 潮气已渗透到木板饰面的接缝处。 \n, a joint of beef/pork \n 一大块烤牛肉／烤猪肉 \n, Fry four chicken joints in a pan with some mushrooms and 