/dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukl/ukldr/ukldriv013.mp3'),('leap','跳，跳跃快速提供（帮助、保护等）一举获得（常指名望或权势）激增；猛涨；快速提高巨变；激增；提高跳，跳跃；突然的动作','uk :liːp, us :liːp','[He leaped out of his car and ran towards the house. \n 他跳下车朝那所房子跑去。 \n, I leaped up to answer the phone. \n 我跳起来去接电话。 \n, The dog leaped over the gate into the field. \n 狗越过大门朝田野跑去。 \n, He leaped to his friend s defence. \n 他立即为他的朋友进行辩护。 \n, Scott leapt to the rescue when he spotted the youngster in difficulty. \n 斯科特一发现那孩子处境艰难就立即出手帮忙。 \n, Mr Davies leaped in to explain. \n 戴维斯先生赶忙出来解释。 \n, He leapt to fame after his appearance in a Broadway play. \n 他在参加一出百老汇演出后一举成名。 \n, Shares in the company leaped 250 percent. \n 公司的股票大涨250%。 \n, a leap in profits \n 利润激增 \n, It takes quite a leap of the imagination to believe that it s the same person. \n 让人相信这是同一个人着实要费一番脑筋。 \n, With one leap he crossed the stream. \n 他一跃跳过了小溪。 \n]\n','2020-01-10',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukl/ukldr/ukldriv023.mp3'),('leash','（拴狗等动物用的）绳索，链子','uk :liːʃ, us :liːʃ','[Please keep your dog on a leash when on the beach. \n 在海滩上请牵住你的狗。 \n]\n','2020-01-10',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukl/uklea/uklearn006.mp3'),('lecture','（尤指面向学生的）讲座，课教训，训斥，斥责（常指在大学里）讲课，讲授教训，训斥，斥责','uk :ˈlek.tʃər, us :ˈlek.tʃɚ','[We went to a lecture on Italian art. \n 我们去参加了一个关于意大利艺术的讲座。 \n, Who s giving the lecture this afternoon? \n 今天下午的课由谁来讲？ \n, My dad gave me a lecture on the evils of alcohol last night. \n 昨天晚上爸爸教训了我一顿，给我讲了酒的危害。 \n, For ten years she lectured in law. \n 她教了10年的法律课。 \n, She travelled widely in North America, lecturing on women s rights. \n 她到北美各地宣讲妇女的权利。 \n, His parents used to lecture him on his table manners. \n 以前他的父母经常批评他的餐桌礼仪。 \n]\n','2019-12-26',0,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukl/uklea/uklearn027.mp3'),('leech','水蛭，蚂蟥（指人）吸血鬼，寄生虫','uk :liːtʃ, us :liːtʃ','[]\n','2019-12-19',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukl/ukldr/ukldriv002.mp3'),('legislate','立法','uk :ˈledʒ.ɪ.sleɪt, us :ˈledʒ.ə.sleɪt','[They promised to legislate against cigarette advertising. \n 他们承诺要立法来打击香烟广告。 \n, It\'s hard to legislate for (= make a law that will protect) the ownership of an idea. \n 通过立法来保护创意所有权非常困难。 \n]\n','2019-10-08',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukl/ukleg/uklegal012.mp3'),('legislative','法律的；立法的','uk :ˈledʒ.ɪ.slə.tɪv, us :ˈledʒ.ə.slə.t̬ɪv',NULL,'2021-03-08',6,8,1,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukl/ukleg/uklegal014.mp3'),('leisure','空闲，闲暇，休闲','uk :ˈleʒ.ər, us :ˈliː.ʒɚ','[leisure activities \n 休闲活动 \n, Most people only have a limited amount of leisure time. \n 大多数人只有有限的空闲时间。 \n, The town lacks leisure facilities such as a swimming pool or squash courts. \n 这个城镇缺少游泳池、壁球场等休闲设施。 \n]\n','2020-02-13',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukl/ukleg/uklegal030.mp3'),('lesion','（对人体或体内器官的）伤害，损伤','uk :ˈliː.ʒən, us :ˈliː.ʒən','[skin/brain lesions \n 皮肤／大脑损伤 \n]\n','2020-01-23',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukl/ukles/ukles__004.mp3'),('lest','以免，唯恐','uk :lest, us :lest','[They were afraid to complain about the noise lest they annoyed the neighbours. \n 他们不敢对噪声有任何抱怨，唯恐惹恼了邻居。 \n]\n','2021-03-08',6,8,1,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukl/ukles/ukles__009.mp3'),('lethal','致命的；极其危险的','uk :ˈliː.θəl, us :ˈliː.θəl','[Three minutes after the fire started, the house was full of lethal fumes. \n 起火3分钟后，房子里充满了致命的毒气。 \n, In the car the police found guns, knives, and other lethal weapons (= weapons that can kill). \n 警察在车里找到了枪支、刀具及其他一些凶器。 \n, A 59-year-old man was executed by lethal injection (= by having a poisonous substance put into his body) this morning. \n 今晨一位59岁的男性罪犯被执行注射死刑。 \n, nformal \n That combination of tiredness and alcohol is lethal (= has a very bad effect). \n 身体的疲劳加上酒精的作用会产生非常严重的后果。 \n]\n','2020-01-24',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukl/ukles/ukles__013.mp3'),('liable','承担责任的；负有（法律）责任的很可能会发生的，可能性很大的','uk :ˈlaɪ.ə.bəl, us :ˈlaɪ.ə.bəl','[The law holds parents liable if a child does not attend school. \n 法律规定孩子不上学父母要负责任。 \n, If we lose the case we may be liable for (= have to pay) the costs of the whole trial. \n 如果我们输掉了这场官司，就可能要承担官司的全部费用。 \n, The areas of town near the river are liable to flooding (= are often flooded). \n 这个城镇靠近河边的地区很容易遭到水淹。 \n, [ + to infinitive ] \n He s liable to make a fuss if you wake him. \n 你如果把他吵醒了，他会大发雷霆的。 \n]\n','2020-04-01',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukl/uklev/uklevel021.mp3'),('liberty','自由被准许做…自由放肆，无礼，失礼任意歪曲，随意改动（对某人）过分亲昵，过分亲热；调戏','uk :ˈlɪb.ə.ti, us :ˈlɪb.ɚ.t̬i','[For most citizens, liberty means the freedom to practise their religious or political beliefs. \n 对大多数公民而言，自由意味着可以不受限制地信奉自己的宗教或政治信仰。 \n, Hundreds of political prisoners are to be given their liberty (= released from prison). \n 数百名政治犯将获得自由。 \n, Of the ten men who escaped this morning from Dartmoor Prison, only two are still at liberty (= free or not yet caught). \n 今晨从达特摩尔监狱逃跑的10人当中，目前只有两人依然在逃。 \n, I m not at liberty to reveal any names. \n 我无权透露任何人的名字。 \n, These laws will restrict our ancient rights and liberties. \n 这些法律将限制我们由来已久的权利和自由。 \n, What a liberty, to refuse the invitation on your behalf, without even asking you! \n 太放肆了，连问你都不问就以你的名义一口回绝了邀请！ \n, Some of the younger women complained that he d been taking liberties with them. \n 一些年轻一点的妇女抱怨说他对她们过分亲热。 \n]\n','2020-03-19',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukl/uklib/ukliber015.mp3'),('ligament','韧带','uk :ˈlɪɡ.ə.mənt, us :ˈlɪɡ.ə.mənt','[]\n','2020-02-19',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/j