lan Bennett wrote a series of monologues called  Talking Heads . \n 艾伦‧贝内特写了一系列名为《头脑独白》的独角戏。 \n]\n','2020-02-27',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukm/ukmon/ukmonk_017.mp3'),('monopoly','垄断（机构）；专卖；独占','uk :məˈnɒp.əl.i, us :məˈnɑː.pəl.i','[The government is determined to protect its tobacco monopoly. \n 政府下决心保护其烟草专卖权。 \n, Is Microsoft a monopoly? \n 微软是垄断企业吗？ \n, The drafting of a new constitution cannot be a monopoly of the white minority regime (= other people should do it too). \n 新宪法的起草不能由占人口少数的白人政权垄断。 \n, He does not have a/the monopoly on (= he is not the only one who has) good looks. \n 长得好看的不止他一个。 \n]\n','2020-03-24',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukm/ukmon/ukmonk_024.mp3'),('moonshine','非法酿制的酒，私酿酒胡言乱语；蠢话','uk :ˈmuːn.ʃaɪn, us :ˈmuːn.ʃaɪn','[]\n','2020-01-03',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukm/ukmoo/ukmooni006.mp3'),('moral','道德的有道德的，品行端正的道德；品行；道德规范道德教训；寓意','uk :ˈmɒr.əl, us :ˈmɔːr.əl','[It s her moral obligation to tell the police what she knows. \n 她把所知道的告诉警方是道义上的责任。 \n, It is not part of a novelist s job to make a moral judgment. \n 小说家并不需要作道德上的评判。 \n, She was the only politician to condemn the proposed law on moral grounds (= for moral reasons). \n 她是唯一一个从道义上对提议施行的法律进行谴责的政治家。 \n, The Democrats are attempting to capture the moral high ground (= are trying to appear more honest and good than the other political parties). \n 民主党试图显出在道义上占优势。 \n, She s a very moral woman. \n 她是个品行极为端正的女人。 \n, Oh, stop being so moral! \n 哦，别这么一本正经！ \n, Is TV responsible for weakening people s moral fibre (= ability to behave well and honestly and work hard)? \n 电视是否对人们的道德品质下降负有责任？ \n, public/private morals \n 公共／个人道德 \n, ld-fashioned disapproving \n a person of loose morals (= whose character or sexual behaviour is considered unacceptable) \n 放荡的人 \n, And the moral of the story is that honesty is always the best policy. 