y after the storm. \n 暴风雨过后，河水变成了褐色，浑浊不清。 \n, He became involved in the murky world of international drug-dealing. \n 他卷入了阴暗复杂的跨国贩毒生意中。 \n, I don t want to get into the murky waters of family arguments. \n 我不想趟家庭纠纷这道浑水。 \n]\n','2020-01-03',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukm/ukmun/ukmunif010.mp3'),('mustache','小胡子','uk :məˈstɑːʃ, us :ˈmʌs.tæʃ','[]\n','2020-01-10',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukm/ukmou/ukmourn008.mp3'),('mutation','（基因的）变异，突变（生物体的）变异，突变；突变生物体','uk :mjuːˈteɪ.ʃən, us :mjuːˈteɪ.ʃən','[It is well known that radiation can cause mutation. \n 众所周知，辐射可能造成基因突变。 \n, Environmental pressures encourage genes with certain mutations to persist and others to die out. \n 环境的影响使发生了某些突变的基因存活下来，另一些则消亡了。 \n, These plants carry the mutation for red flowers. \n 这些植物携带红花变种。 \n]\n','2020-03-06',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukm/ukmus/ukmusic019.mp3'),('mute','沉默的；（活动）无声的无法说话的；（人）哑的（乐器上的）弱音器静音按钮哑巴减轻（噪音）（给乐器）加弱音器','uk :mjuːt, us :mjuːt','[The president has remained mute about plans to curtail the number of immigrants. \n 总统对于减少外来移民人数的方案保持沉默。 \n, I gazed at her in mute admiration. \n 我默默地凝视着她，心生爱慕之情。 \n, a mute child \n 哑巴孩子 \n, He was playing his trumpet with a mute. \n 他正在吹装了弱音器的小号。 \n, I pressed the mute on my phone so she couldn t hear the people talking in the background. \n 我按下手机上的静音按钮，这样她就不会听到背景中别人的说话声了。 \n, He was watching TV with the mute button on. \n 他正在按了静音键看电视。 \n, Heavy curtains muted the noise of the traffic. \n 厚厚的窗帘减弱了交通噪声。 \n, The song features muted trumpets. \n 这首歌的伴奏中用上了装了弱音器的小号。 \n]\n','2019-12-24',0,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukm/ukmus/ukmusic020.mp3'),('mutual','相互的，彼此的；共同的，共有的互惠机构（由成员而不是持股人拥有的金融机构）','uk :ˈmjuː.tʃu.əl, us :ˈmjuː.tʃu.əl','[Theirs was a partnership based on mutual respect, trust and understanding. \n 他们的合作是建立在相互尊重、信任和理解的基础之上的。 \n, Both countries are acting to their mutual advantage. \n 两国的做法对彼此都有好处。 \n, The agreement was terminated by mutual consent. \n 经双方同意，这项协议被终止了。 \n]\n','2019-10-07',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukm/ukmut/ukmutto002.mp3'),('nail','钉，钉子指甲；趾甲用钉子钉，将…钉牢（尤指当场）抓获，逮住；证明…有罪，揭发','uk :neɪl, us :neɪl','[a three-inch nail \n 3英寸长的钉子 \n, I stepped on a nail sticking out of the floorboards. \n 我踩到了地板上凸出来的一颗钉子。 \n, Hammer a nail into the wall and we ll hang the mirror from it. \n 在墙上钉个钉子，我们要把镜子挂在上面。 \n, Stop biting your nails! \n 别再咬指甲了！ \n, nail clippers \n 指甲刀 \n, a nail file \n 指甲锉 \n, She had nailed a small shelf to the door. \n 她在门上钉了一个小架子。 \n, A notice had been nailed up on the wall. \n 墙上钉了一张通知。 \n, The lid of the box had been nailed down. \n 棺材盖被钉死了。 \n, The police had been trying to nail those guys for months. \n 数月来警方一直想抓住那帮家伙。 \n]\n','2020-01-03',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukm/ukmyt/ukmyth_020.mp3'),('narrator','（书或电影中的）叙述者，讲述者，旁白者','uk :nəˈreɪ.tər, us :ˈner.eɪ.t̬ɚ','[]\n','2020-02-28',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukn/uknar/uknark_006.mp3'),('nasty','糟糕的；令人不快的，让人讨厌的不友善的，恶意的危险的；狂暴的粗鲁的；冒犯的有种不祥的预感','uk :ˈnɑː.sti, us :ˈnæs.ti','[a nasty shock/surprise \n 极度的震惊／惊奇 \n, There s a nasty smell in here. \n 这里有股难闻的气味。 \n, He had a nasty cut above the eye. \n 他眼睛上方有一道严重的伤口。 \n, She has a nasty habit of picking on people in meetings. \n 她有一个在会上故意挑别人毛病的坏习惯。 \n, Don t be so nasty to your brother - he s four years younger than you! \n 别对你弟弟这么凶——他可比你小4岁！ \n, In an emergency you could get out through a window, but it would be a nasty drop. \n 遇上紧急情况，你可以从窗户跳出去，不过这样会有危险。 \n, The situation could turn (= become) nasty at any moment. \n 局势随时可能恶化。 \n, She said some really nasty things about him. \n 她说了一些恶意中伤他的话。 \n, I ve got a nasty feeling that I forgot to tell Joe I couldn t come. \n 我怀疑自己忘了告诉乔我不能来了。 \n]\n','2021-0