g a job. \n 他母亲总是数落他，让他去找份工作。 \n]\n','2020-02-19',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukn/ukneb/uknebbo030.mp3'),('negotiation','谈判，磋商，洽谈','uk :nəˌɡəʊ.ʃiˈeɪ.ʃən, us :nəˌɡoʊ.ʃiˈeɪ.ʃən','[The agreement was reached after a series of difficult negotiations. \n 该协议是在经历了一系列艰难的谈判之后达成的。 \n, The exact details of the agreement are still under negotiation. \n 协议的确切条款尚待磋商。 \n, Negotiation for the pay increase is likely to take several weeks. \n 加薪谈判可能要持续数周。 \n]\n','2019-10-08',0,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukn/ukneg/uknegot003.mp3'),('neon','氖，氖气','uk :ˈniː.ɒn, us :ˈniː.ɑːn','[a neon light/sign \n 霓虹灯／霓虹灯广告牌 \n]\n','2019-12-26',0,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukn/ukneg/uknegot023.mp3'),('neonate','不足四周的婴儿','uk :ˈniː.əʊ.neɪt, us :ˈniː.əˌneɪt','[We provide intensive care for seriously ill neonates. \n 我们为病情严重的新生儿提供重症特别护理。 \n]\n','2020-01-23',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/c/ces/cespu/cespuk000757.mp3'),('neuroinvasive','神经侵袭','null','null\n','2020-01-23',0,0,0,'null'),('nevertheless','不过，仍然；尽管如此','uk :ˌnev.ə.ðəˈles, us :ˌnev.ɚ.ðəˈles','[I knew a lot about the subject already, but her talk was interesting nevertheless. \n 关于这个话题我已经知之甚多，但她的报告听起来还是很有趣。 \n]\n','2020-02-21',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukn/ukneu/ukneuro018.mp3'),('nickel','镍（美国或加拿大的）5分镍币','uk :ˈnɪk.əl, us :ˈnɪk.əl','[a nickel alloy \n 镍合金 \n]\n','2021-03-26',4,6,1,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukn/uknic/ukniche003.mp3'),('nod','点头；（尤指）点头赞同，点头致意，点头示意点头','uk :nɒd, us :nɑːd','[Many people in the audience nodded in agreement. \n 许多听众点头表示赞同。 \n, When I suggested a walk, Elena nodded enthusiastically. \n 当我提议去散步时，埃琳娜使劲地点头。 \n, She looked up and nodded for me to come in. \n 她抬起头，点头示意让我进来。 \n, Chen gave her a nod of recognition across the crowded room. \n 陈从挤满人的房间的另一头向她点头致意。 \n]\n','2020-01-03',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukn/uknoc/uknoctu003.mp3'),('nonagon','九角形','uk :ˈnɒn.ə.ɡən, us :ˈnɑː.nə.ɡɑːn','[]\n','2020-01-10',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english/uk_pron/c/cdo/cdo03/cdo0318uknona0941.mp3'),('nonconformity','不合规','uk :ˌnɒn.kənˈfɔː.mə.ti, us :ˌnɑːn.kənˈfɔːr.mə.t̬i',NULL,'2021-03-08',7,9,1,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english/uk_pron/u/ukn/uknon/uknonag011.mp3'),('nosocomial','院内()染','/nɒsəˈkoʊmi.əl/','null\n','2020-01-23',0,0,0,'null'),('notable','显要的；显著的；值得注意的显要人物；名流','uk :ˈnəʊ.tə.bəl, us :ˈnoʊ.t̬ə.bəl','[a notable collection of rare plants \n 一批引人注目的奇花异草 \n, Getting both sides to agree was a notable achievement. \n 使双方达成共识是一项显著的成就。 \n, This attractive building is particularly notable for its woodland setting. \n 这幢漂亮的建筑因其树林背景而格外引人注目。 \n, Other notables among his pupils were the kings of Saudi Arabia and Thailand. \n 他的学生中，另外两位显要人物是沙特阿拉伯国王和泰国国王。 \n]\n','2020-03-25',3,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukn/uknos/uknosh_011.mp3'),('notion','观念；看法缝纫用品；缝纫用品店；缝纫用品部','uk :ˈnəʊ.ʃən, us :ˈnoʊ.ʃən','[[ + that ] \n The show\'s director rejects the notion that seeing violence on television has a harmful effect on children. \n 节目制片人们并不认为看到电视上的暴力场景会对孩子们造成不良影响。 \n, I have only a vague notion of what she does for a living. \n 我不太清楚她靠什么谋生。 \n]\n','2019-10-08',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukn/uknot/uknotif004.mp3'),('nought','（数字）0；零无（同 naught）','uk :nɔːt, us :nɑːt','[He said it was only worth £10, but really you could add a couple of noughts to that (= it is really worth £1,000). \n 他说这只值10英镑，但事实上你在后面加上两个零还差不多。 \n]\n','2020-04-03',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukn/uknat/uknativ018.mp3'),('novel','https://www.99lib.net/book/2126/62122.htm',NULL,NULL,'2021-03-08',0,1003,1,NULL),('nudge','（尤指用肘部）轻推，轻触接近（更高点或水平）轻推','uk :nʌdʒ, us :nʌdʒ','[The children were giggling and nudging each other. \n 孩子们咯咯地笑着，互相推来推去。 \n, He nudged the cat off the sofa so that he could sit down. \n 他把猫轻轻推下沙发，这样自己可以坐下来。 \n, Oil prices continue to nudge higher. \n 油价持续上涨。 \n, Peter must be nudging 40 now. \n 彼得现在肯定将近40岁了。 \n, I gave him a nudge to wake him up. \n 我轻轻推醒他。 \n]\n','2019-11-08',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukn/uknow/uknowac021.mp3'),('nuke','用核武器攻击用微波炉加热；用微波炉烹制核武器','uk :njuːk, us :nuːk','[The two countries were threatening to nuke each other. \n 两个国家都威胁要对对方使用核武器。 \n,  No nukes here!  the banner read. \n 横幅上写着“禁止在此使用核武器！” \n]\n','2019-12-19',0,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukn/uknow/uknowac028.mp3'),('numb','（身体部位）麻木的，失去感觉的（由于过度震惊或恐惧而）麻木的，思维迟钝的使麻木，使失去感觉','uk :nʌm, us :nʌm','[I was lying in a weird position and my leg went numb. \n 我躺卧的姿势很奇怪，结果腿都麻了。 \n, My fingers were numb with cold. \n 我的手指冻僵了。 \n, When she first heard the news, she was numb with disbelief. \n 她最初听到这条消息的时候，简直不敢相信自己的耳朵。 \n, Ever since his girlfriend left him he has felt numb. \n 自从女朋友离开他之后，他就变得麻木迟钝了。 \n, The extreme cold numbed her face and hands. \n 她的脸和手在严寒中冻得都麻木了。 \n, The children are still numbed by their father s death. \n 孩子们仍旧沉浸在父亲去世的打击中，麻木迟钝。 \n]\n','2020-01-20',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukn/uknow/uknowac030.mp3'),('numerous','许多的，大量的','uk :ˈnjuː.mə.rəs, us :ˈnuː.mə.rəs','[We have discussed these plans on numerous occasions. \n 我们已经多次讨论过这些计划。 \n, Retailers of this type, once rare, are now numerous. \n 这种商店从前很少见，但现在已经遍地开花。 \n]\n','2020-01-10',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukn/uknum/uknumbe013.mp3'),('nursery','幼儿园，托儿所（家中的）育儿室（尤指商业目的的）苗圃，育苗场幼儿教育的','uk :ˈnɜː.sər.i, us :ˈnɝː.sɚ.i','[Does Jake go to a nursery or a childminder? \n 杰克是去托儿所还是由家庭保育员照看？ \n, Do you think the state should provide free nursery education? \n 你认为国家应该提供免费幼儿教育吗？ \n]\n','2020-02-27',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukn/uknum/uknumbe020.mp3'),('oblivion','被遗忘，被忘却；湮没完全被毁灭；彻底被消灭无知觉，无意识；不省人事','uk :əˈblɪv.i.ən, us :əˈblɪv.i.ən','[He was another minor poet who was consigned to oblivion. \n 他又是一位湮没无闻的小诗人。 \n, These toys will be around for a year or two, then fade/slide/sink into oblivion. \n 这些玩具会风行一两年，然后渐渐被人遗忘。 \n, The planes bombed the city into oblivion. \n 飞机将该市炸成一片废墟。 \n, He sought oblivion in a bottle of whisky. \n 他试图用一瓶威士忌酒来忘却一切。 \n]\n','2019-11-19',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uko/ukobj/ukobjec020.mp3'),('obscene','猥亵的；淫秽的；下流的；粗俗的伤风败俗的；骇人听闻的；令人震惊的','uk :əbˈsiːn, us :əbˈsiːn','[In the raid, police found several boxes of obscene DVDs. \n 警方在这次突击搜查中发现了几箱淫秽光盘。 \n, He was jailed for making obscene phone calls (= ones in which unwanted sexual suggestions were made to the listener). \n 他因拨打色情骚扰电话而入狱。 \n, obscene language/graffiti \n 下流的语言／涂鸦 \n, to make obscene profits \n 大捞一笔 \n, The salaries some bankers earn are obscene. \n 有些银行高管的薪水高得令人咋舌。 \n, He eats obscene amounts of food. \n 他食量惊人。 \n]\n','2020-01-15',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uko/ukobj/ukobjec030.mp3'),('obscure','无名的；鲜为人知的；默默无闻的费解的，晦涩的；模糊的，朦胧的；不清楚的遮掩；遮蔽；使不分明隐藏，掩盖；使难理解，使晦涩','uk :əbˈskjʊər, us :əbˈskjʊr','[an obscure island in the Pacific \n 太平洋中的无名小岛 \n, an obscure 12th-century mystic \n 12世纪一位鲜为人知的神秘主义者 \n, Official policy has changed, for reasons that remain obscure. \n 官方的政策已改变，原因尚不清楚。 \n, His answers were obscure and confusing. \n 他的回答模糊不清，令人费解。 \n, Two new skyscrapers had sprung up, obscuring the view from her window. \n 两座新摩天大楼拔地而起，挡住了她窗外的风景。 \n, The sun was obscured by clouds. \n 太阳被云层遮住了。 \n, Managers deliberately obscured the real situation from federal investigators. \n 经理们故意对联邦调查人员掩盖真实情况。 \n]\n','2020-01-20',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uko/ukobs/ukobsce003.mp3'),('obsess','（使）着迷；（使）困扰；（使）牵挂；（使）萦回于心','uk :əbˈses, us :əbˈses','[The whole relationship obsessed me for years. \n 这一关系多年来一直困扰着我。 \n, She used to obsess about her weight. \n 她过去总是过分在意自己的体重。 \n]\n','2020-03-19',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uko/ukobs/ukobsce014.mp3'),('obsessive','着迷的；迷恋的；难以释怀的过分（到不正常程度）的强迫症患者','uk :əbˈses.ɪv, us :əbˈses.ɪv','[He s obsessive about punctuality. \n 他过分讲究准时。 \n, obsessive secrecy \n 过分的遮遮掩掩 \n, obsessional behaviour \n 痴迷的行为 \n]\n','2020-01-09',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uko/ukobs/ukobsce019.mp3'),('obsolete','废弃的；过时的；淘汰的；老化的','uk :ˌɒb.səlˈiːt, us :ˌɑːb.səlˈiːt','[Gas lamps became obsolete when electric lighting was invented. \n 电灯发明以后煤气灯就被淘汰了。 \n]\n','2020-03-25',2,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uko/ukobs/ukobsce024.mp3'),('obstacle','障碍；阻碍；妨碍','uk :ˈɒb.stə.kəl, us :ˈɑːb.stə.kəl','[The biggest obstacle in our way was a tree trunk in the road. \n 我们路上最大的障碍是横在路上的一棵树。 \n, This decision has removed the last obstacle to the hostages\' release. \n 这个决定清除了释放人质的最后障碍。 \n]\n','2019-10-08',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uko/ukobs/ukobsce025.mp3'),('obstruct','阻塞，堵塞，阻挡（道路、通道、入口等）阻碍；阻止，阻挠；妨碍','uk :əbˈstrʌkt, us :əbˈstrʌkt',NULL,'2021-03-08',6,8,1,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uko/ukobs/ukobsti004.mp3'),('occasional','偶尔的；不经常的','uk :əˈkeɪ.ʒən.əl, us :əˈkeɪ.ʒən.əl','[I play the occasional game of tennis. \n 我偶尔打打网球。 \n, He has the occasional cigar after dinner. \n 他饭后偶尔抽支雪茄。 \n]\n','2019-12-20',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uko/ukobs/ukobsti023.mp3'),('occupy','占有，占用，占据（空间或时间）使（某人）忙于；使（某人）感兴趣（军队或一伙人）占领，占据','uk :ˈɒk.jə.paɪ, us :ˈɑː.kjə.paɪ','[The rest of the time was occupied with writing a report. \n 剩下的时间用来写了份报告。 \n, The house hasn t been occupied (= lived in) by anyone for a few months. \n 这幢房子已经有几个月没人住了。 \n, ormal \n A large picture of the battle of Waterloo occupied the space above the fireplace. \n 一幅描绘滑铁卢战役的巨幅画作占据了壁炉上方的空间。 \n, On long journeys I occupy myself with solving maths puzzles. \n 长途旅行时，我用解数学难题来打发时间。 \n, Troops quickly occupied the city. \n 军队很快占领了城市。 \n, Protesting students occupied the university office for two weeks. \n 抗议的学生占领大学办公楼达两个星期。 \n, the occupying forces \n 占领军 \n]\n','2020-01-23',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uko/ukocc/ukoccup004.mp3'),('odour','（常指难闻的）气味；臭味','uk :ˈəʊ.dər, us :ˈoʊ.dɚ','[Inside the room there was the unmistakable odour of sweaty feet. \n 房间里有一股明显的臭脚汗味。 \n, igurative \n The odour of hypocrisy hung about everything she said. \n 她说的每句话都假惺惺的。 \n]\n','2020-04-03',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uko/ukodd/ukodd__014.mp3'),('offset','补偿；抵消；弥补支付具有减排作用的东西，以弥补之前的排放所造成的损害','uk :ˌɒfˈset, us :ˌɑːfˈset','[The extra cost of travelling to work is offset by the lower price of houses here. \n 这里低廉的房价抵消了因上班路途远而产生的额外费用。 \n, K \n He keeps his petrol receipts because petrol is one of the expenses that he can offset against tax (= can show to the government as being a business cost, and so not pay tax). \n 他保留着他的汽油费收据，因为汽油费是可以抵扣税款的一项开支。 \n, We offset all our long-haul flights. \n 我们补偿了之前长途运输机的排放所带来的损害。 \n]\n','2021-03-26',2,5,1,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uko/ukoff/ukoffen024.mp3'),('omen','预兆，征兆，兆头','uk :ˈəʊ.mən, us :ˈoʊ.mən','[The team s final victory of the season is a good omen for the playoffs, which start next week. \n 球队在本赛季最后一场比赛中获得胜利，这对下星期就开始的季后加赛来说是一个好兆头。 \n, a bad omen \n 坏兆头 \n, Many people believe that a broken mirror is an omen of bad luck. \n 许多人相信打碎镜子是噩运之兆。 \n]\n','2020-01-10',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uko/ukold/ukolden019.mp3'),('omniscience','','uk :ɒmˈnɪs.i.əns, us :ɑːmˈnɪʃ.əns','[ do not claim omniscience, nor am I incapable of making mistakes.\n, The biographer lacks the novelist\'s omniscience.\n]\n','2020-02-19',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english/uk_pron/u/uko/ukold/ukolden029.mp3'),('opinion','>意见，看法，主张>（一群人的）意见，看法；民意>看法，评价>专家意见；鉴定','uk :>əˈpɪn.jən, us :>əˈpɪn.jən',NULL,'2020-03-25',0,6,0,NULL),('optimal','（同 optimum）','uk :ˈɒp.tɪ.məl, us :ˈɑːp.tə.məl','[]\n','2020-01-09',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uko/ukopp/ukoppre011.mp3'),('ordain','授予（某人）圣职（上帝或权威人士）命令，下令','uk :ɔːˈdeɪn, us :ɔːrˈdeɪn','[He was ordained (as) a priest in Ely cathedral in 1987. \n 他于1987年在伊利大教堂被授予圣职。 \n, There is strong support here for the tough economic reforms ordained in the federal capital, Prague. \n 这里的人们坚决支持由联邦首都布拉格下令进行的强有力的经济改革。 \n, [ + that ] \n humorous \n I don t know who came up with the idea, but the city council has ordained that all the local libraries will close on Mondays. \n 我不知道这是谁的主意，但是市政会命令本地所有的图书馆每星期一一律闭馆。 \n]\n','2020-03-05',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uko/ukora/ukorang020.mp3'),('organism','生物体；有机体；微生物','uk :ˈɔː.ɡən.ɪ.zəm, us :ˈɔːr-','[Amoebae and bacteria are single-celled organisms. \n 变形虫和细菌是单细胞生物。 \n]\n','2020-03-13',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uko/ukord/ukordin007.mp3'),('ornament','装饰物，饰品装饰，摆设装饰，点缀','uk :ˈɔː.nə.mənt, us :ˈɔːr.nə.mənt','[a glass ornament \n 玻璃饰物 \n, garden ornaments such as statues and fountains \n 如雕像、喷泉等花园装饰物 \n, The building relies on clever design rather than on ornament for its impressive effect. \n 这幢大楼依靠其巧妙设计而非装饰给人留下了深刻的印象。 \n, She ornamented her letters with little drawings in the margin. \n 她在信的页边空白处画上小图案来作装饰。 \n]\n','2021-03-26',9,2,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uko/ukori/ukorigi005.mp3'),('orphan','孤儿使成为孤儿','uk :ˈɔː.fən, us :ˈɔːr.fən','[The civil war is making orphans of many children. \n 内战正在使许多孩子成为孤儿。 \n, He was orphaned as a baby (= his parents died when he was a baby). \n 他尚在襁褓中时就成了孤儿。 \n, The children were orphaned by the war (= their parents were killed in the war). \n 战争使这些孩子成为孤儿。 \n]\n','2020-02-27',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uko/ukori/ukorigi014.mp3'),('osteoarthritis','骨关节炎','uk :ˌɒs.ti.əʊ.ɑːˈθraɪ.tɪs, us :ˌɑː.sti.oʊ.ɑːrˈθraɪ.t̬əs','[]\n','2020-02-19',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uko/ukosc/ukoscil014.mp3'),('out-in-force','in','null','null\n','2019-10-09',0,1,0,'null'),('outcry','呐喊；大声疾呼；强烈抗议','uk :ˈaʊt.kraɪ, us :ˈaʊt.kraɪ','[The release from prison of two of the terrorists has provoked a public outcry. \n 释放两名恐怖分子激起了公众的强烈抗议。 \n]\n','2020-02-28',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uko/ukoug/ukough_024.mp3'),('outpost','前哨','Qiánshào','\n','2019-11-08',0,0,0,'https://translate.google.cn/translate_tts?ie=UTF-8&q=outpost &tl=ja&tk=945297.547045&client=webapp&prev=input'),('outrageous','骇人的；无耻的；无法接受的（因反常或怪异）吓人的，惊人的，令人震惊的','uk :ˌaʊtˈreɪ.dʒəs, us :ˌaʊtˈreɪ.dʒəs','[The judge criticized the  outrageous greed  of some of the bankers. \n 法官批评有些银行家“无耻贪婪”。 \n, [ + that ] \n It is outrageous that these buildings remain empty while thousands of people have no homes. \n 这些大楼空着，而成千上万的人却无家可归，这真是令人难以容忍。 \n, These prices are just outrageous (= much too high). \n 这些价格高得吓人。 \n, outrageous clothes/behaviour \n 奇装异服／怪异的举止 \n, an outrageous character \n 怪人 \n]\n','2020-03-06',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uko/ukout/ukoutle017.mp3'),('outstanding','优秀的；卓越的；出众的未支付的；未解决的；未完成的','uk :ˌaʊtˈstæn.dɪŋ, us :ˌaʊtˈstæn.dɪŋ','[an outstanding performance/writer/novel/year \n 杰出的表现／优秀的作家／出色的小说／不同凡响的一年 \n, It s an area of outstanding natural beauty. \n 这一地区自然风景极为优美。 \n, $450 million in outstanding debts \n 4.5亿美元的拖欠债款 \n, There are still a couple of problems outstanding. \n 还有几个问题没有解决。 \n]\n','2020-04-01',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uko/ukout/ukoutsh012.mp3'),('overhaul','彻底检修，大修；改造；改进','uk :ˈəʊ.və.hɔːl, us :ˈoʊ.vɚ.hɑːl','[I got the engine overhauled. \n 我彻底检修了发动机。 \n, The government has recently overhauled the healthcare system. \n 政府最近彻底改革了公共医疗保健服务。 \n]\n','2020-02-21',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uko/ukove/ukoverh001.mp3'),('overture','（尤指歌剧的）序曲，前奏曲主动表示，提议','uk :ˈəʊ.və.tjʊər, us :ˈoʊ.vɚ.tʃɚ','[the overture to  The Magic Flute  \n 《魔笛》序曲 \n, overtures of friendship. \n 友好的表示 \n, Neither side in the conflict seems willing to make peace overtures. \n 冲突双方似乎都不愿意主动向对方示好。 \n, nformal \n So he s been making overtures (= showing a sexual interest), has he? \n 那么说他一直在示爱，是吗？ \n]\n','2020-03-06',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uko/ukove/ukovers218.mp3'),('oxygen','氧，氧气','uk :ˈɒk.sɪ.dʒən, us :ˈɑːk.sɪ.dʒən','[]\n','2020-02-27',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uko/ukove/ukoverw026.mp3'),('pajama','（pyjama的美式拼写）','uk :pəˈdʒɑː.mə, us :pəˈdʒɑː.mə','[]\n','2020-03-06',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukput/ukputz_011.mp3'),('pale','（脸色或肤色）苍白的，白的暗淡的；浅的，淡的变苍白，失去血色','uk :peɪl, us :peɪl','[You re looking pale - are you feeling well? \n 你看上去脸色苍白——你病了吗？ \n, She has a naturally pale complexion and dark hair. \n 她天生肤色白皙，头发乌黑。 \n, She wore a pale blue hat. \n 她戴着一顶浅蓝色的帽子。 \n, pale winter sunlight \n 冬天惨淡的日光 \n, His face paled and he looked as if he might faint. \n 他脸色变得苍白，看上去像要晕倒一样。 \n]\n','2019-12-24',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukpad/ukpaddl025.mp3'),('palm','手掌，手心给（某人）看手相（算命）棕榈树（变戏法或偷窃时）把…藏在手心内','uk :pɑːm, us :pɑːm','[This tiny device fits into the palm of your hand. \n 这种微型装置可以放入你的掌心。 \n, date palms \n 枣椰树 \n, palm fronds \n 棕榈叶 \n, The island has long golden beaches fringed by palm trees. \n 这个小岛周围金色海滩绵延，环抱于绿色的棕榈中。 \n, I suspected that he had palmed a playing card. \n 我怀疑他把一张纸牌藏在了手心里。 \n]\n','2019-12-19',0,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukpal/ukpalef019.mp3'),('pandemic','（疾病）大规模流行的，广泛蔓延的大流行病','uk :pænˈdem.ɪk, us :pænˈdem.ɪk','[In some parts of the world malaria is still pandemic. \n 在世界上一些地区疟疾仍在大规模流行。 \n, a pandemic of influenza \n 流感大爆发 \n, an influenza pandemic \n 流感大爆发 \n]\n','2020-03-19',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukpam/ukpampe015.mp3'),('panel','（选定的）专家小组嵌板，镶板仪表板；操纵台嵌板，镶板','uk :ˈpæn.əl, us :ˈpæn.əl','[The competition will be judged by a panel of experts. \n 这次竞赛将由一个专家小组来评判。 \n, a beautiful old door with oak panels \n 一扇嵌有橡木板的漂亮的老式门 \n, White silk panels were inset into the sides of the dress. \n 衣边镶有白绸布。 \n, At the bottom of each page is a panel with grammatical information. \n 每页底部都有语法知识板块。 \n, a control/instrument panel \n 控制／仪表板 \n, The walls of the dining hall were panelled in oak. \n 餐厅的墙上嵌了橡木板。 \n, a panelled room/wall/door \n 有镶板的房间／墙／门 \n]\n','2020-03-04',2,4,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukpam/ukpampe018.mp3'),('parade','（庆祝）游行一队人；一系列事物接受检阅购物街用于路名中（庆祝）游行，列队行进夸示，炫耀','uk :pəˈreɪd, us :pəˈreɪd','[a victory parade \n 胜利游行 \n, For three hours a committee of state senators listened to a parade of local residents giving their opinions. \n 整整3个小时，州参议员组成的委员会听取了一批又一批当地居民发表自己的看法。 \n, The entire regiment was on parade. \n 整个军团在接受检阅。 \n, Park Parade \n 帕克大道 \n, The Saint Patrick s Day marchers paraded up Fifth Avenue, past the cathedral. \n 在圣帕特里克节那天，游行者一路经过第五大道，路过大教堂。 \n, In ancient Rome, captured generals were paraded through the streets in chains. \n 在古罗马，俘获的将军被带上枷锁游街示众。 \n, It s sickening the way he parades his wealth, his car, and his expensive clothes. \n 他炫耀他的财富、汽车和高档衣服的样子令人作呕。 \n, The children paraded about/around in their new clothes. \n 孩子们穿着新衣服四处炫耀。 \n]\n','2020-02-28',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukpap/ukpaper020.mp3'),('parasite','寄生生物；寄生动物；寄生植物靠他人为生者，寄生虫','uk :ˈpær.ə.saɪt, us :ˈper.ə.saɪt','[The older drugs didn t deal effectively with the malaria parasite. \n 以前的药物不能有效对付引起疟疾的寄生虫。 \n, Financial speculators are parasites on the national economy. \n 金融投机者是国民经济的寄生虫。 \n]\n','2020-01-17',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukpar/ukparag030.mp3'),('parlor','（提供某种服务或销售某种商品的）店堂，店铺（尤指旧时的）起居室，客厅，会客室','uk :ˈpɑː.lər, us :ˈpɑːr.lɚ','[a beauty parlour \n 美容院 \n, an ice-cream/pizza parlour \n 冷饮店／比萨屋 \n, the front parlour \n 前厅 \n, an Edwardian parlour \n 爱德华七世时代的客厅 \n]\n','2021-03-26',10,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukpar/ukparis016.mp3'),('parlour','（提供某种服务或销售某种商品的）店堂，店铺（尤指旧时的）起居室，客厅，会客室','uk :ˈpɑː.lər, us :ˈpɑːr.lɚ','[a beauty parlour \n 美容院 \n, an ice-cream/pizza parlour \n 冷饮店／比萨屋 \n, the front parlour \n 前厅 \n, an Edwardian parlour \n 爱德华七世时代的客厅 \n]\n','2019-10-08',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukpar/ukparis016.mp3'),('particle','小品词，语助词微粒，粒子极小量','uk :ˈpɑː.tɪ.kəl, us :ˈpɑːr.t̬ə.kəl','[In the sentence  I tidied up the room , the adverb  up  is a particle. \n 在句子 I tidied up the room 中，副词 up 是个小品词。 \n, Dust particles must have got into the motor. \n 发动机里一定是进灰了。 \n, Electrons are atomic particles. \n 电子是原子粒子。 \n, She wouldn t give me even the slightest particle of information about what she d been doing. \n 对于她所做的事情，她一丁点消息都不会透露给我。 \n]\n','2020-01-10',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukpar/ukparsi022.mp3'),('particularly','特别，尤其，异乎寻常地','uk :pəˈtɪk.jə.lə.li, us :pɚˈtɪk.jə.lɚ.li','[We\'re particularly interested to hear from people who speak two or more European languages. \n 我们特别希望能收到说两种或两种以上欧洲语言的人的来信。 \n, I didn\'t particularly want to go, but I had to. \n 我并不是特别想去，但我不得不去。 \n]\n','2019-10-09',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukpar/ukparsi026.mp3'),('partnerships','合伙关系，伙伴关系合伙企业，合股公司','uk :ˈpɑːt.nə.ʃɪp, us :ˈpɑːrt.nɚ.ʃɪp','[the John Lewis Partnership \n 约翰‧刘易斯合伙公司 \n]\n','2020-02-13',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukpar/ukparti006.mp3'),('passionate','情绪激昂的，热情的','uk :ˈpæʃ.ən.ət, us :ˈpæʃ.ən.ət','[a passionate speech \n 热情洋溢的演讲 \n, a passionate kiss/embrace \n 热烈的亲吻／拥抱 \n, The Italians are said to be the most passionate people in Europe. \n 据说意大利人是欧洲最富激情的民族。 \n, The child s mother made a passionate plea for help. \n 那孩子的母亲急切地向人们求助。 \n, Joe is passionate about baseball (= he likes it very much). \n 乔非常喜欢打棒球。 \n]\n','2020-02-21',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukpar/ukparti027.mp3'),('patent','专利权（见patent leather）申请专利显然的，显而易见的专利权','uk :ˈpeɪ.tənt, us :ˈpæt.ənt','[In 1880 Alexander Graham Bell was granted a patent on an apparatus for signalling and communicating called a Photophone. \n 亚历山大‧格雷厄姆‧贝尔发明了一个可用来发送和传输讯号，称为「光线电话」的装置，并于1880年获授了此装置的专利权。 \n, The company took out/filed a patent on a genetically engineered tomato. \n 该公司取得／申请了一项转基因西红柿的专利权。 \n, If you don t patent your invention, other people may make all the profit out of it. \n 如果你不为你的发明申请专利权，其他人就会从中渔利。 \n, a patent lie \n 昭然若揭的谎言 \n, a patent disregard of the law \n 对法律的公然漠视 \n,  No,  he replied, with patent distaste. \n “不，”他带着明显的厌恶回答道。 \n, a patent screwdriver \n 获专利的螺丝刀 \n]\n','2020-03-24',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukpat/ukpatch009.mp3'),('pathogen','病原体','uk :ˈpæθ.ə.dʒən, us :ˈpæθ.ə.dʒən','[a dangerous pathogen \n 一种危险的病原体 \n]\n','2020-01-23',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukpat/ukpatch023.mp3'),('patriot','爱国者','uk :ˈpæt.ri.ət, us :ˈpeɪ.tri.ɑːt',NULL,'2021-03-08',4,9,1,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukpat/ukpatie016.mp3'),('pattern','方式，形式；模式图案，花样范本，典范；榜样图样，底样样品，样本','uk :ˈpæt.ən, us :ˈpæt̬.ɚn','[The pattern of family life has been changing over recent years. \n 近年来家庭生活的模式一直在变化。 \n, A pattern is beginning to emerge from our analysis of the accident data. \n 我们对事故数据进行分析后发现一种模式开始显现出来。 \n, In this type of mental illness, the usual pattern is bouts of depression alternating with elation. \n 这种精神病通常的发病症状是时而萎靡不振，时而兴高采烈。 \n, Many behaviour(al) patterns have been identified in the chimp colony. \n 黑猩猩群体中的许多行为模式已被识别。 \n, Look, the frost has made a beautiful pattern on the window. \n 看啊，霜在窗户上形成了美丽的图案。 \n, The curtains had a floral pattern. \n 窗帘上有花的图案。 \n, The design is so good it s sure to set the pattern for many others. \n 这个设计太好了，一定会成为许多其他设计的样板。 \n, a knitting pattern \n 编织图样 \n, a dress pattern \n 服装底样 \n, Cut out all of the pieces from the paper pattern and pin them on the cloth. \n 剪下服装纸样上的每一片，把它们别在布上。 \n, a pattern book \n 样书 \n]\n','2020-02-13',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukpat/ukpatie028.mp3'),('pearl','珍珠珍珠首饰人造珍珠液态珠状物珠灰色，银白色珍珠母（同 mother-of-pearl）','uk :pɜːl, us :pɝːl','[a string of pearls \n 一串珍珠 \n, a pearl necklace \n 珍珠项链 \n, He gave her pearls for her birthday. \n 他送给她珍珠首饰作为生日礼物。 \n, cultured pearls \n 养殖的珍珠 \n, There were pearls of dew on the grass. \n 草地上有点点露珠。 \n, pearl buttons \n 珍珠母纽扣 \n]\n','2019-12-26',0,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukpay/ukpayro030.mp3'),('peculiarly','奇怪地，古怪地非常；特别，尤其','uk :pɪˈkjuː.li.ə.li, us :pɪˈkjuːl.jɚ.ə.li','[He looked at me most peculiarly. \n 他很怪异地看着我。 \n, The streets were peculiarly quiet for the time of day. \n 白天这个时候街道上异常安静。 \n, It s peculiarly painful where I burned my hand. \n 我手上烧伤的地方很疼。 \n, She s a peculiarly attractive woman. \n 她是个非常有魅力的女人。 \n]\n','2020-04-01',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukpea/ukpearl024.mp3'),('peer','仔细看，端详；费力地看同龄人；同辈；同等社会地位（或能力）的人贵族','uk :pɪər, us :pɪr','[When no one answered the door, she peered through the window to see if anyone was there. \n 没有人开门，她就费力地透过窗户朝里望去，看是否有人在。 \n, The driver was peering into the distance trying to read the road sign. \n 司机费力地看着远方，想要看清路标。 \n, Do you think it s true that teenage girls are less self-confident than their male peers? \n 你是否认为十几岁的女孩子不如同年龄的男孩子自信？ \n, He wasn t a great scholar, but as a teacher he had few peers (= not as many people had the same ability as him). \n 他算不上伟大的学者，但作为教师没有几个人能与他相提并论。 \n, a hereditary peer \n 世袭贵族 \n, a Conservative peer \n 保守党推荐任命的上议院议员 \n]\n','2020-03-06',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukped/ukpedal024.mp3'),('penitence','忏悔苦行','uk :ˈpen.ɪ.təns, us :ˈpen.ə.təns','[e expressed penitence for what he had done.\n, She cried tears of penitence.\n, e expressed his penitence for what he had done.\n]\n','2020-01-10',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukpen/ukpenet008.mp3'),('pension','养老金；退休金；抚恤金','uk :ˈpen.ʃən, us :ˈpen.ʃən','[S \n a government pension \n 政府养老金 \n, K \n a state pension. \n 政府养老金 \n, He won\'t be able to draw (= receive) his pension until he\'s 65. \n 他得等到65岁以后才能领取养老金。 \n]\n','2019-10-03',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukpen/ukpenet022.mp3'),('pentagon','五边形，五角形美国五角大楼，美国国防部','uk :ˈpen.tə.ɡən, us :-t̬ə.ɡɑːn','[The Pentagon is aiming to cut US forces by over 25 percent in the next five years. \n 美国国防部计划在接下来的五年内裁军25%以上。 \n]\n','2020-01-10',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukpen/ukpenet027.mp3'),('perception','认识，观念，看法感觉，知觉；感知感知能力；认识能力；洞察力','uk :pəˈsep.ʃən, us :pɚ-','[We have to change the public s perception that money is being wasted. \n 公众认为是在浪费钱，我们必须改变他们的这种看法。 \n, These photographs will affect people s perceptions of war. \n 这些照片会影响人们对战争的看法。 \n, Drugs can alter your perception of reality. \n 毒品会改变你对现实的感知。 \n, She has extraordinary powers of perception for one so young. \n 她年纪轻轻就有着非凡的洞察力。 \n, He s not known for his perception. \n 他的洞察力并不怎么样。 \n]\n','2020-01-09',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukpen/ukpente025.mp3'),('perch','坐在…（的边缘）上；栖息于；停留于（使）位于高处（或…的边缘）；（使）栖息在高处（或…的边缘）河鲈（鸟的）栖息处（尤指鸟笼里的细杆）（常指能很好地俯视低处的）高座，高处','uk :pɜːtʃ, us :pɝːtʃ','[We perched on bar stools and had a beer. \n 我们坐在酒吧高凳上，喝了一杯啤酒。 \n, A blackbird was perching on the gate. \n 一只乌鸫停落在大门上。 \n, The village is perched on top of a high hill. \n 村子坐落在一个高山顶上。 \n, We watched the parade from our perch on the scaffolding. \n 我们从脚手架的高处观看游行。 \n]\n','2020-01-10',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukpen/ukpente029.mp3'),('perchance','偶然，碰巧；可能，也许','uk :pəˈtʃɑːns, us :pɚˈtʃæns','[Do you know her, perchance? \n 你是否碰巧认识她？ \n]\n','2020-03-18',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukpen/ukpente030.mp3'),('peril','巨大的危险；险情，险境自冒风险做…','uk :ˈper.əl, us :ˈper.əl','[I never felt that my life was in peril. \n 我从未意识到我的生命受到了严重的威胁。 \n, The journey through the mountains was fraught with peril (= full of dangers). \n 穿越山岭的旅途充满了危险。 \n, Teenagers must be warned about the perils of unsafe sex. \n 必须告诫青少年不安全性行为存在重大危险。 \n, We underestimate the destructiveness of war at our peril. \n 我们低估了战争的破坏性，这对我们是很危险的。 \n]\n','2021-03-08',8,10,1,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukper/ukperfu006.mp3'),('permanently','总是；持久地；永久地','uk :ˈpɜː.mə.nənt.li, us :ˈpɝː.mə.nənt.li','[Smoking is likely to damage your health permanently. \n 吸烟可能会永久性地损害你的健康。 \n, Michael and his family have settled permanently in the States. \n 迈克尔和他的家人在美国永久定居下来。 \n, I seem to be permanently broke. \n 我似乎永远一贫如洗。 \n]\n','2020-01-10',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukper/ukperki009.mp3'),('perpetrate','犯（罪）；施（暴）；干（坏事）','uk :ˈpɜː.pə.treɪt, us :ˈpɝː.pə.treɪt','[In this country, half of all violent crime is perpetrated by people who have been drinking alcohol. \n 在这个国家，一半的暴行是酗酒者犯下的。 \n, Federal soldiers have been accused of perpetrating atrocities against innocent people. \n 联邦士兵被控对无辜民众犯下暴行。 \n]\n','2020-01-09',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukper/ukperki026.mp3'),('perpetual','永久的，永恒的；长期的不断重复的；永无休止的','uk :pəˈpetʃ.u.əl, us :pɚˈpetʃ.u.əl','[They lived in perpetual fear of being discovered. \n 他们长期生活在恐惧中，担心被发现。 \n, He has hard, cold eyes and his mouth is set in a perpetual sneer. \n 他双眼又凶又冷，嘴角总是挂着一丝蔑笑。 \n, a perpetual student \n 终生学习者 \n, perpetual vandalism \n 对公共财物不断的蓄意破坏 \n]\n','2019-10-07',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukper/ukperki029.mp3'),('persist','持续；存留坚持不懈；执意','uk :pəˈsɪst, us :pɚˈsɪst','[If the pain persists, consult a doctor. \n 如果疼痛持续就去看医生。 \n, The cold weather is set to persist throughout the week. \n 寒冷天气很可能将持续整个星期。 \n, If he persists in asking awkward questions, then send him to the boss. \n 如果他没完没了地问令人尴尬的问题，就把他打发到老板那里去。 \n, The government is persisting with its ambitious public works programme. \n 政府在坚持实施其雄心勃勃的市政工程规划。 \n]\n','2020-01-21',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukper/ukperpe018.mp3'),('persistence','持续存在；坚持不懈，执意','uk :pəˈsɪs.təns, us :pɚˈsɪs.təns','[Most financial analysts have been surprised by the persistence of the recession. \n 大多数金融分析家都对这种持续的衰退表示惊讶。 \n, Her persistence and enthusiasm have helped the group to achieve its international success. \n 她的坚持不懈和极大热情帮助该集团在国际上获得了成功。 \n]\n','2020-02-20',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukper/ukperpe019.mp3'),('persistent','持续的；存留的；顽强存在的坚持不懈的；执意的','uk :pəˈsɪs.tənt, us :pɚˈsɪs.tənt','[a persistent smell/skin rash \n 持续不散的气味／顽固的皮疹 \n, Symptoms of the illness include a high temperature and a persistent dry cough. \n 病症包括高烧和持久的干咳。 \n, There have been persistent rumours that the principal might take early retirement. \n 不断有谣言说校长可能会提前退休。 \n, Be persistent - don t give up. \n 要坚持不懈——别放弃。 \n, He has been a persistent critic of the president. \n 他一贯对总统持批评态度。 \n, She is a persistent offender and has been arrested five times this year for shoplifting. \n 她是个惯犯，今年已5次因在商店行窃被捕。 \n]\n','2020-01-23',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukper/ukperpe020.mp3'),('perspective','（思考问题的）角度，观点，想法恰当地估计；合理地评价；正确地看待客观地比较；客观地审查透视（画）法透视比例正确的；有透视效果的透视尺度失真的；比例（或位置）不当的','uk :pəˈspek.tɪv, us :pɚˈspek.tɪv','[Her attitude lends a fresh perspective to the subject. \n 她的态度为这一问题提供了新的视角。 \n, He writes from a Marxist perspective. \n 他从一个马克思主义者的视角进行写作。 \n, Because of its geographical position, Germany s perspective on the situation in Russia is very different from Washington s. \n 由于地理位置不同，德国对俄罗斯局势的看法与华盛顿大相径庭。 \n, You must keep things in perspective - the overall situation isn t really that bad. \n 你必须正确看待问题——总体局势还没那么糟糕。 \n, Total investments for this year reached $53 million, and, to put this into perspective, investments this year were double those made in 2013. \n 今年的总投资额达到5300万美元，客观地来看，这是2013年的两倍。 \n, In 15th-century Italy, artists rediscovered the rules of perspective. \n 在15世纪的意大利，艺术家们重新发现了透视规则。 \n]\n','2020-02-28',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukper/ukperso009.mp3'),('pervert','侵害；歪曲；使走上邪路，使变坏妨碍司法公正，枉法性行为反常者，性变态者','uk :pəˈvɜːt, us :pɚˈvɝːt','[Her ideas have been shamelessly perverted to serve the president s propaganda campaign. \n 为了配合总统的宣传活动，她的想法被无耻地曲解了。 \n, The history teacher tried to pervert (= persuade into unacceptable sexual activity) the boys by showing them pornographic magazines. \n 这名历史教师给男学生们看色情杂志，想引他们走上邪路。 \n, The two police officers were charged with perverting the course of justice by fabricating evidence in the trial. \n 两名警官因在审判中伪造证据被控妨碍司法公正。 \n]\n','2020-03-25',3,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukper/ukperv_011.mp3'),('pestilence','瘟疫，疫病毒瘤，日益严重的问题','uk :ˈpes.tɪ.ləns, us :ˈpes.təl.əns','[The report states that vandalism is a pestilence that must be stamped out. \n 该报告说明，恶意破坏行为是一种毒瘤，必须铲除。 \n]\n','2020-01-20',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukper/ukperv_023.mp3'),('petition','请愿书（向法院递交的）上诉书，诉状（向法院）递交上诉书，上诉','uk :pəˈtɪʃ.ən, us :pəˈtɪʃ.ən','[I signed a petition against the proposed closure of the local hospital today. \n 今天我在反对关闭当地医院的请愿书上签了名。 \n, She s filing a petition for divorce. \n 她将要递交离婚诉状。 \n, They re petitioning for/about better facilities for disabled people. \n 他们正在请愿，希望当局能为残疾人安装更好的设施。 \n, [ + obj + to infinitive ] \n I think we should petition the government to increase the grant for the project. \n 我认为我们应该请求政府增加对该项目的拨款。 \n, She is petitioning for a re-trial. \n 她将上诉要求重审。 \n]\n','2019-12-19',0,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukpet/ukpeter006.mp3'),('phase-out','停用','null','null\n','2019-10-08',1,0,0,'null'),('philosophical','哲学的；研究哲学的豁达的，达观的；泰然自若的','uk :ˌfɪl.əˈsɒf.ɪ.kəl, us :ˌfɪl.əˈsɑː.fɪ.kəl','[philosophical writings/essays \n 哲学著作／论文 \n]\n','2020-02-28',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukphe/ukpheno020.mp3'),('phony','虚伪的；假冒的，伪造的','uk :ˈfəʊ.ni, us :ˈfoʊ.ni','[All salespeople seem to have the same phoney smile. \n 所有推销员的微笑似乎都一样，假惺惺的。 \n, He gave the police a phoney address. \n 他给了警察一个假地址。 \n]\n','2019-12-11',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukpho/ukphone004.mp3'),('phrase','短语说法；用语；警句乐句；乐节用…方式表达，以…措词表达','uk :freɪz, us :freɪz','[We are governed, in Lord Hailsham s famous phrase, by an  elective dictatorship . \n 套用一下黑尔什姆勋爵的名言，我们被“选举出来的独裁者”统治着。 \n, The declaration was carefully/cleverly/tactfully, etc. phrased. \n 宣言措词谨慎／巧妙／圆滑等。 \n]\n','2019-12-19',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukpho/ukphoto010.mp3'),('physicist','物理学家','uk :ˈfɪz.ɪ.sɪst, us :ˈfɪz.ɪ.sɪst',NULL,'2021-03-26',3,4,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukpho/ukphoto018.mp3'),('pick','挑选；选择挑挑拣拣；精挑细选从…上剔除，从…摘下（从植物或树上）采，摘弹拨，弹奏（吉他等弦乐器）挑选；选择可以挑选；任意挑选挑选，选择镐；鹤嘴锄（同 pickaxe）牙签（弹弦乐器用的）拨子，琴拨','uk :pɪk, us :pɪk','[Pick a card from the pack. \n 从这纸牌中挑出一张。 \n, One of my sisters has been picked for the Olympic team. \n 我的一个姐姐入选了奥运代表队。 \n, [ + obj + to infinitive ] \n She was picked to play for the team. \n 她被选中代表该队参赛。 \n, The police asked him if he could pick (out) the killer from a series of photos. \n 警察问他能否从一组照片中认出凶手。 \n, The fairest way to decide the winner is to pick a name out of a hat/at random (= without looking or choosing). \n 决出优胜者最公平的办法是任意／随机选取一个名字。 \n, They picked their way (= carefully chose a route) down the broken steps. \n 他们小心翼翼地走下断裂的台阶。 \n, He s brilliant at picking winners (= choosing what will be successful). \n 他在判断谁能获胜方面很有眼力。 \n, The richest universities can pick and choose which students they take. \n 最有钱的大学可以对生源精挑细选。 \n, I picked a piece of fluff off my shiny black suit. \n 我从闪闪发亮的黑色套装上拽掉一根绒毛。 \n, The child continued picking (at) a sore on his leg (= trying to remove parts of it with his fingers). \n 那个孩子不停地抓挠他腿上的疮。 \n, [ + obj + adj ] \n The carcass had been picked clean (= all the flesh had been removed) by other animals and birds. \n 动物尸体上的肉已被别的动物和鸟吃得干干净净。 \n, isapproving \n He kept picking his nose (= removing mucus from it with his finger). \n 他在不停地掏鼻孔。 \n, They were picking strawberries for twelve hours a day. \n 他们每天摘12小时的草莓。 \n, I picked some roses this morning. \n 今天早上我摘了一些玫瑰。 \n, Machines pick the fruit (from/off the trees). \n 机器把果子（从树上）摘下来。 \n, You can have first pick of the desserts. \n 你可以头一个挑选甜点。 \n, The plane was fairly empty so we had our pick of seats. \n 飞机很空，所以我们可以自由选择座位。 \n, The shirts come in five different colours - just take your pick. \n 这种衬衣有5种不同的颜色——你随便挑吧。 \n, picks and shovels \n 镐和铲 \n, a toothpick \n 牙签 \n]\n','2020-01-09',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukpia/ukpiano004.mp3'),('picket','（罢工时阻止其他工人上班的）纠察队员；纠察队罢工纠察时期','uk :ˈpɪk.ɪt, us :ˈpɪk.ɪt','[There were pickets outside the factory gates. \n 工厂门外有一些纠察队员。 \n, The union organized a month-long picket. \n 工会组织了长达一个月的罢工纠察。 \n]\n','2020-02-27',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukpia/ukpiano012.mp3'),('picket-line','示威抗议','','null\n','2020-02-27',0,0,0,'null'),('pickle','腌菜，泡菜；菜酱醋渍黄瓜（片）；腌黄瓜（片）（用醋或盐水）腌制，腌渍','uk :ˈpɪk.əl, us :ˈpɪk.əl','[cheese and pickle sandwiches \n 奶酪和腌菜三明治 \n, Have some pickles with your sandwich. \n 在色拉里加些泡菜。 \n, a sweet/sour pickle \n 甜／酸黄瓜 \n, The onions had been pickled in brine. \n 洋葱已经在卤水中腌过了。 \n]\n','2021-03-26',7,4,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukpia/ukpiano016.mp3'),('picturesque','（尤指某地）美丽的，古色古香的','uk :ˌpɪk.tʃərˈesk, us :ˌpɪk.tʃərˈesk','[the picturesque narrow streets of the old city \n 古城里如画的狭窄街道 \n]\n','2020-02-28',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukpia/ukpiano030.mp3'),('pierce','刺穿，刺透，刺破（光、声音等）透入，进入','uk :pɪəs, us :pɪrs','[The needle pierces the fabric four times a second. \n 针穿过织物的速度是每秒钟4次。 \n, I couldn t wear these earrings because my ears aren t pierced. \n 我没法戴这些耳环，因为我没有穿耳孔。 \n, The gun fires a shell capable of piercing the armour of an enemy tank. \n 这种炮发射的炮弹能穿透敌人坦克的装甲。 \n, The hole they drilled pierces six kilometres into the earth s crust. \n 他们钻的孔深入地壳6公里。 \n, A few rays of sunlight pierced the smoke. \n 几缕阳光穿透了烟幕。 \n]\n','2020-01-10',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukpic/ukpictu012.mp3'),('pile','摞；垛；堆一堆一大堆，许多（建筑物的）柱，桩（地毯或天鹅绒等布料的）绒面高大建筑物，大厦痔，痔疮把…堆积（或堆叠）起来（人群）拥，挤，蜂拥','uk :paɪl, us :paɪl','[a pile of books \n 一摞书 \n, a pile of dirty clothes \n 一大堆脏衣服 \n, a large pile of sand \n 一大堆沙子 \n, I ve got piles/a pile of things to do today. \n 我今天有一大堆事情要做。 \n, a luxurious deep-pile carpet \n 豪华的长毛地毯 \n, They ve got a great big Victorian pile somewhere out in the country. \n 他们在乡下的某个地方有一座雄伟的维多利亚式的房子。 \n, We piled plenty of logs up next to the fire. \n 我们在炉火旁堆了很多木柴。 \n, Please pile your homework books neatly on the table as you leave. \n 离开时请把你们的作业本整齐地叠放在桌子上。 \n, Her plate was piled (high) with salad. \n 她的盘子里盛满了色拉。 \n, Snow had piled up against the walls. \n 雪在墙根堆积起来。 \n, As soon as the train stopped, they all piled in/out. \n 火车刚停下，他们就挤了进去／出来。 \n]\n','2020-01-03',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukpig/ukpigmy016.mp3'),('pillage','（尤指在战争中）掠夺，抢劫，劫掠','uk :ˈpɪl.ɪdʒ, us :ˈpɪl.ɪdʒ','[Works of art were pillaged from many countries in the dark days of the Empire. \n 在该帝国一手遮天的黑暗时期，许多国家的艺术品被肆意掠夺。 \n]\n','2020-01-14',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukpig/ukpigmy022.mp3'),('pillow','枕头坐垫；靠垫（同 cushion）','uk :ˈpɪl.əʊ, us :ˈpɪl.oʊ','[Do you prefer a feather pillow or a foam pillow? \n 你喜欢羽绒枕头还是海绵枕头？ \n]\n','2019-12-26',0,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukpig/ukpigmy028.mp3'),('pimp','拉皮条的男子；妓院男老板拉皮条（通常通过加上些东西）把…变得时髦（或好看）','uk :pɪmp, us :pɪmp','[He spent most of his adult life pimping. \n 成年之后他大部分时间都在拉皮条。 \n, They pimped the girls to a range of clients in the area. \n 他们把女孩们介绍给这一地区的许多召妓者。 \n, He had pimped his truck with new lights and chrome accessories. \n 他装了新的灯和一些镀铬附件，把他的卡车弄得好看了。 \n]\n','2020-03-05',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukpil/ukpilot005.mp3'),('pinch','捏，拧，掐，夹拧自己一下（表示某事太好或太奇怪，简直令人难以置信）偷窃（一）撮；少量捏，拧，掐，夹','uk :pɪntʃ, us :pɪntʃ','[Ouch! Stop pinching (me)! \n 哎哟，别掐我！ \n, These shoes are too tight, they pinch (my feet). \n 这双鞋太紧了，夹我的脚。 \n, I can t believe that he s back from Canada and he s mine - I keep having to pinch myself to make sure I m not dreaming. \n 我不敢相信他从加拿大回来了，而且他属于我——我不停地拧自己以确信我不是在做梦。 \n, Right, who s pinched my chair? \n 好嘛，谁把我的椅子偷走了？ \n, While the tomatoes are cooking add a pinch of salt/sugar/dried thyme. \n 烧西红柿时加一小撮盐／糖／干百里香。 \n, igurative \n Opinion polls on subjects like this should be taken with a pinch of scepticism. \n 对这种话题的民意测验应持半信半疑的态度。 \n, She gave Emma a painful pinch on the arm. \n 她在埃玛的胳膊上狠狠地掐了一下。 \n]\n','2020-02-19',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukpil/ukpilot015.mp3'),('pinky','小指','uk :ˈpɪŋ.ki, us :ˈpɪŋ.ki','[a pinkie ring \n 小指戒指 \n]\n','2020-03-18',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukpil/ukpilot028.mp3'),('pinnacle','极点；顶点，顶峰（建筑物的）尖顶，小尖塔；山顶','uk :ˈpɪn.ə.kəl, us :ˈpɪn.ə.kəl','[By the age of 32 she had reached the pinnacle of her career. \n 她在32岁时事业达到顶峰。 \n, iterary \n The pinnacles of the Himalayas were visible above the clouds. \n 喜马拉雅山的山顶显现在云端之上。 \n]\n','2020-03-12',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukpin/ukpinkn006.mp3'),('pipe','管；管子；管道烟斗笛（子）；管乐器（bagpipes 的另一种说法）（管风琴的）音管计算机键盘上的“|”键用尖嗓子说；尖声唱管道运输','uk :paɪp, us :paɪp','[a water/gas/sewer pipe \n 供水／煤气／下水管道 \n, a burst/fractured/leaking pipe \n 爆裂／破裂／泄漏的管道 \n, I ordered some tea for myself and lit my pipe. \n 我叫了茶，点着了烟斗。 \n, Hot water is piped to all apartments from the central boiler room. \n 热水从中央锅炉房通过管道输送到每个公寓套房。 \n, igurative \n Music is piped throughout the hotel complex. \n 音乐声在整座酒店大楼里回荡。 \n]\n','2019-12-24',0,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukpin/ukpinkn023.mp3'),('pique','（尤指因自尊心受损而产生的）不悦，生气','uk :piːk, us :piːk','[He stormed from the room in a fit of pique, shouting that he had been misunderstood. \n 他怒气冲冲地冲出房间，嚷嚷着说他被误解了。 \n]\n','2020-01-09',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukpay/ukpayro024.mp3'),('pit','坑；麻子，痘瘢矿道，矿井异常凌乱的地方；肮脏的地方剧院的正厅后座；乐池质量极为低劣之物赛车场检修加油站果核果核（stone的美式说法）','uk :pɪt, us :pɪt','[They d dug a shallow pit and left the bodies in it. \n 他们挖了一个浅坑把尸体扔在里面。 \n, These pits in my skin are from when I had chickenpox. \n 我皮肤上的痘瘢是我出水痘时留下的。 \n, The coal-mining industry wants new pits to be opened. \n 煤矿业需要开凿新的矿井。 \n, a gravel/chalk pit \n 砾石／白垩坑 \n, I m afraid my room is a complete pit! \n 恐怕我的房间乱得一塌糊涂！ \n, The hotel we stayed in was the pits! \n 我们住的宾馆实在太糟糕了！ \n, Peaches, plums, and olives all contain pits. \n 桃子、李子和橄榄都有果核。 \n]\n','2020-02-21',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukpiq/ukpiqua023.mp3'),('pitch','运动场地；（尤指）足球场水平；程度（感觉的）程度推销用语；推销摊位（尤指屋顶的）坡度沥青，柏油投球宿营地（使）突然移动；（尤指）投，扔投（球）支，搭（帐篷）调校至某一水平竭力劝说倾斜','uk :pɪtʃ, us :pɪtʃ','[a football/hockey/cricket pitch \n 足球／曲棍球／板球赛场 \n, Supporters invaded (= ran onto) the pitch. \n 球迷们跑进了球场。 \n, The piano and organ were tuned to the same pitch (= note). \n 钢琴和风琴被定在同一音调上。 \n, If you teach children and adults in the same class, it s difficult to get the pitch (= level of difficulty or interest) right. \n 如果你把孩子和成人放在同一个班级里教，就很难完全找出适合学生的难度和他们的兴趣。 \n, By this time their disagreement had reached such a pitch that there was no hope of an amicable conclusion. \n 此时，他们的分歧已如此之大，不可能善罢罢休。 \n, The children were at fever pitch (= very excited) the day before the party. \n 派对的前一天孩子们特别兴奋。 \n, The man in the shop gave me his (sales) pitch about quality and reliability. \n 商店里的那个男人对我大谈质量上乘信誉可靠之类的推销行话。 \n, She made a pitch for the job but she didn t get it. \n 她竭力争取这份工作，但却未得到。 \n, [ + to infinitive ] \n The city made a pitch to stage the Olympics. \n 该市竭力争取主办奥运会。 \n, The flower seller was at his usual pitch outside the station. \n 那个卖花人在车站外他平时的摊位上。 \n, This roof has a very steep/high/gentle/low pitch. \n 这屋顶坡度很陡／大／平缓／小。 \n, a good/bad pitch \n 质量好／差的投球 \n, We chose a large level grassy pitch for our caravan. \n 我们选了一大片平坦的草地停放我们的旅行拖车。 \n, She pitched the stone into the river. \n 她把石头扔到河里。 \n, The ball pitched (= landed) short. \n 球投到了不远处。 \n, The bike hit a rut and I was pitched (forward) onto the road. \n 自行车卡进车辙，我重重地（向前）摔在路上。 \n, The ship pitched up and down/from side to side in the rough seas. \n 船在汹涌的海浪里上下／左右颠簸。 \n, Who will be pitching first for the White Sox this evening? \n 今晚谁是白短袜队第一个投球的？ \n, We pitched camp/our tent in the shade. \n 我们在阴凉处安营／搭起帐篷。 \n, The tune was pitched (= the notes in it were) too high for me to reach the top notes. \n 调定得太高，高音处我唱不上去。 \n, A teacher s got to pitch a lesson at the right level for the students. \n 老师必须把课的难易程度定得与学生的水平相符。 \n, She pitched her idea to me over a business lunch. \n 她在一次吃工作午餐时竭力向我游说她的想法。 \n, They are pitching for business at the moment. \n 他们正在招揽生意。 \n]\n','2020-02-28',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukpiq/ukpiqua024.mp3'),('plank','木板；板条（尤指政治组织的）政纲条目，政策准则','uk :plæŋk, us :plæŋk','[oak/concrete planks \n 橡木／水泥板 \n, a plank of wood \n 一块木板条 \n, We used a plank to cross the ditch. \n 我们用一块跳板过了沟。 \n, Educational reform was one of the main planks of their election campaign. \n 教育改革是他们竞选活动的主要纲领之一。 \n, The party s policy is based on five central planks. \n 该党的政策基于5条中心政治纲领。 \n]\n','2020-01-03',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukpla/ukplain011.mp3'),('plastered','烂醉的','uk :ˈplɑː.stəd, us :ˈplæs.tɚd','[They went out to the bars and got plastered. \n 他们去酒吧喝了个烂醉。 \n]\n','2020-03-11',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukpla/ukplain025.mp3'),('plate','盘子，碟子一盘；一盘之量平板；板条；板材印版（书籍的）插图，彩色插图（棒球运动中的）本垒板（home plate的非正式说法）表面有镀层的金属制品贵重金属制品（尤指餐具）镀上；用（金、银等）覆镀','uk :pleɪt, us :pleɪt','[paper/plastic/china plates \n 纸／塑料／瓷盘子 \n, a dinner/salad plate \n 餐盘／色拉盘 \n, clean/dirty plates \n 干净／脏盘子 \n, There s still lots of food on your plate. \n 你的盘子里还有很多食物。 \n, Stephen ate three plates of spaghetti. \n 斯蒂芬吃了3盘意大利面条。 \n, Thick bony plates protected the dinosaur against attack. \n 厚厚的骨质鳞甲帮助恐龙抵御攻击。 \n, The ship s deck is composed of steel plates. \n 该船的甲板由钢板构成。 \n, The three birds differ in small features (see Plate 4). \n 这3只鸟的细微特征有区别（见插图4）。 \n, The knives and forks are silver plate. \n 这些刀叉是镀银的。 \n, The thieves got away with a large quantity of church plate. \n 小偷盗走了教堂中大量的餐具。 \n, We normally plate the car handles with nickel and then chrome. \n 我们通常先用镍再用铬来镀汽车的拉手。 \n]\n','2020-01-17',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukpla/ukplate001.mp3'),('playwright','剧作家','uk :ˈpleɪ.raɪt, us :ˈpleɪ.raɪt','[]\n','2020-04-01',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukpla/ukplayg010.mp3'),('pledge','誓言；诺言；保证发誓；保证','uk :pledʒ, us :pledʒ','[[ + to infinitive ] \n All the candidates have given/made pledges not to raise taxes if they are elected. \n 所有的候选人都保证当选后不增税。 \n, Thousands of people made pledges (= promised to give money) to the charity campaign. \n 数千人许诺向救助儿童慈善运动捐款。 \n, I give you this ring as a pledge of my everlasting love for you. \n 我把这枚戒指送给你作为我永远爱你的信物。 \n, We are asking people to pledge their support for our campaign. \n 我们正请求人们承诺支持我们的运动。 \n, If you join the armed forces, you have to pledge allegiance to your country. \n 如果参军，你必须宣誓效忠你的祖国。 \n, So far, £50,000 has been pledged (= people have promised to pay this amount) in response to the appeal. \n 到目前为止，人们已承诺捐款5万英镑以响应这项呼吁。 \n, [ + to infinitive ] \n Both sides have pledged to end the fighting. \n 双方均已保证停战。 \n, I\'ve been pledged to secrecy. \n 我已发誓保守秘密。 \n]\n','2019-10-08',0,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukple/ukplebb008.mp3'),('plod','艰难地行走；吃力地行进（缺乏想象力、热情和兴趣地）埋头工作','uk :plɒd, us :plɑːd','[We plodded through the mud. \n 我们在泥泞中艰难行进。 \n, Despite the wind and the rain, they plodded on until they reached the cabin. \n 他们顶风冒雨坚持走到了小屋。 \n, For years, he s plodded away at the same dull routine job. \n 多年来，他一直在做同一项单调的工作。 \n, Alex is just plodding along at school, making very little progress. \n 亚历克斯一直在校苦学，但几乎没有什么进步。 \n]\n','2020-03-06',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukple/ukplebb029.mp3'),('plot','情节秘密计划；阴谋小块土地，小块地皮示意图（或图表）在纸（或地图）上标出，画出在图上标绘…的位置；绘制…的图；标出…的航线密谋；策划密谋，策划（开某人的玩笑）为…设计情节','uk :plɒt, us :plɑːt','[The movie has a very simple plot. \n 这部电影情节很简单。 \n, The plots of his books are basically all the same. \n 他的书情节基本上都一样。 \n, The plot was discovered before it was carried out. \n 这项阴谋还未得逞就暴露了。 \n, [ + to infinitive ] \n The police have foiled a plot to assassinate the president. \n 警方挫败了一个刺杀总统的阴谋。 \n, a vegetable plot \n 菜地 \n, There are several plots of land for sale. \n 有好几块地要出售。 \n, Radar operators plotted the course of the incoming missile. \n 雷达操作员标绘出了来袭导弹的轨迹。 \n, We ve plotted our projected costs for the coming year, and they show a big increase. \n 我们绘制出了来年的预计成本曲线，从中可以看出成本将大幅增加。 \n, The army is plotting the overthrow of the government. \n 军队正密推翻政府。 \n, I can t believe that he s plotting against his own father. \n 我难以相信他正暗中和自己的父亲作对。 \n, [ + to infinitive ] \n They re plotting (together) to take over the company. \n 他们在（一起）谋划接管该公司。 \n, [ + to infinitive ] \n They re plotting to play a trick on their brother. \n 他们正密谋捉弄他们的哥哥。 \n, He s plotting a surprise party for his wife s birthday. \n 他在偷偷为妻子的生日策划一个惊喜聚会。 \n, So far I ve only plotted (out) the story in a rough form. \n 到目前为止，我仅仅构思出了故事的基本框架。 \n]\n','2020-02-21',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukplo/ukplodd006.mp3'),('ploy','计谋，策略；手法，花招','uk :plɔɪ, us :plɔɪ','[There are various ploys we can use if necessary. \n 必要的话，我们可以用各种手段。 \n, [ + to infinitive ] \n He only said he had a meeting as a ploy to get her to leave. \n 他说他有一个会议要参加，只是为了把她支开。 \n]\n','2020-01-09',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukplo/ukplodd014.mp3'),('plunge','（使）（某人或某物）骤然移动，骤然下降（价值或程度）暴跌，骤降跳入；下跌；落下暴跌，骤降','uk :plʌndʒ, us :plʌndʒ','[We ran down to the beach and plunged into the sea. \n 我们跑向海滩，纵身跳入海中。 \n, The car went out of control and plunged over the cliff. \n 轿车失去控制坠下悬崖。 \n, Cook the peas by plunging them into boiling water. \n 把豌豆倒入沸水中煮。 \n, Niagara Falls plunges 55.5 metres. \n 尼亚加拉大瀑布落差为55.5米。 \n, The fall in demand caused share prices to plunge. \n 需求下降导致股价大幅下跌。 \n, Our income has plunged dramatically. \n 我们的收入骤减。 \n, I really enjoyed my plunge (= jumping in and swimming) in the pool. \n 我很喜欢在游泳池里跳水游泳。 \n, We are expecting a plunge in profits this year. \n 我们预计今年利润将大幅下降。 \n]\n','2020-01-24',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukplu/ukplump004.mp3'),('pneumonia','肺炎得肺炎','uk :njuːˈməʊ.ni.ə, us :nuːˈmoʊ.njə','[People who are bedridden can easily get pneumonia. \n 长期卧床的人易患肺炎。 \n, She ll catch pneumonia going out without a coat in this weather! \n 她这种天气不穿大衣出去会得肺炎的！ \n]\n','2020-01-23',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukpmt/ukpmt__004.mp3'),('poignancy','激痛','uk :ˈpɔɪ.njən.si, us :ˈpɔɪ.njən.si','[he production took on added poignancy due to the director\'s recent death.\n, The poem has a haunting poignancy.\n]\n','2019-12-19',0,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukpog/ukpogos003.mp3'),('polaris','北极星','uk :pəˈlɑː.rɪs, us :pəˈler.ɪs','[]\n','2020-03-13',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/e/epd/epd22/epd22661.mp3'),('pole','杆，柱（地球的）极（点）（意见、立场或特点）截然相反的一端，极端波兰人','uk :pəʊl, us :poʊl','[a telegraph/electricity pole \n 电线杆 \n, A flag fluttered from a 40-foot pole. \n 一面旗帜在40英尺高的旗杆上飘扬。 \n, the North/South Pole \n 北／南极 \n, Most weather satellites are stationed over the Equator or travel over the poles. \n 大部分气象卫星定位于赤道上空或绕地球两极飞行。 \n, These two men might be thought to represent the opposite poles of economic ideology. \n 这两个人可能被认为是两种截然相反的经济思想体系的代表者。 \n]\n','2020-01-03',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukpol/ukpolar007.mp3'),('poop','屎，大便信息筋疲力尽排便','uk :puːp, us :puːp','[Did you get the poop on all the candidates? \n 你弄到所有候选人的信息了吗？ \n, I m pooped! I must get some sleep. \n 我累死了！得睡会儿觉。 \n, Your puppy s just pooped right outside my front door. \n 你的小狗刚在我家前门外拉屎了。 \n]\n','2020-03-05',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukpon/ukponti013.mp3'),('pop-out','弹出','Dànchū','\n','2019-12-26',0,1,0,'https://translate.google.cn/translate_tts?ie=UTF-8&q=pop-out&tl=ja&tk=443174.63314&client=webapp&prev=input'),('pope','教皇（头衔）','uk :pəʊp, us :poʊp','[Pope John Paul II \n 教皇约翰•保罗二世 \n]\n','2020-01-20',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukpon/ukponti022.mp3'),('popinjay','自负的家伙','uk :ˈpɒp.ɪn.dʒeɪ, us :ˈpɑː.pɪn.dʒeɪ','[e regarded his rival as a conceited popinjay.\n]\n','2019-10-08',0,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english/uk_pron/c/cdo/cdo03/cdo0318ukpopi1094.mp3'),('populist','平民主义的；民粹主义的','uk :ˈpɒp.jə.lɪst, us :ˈpɑː.pjə.lɪst','[a populist manifesto \n 民粹主义宣言 \n, a populist leader \n 民粹主义领袖 \n]\n','2019-10-08',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukpop/ukpopsi013.mp3'),('portfolios','公文包；文件夹（尤指艺术家的）代表作选辑（个人或机构的）投资组合（部长或大臣）职务；（部长或大臣）职责不管部的（指在英国政府中任要职但并不具体负责某个部门）','uk :ˌpɔːtˈfəʊ.li.əʊ, us :ˌpɔːrtˈfoʊ.li.oʊ','[She\'s trying to build up a portfolio of work to show during job interviews. \n 她正想整理出自己的代表作以便找工作面试时展示一下。 \n, The prime minister offered her the foreign affairs portfolio. \n 首相邀请她出任外交部长。 \n]\n','2019-10-07',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukpor/ukporta013.mp3'),('portion','一部分；一份（食物的）一份，一客','uk :ˈpɔː.ʃən, us :ˈpɔːr.ʃən','[A large/major portion of the company s profit goes straight back into new projects. \n 公司利润的一大部分／主要部分又直接投入了新的项目。 \n, I accept my portion of the blame. \n 我承担部分责任。 \n, The portions are very generous in this restaurant. \n 这家饭店每份菜量都很足。 \n]\n','2020-01-23',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukpor/ukporta019.mp3'),('portrait','肖像，画像；人像照片电影（或书中）的描写，描述；表现竖向（描述计算机文件打印的一种方式，即纸的短边置于顶部和底部）','uk :ˈpɔː.trət, us :ˈpɔːr.trɪt','[She s commissioned an artist to paint her portrait/paint a portrait of her. \n 她委托一位画家为她画一幅肖像。 \n, a portrait gallery \n 肖像画廊 \n, a portrait painter \n 肖像画家 \n, Her latest novel paints a very vivid portrait of the aristocracy in the 1920s. \n 她最新的一部小说生动地描绘了20世纪20年代的贵族生活。 \n]\n','2021-03-23',3,6,1,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukpor/ukporta025.mp3'),('portray','描绘，描述，描写把（某人）刻画成，将（某人）塑造成','uk :pɔːˈtreɪ, us :pɔːrˈtreɪ',NULL,'2021-03-08',11,15,1,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukpor/ukporta027.mp3'),('possess','拥有；具有（欲望或想法）影响，控制，支配','uk :pəˈzes, us :pəˈzes','[I don t possess a single DVD (= I don t have even one DVD). \n 我一张DVD光盘都没有。 \n, In the past the root of this plant was thought to possess magical powers. \n 过去这种植物的根被认为具有神奇的力量。 \n, [ + to infinitive ] \n Whatever possessed him to wear that appalling jacket! \n 他中了什么邪竟穿了那件怪异的夹克衫！ \n]\n','2020-03-11',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukpos/ukposer015.mp3'),('possession','拥有，占有；具有所有物，个人物品；财产殖民地，托管地；属地（足球和橄榄球等比赛中，一方球队的）控球时间占有，拥有','uk :pəˈzeʃ.ən, us :pəˈzeʃ.ən','[The possession of large amounts of money does not ensure happiness. \n 拥有大量金钱并不能保证一定会幸福。 \n, ormal \n I have in my possession a letter which may be of interest to you. \n 我有一封信，也许你会感兴趣。 \n, ormal \n He was found in possession of explosives. \n 他被发现私藏爆炸物。 \n, Please remember to take all your personal possessions with you when you leave the aircraft. \n 下飞机时请记得携带好所有个人物品。 \n, a former overseas possession \n 前海外领地 \n, Wolves had a lot of possession but failed to score. \n 沃尔夫队控球时间很多，但没能进球。 \n, We need to keep possession of the ball to give ourselves a chance. \n 我们需要把球控制住才能有机会。 \n, We ve already bought the house but we won t take possession of it until May. \n 我们已买下这所房子，但直到5月份才能搬进去。 \n]\n','2020-03-19',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukpos/ukposer017.mp3'),('possum','负鼠（同 opossum）','uk :ˈpɒs.əm, us :ˈpɑː.səm','[]\n','2020-01-03',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukpos/ukposer023.mp3'),('potency','力量；影响力；效力（男子的）性能力','uk :ˈpəʊ.tən.si, us :ˈpoʊ.t̬ənt.si','[This new drug s potency is not yet known. \n 这种新药的效力目前还不清楚。 \n, He owed his popular support to the potency of his propaganda machine. \n 他获得广泛支持，他将这归功于他的宣传机器的力量。 \n, Consuming large amounts of alcohol can significantly reduce a man s potency. \n 大量饮酒会大大降低男子的性机能。 \n]\n','2020-02-21',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukpos/ukpostw011.mp3'),('pouch','小袋；一小袋东西（某些雌性动物的）育儿袋（某些动物贮存食物的）喉囊，颊袋','uk :paʊtʃ, us :paʊtʃ','[All our electric shavers are supplied with a free travel pouch. \n 我们的电动剃须刀都免费提供一个旅行套。 \n, Food sealed in foil pouches lasts for a long time. \n 密封在箔纸袋中的食物可以放很长时间。 \n, Kangaroos carry their young in pouches. \n 袋鼠将它们的幼崽放在育儿袋中。 \n]\n','2021-03-11',7,9,1,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukpot/ukpotti003.mp3'),('precaution','预防，预防措施（委婉的说法）避孕','uk :prɪˈkɔː.ʃən, us :prɪˈkɑː.ʃən','[Many people have been stockpiling food as a precaution against shortages. \n 为了预防食物短缺，很多人一直在大量储备食品。 \n, They failed to take the necessary precautions to avoid infection. \n 他们未能采取必要的预防措施来避免感染。 \n, If you re going to have sex, make sure you take precautions. \n 发生性行为一定要采取避孕措施。 \n]\n','2020-03-31',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukpra/ukpraye012.mp3'),('precious','珍贵的，宝贵的过分讲究的，做作的（表示讨厌和／或恼怒）宝贝似的极其，非常（同 very）','uk :ˈpreʃ.əs, us :ˈpreʃ.əs','[a precious gift \n 珍贵的礼物 \n, a precious moment/memory \n 宝贵的时刻／记忆 \n, Clean water is a precious commodity in many parts of the world. \n 在世界上很多地方洁净的水是昂贵的商品。 \n, You re so precious to me. \n 你对我来说就是珍宝。 \n, He s so precious about his work that he never gets anything done. \n 他对自己的活儿太讲究了，反而什么都做不成。 \n, Don t you hate the precious way she speaks, pronouncing each single consonant so precisely. \n 她讲话做作的样子真让人讨厌，每个辅音都发得那么准确。 \n, You and your precious car - it s all you re interested in! \n 你心里只有你和你那辆宝贝车！ \n, Lots of people will start, but precious few will finish. \n 许多人将开始去做，但极少数能完成。 \n, Be careful - you ll be precious little help if you come back injured. \n 小心——如果你受了伤回来就帮不上什么忙了。 \n]\n','2019-12-20',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukpra/ukpraye022.mp3'),('precise','精确的；准确的，确切的（尤指在细节上）严谨的，细致的','uk :prɪˈsaɪs, us :prəˈsaɪs','[The bunker s precise location is a closely guarded secret. \n 掩体的确切位置严格保密。 \n, He caught me at the precise moment that I fainted. \n 他正好在我晕倒的那一刻抓住了我。 \n, There was a good turnout for the meeting - twelve of us to be precise. \n 出席会议的人不少——确切地说有我们12个人。 \n, Years of doing meticulous research had made her very precise in her working methods. \n 多年来一丝不苟的研究使她养成了严谨的工作方法。 \n]\n','2020-01-23',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukpre/ukpreci003.mp3'),('predicament','尴尬的处境，窘境，困境','uk :prɪˈdɪk.ə.mənt, us :prəˈdɪk.ə.mənt','[She is hoping to get a loan from her bank to help her out of her financial predicament. \n 她希望能从银行得到一笔贷款以摆脱经济困境。 \n, I m in a bit of a predicament because I ve accidentally accepted two invitations to dinner on the same night. \n 我有些左右为难，因为我无意间接受了同一天晚上两个晚餐的邀请。 \n]\n','2020-03-06',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukpre/ukpreci030.mp3'),('predicate','谓语断言，断定，肯定基于，取决于','uk :ˈpred.ɪ.kət, us :ˈpred.ə.kət','[In the sentence  We went to the airport ,  went to the airport  is the predicate. \n 在 We went to the airport 这句话中，went to the airport 是谓语。 \n, [ + that ] \n It would be unwise to predicate that the disease is caused by a virus before further tests have been carried out. \n 在进一步化验前就断言这种病由病毒引起是不明智的。 \n, The sales forecast is predicated on the assumption that the economy will grow by four percent. \n 销售预测是基于经济将会增长4％这一假设之上的。 \n]\n','2020-02-20',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukpre/ukpredi002.mp3'),('predilection','偏爱，偏好','uk :ˌpriː.dɪˈlek.ʃən, us :ˌpred.əlˈek.ʃən','[Ever since she was a child, she has had a predilection for spicy food. \n 从孩提时起，她就偏好辛辣食物。 \n]\n','2020-04-03',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukpre/ukpredi009.mp3'),('prelude','序幕，先声，前奏序曲（尤指钢琴）前奏曲','uk :ˈprel.juːd, us :ˈprel.juːd','[The changes are seen as a prelude to wide-ranging reforms. \n 这些变化被视为大范围改革的序幕。 \n]\n','2020-03-05',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukpre/ukprefe021.mp3'),('premium','奖金，津贴；加价；附加费保险费优质汽油，高级汽油（品质）高级的；优质的，顶级的','uk :ˈpriː.mi.əm, us :','[We re willing to pay a premium for the best location. \n 为了得到最好的地段，我们愿意多支付些钱。 \n, Because of their location, these offices attract a premium. \n 由于地段好，这些办公室租金更高。 \n, The modified cars are available at a premium of five percent over the original price. \n 改进后的汽车的售价要比原价高5%。 \n, The busy shopper puts a premium on (= appreciates and will pay more for) finding everything in one big store. \n 时间有限的购物者若能在一家大商店买齐所有的东西，价钱高点儿也是愿意的。 \n, Car insurance premiums have increased this year. \n 今年汽车保险费涨了。 \n, The premiums for healthcare plans are high. \n 保健计划的保险费很高。 \n, premium ice cream \n 优质冰激凌 \n, The building is on a premium site. \n 这幢大楼建在一块风水宝地上。 \n]\n','2019-12-10',0,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukpre/ukpremi005.mp3'),('preoccupation','（时常想的）想法、事情全神贯注，入神；心事重重','uk :priːˌɒk.jəˈpeɪ.ʃən, us :priːˌɑː.kjəˈpeɪ.ʃən','[My main preoccupation now is trying to keep life normal for the sake of my two boys. \n 我现在想得最多的是要为了我的两个儿子而尽力使生活保持正常。 \n, Lately, his preoccupation with football had caused his marks at school to slip. \n 最近他一心想着足球，学习成绩都下降了。 \n]\n','2020-03-06',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukpre/ukpremi010.mp3'),('preposterous','荒谬的，愚蠢的','uk :prɪˈpɒs.tər.əs, us :prɪˈpɑː.stɚ.əs','[The very idea is preposterous! \n 这个想法很荒谬！ \n, a preposterous suggestion \n 愚蠢的建议 \n]\n','2020-02-28',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukpre/ukprepo001.mp3'),('prerogative','独有的权利（或权力），特权','uk :prɪˈrɒɡ.ə.tɪv, us :prɪˈrɑː.ɡə.t̬ɪv',NULL,'2021-03-26',6,5,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukpre/ukprepo008.mp3'),('prescient','预知的，有预知能力的，有先见之明的','uk :ˈpres.i.ənt, us :ˈpres.i.ənt','[a prescient warning \n 预见性的警告 \n]\n','2020-03-11',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukpre/ukprepo014.mp3'),('president','总统；国家主席（机构的）负责人，会长，主席；（尤指美国的）总裁，董事长','uk :ˈprez.ɪ.dənt, us :ˈprez.ɪ.dənt','[President Kennedy \n 肯尼迪总统 \n, the president of France \n 法国总统 \n, [ as form of address ] \n Thank you, Mr/Madam President. \n 谢谢您，总统阁下。 \n, a former president of the Royal Society \n 皇家学会的前会长 \n, ainly US \n She s a friend of the president of the bank. \n 她是银行总裁的朋友。 \n]\n','2020-02-13',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukpre/ukprese007.mp3'),('presumably','据推测，大概，可能','uk :prɪˈzjuː.mə.bli, us :prɪˈzuː.mə.bli','[They can presumably afford to buy a bigger apartment. \n 他们大概买得起一套大一点的公寓。 \n, Presumably he just forgot to send the letter. \n 他可能是忘了寄信。 \n]\n','2020-02-28',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukpre/ukprese020.mp3'),('prevention','阻止，妨碍；预防','uk :prɪˈven.ʃən, us :prɪˈven.ʃən','[crime prevention \n 预防犯罪 \n, The organization is committed to AIDS prevention and education. \n 该组织致力于艾滋病的预防和教育。 \n]\n','2020-01-23',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukpre/ukprete023.mp3'),('pride','自豪，得意为…自豪，为…骄傲自尊（心）自负，骄傲狮群','uk :praɪd, us :praɪd','[She felt a great sense of pride as she watched him accept the award. \n 看着他接过那个奖，她感到非常自豪。 \n, He felt such pride walking his little daughter down the street. \n 他陪着小女儿在街上走，感到非常自豪。 \n, If you don t take professional pride in your work, you re probably in the wrong job. \n 如果你对自己的工作没有职业自豪感，那可能是入错了行。 \n, She has too much pride to accept any help. \n 她自尊心太强，不肯接受任何帮助。 \n, The country s national pride has been damaged by its sporting failures. \n 体育方面的失利使这个国家的民族自尊心受到了伤害。 \n, Pride was his downfall. \n 骄傲是他失败的原因。 \n]\n','2020-01-03',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukpri/ukprice009.mp3'),('primarily','主要地','uk :praɪˈmer.əl.i, us :praɪˈmer.əl.i','[We re primarily concerned with keeping expenditure down. \n 我们主要关心的是缩减开支。 \n, Baseball is primarily a summer game. \n 篮球基本上是一项夏季运动。 \n]\n','2020-01-23',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukpri/ukprice024.mp3'),('primeval','原始的；早期的','uk :praɪˈmiː.vəl, us :praɪˈmiː.vəl','[primeval forests \n 原始森林 \n]\n','2020-03-25',2,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukpri/ukprice029.mp3'),('profile','传略；人物简介公众注意（面部的）侧面（像）','uk :ˈprəʊ.faɪl, us :ˈproʊ.faɪl','[We need to increase our company s profile in Asia. \n 我们需要扩大公司在亚洲的影响力。 \n, There is a growing number of women in high-profile positions (= positions which they are noticed) in the government. \n 在备受注目的政府职位上，女性的数量在逐渐增长。 \n, Drawing profiles is somehow easier than drawing the full face. \n 不知为什么画侧面像要比画整张脸容易。 \n, a strong profile \n 轮廓分明的侧影 \n, The actor is photographed in profile, smoking a cigarette. \n 这个演员被人从侧面拍了一张抽烟的照片。 \n]\n','2019-12-11',0,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukpro/ukprofi002.mp3'),('profit','利润，盈利开始盈利好处，益处','uk :ˈprɒf.ɪt, us :ˈprɑː.fɪt','[She makes a big profit from selling waste material to textile companies. \n 她将废弃材料卖给纺织公司，从中赚取大笔利润。 \n, A year ago the Tokyo company had a pretax profit of 35 million yen. \n 一年以前，东京公司的税前利润是3500万日元。 \n, Company profits are down from last year s figures. \n 从去年的统计数字看，公司的利润下降了。 \n, You don t expect to make much profit within the first couple of years of setting up a company. \n 你不要指望在开办公司的头几年里赚取很多利润。 \n, He sold his house at a huge profit. \n 他卖掉自己的房子，赚了很多钱。 \n, He’s been in business five years, but has not yet turned a profit. \n 他进入这个行业已有五年，但还没有开始盈利。 \n, There s no profit to be gained from endlessly discussing whose fault it was. \n 没完没了地讨论谁是谁非是徒劳无益的。 \n]\n','2020-01-24',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukpro/ukprofi003.mp3'),('profound','强烈的；深沉的；极度的造诣深的；思想深邃的','uk :prəˈfaʊnd, us :prəˈfaʊnd',NULL,'2021-03-26',15,16,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukpro/ukprofi013.mp3'),('profusely','大量地·','uk :prəˈfjuːs.li, us :prəˈfjuːs.li','[he apologized/thanked us profusely.\n, He was bleeding/sweating profusely.\n,  profusely illustrated book\n, Quinn was bleeding profusely.\n]\n','2020-02-28',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukpro/ukprofi018.mp3'),('progressive','逐渐的；渐进的（指思想或体制）进步的，先进的累进（税）的（动词）进行时的支持进步政策者；改革派人士','uk :prəˈɡres.ɪv, us :prəˈɡres.ɪv','[There s been a progressive decline in the standard of living over the past few years. \n 最近几年的生活水平每况愈下。 \n, a progressive disease \n 慢性病 \n, progressive ideas/attitudes \n 进步的思想／态度 \n, The left of the party is pressing for a more progressive social policy. \n 该政党的左派敦促实行更加进步的社会政策。 \n, a progressive school \n 实行进步教育法的学校 \n,  He s working hard at the moment  is an example of the present progressive form of the verb  work . \n He s working hard at the moment 是动词 work 的现在进行时的一个例子。 \n,  I was eating when the phone rang  is an example of the past progressive. \n I was eating when the phone rang 是过去进行时的一个例子。 \n]\n','2019-12-20',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukpro/ukprogr002.mp3'),('prohibition','禁止；禁令禁酒时期（1920至1933年间美国禁止生产和销售酒的时期）','uk :ˌprəʊ.ɪˈbɪʃ.ən, us :ˌproʊ.ɪˈbɪʃ.ən','[New York City has announced a prohibition on smoking on buses. \n 纽约市宣布禁止在公共汽车上吸烟。 \n, The environmental group is demanding a complete prohibition against the hunting of whales. \n 该环保团体要求彻底禁止捕猎鲸鱼。 \n, It s my feeling that the money spent on drug prohibition would be better spent on information and education. \n 我觉得花钱禁毒不如把钱用在信息和教育上。 \n]\n','2019-12-27',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukpro/ukprogr005.mp3'),('projectile','投掷物；抛射物；发射物（尤指子弹、炮弹等）投射的，推进的','uk :prəˈdʒek.taɪl, us :prəˈdʒek.təl','[The second projectile exploded after hitting a tank. \n 第二发炮弹击中坦克后爆炸了。 \n, projectile weapons \n 投射武器 \n, projectile vomiting \n 喷射性呕吐 \n]\n','2019-12-13',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukpro/ukprogr011.mp3'),('prologue','（戏剧的）开场白，开场诗，引子（重大事件的）开端，序幕','uk :ˈprəʊ.lɒɡ, us :ˈproʊ.lɑːɡ','[nformal \n A series of internal struggles was the prologue to full-scale civil war. \n 一系列内部斗争是爆发全面内战的序幕。 \n]\n','2020-04-03',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukpro/ukprogr024.mp3'),('prone','易于遭受（疾病）的；有（消极）倾向的俯卧的，趴着的较常碰到…问题的','uk :prəʊn, us :proʊn','[I ve always been prone to headaches. \n 我总是容易头疼。 \n, He was prone to depression even as a teenager. \n 甚至在青少年时期他就容易情绪抑郁。 \n, She s prone to exaggerate, that s for sure. \n 她喜欢夸大其词，这一点是肯定的。 \n, The photograph showed a man lying prone on the pavement, a puddle of blood around his head. \n 这张照片上一名男子趴在人行道上，头部周围有一滩血。 \n, accident-prone \n 易出事故的 \n, injury-prone \n 易受伤的 \n]\n','2021-03-24',5,7,1,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukpro/ukpromi022.mp3'),('proportion','部分；份额比率，比例（某物各个组成部分或一物与另一物之间的）相称，协调，均衡，匀称尺寸；大小；形状；程度重要性，严重性','uk :prəˈpɔː.ʃən, us :prəˈpɔːr.ʃən','[Children make up a large proportion of the world s population. \n 孩子占世界人口的很大一部分。 \n, A higher proportion of men are willing to share household responsibilities than used to be the case. \n 现在愿意共同承担家务的男人比例比过去要高。 \n, The report shows that poor families spend a larger proportion of their income on food. \n 报告显示，贫困家庭食物支出所占其收入比例更大了。 \n, The proportion of women to men at my college was about five to one. \n 我所在大学的男女比例大约为1：5。 \n, The chart shows how weight increases in proportion to height (= the increase in weight depends on the increase in height). \n 图表表明了体重是如何随身高成正比例上升的。 \n, The level of crime in an area is almost always in direct proportion to the number of unemployed. \n 一个地区的犯罪率几乎总是与失业人数成正比。 \n, Your legs are very much in proportion to (= the right size for) the rest of your body. \n 你的腿和你身体的其他部位比例非常协调。 \n, His feet seem very small in proportion to his body. \n 和他的身体相比，他的脚似乎显得太小了。 \n, My head was much nearer the camera than the rest of me so I m all out of proportion. \n 我的脑袋比身体其他部位离相机近得多，所以照片里我显得比例失调了。 \n, a building of elegant proportions \n 造型优美的建筑物 \n, I m not very good at drawing people - I can never get the proportions right. \n 我画人物不太在行——我从来都拿不准比例。 \n, umorous \n She s a woman of generous proportions (= she is fat). \n 她是个胖女人。 \n, A small worry in the back of your mind can for no apparent reason assume/take on massive proportions in the middle of the night. \n 内心深处的一点点忧虑在深夜里便会莫名其妙地无限放大。 \n, You have to keep a sense of proportion (= the ability to understand what is important and what is not). \n 你得会辨别轻重缓急。 \n, I think a certain amount of worry about work is very natural, but you ve got got to keep it in proportion (= judge correctly its seriousness). \n 我认为对工作有点担心是很自然的，但不要过分担心。 \n]\n','2020-01-10',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukpro/ukproof030.mp3'),('proposal','建议；计划；提案求婚','uk :prəˈpəʊ.zəl, us :prəˈpoʊ.zəl','[Congress has rejected the latest economic proposal put forward by the President. \n 议会否决了总统最近提出的经济计划。 \n, [ + to infinitive ] \n There has been an angry reaction to the government\'s proposal to reduce unemployment benefit. \n 政府削减失业救济金的计划遭到了强烈的反对。 \n, Have you read Steve\'s proposals for the new project? \n 你看了史蒂夫对新项目的建议了吗？ \n, [ + that ] \n There was anger at the proposal that a UN peacekeeping force should be sent to the area. \n 有人对向该地区派遣联合国维和部队的建议很恼火。 \n]\n','2019-10-03',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukpro/ukpropo007.mp3'),('propose','建议；提议；提出提名，推荐（某人）担任某职（或参加某组织）求婚提议为…祝酒；提议为…干杯计划，打算','uk :prəˈpəʊz, us :prəˈpoʊz','[[ + that ] \n I propose that we wait until the budget has been announced before committing ourselves to any expenditure. \n 我建议我们在预算没有宣布以前不要有任何支出。 \n, [ + -ing verb ] \n He proposed dealing directly with the suppliers. \n 他提议直接和供应商打交道。 \n, She proposed a boycott of the meeting. \n 她建议抵制这次会议。 \n, He proposed a motion that the chairman resign. \n 他提出了一项让主席辞职的动议。 \n, To be nominated for union president you need one person to propose you and another to second you. \n 要被提名为工会主席，你需要有一个推荐人和一个附议人。 \n, I remember the night your father proposed to me. \n 我记得你父亲向我求婚的那个晚上。 \n, Now, if you\'d all please raise your glasses, I\'d like to propose a toast to the bride and groom. \n 现在，请大家举起酒杯，让我们为新郎和新娘干杯。 \n, [ + to infinitive ] \n How do you propose to complete the project in such a short time? \n 你打算怎样在这么短的时间内完成这个项目？ \n, [ + -ing verb ] \n How do you propose tackling this problem? \n 你打算怎么解决这个问题？ \n, I do not propose to reveal details at this stage. \n 我不打算在这个阶段透露细节。 \n, What we are proposing is a radical change in approach. \n 我们打算在方法上来个彻底转变。 \n]\n','2019-10-08',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukpro/ukpropo008.mp3'),('proposition','（通常指商业上的）提议，建议主张；观点；见解要求与（某人）发生性关系，向…提出猥亵的要求','uk :ˌprɒp.əˈzɪʃ.ən, us :ˌprɑː.pəˈzɪʃ.ən','[He wrote to me last week regarding a business proposition he thought might interest me. \n 他上周写信给我，提出一项他认为我会感兴趣的商业建议。 \n, I ve put my proposition to the company director for his consideration. \n 我已将我的提议交给公司主管考虑。 \n, They were debating the proposition that  All people are created equal . \n 他们正就“人人生而平等”这一命题展开辩论。 \n, I was propositioned by a complete stranger. \n 一个素不相识的人提出想和我上床。 \n]\n','2019-12-19',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukpro/ukpropo011.mp3'),('protagonists','（某一想法或政治制度的）主要支持者，主要拥护者（故事或戏剧中的）主要人物，主角','uk :prəˈtæɡ.ən.ɪst, us :prəˈtæɡ.ən.ɪst','[Key protagonists of the revolution were hunted down and executed. \n 这次革命的主要发起者被捕并被处决。 \n]\n','2020-04-03',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukpro/ukprose022.mp3'),('protocol','礼仪，礼节（正式的国际性）条约，公约，议定书规程，协议（计算机之间交换信息的计算机语言）','uk :ˈprəʊ.tə.kɒl, us :ˈproʊ.t̬ə.kɑːl','[a breach of Royal protocol \n 对皇家礼仪的违反 \n, diplomatic protocol \n 外交礼仪 \n, The Geneva Protocol of 1925 prohibits the use of poisonous gases in war. \n 1925年通过的《日内瓦公约》禁止在战争中使用有毒气体。 \n]\n','2019-10-08',0,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukpro/ukprote013.mp3'),('proverbial','谚语的，俗话所说的，常言中的众所周知的','uk :prəˈvɜː.bi.əl, us :prəˈvɝː.bi.əl','[The players pointed the proverbial finger at themselves as the ones needing to improve. \n 这些球员简直就是在对自己竖中指，其实他们才是需要提高的人。 \n, his proverbial good humour \n 他那人人皆知的好脾气 \n]\n','2020-03-18',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukpro/ukprove005.mp3'),('prowess','杰出的才能；高超的技能','uk :ˈpraʊ.es, us :ˈpraʊ.es',NULL,'2021-03-08',10,12,1,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukpro/ukprowe001.mp3'),('prune','修剪（树枝）删除，删节西梅干，洋李脯','uk :pruːn, us :pruːn','[She spent the afternoon pruning roses. \n 她用下午的时间修剪了玫瑰。 \n, Arco has reacted to the loss in revenue by pruning (back) its expansion plans. \n 大西洋里奇菲尔德公司通过缩减扩张计划以应对收益亏损。 \n, I felt his essay needed a little pruning. \n 我认为他的文章需要稍作删节。 \n]\n','2020-02-21',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukpro/ukprowe015.mp3'),('psychedelic','迷幻的','Mí huàn de','\n','2019-12-10',1,0,0,'https://translate.google.cn/translate_tts?ie=UTF-8&q=psychedelic &tl=ja&tk=313923.196151&client=webapp&prev=input'),('psycho','精神失常者，精神病人，变态人格者心理的，精神的','uk :ˈsaɪ.kəʊ, us :ˈsaɪ.koʊ','[The man s a psycho. \n 那个男子是个变态狂。 \n, psychopharmacology (= the study of drugs which affect the mind) \n 精神药理学 \n]\n','2020-01-17',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukpss/ukpsst_011.mp3'),('puff','喘气气喘吁吁吸（烟），抽（烟）吹，喷出，冒出一小口（烟雾），一小股（空气）泡夫，松饼吹捧文字，吹捧的言论气喘吁吁，呼吸急促吸烟，抽烟','uk :pʌf, us :pʌf','[He came puffing up the stairs. \n 他气喘吁吁地上了楼。 \n, [ + speech ] \n  I ran all the way home,  she puffed (= said while puffing). \n “我是一路跑回家的，”她气喘吁吁地说。 \n, She was puffing on a cigarette at the time. \n 她当时正在吸烟。 \n, He sat there, puffing away at a cigarette. \n 他坐在那里，抽着烟。 \n, The engine puffed a huge cloud of steam, then rolled down the tracks. \n 火车头喷出一大股水蒸气，沿着轨道开始移动。 \n, The chimney was puffing out clouds of smoke. \n 烟囱向外冒出一股股的烟。 \n, Sean blew a puff of smoke at his reflection in the mirror. \n 肖恩朝镜中的自己喷了一口烟。 \n, He hit the ground with his stick and a puff of dust rose up into the air. \n 他用拐杖敲打地面，扬起一股浮尘。 \n, a cream/jam puff \n 奶油／果酱松饼 \n, cheese puffs \n 奶酪松饼 \n, She took a puff on her cigarette and thought for a moment. \n 她抽了一口烟，沉思了一会儿。 \n]\n','2019-12-24',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukpue/ukpueri002.mp3'),('pulmonary','肺的','uk :ˈpʊl.mə.nər.i, us :ˈpʊl.mə.ner.i','[the pulmonary artery \n 肺动脉 \n]\n','2020-01-23',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukpue/ukpueri019.mp3'),('pulpit','布道坛','uk :ˈpʊl.pɪt, us :ˈpʊl.pɪt','[]\n','2020-03-25',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukpue/ukpueri021.mp3'),('pulse','脉搏测（某人的）脉搏（声波或光波的）脉冲豆类植物的种子；荚果；豆子（以规律且强有力的节拍）跳动，搏动，振动','uk :pʌls, us :pʌls','[The child s pulse was strong/weak. \n 那个孩子的脉搏很有力／虚弱。 \n, Exercise increases your pulse rate. \n 锻炼能加快你的脉搏。 \n, The data, normally transmitted electronically, can be changed into pulses of light. \n 这一数据通常是电子传送的，现在可被改为光波脉冲。 \n, Pulses include peas, lentils, and chickpeas. \n 豆类包括豌豆、小扁豆和鹰嘴豆。 \n, I could feel the blood pulsing through my veins. \n 我能感觉到血液在我的血管里翻腾。 \n]\n','2019-12-26',0,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukpue/ukpueri025.mp3'),('pupil','学生，（尤指）小学生学徒；弟子；门徒瞳孔','uk :ˈpjuː.pəl, us :ˈpjuː.pəl','[a second-year pupil \n 小学二年级学生 \n, a primary-school pupil \n 小学生 \n, The school has over 400 pupils. \n 这所学校有400多名学生。 \n, There is a very relaxed atmosphere between staff and pupils at the school. \n 这所学校师生之间的气氛很轻松。 \n, Her school report described her as a very promising pupil. \n 在她的成绩单中她被描述成一个非常有前途的学生。 \n, The painting is believed to be by a pupil of Titian. \n 这幅画被认为是提香的一位门徒所作。 \n, Pupils contract in bright light, and dilate in darkness. \n 瞳孔在明亮的光线下会收缩，在黑暗中会扩大。 \n]\n','2020-03-06',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukpun/ukpunst008.mp3'),('purgatory','（天主教教义中的）炼狱，涤罪所痛苦的经历','uk :ˈpɜː.ɡə.tər.i, us :ˈpɝː.ɡə.tɔːr.i','[I ve been on a diet for two weeks now, and it s purgatory! \n 我已经节食两周了，真是太痛苦了！ \n]\n','2020-01-09',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukpun/ukpunst021.mp3'),('pursuit','嗜好，消遣，娱乐追踪；追击追求；从事；实行','uk :pəˈsjuːt, us :pɚˈsuːt','[I enjoy outdoor pursuits, like hiking and riding. \n 我喜欢户外活动，比如徒步旅行和骑马。 \n, I don t have much opportunity for leisure pursuits these days. \n 我近来没有多少时间可以花在业余爱好上。 \n, Three people have been killed in high-speed pursuits by the police recently. \n 有3人在最近警察的高速追捕中毙命。 \n, The robbers fled the scene of the crime, with the police in pursuit. \n 抢劫者逃离了犯罪现场，警察紧追不舍。 \n, the pursuit of happiness \n 对幸福的追求 \n, The company is ruthless in its pursuit of profit. \n 公司为追求利润不择手段。 \n, The union is on strike in pursuit of (= trying to achieve) a ten percent pay increase. \n 工会为了争取10%的加薪而罢工。 \n]\n','2020-03-17',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukpur/ukpurit024.mp3'),('puzzle','令人费解的情况；难题；谜测验智力的游戏（或玩具）（使）感到迷惑；（使）感到为难，（使）感到困窘','uk :ˈpʌz.əl, us :ˈpʌz.əl','[Scientists have been trying to solve this puzzle for years. \n 多年来科学家们一直试图解开这个谜。 \n, a jigsaw puzzle \n 智力拼图玩具 \n, a crossword puzzle \n 纵横字谜 \n, a puzzle book \n 谜语书 \n, The findings of the survey puzzle me - they re not at all what I would have expected. \n 调查的结果使我感到迷惑——它们根本不像我原本预料的那样。 \n, [ + question word ] \n It puzzles me why she said that. \n 我想不通她为什么那么说。 \n, Management are still puzzling about/over how the accident could have happened. \n 管理层仍对事故发生的原因感到迷惑不解。 \n]\n','2019-12-26',0,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukput/ukputz_002.mp3'),('pyjama','（某些亚洲国家人所穿的）束腰宽松裤睡衣裤的','uk :pɪˈdʒɑː.mə, us :pɪˈdʒɑː.mə','[pyjama bottoms (= trousers) \n 睡裤 \n, a pyjama top \n 睡衣 \n]\n','2020-03-06',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/e/epd/epd32/epd32769.mp3'),('quantitative','定量的','uk :ˈkwɒn.tɪ.tə.tɪv, us :ˈkwɑːn.t̬ə.teɪ.t̬ɪv','[quantitative analysis \n 定量分析 \n]\n','2019-10-07',0,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukq/ukqua/ukquali017.mp3'),('quartz','石英','uk :ˈkwɔːts, us :ˈkwɔːrts','[]\n','2019-10-11',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukq/ukqua/ukquart004.mp3'),('racial','种族的；种族间的；种族关系的人种的，种族的；作为人种（或种族、民族）特点的','uk :ˈreɪ.ʃəl, us :ˈreɪ.ʃəl','[racial discrimination/prejudice \n 种族歧视／偏见 \n, He had a vision of a society living in racial harmony. \n 他梦想在一个社会中各种族能和谐共处。 \n, They are members of a racial minority. \n 他们属于一个少数民族。 \n]\n','2020-01-10',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukr/ukrab/ukrabbi014.mp3'),('rack','架子；搁物架（用于台球或斯诺克比赛开球时放置球的）三角框（旧时为逼供而使用的）拉肢刑具（羊或猪）颈肉齿条；齿轨；齿棒糟糕透顶（的状态）；破损，损坏使肉体（或精神上）受巨大痛苦；折磨','uk :ræk, us :ræk','[a vegetable rack \n 摆放蔬菜的货架 \n, a plate rack \n 盘碟架 \n, a luggage rack \n 行李架 \n, The butcher prepared a rack of pork. \n 那个屠夫准备了一块猪颈肉。 \n, We re having rack of lamb for dinner. \n 我们晚餐吃羊颈肉。 \n, The whole farm was going to rack and ruin. \n 整个农场逐渐变得破败不堪。 \n, Even at the end, when cancer racked his body, he was calm and cheerful. \n 即使在最后，当他的身体备受癌症病魔摧残的时候，他仍然镇定自若、乐观开朗。 \n, The dog was already racked by/with the pains of old age. \n 那条狗已经又老又病，痛苦不堪。 \n, He was racked by/with doubts/guilt. \n 他被疑虑／内疚所折磨。 \n]\n','2020-03-05',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukr/ukrab/ukrabbi023.mp3'),('raid','（通常由一小队人发起的）突袭，袭击抢劫；打劫（警方）查抄，突然搜查突袭，突击抢劫；洗劫；劫掠（警方）突击检查，突然搜查（通常指偷偷地）从…把东西拿走，取走（某处的）东西','uk :reɪd, us :reɪd','[The commandos made/staged/carried out a daring raid (on the enemy). \n 突击队大胆（向敌人）发起了突袭。 \n, planes on a bombing raid \n 执行空袭轰炸任务的飞机 \n, Millions of dollars were stolen in a bank raid last night. \n 昨晚一家银行被劫走数百万美元。 \n, The drugs were found during a police raid on the house. \n 这些毒品是在警方查抄这栋房子时发现的。 \n, The nomads raided the enemy camp and captured over 100 camels. \n 游牧部落突袭了敌人的营地，掠走了上百头骆驼。 \n, The post office was raided late at night. \n 昨晚深夜邮局遭到抢劫。 \n, Police officers from the organized crime division have raided businesses in central London. \n 有组织犯罪调查处的警察已经突击搜查了位于伦敦中心的一些公司。 \n, I caught Toby raiding the fridge. \n 托比从冰箱里偷拿东西时被我撞上了。 \n]\n','2020-03-17',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukr/ukraf/ukraffl016.mp3'),('raise','举起；抬起；提起增加；提高；改善引起，导致；使存在养育；喂养；种植（赌牌时）比对手多下赌注，提高（赌注），加赌注解除；终止；解（禁）（尤指通过电话或无线电）与…取得联系，与…通话加薪','uk :reɪz, us :reɪz','[Would all those in favour please raise their hands? \n 赞成的人请举手好吗？ \n, He raised the window and leaned out. \n 他把窗户推上去后探出身子。 \n, Mary Quant was the first fashion designer to raise hemlines. \n 玛丽．匡特是第一个把裙子裁短的时装设计师。 \n, The government plan to raise taxes. \n 政府计划增税。 \n, I had to raise my voice (= speak more loudly) to make myself heard over the noise. \n 在一片喧哗声中，我不得不提高嗓门好让大家听见。 \n, The inspector said that standards at the school had to be raised. \n 督学说学校必须提高办学标准。 \n, Our little chat has raised my spirits (= made me feel happier). \n 我们闲聊了一小会儿，我的情绪好些了。 \n, Her answers raised doubts/fears/suspicions in my mind. \n 她的回答使我心里感到疑惑／害怕／怀疑。 \n, This discussion has raised many important issues/problems. \n 这次讨论引出了很多重要的议题／问题。 \n, The announcement raised a cheer/laugh. \n 该通知引起大家一片欢呼／哄堂大笑。 \n, I want to raise (= talk about) two problems/questions with you. \n 我想跟你探讨／问你两个问题。 \n, I want to start my own business if I can raise (= obtain) the money/cash/capital/funds. \n 如果我能够筹集到钱款／现金／资本／资金的话，我想创办自己的公司。 \n, ormal \n The chapel was raised (= built) as a memorial to her son. \n 这座小教堂是为了纪念她的儿子而修建的。 \n, Her parents died when she was a baby and she was raised by her grandparents. \n 她从小父母就去世了，是祖父母把她抚养大的。 \n, The lambs had to be raised by hand (= fed milk by people) when their mother died. \n 母羊死后，这些小羊羔只得靠人工喂养。 \n, The farmer raises (= breeds) chickens and pigs. \n 这个农场主饲养鸡和猪。 \n, The soil around here isn t good enough for raising (= growing) crops. \n 这附近地区的土壤不够肥沃，不能种庄稼。 \n, I ll raise you. \n 我要提高赌注。 \n, [ + two objects ] \n I ll raise you $50. \n 我要比你多押50美元。 \n, They agreed to raise the trade embargo if three conditions were met. \n 如果满足3个条件，他们同意解除贸易禁运。 \n, After three weeks the siege was raised. \n 3个星期后解除了围困。 \n, I ve been trying to raise Jack/Tokyo all day. \n 我一整天都在试图与杰克／东京取得联系。 \n, She asked the boss for a raise. \n 她要求老板给她加薪。 \n]\n','2020-01-24',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukr/ukrai/ukrains003.mp3'),('rash','皮疹，疹子（一下子出现的）大量令人不快的事轻率的；鲁莽的；毛躁的','uk :ræʃ, us :ræʃ','[I ve got an itchy rash all over my chest. \n 我胸部出满了疹子，痒得要命。 \n, If you stay in the sun too long you ll get (a) heat rash. \n 如果你在阳光下呆得太久，就会生痱子。 \n, K \n He came out/up in a rash after he fell in a patch of nettles. \n 他摔倒在一片荨麻地里，结果身上就起了疹子。 \n, There has been a rash of robberies/accidents/complaints in the last two months. \n 过去两个月中，突然发生很多起抢劫案／一下出了很多起事故／接二连三收到多起投诉。 \n, That was a rash decision - you didn t think about the costs involved. \n 那个决定太轻率了——你没有考虑到这样做的代价。 \n, [ + to infinitive ] \n I think it was a bit rash of them to get married when they d only known each other for a few weeks. \n 我觉得他们刚认识几周就结婚有些草率。 \n]\n','2020-03-11',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukr/ukrap/ukrapac027.mp3'),('ratify','（尤指政府或组织）正式批准，使正式生效，正式签署','uk :ˈræt.ɪ.faɪ, us :ˈræt̬.ə.faɪ','[Many countries have now ratified the UN convention on the rights of the child. \n 很多国家现在已经正式签署了联合国儿童权利公约。 \n, The decision will have to be ratified (= approved) by the executive board. \n 这个决议必须要经过管理委员会的批准。 \n]\n','2019-10-08',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukr/ukras/ukrasp_017.mp3'),('raw','（食物）生的，未经烹调的，没煮的原料未经加工的，自然状态的（信息）没有经过处理的，未经分析的，原始的（人）无经验的，未经培训的，生疏无知的（感情、品质等）处于自然状态的，强烈的，粗犷的（文字）不加掩饰的，如实坦陈的，反映真实情况的（肌肉）擦掉表皮而外露的；（伤口）露肉而刺痛的；创痛的（天气）严寒的，寒冷的，刺骨的','uk :rɔː, us :rɑː','[raw fish \n 生鱼 \n, Oil is an important raw material that can be processed into many different products, including plastics. \n 石油是一种重要的原料，可以加工成包括塑料在内的许多种产品。 \n, They claimed that raw sewage was being pumped into the sea. \n 他们断言，下水道的污水未经处理就被直接排入了大海。 \n, raw data/evidence/figures \n 原始数据／第一手证据／初始数字 \n, I would prefer not to leave this job to John while he s still a raw recruit/beginner. \n 约翰刚被招进来／刚开始工作，还是个生手，我不想把这项工作留给他来做。 \n, We were struck by the raw energy/power of the dancers  performances. \n 舞蹈演员们那粗狂奔放、富有激情的表演给我们留下了很深的印象。 \n, Her emotions are still a bit raw after her painful divorce. \n 经历过那段痛苦的离婚后，她的情绪仍然无法平静下来。 \n, His new play is a raw drama about family life. \n 他的新剧本是家庭生活的真实写照。 \n, The shoe had rubbed a raw place on her heel. \n 鞋把她的一个脚后跟磨破了。 \n, a raw morning \n 一个寒冷的早晨 \n, a raw wind \n 刺骨的寒风 \n, The evening was cold and raw. \n 那个晚上寒冷刺骨。 \n]\n','2020-01-20',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukr/ukrat/ukratio028.mp3'),('reactionary','反动分子；保守分子；反对进步者','uk :riˈæk.ʃən.ər.i, us :riˈæk.ʃən.er.i',NULL,'2021-03-08',6,8,1,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukr/ukray/ukrayon019.mp3'),('real-estate','房地产','Fángdìchǎn','\n','2020-02-21',0,0,0,'https://translate.google.cn/translate_tts?ie=UTF-8&q=real-estate&tl=ja&tk=972172.582136&client=webapp&prev=input'),('receptor','受体','uk :rɪˈsep.tər, us :-tɚ','[]\n','2020-01-24',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukr/ukrec/ukrecep001.mp3'),('recess','（议会）休会期课间休息壁龛；（墙的）凹进处；凹室幽深处；隐秘处；藏身处','uk :rɪˈses, us :rɪˈses','[The room has a recess designed to hold bookshelves. \n 这个房间有个壁凹，是为放书架而设计的。 \n, Psychoanalysts aim to explore the deepest/innermost recesses of the mind. \n 精神分析学家致力于探索心灵最深处的奥秘。 \n]\n','2020-03-06',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukr/ukrec/ukrecep002.mp3'),('reciprocate','回报，报答，酬答（机件）往返运动，沿直线往复移动','uk :rɪˈsɪp.rə.keɪt, us :rɪˈsɪp.rə.keɪt','[Sadly, my feelings for him were not reciprocated. \n 很不幸，我为他付出的感情没有得到回报。 \n, We invited them to dinner and a week later they reciprocated. \n 我们请他们吃晚餐，一星期后他们回请了我们。 \n, Some electric razors have reciprocating heads. \n 有些电动剃须刀的刀头是往返运动式的。 \n]\n','2020-03-19',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukr/ukrec/ukrecep015.mp3'),('recite','背诵；朗诵；当众吟诵','uk :rɪˈsaɪt, us :rɪˈsaɪt','[She proudly recited the Pledge of Allegiance. \n 她自豪地背诵《效忠誓言》。 \n, The opposition party recited a long list of the government s failings. \n 反对党列举出政府一大堆失误之处。 \n]\n','2020-02-19',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukr/ukrec/ukrecep021.mp3'),('reckless','鲁莽的；轻率的；不顾后果的','uk :ˈrek.ləs, us :ˈrek.ləs','[He was found guilty of reckless driving. \n 他被判鲁莽驾驶罪名成立。 \n]\n','2020-01-09',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukr/ukrec/ukrecep022.mp3'),('recklessness','鲁莽','uk :ˈrek.ləs.nəs, us :ˈrek.ləs.nəs','[he accident was a result of recklessness.\n, She had acted with extreme recklessness.\n]\n','2020-03-18',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english/uk_pron/u/ukr/ukrec/ukrecep024.mp3'),('reckon','想；认为，以为认为；把…看作计算','uk :ˈrek.ən, us :ˈrek.ən','[I reckon it s going to rain. \n 我觉得天要下雨了。 \n, [ + (that) ] \n How much do you reckon (that) it s going to cost? \n 你认为这会花多少钱？ \n,  Can you fix my car today?   I reckon not/so (= probably not/probably).  \n “你能今天把我的汽车修好吗？”“我想不行／大概可以。” \n, I don t reckon much to (US of) their chances of winning (= I do not think they will win). \n 我认为他们获胜的希望不大。 \n, She was widely reckoned (to be) the best actress of her generation. \n 人们普遍认为她是她那一代最优秀的演员。 \n, Angela quickly reckoned the amount on her fingers. \n 安吉拉掰着手指头快速计算了一下数量。 \n, The inflation rate is now reckoned to be 10 percent. \n 据计算，现在的通货膨胀率是10%。 \n]\n','2020-01-10',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukr/ukrec/ukrecep025.mp3'),('recluse','隐居者；喜欢独处的人','uk :rɪˈkluːs, us :rɪˈkluːs','[He is a millionaire recluse who refuses to give interviews. \n 他是个喜欢独处的百万富翁，不接受别人的采访。 \n]\n','2020-01-09',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukr/ukrec/ukrecli002.mp3'),('redundant','（尤指词、短语等）多余的，不需要的，累赘的，啰唆的失业的，被解雇的，被裁减的','uk :rɪˈdʌn.dənt, us :rɪˈdʌn.dənt','[In the sentence  She is a single unmarried woman , the word  unmarried  is redundant. \n 在句子 She is a single unmarried woman 中，unmarried 一词是多余的。 \n, To keep the company alive, half the workforce is being made redundant. \n 为了使公司生存下去，一半的员工要被裁掉。 \n, igurative \n New technology often makes old skills and even whole communities redundant. \n 新技术常常会使古老的技艺甚至是某个行业完全消失。 \n]\n','2020-03-10',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukr/ukred/ukredou009.mp3'),('reel','卷轴；卷筒；卷盘；绕在卷轴上的线里尔舞（一种轻快的苏格兰或爱尔兰舞蹈）；里尔舞曲踉跄；打趔趄；蹒跚；摇摇晃晃地挪动仿佛天旋地转发蒙；感到眩晕','uk :rɪəl, us :rɪəl','[At closing time he reeled out of the bar and fell down on the pavement. \n 酒吧关门时，他踉踉跄跄走了出来，一跤摔在人行道上。 \n, She hit him so hard that he reeled backwards. \n 她出手太重，打得他朝后打了个趔趄。 \n, A stone hit his head and the street reeled before his eyes. \n 一块石头砸在他头上，他顿时觉得街道在他眼前打旋。 \n, We were reeling (in amazement/shock/delight, etc.) from/with the news that we had won all that money. \n 得知赢了那么多钱，我们都（惊愕得／震惊得／高兴得）发蒙了。 \n]\n','2020-02-28',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/e/epd/epd32/epd32821.mp3'),('referendum','（就重大政治或社会问题进行的）全民公决，全民公投','uk :ˌref.əˈren.dəm, us :ˌref.əˈren.dəm','[Is it more democratic to hold a referendum, rather than let the government alone decide? \n 进行一次全民公决，而不是由政府自己作出决定，是不是要更民主些？ \n]\n','2019-10-08',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukr/ukred/ukredou021.mp3'),('regime','政府；政权；政体组织方法；管理体制；体系生活规则，养生之道（同 regimen）','uk :reɪˈʒiːm, us :reɪˈʒiːm','[The old corrupt, totalitarian regime was overthrown. \n 腐败的旧极权政府被推翻。 \n, The regime in this office is hard work and more hard work. \n 该事务所的管理方式是让人努力再努力。 \n]\n','2019-10-09',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukr/ukreg/ukregen008.mp3'),('regulation','规则，条例，法规；控制，管理一般的，普通的；规定的；正规的','uk :ˌreɡ.jəˈleɪ.ʃən, us :ˌreɡ.jəˈleɪ.ʃən','[safety/health/traffic/fire/security regulations \n 安全／卫生／交通／消防／保安条例 \n, The correct procedure is laid down in the rules and regulations. \n 正确的程序在规章条例中有规定。 \n, government regulation of inflation \n 政府对通货膨胀的控制 \n, businessmen in their regulation pinstripe suits \n 身着细条纹正式西服的商人 \n, It\'s regulation to wear suits at the office. \n 按规定在办公室要穿西服。 \n, a regulation football pitch \n 符合规范的足球场 \n]\n','2019-10-03',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukr/ukreg/ukregul006.mp3'),('regulatory','管理的；控制的；监管的','uk :ˌreɡ.jəˈleɪ.tər.i, us :ˈreɡ.jə.lə.tɔːr.i','[a regulatory body/organization \n 监管部门／组织 \n]\n','2019-10-03',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukr/ukreg/ukregul008.mp3'),('reincarnation','轮回转世说（灵魂的）转世化身，化身','uk :ˌriː.ɪn.kɑːˈneɪ.ʃən, us :ˌriː.ɪn.kɑːrˈneɪ.ʃən','[Hindus and Buddhists believe in reincarnation. \n 印度教徒和佛教徒相信轮回转世说。 \n, He believes he s a reincarnation of Julius Caesar. \n 他认为自己是尤利乌斯‧恺撒再生。 \n]\n','2020-01-10',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukr/ukreg/ukregul022.mp3'),('reinforce','加固；使更结实强化，加深，进一步证实（观点、看法等）增援；加强…的力量；给…增强装备','uk :ˌriː.ɪnˈfɔːs, us :ˌriː.ɪnˈfɔːrs','[The pockets on my jeans are reinforced with double stitching. \n 我牛仔裤的裤兜缝了两道线，很结实。 \n, The final technical report into the accident reinforces the findings of initial investigations. \n 对事故作出的最终的技术性报告进一步证实了最初的调查结果。 \n, His behaviour merely reinforced my dislike of him. \n 他的行为只能使我更讨厌他。 \n, The garrison is to be reinforced with/by another two battalions of soldiers. \n 守备部队将得到另外两个营的增援。 \n]\n','2020-01-23',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukr/ukreg/ukregul024.mp3'),('reinvent','（在已有事物的基础上）重新创造，改造（通过改换工作或形象、行为方式而）改造自己，洗心革面，换个活法','uk :ˌriː.ɪnˈvent, us :ˌriː.ɪnˈvent','[The story of Romeo and Juliet was reinvented as a Los Angeles gangster movie. \n 罗密欧和朱丽叶的故事被改编成了一部洛杉矶黑帮题材电影。 \n, He\'s one of those sportsmen who reinvent themselves as TV presenters. \n 他是那些半路出家做电视节目主持人的运动员之一。 \n]\n','2019-10-07',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukcld/ukcld01196.mp3'),('reiterate','反复地说，反复讲；重申','uk :riˈɪt.ər.eɪt, us :riˈɪt̬.ɚ.eɪt','[The government has reiterated its refusal to compromise with terrorists. \n 政府重申拒绝向恐怖分子妥协。 \n, [ + that ] \n She reiterated that she had never seen him before. \n 她一再重申自己以前从未见过他。 \n]\n','2019-10-08',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukr/ukreg/ukregul030.mp3'),('relativity','相对论相对性','uk :ˌrel.əˈtɪv.ə.ti, us :ˌrel.əˈtɪv.ə.t̬i',NULL,'2020-03-25',0,5,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukr/ukrej/ukrejec021.mp3'),('relentless','持续严厉的；持续强烈的','uk :rɪˈlent.ləs, us :rɪˈlent.ləs','[relentless criticism/pressure \n 不断的严厉批评／施压 \n, relentless heat \n 持续高温 \n]\n','2020-01-09',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukr/ukrel/ukrelen002.mp3'),('relieve','缓解，减轻，解除（疼痛或担忧）；使宽心，使宽慰缓和，缓解（令人不快的局势）救济；救援；救助接替；换…的班；替下将（某地从敌人的围困中）解围；解救撒尿，排尿（urinate 的礼貌性说法）','uk :rɪˈliːv, us :rɪˈliːv','[She was given a shot of morphine to relieve the pain. \n 医生给她注射了一针吗啡来止痛。 \n, She relieved her boredom at home by learning how to type. \n 她在家学打字来打发无聊的时光。 \n, New toll roads could help relieve congestion on other routes. \n 新建的收费道路可以帮助缓解其他道路的拥堵情况。 \n, emergency food aid to help relieve the famine \n 为了救济饥民而提供的紧急食品援助 \n, I\'m on duty until 2 p.m. and then Peter is coming to relieve me. \n 我要值班到下午两点，两点以后彼得就会来换班。 \n, An armoured battalion was sent to relieve the besieged town. \n 那个城市被困，一个装甲营被派去解围。 \n, He proceeded to relieve himself against a tree. \n 他走到一棵树旁小解。 \n]\n','2019-10-03',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukr/ukrel/ukrelen014.mp3'),('remunerative','给酬报的；给酬劳的','uk :rɪˈmjuː.nər.ə.tɪv, us :rɪˈmjuː.nə.reɪ.t̬ɪv','[a highly remunerative (= well paid) job \n 高薪工作 \n, Charity work is not very remunerative. \n 做慈善工作报酬不是很高。 \n]\n','2020-02-14',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukr/ukrem/ukremor015.mp3'),('render','使成为；使变得；使处于某种状态翻译；把…译成给予，提供；表达；表演粉刷；给（墙壁）抹灰（或水泥）','uk :ˈren.dər, us :ˈren.dɚ','[[ + adj ] \n His rudeness rendered me speechless. \n 他的粗暴无礼让我无言以对。 \n, New technology has rendered my old computer obsolete. \n 新技术发展太快，我的旧电脑已经过时了。 \n, She is rendering the book into English from French. \n 她正在把这本书从法语译成英语。 \n, The singers rendered the song with enthusiasm. \n 歌手们热情洋溢地演唱了这首歌。 \n, We see that freight railroads make good profits while rendering excellent service. \n 我们看到铁路货运公司在提供优质服务的同时也赢得了丰厚的利润。 \n]\n','2020-01-20',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukr/ukrem/ukremor020.mp3'),('repel','驱逐；逐回；击退；抗御排斥；相斥使厌恶；使极反感','uk :rɪˈpel, us :rɪˈpel','[This coat has a special surface that repels moisture. \n 这件外套面料特殊，可以防潮。 \n, ormal \n The defenders repelled the attack without losing any men. \n 守军击退了敌人的进攻，自己没有损失一个人。 \n, Similar poles of magnets repel each other, and opposite poles attract. \n 磁铁同极相斥，异极相吸。 \n, She was repelled by his ugliness. \n 她厌恶他那丑陋的相貌。 \n, Her arrogance repels many people. \n 她的傲慢令很多人十分反感。 \n]\n','2020-01-17',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukr/ukren/ukrenni028.mp3'),('repent','后悔；悔过，忏悔','uk :rɪˈpent, us :rɪˈpent','[He repented (of his sins) just hours before he died. \n 在临死前数小时，他才（对自己的罪孽）做了忏悔。 \n]\n','2020-02-13',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukr/ukren/ukrenni030.mp3'),('repentatleisure','悔婚','','null\n','2020-02-13',0,0,0,'null'),('reproach','（尤指因为某人没成功或没达到预期目标而）责备，责怪，批评（尤指因为某人没成功或没达到预期目标而）责备，责怪，批评','uk :rɪˈprəʊtʃ, us :rɪˈproʊtʃ','[His mother reproached him for not eating all his dinner. \n 他因为吃晚饭时没有把饭全吃完而受到妈妈的责备。 \n, You have nothing to reproach yourself for/with. \n 你没有什么可自责的。 \n, The look of reproach on his face made her feel guilty. \n 他责备的神情让她感到很愧疚。 \n, Your reproaches are useless - what s done is done. \n 你再指责也没有用了——做过的事无法改变。 \n]\n','2020-03-06',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukr/ukrep/ukrepos021.mp3'),('repulse','赶走，驱逐；击退（尤指进攻）；拒绝，拒绝接受令人厌恶；使人反感击退；败退；拒绝','uk :rɪˈpʌls, us :rɪˈpʌls',NULL,'2021-03-08',6,8,1,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukr/ukrep/ukrepro011.mp3'),('reputation','名誉；声望；名望','uk :ˌrep.jəˈteɪ.ʃən, us :ˌrep.jəˈteɪ.ʃən','[The company has a worldwide reputation for quality. \n 这家公司的产品质量誉满全球。 \n, She has the reputation of being a good doctor. \n 作为一名优秀的医生，她很有声望。 \n, His reputation was destroyed when he was caught stealing some money. \n 他偷钱时被当场抓住，这使他声名扫地。 \n, The hotel has a bad/good reputation. \n 这家旅馆名声很好／坏。 \n, He earned/established/gained/acquired a reputation as an entertaining speaker. \n 他因为演讲妙趣横生而赢得／享有／得到／获得盛名。 \n]\n','2019-10-08',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukr/ukrep/ukrepro016.mp3'),('rescue','救援；营救；解救救援；营救；解救','uk :ˈres.kjuː, us :ˈres.kjuː','[The lifeboat rescued the sailors from the sinking boat. \n 救生艇将水手们从正在下沉的船上救起。 \n, The government has refused to rescue the company from bankruptcy. \n 政府已经拒绝援助这家濒于破产的公司。 \n, Lifeboats carry out many rescues every month. \n 救生艇每月都会执行很多救援任务。 \n, We huddled together on the cliff ledge, waiting for rescue. \n 我们挤作一团蜷缩在悬崖边，等待救援。 \n, I didn\'t know anybody at the party, but the hostess came to my rescue (= helped me out of a difficult situation) by introducing me to a few people. \n 在聚会上我谁也不认识，但女主人过来救了我的驾，把我介绍给几个客人。 \n]\n','2019-10-08',0,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukr/ukrer/ukrerun005.mp3'),('resemblance','相似；形似，相貌相似','uk :rɪˈzem.bləns, us :rɪˈzem.bləns','[There was a clear family resemblance between all the brothers. \n 所有兄弟都长得很像，一眼就看得出是一家人。 \n, These prices bear no resemblance to (= are completely different from) the ones I saw printed in the newspaper. \n 这些价格和我在报纸上看到的大相径庭。 \n]\n','2020-01-10',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukr/ukrer/ukrerun010.mp3'),('resident','居民；住户（美国的）高级专科住院实习医生居住的；定居的；居留的（有特殊技能或品质者）常驻的','uk :ˈrez.ɪ.dənt, us :ˈrez.ə.dənt','[a resident of the UK/Australia \n 英国／澳大利亚居民 \n, The local residents were angry at the lack of parking spaces. \n 当地居民对停车位短缺一事非常恼火。 \n, The hotel bar was only open to residents (= to people staying at the hotel). \n 这家旅馆的酒吧只对其住客开放。 \n, She s a first-year resident in oncology at Boston General Hospital. \n 她现在波士顿综合医院肿瘤科做高级专科住院实习医生。 \n, She s resident abroad/in Moscow. \n 她现居住在国外／莫斯科。 \n, She is the university s resident expert on Italian literature. \n 她是这所大学意大利文学方面的常驻专家。 \n, umorous \n Tony is the company s resident clown. \n 托尼是公司里的专职小丑。 \n]\n','2020-02-28',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukr/ukrer/ukrerun029.mp3'),('resignation','辞职；辞去（职务）；放弃（工作）听任；顺从','uk :ˌrez.ɪɡˈneɪ.ʃən, us :ˌrez.ɪɡˈneɪ.ʃən','[There have been calls for his resignation. \n 一直有呼声要求他辞职。 \n, I handed in/gave in/sent in my resignation this morning. \n 我今天上午提交了辞职信。 \n, They received the news with resignation. \n 消息传来，他们听天由命接受了一切。 \n]\n','2020-03-18',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukr/ukres/ukresid004.mp3'),('resist','反抗；回击；抵抗抵制；阻挡；抗拒按捺；忍住；拒受…的影响','uk :rɪˈzɪst, us :rɪˈzɪst','[The soldiers resisted (the enemy attacks) for two days. \n （面对敌人的进攻）士兵们抵抗了两天。 \n, The party leader resisted demands for his resignation. \n 该党领导人拒不答应他辞职的要求。 \n, He tried to run away from the police and was charged with resisting arrest. \n 警方逮捕他时，他企图逃跑，结果被控拒捕。 \n, The new hybrid crops are much better at resisting disease. \n 这种新杂交作物抗病能力更强。 \n, I can never resist temptation/chocolate/the urge to laugh. \n 我向来无法抗拒诱惑／我永远不可能抵挡巧克力的诱惑／我要是想笑，怎么也忍不住。 \n, [ + -ing verb ] \n She couldn t resist laughing at him in those clothes. \n 看到他那副穿戴，她忍不住大笑起来。 \n]\n','2020-03-18',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukr/ukres/ukresid012.mp3'),('resolution','决议；正式决定决心；决定决心；决意；坚决解决；解除；消除（显微镜、电视、计算机显示屏等的）清晰度，分辨率分解；解析','uk :ˌrez.əˈluː.ʃən, us :ˌrez.əˈluː.ʃən','[to approve/adopt a resolution \n 批准／通过决议 \n, [ + to infinitive ] \n The United Nations passed (= voted to support) a resolution to increase aid to developing nations. \n 联合国通过了一项向发展中国家增加援助的决议。 \n, [ + to infinitive ] \n I made a resolution to give up chocolate. \n 我下决心不再吃巧克力了。 \n, He showed great resolution in facing the robbers. \n 面对强盗，他表现得英勇无畏。 \n, a successful resolution to the crisis \n 危机的成功解决 \n, a high/low resolution image \n 高／低清晰度图像 \n, the resolution of oil into bitumen and tar \n 石油分解成沥青和焦油 \n]\n','2020-01-09',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukr/ukres/ukresid022.mp3'),('respirator','>人工呼吸器；呼吸机>防毒面具','uk :>ˈres.pɪ.reɪ.tə, us :>ˈres.pə.reɪ.t̬ɚ',NULL,'2021-03-08',11,14,1,NULL),('respiratory','呼吸的','uk :rɪˈspɪr.ə.tər.i, us :ˈres.pə.rə.tɔːr.i','[Smoking can cause respiratory diseases. \n 吸烟会导致呼吸系统疾病。 \n]\n','2020-01-23',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukr/ukres/ukresou021.mp3'),('retail','零售，零卖零售，零卖以…价格零售，零售价格为…','uk :ˈriː.teɪl, us :ˈriː.teɪl','[The job is open to applicants with over two years  experience in retail. \n 这份工作面向有两年以上零售经验的求职者。 \n, The clothing company has six retail outlets (= shops) in Perth. \n 这家服装公司在佩思开设了6家零售店。 \n, $13 off the manufacturer s recommended retail price \n 比生产商的建议零售价便宜13美元 \n, The company makes and retails moderately priced sportswear. \n 这家公司生产和零售价格适中的运动服。 \n, This laptop retails at £850. \n 这款计算机零售价为850英镑。 \n]\n','2020-02-26',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukr/ukres/ukrestr018.mp3'),('retain','保持；保留；保有保存；留住；容纳付定金聘请（律师）','uk :rɪˈteɪn, us :rɪˈteɪn','[She has lost her battle to retain control of the company. \n 她被打败了，失去了继续掌管公司的权力。 \n, He managed to retain his dignity throughout the performance. \n 在整个表演过程中，他设法保持了自己的尊严。 \n, She succeeded in retaining her lead in the second half of the race. \n 在比赛的后半程中，她成功地保住了领先地位。 \n, I have a good memory and am able to retain (= remember) facts easily. \n 我记忆力很好，记东西不费劲。 \n, The sea retains the sun s warmth longer than the land. \n 海水储存太阳的热量的时间比陆地要长。 \n]\n','2020-02-28',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukr/ukres/ukrestr020.mp3'),('retaliation','反击报复','uk :rɪˌtæl.iˈeɪ.ʃən, us :rɪˌtæl.iˈeɪ.ʃən','[he bomb attack was in retaliation for the recent arrest of two well-known terrorists.\n, She suffered severe retaliation for writing articles for the newspapers.\n]\n','2020-01-14',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english/uk_pron/u/ukr/ukres/ukrestr025.mp3'),('reveal','揭露；泄露；透露使显露；展现；显示（电视节目最后的）揭示','uk :rɪˈviːl, us :rɪˈviːl',NULL,'2021-03-08',5,10,1,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukr/ukrev/ukrev__005.mp3'),('revere','>尊敬；崇敬','uk :>rɪˈvɪə, us :>rɪˈvɪr',NULL,'2021-03-11',10,12,1,NULL),('revert','回复','uk :rɪˈvɜːt, us :rɪˈvɝːt','[Please revert by email. \n 请通过电子邮件回复。 \n]\n','2019-10-03',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukcld/ukcld01216.mp3'),('revolution','（通常指改变政治体制的）革命革命性剧变；大变革旋转；绕转；循环运动（轮子等的）一转，一圈','uk :ˌrev.əˈluː.ʃən, us :ˌrev.əˈluː.ʃən','[The French Revolution changed France from a monarchy to a republic. \n 法国大革命使法国由君主政体变成共和政体。 \n, The country seems to be heading towards revolution. \n 这个国家似乎正在走向革命。 \n, a technological revolution \n 技术革命 \n, Penicillin produced a revolution in medicine. \n 青霉素的发现引起了医学上的一次革命。 \n, The revolution of the earth around the sun was proposed by Copernicus. \n 地球围绕太阳旋转这一观点是哥白尼提出的。 \n, Engine speed can be measured in revolutions per minute (abbreviation rpm). \n 发动机的速度可以每分钟转数（缩写为rpm）来表述。 \n]\n','2019-10-07',0,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukr/ukrev/ukrevie017.mp3'),('revolutionary','革命的，革命性的革命性的；大变革的；完全创新的革命者','uk :ˌrev.əˈluː.ʃən.ər.i, us :ˌrev.əˈluː.ʃən.er.i','[a revolutionary leader/movement \n 革命领导人／运动 \n, Penicillin was a revolutionary drug. \n 青霉素是具有革命性意义的药物。 \n, The 20th century brought about revolutionary changes in our lifestyles. \n 二十世纪带来人们生活上的巨大转变。 \n]\n','2020-02-21',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukr/ukrev/ukrevie018.mp3'),('rhyme','押韵；成韵；和…同韵押韵词；同韵词押韵诗；（尤指）儿歌在诗中应用同韵词；押韵（诗歌）押韵一个音节中部的元音以及之后的所有音','uk :raɪm, us :raɪm','[ Blue  and  flew  rhyme. \n blue 和 flew 押韵。 \n, Can you think of a word that rhymes with  orange ? \n 你能想出一个和 orange 押韵的词吗？ \n, Can you think of a rhyme for  orange ? \n 你能想出一个和 orange 押韵的词吗？ \n, a book of rhymes and songs \n 一本儿童诗歌集 \n, This poem is her first attempt at rhyme. \n 这首诗是她第一次尝试写的押韵诗。 \n, A lot of modern poetry is not written in rhyme. \n 很多现代诗不押韵。 \n]\n','2020-03-18',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukr/ukrew/ukrewou028.mp3'),('rhythm','（音乐、诗歌和舞蹈的）节奏，韵律，节律规则的运动；（动作的）节奏；律动（尤指自然界中的）规则变化，规律，节律','uk :ˈrɪð.əm, us :ˈrɪð.əm','[He beat out a jazz rhythm on the drums. \n 他击出爵士乐节奏的鼓点。 \n, I ve got no sense of rhythm, so I m a terrible dancer. \n 我根本没有节奏感，所以舞跳得很差劲。 \n, She was lulled to sleep by the gentle rhythm of the boat in the water. \n 船在水中有节奏地轻轻摇动，使她昏昏入睡。 \n, She hit the ball so hard that her opponent had no chance to establish any rhythm in her game. \n 她凌厉的击球让对手根本没有机会找到比赛的节奏。 \n, the rhythm of the seasons \n 四季的交替 \n, Breathing and sleeping are examples of biological rhythms in humans. \n 呼吸和睡眠是人体生物节奏的例证。 \n]\n','2020-01-10',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukr/ukrew/ukrewou029.mp3'),('ribbon','（捆扎或装饰用的）带子，丝带，缎带一缕；一条；一排勋带，绶带（打字机的）色带','uk :ˈrɪb.ən, us :ˈrɪb.ən','[Sandra often wears a ribbon in her hair. \n 桑德拉常在头发上扎条丝带。 \n, He tied up the present with ribbon. \n 他用缎带将礼物包扎起来。 \n, A ribbon of road stretched ahead of us across the desert. \n 沙漠中的一条路宛如一根细长的带子，在我们前方延伸。 \n, My typewriter needs a new ribbon. \n 我的打字机得换色带了。 \n]\n','2019-12-19',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukr/ukrhy/ukrhyth008.mp3'),('riddle','谜；谜语奥秘；费解之事使布满洞孔','uk :ˈrɪd.əl, us :ˈrɪd.əl','[Scientists may have solved the riddle of Saturn s rings. \n 科学家们或许已经揭开了土星环的奥秘。 \n, The anti-aircraft guns riddled the plane s wings with bullets. \n 高射炮炮弹把机翼打得千疮百孔。 \n]\n','2020-03-18',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukr/ukrhy/ukrhyth027.mp3'),('rifle','来福枪；步枪迅速翻查；匆忙翻找','uk :ˈraɪ.fəl, us :ˈraɪ.fəl','[The safe had been rifled and the diamonds were gone. \n 保险柜被洗劫了，钻石不翼而飞。 \n, He rifled through the papers on the desk, but couldn t find the photographs. \n 他把桌上的一堆文件翻了个遍，但是没有找到照片。 \n]\n','2020-01-03',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukr/ukrid/ukrider010.mp3'),('rigor','尸僵；死后强直','uk :ˌrɪɡ.ə ˈmɔː.tɪs, us :ˌrɪɡ.ɚ ˈmɔːr.t̬ɪs','[Rigor mortis usually sets in between two and four hours after death. \n 通常死后2至4小时就会开始出现尸僵。 \n]\n','2020-01-23',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukr/ukrid/ukrider029.mp3'),('rigorously','严谨','uk :ˈrɪɡ.ər.əs.li, us :ˈrɪɡ.ɚ.əs.li','[he plutonium fuel cells had been rigorously tested.\n, Isabel thinks rigorously and creatively about many different things.\n, he rules were applied too rigorously.\n, Driving bans for serious offences should be rigorously enforced.\n, eputable manufacturers test rigorously to make sure their products perform at the highest level.\n, aws are rigorously enforced.\n]\n','2020-01-23',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english/uk_pron/u/ukr/ukrig/ukrigor001.mp3'),('ripple','涟漪；微波；细浪（声音的）传播起伏；（感情的）逐渐扩散彩条冰激凌（使）起涟漪；（使）如波浪般起伏','uk :ˈrɪp.əl, us :ˈrɪp.əl','[The stone she threw caused ripples to spread across the lake. \n 她扔了一块石头，湖面泛起阵阵涟漪。 \n, A ripple of laughter/applause, etc. ran through the crowd. \n 人群中响起一阵阵笑声／掌声等。 \n, A ripple of excitement/unease, etc. flowed up her spine. \n 一阵激动／不安等顺着脊背传遍了她全身。 \n, News of the war hardly caused a ripple (= people showed little interest). \n 战争爆发的消息几乎没有引起任何反响。 \n, raspberry ripple \n 山莓彩条冰激凌 \n, The breeze rippled the water. \n 微风在水面吹起阵阵涟漪。 \n, His muscles rippled under his skin. \n 他皮肤下的肌肉一条条凸起。 \n]\n','2019-12-11',0,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukr/ukrip/ukripof003.mp3'),('rival','竞争对手；敌手可与…相媲美，比得上','uk :ˈraɪ.vəl, us :ˈraɪ.vəl','[He beat his closest/nearest rival by 20 marks. \n 他以领先20分的成绩打败了和他水平最接近的对手。 \n, The companies produce rival versions of the toy. \n 这些公司生产的玩具跟我们的产品争夺市场。 \n, No computer can rival a human brain for/in complexity. \n 没有任何计算机比得上人脑复杂。 \n, The beauty of the country is only rivalled by (= is as great in degree as) the violence of its politics. \n 该国的美丽风光非同寻常，而其国内政治的残暴同样惊世骇俗。 \n]\n','2021-03-26',6,5,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukr/ukrip/ukripof021.mp3'),('robe','长袍，罩袍；（尤指特别正式场合穿的）袍服，礼袍浴衣；睡袍','uk :rəʊb, us :roʊb','[Judges wear black robes when they are in court. \n 法官在法庭上都身穿黑袍。 \n, He wrapped a robe around himself before answering the door. \n 他裹了件浴衣过来开门。 \n]\n','2020-01-17',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukr/ukrn_/ukrn___027.mp3'),('rodent','啮齿动物（如老鼠等）','uk :ˈrəʊ.dənt, us :ˈroʊ.dənt','[]\n','2020-01-03',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukr/ukrob/ukrobot017.mp3'),('routine','惯例，常规；例行公事（表演中）一套固定的动作，固定的一套噱头，固定的表演节目（计算机的）例行程序常规的例行公事的；习惯性的平淡的；乏味的','uk :ruːˈtiːn, us :ruːˈtiːn','[There s no set/fixed routine at work - every day is different. \n 工作内容不固定——每天都不同。 \n, Most companies insure property and equipment against damage or theft as a matter of routine. \n 他只要开车就先习惯性地检查车下是否被安了炸弹。 \n, an exercise/dance routine \n 一套固定的练习／舞蹈动作 \n, He went into his usual  I m the head of the family  routine (= usual way of speaking). \n 他又故态复萌，重弹“我是一家之主”的老调子。 \n, a routine inspection/medical check-up \n 常规检查／体检 \n, a routine case of appendicitis \n 普通阑尾炎病例 \n, He died during a routine operation which went wrong. \n 他因一次常规手术出错而死亡。 \n, My job is so routine and boring - I hate it. \n 我的工作一成不变，枯燥乏味——我厌烦透了。 \n]\n','2020-01-23',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukr/ukrou/ukrough019.mp3'),('roving','漫游的，流浪的','uk :ˈrəʊ.vɪŋ, us :ˈroʊ.vɪŋ','[And now a live report from our roving reporter, Martin Jackson. \n 下面是我们的流动记者马丁‧杰克逊发回的现场报道。 \n]\n','2020-03-18',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukcld/ukcld01241.mp3'),('ruffian','流氓，暴徒，恶棍（通常指男性）','uk :ˈrʌf.i.ən, us :ˈrʌf.i.ən','[]\n','2020-01-09',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukr/ukruc/ukrucks015.mp3'),('rumble','发出隆隆声；发出辘辘声；发出低沉连续的响声发现，察觉，看穿（某人的秘密或非法事情的真相）打架；打群架','uk :ˈrʌm.bəl, us :ˈrʌm.bəl','[Please excuse my stomach rumbling - I haven t eaten all day. \n 不好意思，我肚子在咕咕叫——我一整天都没吃东西了。 \n, Thunder rumbled in the distance. \n 雷声在远处隆隆作响。 \n, Convoys of tanks rumbled (= moved while rumbling) through the city streets.\n, His boss eventually rumbled him, and he was sacked. \n 他的老板最终看穿了他，把他解雇了。 \n]\n','2021-03-26',6,5,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukr/ukrum/ukrum__003.mp3'),('rumple','弄皱；弄乱；使凌乱','uk :ˈrʌm.pəl, us :ˈrʌm.pəl','[You ll rumple your jacket if you don t hang it up properly. \n 你要是不把你的外套挂好，它就会起皱的。 \n]\n','2020-03-05',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukr/ukrum/ukrum__015.mp3'),('ruthless','无情的；冷酷的；残忍的','uk :ˈruːθ.ləs, us :ˈruːθ.ləs','[ruthless ambition \n 冷酷无情的野心 \n, a ruthless dictator \n 残忍的独裁者 \n, Some people believe that to succeed in this world you have to be ruthless. \n 有些人认为，在这个世界上要想成功必须冷酷无情。 \n]\n','2020-01-09',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukr/ukrun/ukruns_028.mp3'),('sabotage','（为阻止敌人或对手成功而）毁坏，破坏（设备、武器或建筑物）阴谋破坏，蓄意破坏（计划或行动）','uk :ˈsæb.ə.tɑːʒ, us :ˈsæb.ə.tɑːʒ','[The rebels had tried to sabotage the oil pipeline. \n 叛乱分子曾试图破坏输油管道。 \n, This was a deliberate attempt to sabotage the ceasefire. \n 这是一次蓄意破坏停火的行为。 \n]\n','2020-01-09',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukr/ukrut/ukrutte015.mp3'),('sack','大布袋；麻袋；大纸袋；大塑料袋食品购物袋开除，解雇（通常指在战争中）洗劫，劫掠（美式橄榄球）擒杀（四分卫）床床上功夫（好或差）解雇，开除（美式橄榄球）擒杀（四分卫）（通常指在战争中）洗劫，劫掠','uk :sæk, us :sæk','[The corn was stored in large sacks. \n 玉米装在大麻袋里。 \n, a sack of potatoes/coal/flour \n 一袋土豆／煤／面粉 \n, a sack of groceries \n 一袋食品杂货 \n, They gave him the sack for being late. \n 因为迟到，他们开除了他。 \n, Two workers got the sack for fighting in the warehouse. \n 两名工人因为在仓库打架而被解雇了。 \n, The sack of Rome by the Visigoths occurred in the fifth century. \n 西哥特人洗劫罗马发生在公元5世纪。 \n, The Colts have allowed only six sacks this season. \n 小马队本赛季只遭受到六次擒杀。 \n, It\'s late - I\'m going to hit the sack (= go to bed). \n 时间不早了，我要上床睡觉了。 \n, He came home and found Judy and Brad in the sack (= in bed) together. \n 回到家，他发现朱迪和布拉德睡在一张床上。 \n, They sacked her for being late. \n 因为迟到，他们把她开除了。 \n, He got sacked from his last job. \n 他上一份工作是被解雇的。 \n, The quarterback was sacked only once and completed 16 out of 23 passes. \n 这名四分卫只被擒杀过一次，23次投掷成功了16次。 \n, The invaders sacked every village they passed on their route. \n 侵略者洗劫了他们途经的每个村庄。 \n]\n','2019-10-07',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukr/ukrut/ukrutte018.mp3'),('saddle','马鞍；（自行车、摩托车等的）车座，鞍座骑马掌握，控制（动物的）脊肉给（马）装鞍','uk :ˈsæd.əl, us :ˈsæd.əl','[He swung himself into the saddle and rode off. \n 他跨上马鞍，骑马走了。 \n, The chairman is back in the saddle after his heart attack. \n 心脏病痊愈之后，主席又重新掌权了。 \n, saddle of lamb \n 羊脊肉 \n, She saddled (up) the horse for her friend. \n 她为朋友备好了马鞍。 \n]\n','2020-01-10',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/uksac/uksacri013.mp3'),('sadist','施虐狂者；性施虐狂者','uk :ˈseɪ.dɪst, us :ˈsæd.ɪst','[]\n','2020-01-20',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/uksac/uksacri017.mp3'),('saga','萨迦（中世纪主要在冰岛用古诺斯语写成的斯堪的纳维亚长篇传奇）长篇故事（通常指负面的）系列事件，一长串事件','uk :ˈsɑː.ɡə, us :ˈsɑː.ɡə','[Norse sagas \n 诺斯萨迦，北欧传奇 \n, Her new novel is a lengthy and compelling family saga. \n 她最新的一部小说是一个篇幅宏大、扣人心弦的家族传奇。 \n, It was just another episode in the ongoing saga of their marriage problems. \n 这只是他们层出不穷的婚姻问题中的又一个插曲。 \n]\n','2020-02-21',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/uksaf/uksafek008.mp3'),('sake','为了（某人）的利益；为了帮助（某人）因为；为了做做好事吧，看在上帝份上，看在老天份上日本清酒','uk :seɪk, us :seɪk','[Please do it, for David s sake. \n 为了戴维，请做这件事。 \n, Their parents only stayed together for the sake of the children. \n 他们的父母仅仅是为了孩子才没有分开。 \n, I hope for both our sakes that you re right! \n 为你我着想，我希望你是对的！ \n, Let s not disagree for the sake of (= because of) a few dollars. \n 咱们不要因为几块钱闹别扭。 \n, Let s say, just for the sake of argument/for argument s sake (= for the purpose of this discussion), that prices rise by three percent this year. \n 为了便于讨论，我们假设今年的价格上涨3％。 \n, You re only arguing for the sake of arguing (= because you like arguing). \n 你只是为争论而争论。 \n, For goodness  sake don t let her know I told you! \n 行行好，千万别让她知道是我告诉你的！ \n]\n','2020-01-15',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/uksaf/uksafek030.mp3'),('salamander','蝾螈','uk :ˈsæl.ə.mæn.dər, us :ˈsæl.ə.mæn.dɚ','[]\n','2020-02-27',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/uksal/uksalaa007.mp3'),('salvage','（尤指从失事船只、火灾或水灾中）抢救，打捞挽救，挽回','uk :ˈsæl.vɪdʒ, us :ˈsæl.vɪdʒ','[gold coins salvaged from a shipwreck \n 从船只残骸中打捞出的金币 \n, After the fire, there wasn t much furniture left worth salvaging. \n 火灾之后，没有剩下多少值得抢救的家具。 \n, It was a desperate attempt to salvage the situation. \n 挽回这种局面的希望渺茫。 \n, After the fraud scandal he had to make great efforts to salvage his reputation. \n 诈骗丑闻传出后，他不得不极力挽回自己的声誉。 \n]\n','2020-03-12',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/uksal/uksalti010.mp3'),('salve','药膏；软膏；油膏慰藉，宽慰使良心得到宽慰；减轻内疚感','uk :sælv, us :sæv','[He salves his conscience by giving money to charity. \n 他通过向慈善机构捐款来使自己良心得到宽慰。 \n]\n','2019-12-19',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/uksal/uksalti013.mp3'),('sanctuary','庇护，保护；避难所，庇护所禁猎区，鸟兽保护区圣殿，圣堂','uk :ˈsæŋk.tʃʊə.ri, us :ˈsæŋk.tʃu.er.i','[Illegal immigrants found/sought/took sanctuary in a local church. \n 非法移民把当地的一座教堂当作避难所。 \n, The chapel became a sanctuary for the refugees. \n 这座小教堂成为难民的庇护所。 \n, igurative \n If I want some peace and quiet, I take sanctuary in my study. \n 如果想清静一会儿，我就躲进自己的书房。 \n, a wildlife/bird sanctuary \n 野生动物／鸟类保护区 \n]\n','2019-12-19',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/uksam/uksampl014.mp3'),('sanguine','乐观的，乐天的','uk :ˈsæŋ.ɡwɪn, us :ˈsæŋ.ɡwɪn','[They are less sanguine about the prospects for peace. \n 他们对和平的前景不乐观。 \n]\n','2020-01-17',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/uksan/uksands012.mp3'),('sarcasm','讽刺，挖苦，嘲笑','uk :ˈsɑː.kæz.əm, us :ˈsɑːr.kæz.əm','[ You have been working hard,  he said with heavy sarcasm, as he looked at the empty page. \n “你工作真卖力，”他看着空白页狠狠地挖苦说道。 \n]\n','2020-03-06',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/uksap/uksappy002.mp3'),('sardonic','讥讽的，冷嘲的，轻蔑的','uk :sɑːˈdɒn.ɪk, us :sɑːrˈdɑː.nɪk','[a sardonic smile/look/comment \n 讥讽的微笑／嘲讽的表情／尖刻的评论 \n]\n','2019-12-20',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/uksap/uksappy012.mp3'),('satchel','（旧时的）皮书包，小背包','uk :ˈsætʃ.əl, us :ˈsætʃ.əl','[]\n','2020-03-06',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/uksat/uksatan003.mp3'),('scale','标度，刻度；等级比例；比例尺大小；规模；范围秤，磅秤一架天平音阶（鱼、蛇等动物皮肤表层的）鳞，鳞片（水管或容器内壁的）水垢爬越；攀登刮除（牙石或牙斑）','uk :skeɪl, us :skeɪl','[the Centigrade/Fahrenheit scale \n 摄氏／华氏温标 \n, How would you rate his work on a scale of 1 to 5? \n 按照1到5的等级，你给他的工作打几分？ \n, a scale of 1:50,000 \n 比例尺为1:50000 \n, This map is large scale (= things are shown in detail). \n 这张地图的比例尺很大。 \n, Is the bridge drawn to scale (= so that it shows the exact shape of the bridge, but much smaller)? \n 这座桥是按比例画的吗？ \n, He was building a scale model of the Empire State Building. \n 他正在做一个帝国大厦的比例模型。 \n, We don t yet know the scale of the problem. \n 我们还不知道问题有多严重。 \n, Nuclear weapons cause destruction on a massive scale (= cause a lot of destruction). \n 核武器杀伤力很大。 \n, My parents used to entertain friends on a large/small scale (= they had large/small parties). \n 我父母过去常常举行大／小规模的宴会招待朋友。 \n, kitchen/bathroom scales \n 厨房用秤／浴室体重秤 \n, the scale of G major \n G大调音阶 \n, You should practise your scales every day. \n 你得每天练习音阶。 \n, The prisoner scaled the high prison wall and ran off. \n 囚犯攀越监狱的高墙逃跑了。 \n, The dentist scaled and polished my teeth last week. \n 上星期牙医给我洗了牙并进行了抛光。 \n]\n','2020-01-14',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/uksax/uksax__019.mp3'),('scandal','丑行；丑闻；震惊；反感丑闻报道丢脸，耻辱','uk :ˈskæn.dəl, us :ˈskæn.dəl','[a financial/political/sex scandal \n 财政／政治／性丑闻 \n, Their affair caused/created a scandal in the office. \n 他们的风流韵事在办公室里成了丑闻。 \n, The scandal broke (= became public knowledge) right at the beginning of the Conservative Party Conference. \n 就在保守党大会开幕的那一刻，丑闻曝了出来。 \n, If there is the slightest suggestion/hint of scandal, the public will no longer trust us. \n 只要有哪怕一丝丑闻，公众就再也不会信任我们。 \n, Some magazines contain nothing but scandal and gossip. \n 有些杂志专门报道丑闻，散播小道消息。 \n, to spread scandal \n 传播丑闻 \n, [ + (that) ] \n It s a scandal (that) children are treated in this way. \n 这样对待孩子真是太可耻了。 \n]\n','2019-12-13',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/uksca/ukscamp004.mp3'),('scar','疤，伤疤，伤痕精神创伤外观的破坏结疤；留下伤痕','uk :skɑːr, us :skɑːr','[a prominent/a noticeable/an ugly scar \n 凸出的／显眼的／丑陋的伤疤 \n, That burn will leave a bad scar. \n 烧伤会留下严重的伤疤。 \n, scar tissue \n 瘢痕组织 \n, His early years in the refugee camp left a deep psychological scar. \n 早年的难民营生活给他留下了深深的心理创伤。 \n, Every village bears the scars of war . \n 每一个村庄都布满了战争留下的疮痍。 \n, He was scarred as a result of the fire. \n 那场大火给他留下了伤疤。 \n, igurative \n His experiences in the army left him scarred for life (= had a serious mental effect on him for the rest of his life). \n 他的军旅生涯给他留下了终身的心灵创伤。 \n]\n','2020-01-09',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/uksca/ukscamp016.mp3'),('scatter','散开，分散；使分散，驱散撒，撒播，撒于…上','uk :ˈskæt.ər, us :ˈskæt̬.ɚ','[The protesters scattered at the sound of gunshots. \n 听到枪声后抗议者便散开了。 \n, The soldiers came in and scattered the crowd. \n 士兵进来把人群驱散了。 \n, Scatter the powder around the plants. \n 把这种药粉撒在植物周围。 \n, I scattered grass seed all over the lawn. \n 我将草籽撒在整个草坪上。 \n, I scattered the whole lawn with grass seed. \n 我在整个草坪上都撒下草籽。 \n]\n','2020-01-20',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/uksca/ukscarl009.mp3'),('scavenge','（从废弃物中）觅食；捡破烂（野生动物）以腐肉为食','uk :ˈskæv.ɪndʒ, us :ˈskæv.ɪndʒ','[The flood has left people and animals desperately scavenging for food. \n 因遭受水灾，村民和牲畜四处寻觅食物。 \n, We managed to scavenge a lot of furniture from the dump. \n 我们从当地的垃圾堆里捡到了许多家具。 \n]\n','2019-12-20',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/uksca/ukscarl015.mp3'),('sceptical','怀疑的，持怀疑态度的','uk :ˈskep.tɪ.kəl, us :ˈskep.tɪ.kəl','[Many experts remain sceptical about/of his claims. \n 很多专家对他的主张仍然持怀疑态度。 \n]\n','2019-10-07',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/uksca/ukscarl026.mp3'),('scholar','（尤指大学的）学者聪颖好学者；善于学习者','uk :ˈskɒl.ər, us :ˈskɑː.lɚ',NULL,'2021-03-08',6,8,1,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/uksch/uksched030.mp3'),('sclerosis','（尤指动脉的）硬化','uk :skləˈrəʊ.sɪs, us :-ˈroʊ-','[]\n','2020-01-23',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/uksci/uksciro005.mp3'),('scoff','嘲笑，讥笑狼吞虎咽地吃','uk :skɒf, us :skɑːf','[The critics scoffed at his paintings. \n 批评家对他的画作嗤之以鼻。 \n, Years ago people would have scoffed at the idea that cars would be built by robots. \n 多年前，人们会嘲笑让机器人来制造汽车这种想法。 \n, I baked a huge cake this morning, and the kids scoffed the lot. \n 我今天早上烤了一个大蛋糕，孩子们狼吞虎咽地全吃光了。 \n]\n','2020-03-11',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/uksci/uksciro007.mp3'),('screw','螺丝（钉）扭转，旋转监狱看守（尤为犯人用语）性行为；性伙伴（同 thumbscrew）用螺丝固定（或拧紧）（用类似螺丝的东西）固定，拧紧旋上，拧合（尤指出于不赞同或疼痛）扭曲（面部）将（尤指纸或布）揉成团拧牢，旋紧骗，欺骗（与…）发生性关系','uk :skruː, us :skruː',NULL,'2021-03-08',5,7,1,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/ukscr/ukscrap025.mp3'),('scrutiny','细看，仔细审查','uk :ˈskruː.tɪ.ni, us :ˈskruː.t̬ən.i',NULL,'2021-03-08',15,17,1,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/ukscr/ukscrum010.mp3'),('seal','海豹密封垫；密封装置封口封蜡；印章；封条封，密封（用特殊液体）封盖…的表面封上（信或包裹）确认，正式批准（协议）','uk :siːl, us :siːl','[Clean the seal on/around the fridge door regularly so that it remains airtight. \n 定期清洁冰箱门上的密封条，可以使它保持密闭。 \n, The lawyer stamped the certificate with her seal. \n 律师在证书上盖上了她的印章。 \n, This floor has just been sealed (with varnish), so don t walk on it! \n 地板刚刚上过清漆，别在上面走！ \n, Seal the package (up) with tape. \n 用透明胶带把包裹封起来。 \n, He sealed (down) the envelope and put a stamp on it. \n 他封上信封，贴上邮票。 \n, The two leaders sealed their agreement with a handshake. \n 两位领导人握手表示达成协议。 \n]\n','2020-03-31',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/ukscu/ukscutt017.mp3'),('secede','退出，脱离（国家或政府）','uk :sɪˈsiːd, us :sɪˈsiːd','[There is likely to be civil war if the region tries to secede from the south. \n 如果这一地区想脱离南方而独立，很可能会爆发内战。 \n]\n','2019-10-08',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/uksea/uksear_030.mp3'),('secretarial','秘书的，文秘的','uk :ˌsek.rəˈteə.ri.əl, us :ˌsek.rəˈter.i.əl','[a secretarial school \n 文秘学院 \n, She s found some part-time secretarial work. \n 她找到了一份兼职的秘书工作。 \n]\n','2019-11-08',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/uksec/ukseces015.mp3'),('secretion','分泌；分泌液','uk :sɪˈkriː.ʃən, us :sɪˈkriː.ʃən','[The excessive secretion of gastric juices in the gut causes ulcers. \n 胃中胃液分泌过多会导致胃溃疡。 \n, toxic secretions \n 有毒分泌物 \n]\n','2020-01-24',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/uksec/ukseces019.mp3'),('security','保护（措施）；安全（保障）保安人员保障；牢靠保证金；担保品证券；债券（在家庭或一段关系中）安全感；安心','uk :sɪˈkjʊə.rə.ti, us :səˈkjʊr.ə.t̬i','[The station was closed for two hours because of a security alert. \n 由于有安全警报，车站关闭了两小时。 \n, 30 demonstrators were killed in clashes with the security forces over the weekend. \n 周末，30名示威者在与保安部队的冲突中丧生。 \n, The tighter security measures/precautions include video cameras throughout the city centre. \n 加强安全保障措施包括在市中心安装摄像头。 \n, The students were deported because they posed a threat to national security. \n 这些学生因对国家安全构成威胁而被驱逐出境。 \n, The banks must tighten security against fraud. \n 银行必须加强安全措施，防止诈骗。 \n, The most dangerous criminals are held in maximum-security prisons (= prisons that are as difficult as possible to escape from). \n 最为危险的罪犯被关押在戒备最森严的监狱里。 \n, You\'ll need to notify security if you want to work late in the office. \n 如果想在办公室里工作到很晚，你需要通知保安人员。 \n, If it\'s a choice between higher pay and job security, I\'d prefer to keep my job. \n 如果在更高的薪酬和安稳的工作两者之间进行选择，我宁愿保住工作。 \n, I\'m on a temporary contract and have little financial security (= cannot be sure of having enough money to live on). \n 我签的是临时合同，没什么经济保障。 \n, She used her shares in the company as security against a $23 million bank loan. \n 她用自己在公司的股票作抵押向银行借了2300万美元。 \n, The hotel held onto our suitcases as security while we went to the bank to get money to pay the bill. \n 宾馆扣下我们的行李作为抵押，我们则去银行取钱来付账。 \n, Most children need the security of a stable family life. \n 大多数孩子需要稳定的家庭生活带来的安全感。 \n]\n','2019-10-07',0,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/uksec/uksecul006.mp3'),('seducer','引诱者；勾引者；诱奸者','uk :sɪˈdʒuː.sər, us :səˈduː.sɚ','[The play tells the story of a wealthy woman who seeks revenge on her heartless seducer. \n 该剧讲的是一个富有的女人试图报复一个引诱了她却又对她无情的人。 \n]\n','2019-11-08',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/uksec/uksecul020.mp3'),('seminary','神学院','uk :ˈsem.ɪ.nər.i, us :ˈsem.ɪ.ner.i','[]\n','2019-12-19',0,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/uksel/ukselfs024.mp3'),('sentimentality','感伤，多愁善感','uk :ˌsen.tɪˈmen.təl.ɪ.zəm, us :ˌsen.t̬əˈmen.t̬əl.ɪ.zəm','[Caring for animals is not sentimentality - it reinforces our respect for life. \n 照顾动物并非多愁善感——这使我们更加尊重生命。 \n]\n','2020-02-21',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/uksen/uksensi014.mp3'),('sequel','（书、电影或戏剧的）续篇，续集后果；结局','uk :ˈsiː.kwəl, us :ˈsiː.kwəl','[I m reading the sequel to  Gone with the Wind . \n 我正在读《飘》的续集。 \n, There was a dramatic sequel to last Thursday s scandalous revelations when the minister suddenly announced his resignation. \n 部长突然宣布辞职，上星期四的丑闻曝光便有了戏剧般的结局。 \n]\n','2020-01-09',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/uksep/uksept_009.mp3'),('sergeant','军士（英国或其他国家的）巡佐；（美国的）警佐','uk :ˈsɑː.dʒənt, us :ˈsɑːr.dʒənt','[Sergeant Lewis/Tom Lewis \n 刘易斯军士／汤姆·刘易斯军士 \n, [ as form of address ] \n Dismiss the men, Sergeant. \n 军士，解散部下吧。 \n, Sergeant Bates/Bill Bates \n 盖茨警佐／比尔·盖茨警佐 \n, [ as form of address ] \n Thank you, Sergeant. \n 谢谢你，警佐。 \n]\n','2020-03-05',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/ukser/ukseren010.mp3'),('serrated','锯齿边的','uk :səˈreɪ.tɪd, us :səˈreɪ.t̬ɪd','[You really need a knife with a serrated edge for cutting bread. \n 你真的需要一把有锯齿刃的刀子来切面包。 \n]\n','2020-01-10',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/ukser/ukseren021.mp3'),('several','一些；几个各自的，分别的','uk :ˈsev.ər.əl, us :ˈsev.ɚ.əl','[I ve seen  Gone with the Wind  several times. \n 我已经看过好几遍《乱世佳人》了。 \n, Several people have complained about the plans. \n 已经有好几个人抱怨过这项计划了。 \n, Several of my friends are learning English. \n 我有几个朋友在学英语。 \n, We are striving to reach an agreement which will satisfy the several interests of the parties concerned. \n 我们正在努力达成一个能满足有关各方各自利益的协议。 \n]\n','2020-01-23',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/uksev/ukseven004.mp3'),('severe','非常严重的；剧烈的；惨重的极度的；非常困难的不和善的；冷酷的；严厉的；苛刻的不加装饰的，朴素的，简朴的','uk :sɪˈvɪər, us :səˈvɪr','[a severe chest infection/leg injury/toothache \n 十分严重的胸腔感染／腿伤／牙痛 \n, This is a school for children with severe learning difficulties. \n 这是一所为有严重学习障碍的孩子设立的学校。 \n, In parts of Africa there is a severe food/water shortage. \n 非洲的一些地方存在严重的粮食／水资源短缺问题。 \n, There is expected to be a severe frost tonight. \n 今晚预计会出现严重的霜冻。 \n, Severe cutbacks in public spending have been announced. \n 已经宣布对公共开支进行大幅度削减。 \n, This will be a severe test of our strength. \n 这将是对我们实力的严峻考验。 \n, The headteacher spoke in a severe voice. \n 校长说话的口吻很严厉。 \n, The president is currently facing severe criticism. \n 总统目前正遭到严厉的批评。 \n, There are severe penalties for failing to declare all your income to the Inland Revenue. \n 未向税务机关申报个人全部收入会受到严厉的处罚。 \n, She wore a severe black dress, and plain black shoes. \n 她穿了一件朴素的黑连衣裙和一双普通的黑鞋子。 \n, I don\'t like these severe modern buildings. \n 我不喜欢这些没有任何装饰的现代建筑。 \n]\n','2019-10-08',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/uksev/ukseven007.mp3'),('sewn','缝；做针线活儿缝制（衣服）缝合（伤口）','uk :səʊ, us :soʊ','[My grandmother taught me to sew. \n 我祖母教我做针线活儿。 \n, I made this skirt just by sewing two pieces of material together. \n 我把两块料子缝在一起，就做成了这条裙子。 \n, He sewed the badge neatly onto his uniform. \n 他把徽章精心地缝在制服上。 \n, She sews all her children s clothes. \n 孩子们的衣服都是她缝制的。 \n, The muscle layer needs to be sewn first. \n 先要缝合肌肉层。 \n, His finger was cut off when he caught it in a machine, but the surgeon was able to sew it back on. \n 他的手指被机器夹住切断了，不过外科医生把断指缝合上去了。 \n]\n','2020-01-03',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/uksev/ukseven010.mp3'),('sexual','性的，性行为的有性繁殖的性别的','uk :ˈsek.sjʊəl, us :','[Most people remember their first sexual experience. \n 大多数人都记得他们的第一次性经历。 \n, a sexual relationship \n 性关系 \n, sexual assault/harassment \n 性侵犯／性骚扰 \n, formal sexual intercourse (= the act of having sex) \n 性交 \n, sexual orientation/preference (= whether someone chooses to have sex with men, women, or both) \n 性倾向 \n, sexual reproduction \n 有性繁殖 \n, Sexual equality will not be achieved until there is more provision for childcare. \n 只有提供更多的幼儿保育服务，才会实现男女平等。 \n, Some steps have been taken towards ending sexual discrimination (= treating people unfairly because of which sex they are). \n 已经采取了一些措施来消除性别歧视。 \n]\n','2020-02-26',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/uksev/ukseven029.mp3'),('shatter','（使）破碎；粉碎终结；严重破坏','uk :ˈʃæt.ər, us :ˈʃæt̬.ɚ','[The glass shattered into a thousand tiny pieces. \n 玻璃碎成无数块细小的碎片。 \n, His leg was shattered in the accident. \n 他