rm - now I just have to add the details. \n 我的书已经有了框架——现在我只需要添加细节了。 \n]\n','2020-03-26',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/uksit/uksitua026.mp3'),('skinny','非常瘦的，皮包骨头的（尤指咖啡）低脂的紧身的（有关…的）确切消息，真实情况，贴身信息紧身牛仔裤','uk :ˈskɪn.i, us :ˈskɪn.i','[You should eat more - you re too skinny. \n 你应该多吃点儿，你太瘦了。 \n, a skinny latte \n 低脂牛奶咖啡 \n, skinny jeans \n 紧身牛仔裤 \n, Get the skinny on hundreds of celebs in our  People Profiles  section. \n 在我们的《人物介绍》栏目可以看到几百位明星的贴身信息。 \n, A white shirt and skinnies is always a good look. \n 白衬衫配紧身牛仔裤总是很好看。 \n]\n','2019-12-27',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/ukski/ukskinl002.mp3'),('slang','俚语谩骂','uk :slæŋ, us :slæŋ','[army slang \n 军队俚语 \n, a slang expression \n 一句俚语 \n,  Chicken  is slang for someone who isn t very brave. \n chicken 是用来称呼胆小者的俚语。 \n, The players started slanging each other in the middle of the game. \n 比赛到中局阶段时，球员们开始互相谩骂。 \n]\n','2021-03-23',3,6,1,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/uksla/uksland004.mp3'),('slice','（切下的食物）薄片（钱等的）份额，部分餐刀；（餐桌用的）小铲（网球运动中）削（球）（高尔夫球和棒球运动中）斜切（球），削（球）把…切成薄片切，割；切开；割破（高尔夫球和棒球运动中）斜切（球），削球（网球运动中）削（球）','uk :slaɪs, us :slaɪs','[a slice of bread/cake \n 一片面包／蛋糕 \n, cucumber/lemon slices \n 黄瓜／柠檬片 \n, Would you like another slice of ham/beef? \n 要不要再来一片火腿／牛肉？ \n, We agreed before we did the deal that we d both take an equal slice of the profit. \n 成交前，我们商定双方各拿利润的一半。 \n, The film presents us with a fascinating slice of history. \n 这部电影向我们展示了一个非常有趣的历史片段。 \n, a cake/fish slice \n 蛋糕刀／煎鱼铲 \n, That wonderful backhand slice of Maria s sends the ball where her opponent just can t reach it. \n 玛丽亚那一记漂亮的反手削球恰好把球打到了对手够不到的地方。 \n, Slice the mushrooms thinly and fry in butter. \n 把蘑菇切成薄片，用黄油煎一下。 \n, [ + two objects ] \n Could you slice me a very thin piece of cake/slice a very thin piece of cake for me? \n 你能帮我切一薄片蛋糕吗? \n, He screamed as the blade sliced into his leg. \n 刀片切入他的腿时，他发出一声尖叫。 \n, igurative \n She watched his slim strong body as it sliced effortlessly through the water. \n 她看着他细长结实的身体毫不费力地破水前进。 \n, Sara sliced the ball, sending it a hundred yards or so to the left. \n 萨拉打了一个斜切球，将球向左送了100米左右。 \n]\n','2020-02-21',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/uksle/uksleep016.mp3'),('slick','熟练自如的，娴熟的油滑的，华而不实的浮油（同 oil slick）高级亮光纸印刷的杂志（同 glossy magazine）使（头发）光滑，使亮滑','uk :slɪk, us :slɪk','[Manilow gave the slick, polished performance that we ve come to expect. \n 正如我们所期望的那样，马尼洛的表演挥洒自如、技艺精湛。 \n, A slick pass from Eaves to Brinkworth set up the goal. \n 布林克沃斯接伊夫斯的妙传射门成功。 \n, It s that sort of slick sales talk that I mistrust. \n 那种油腔滑调的推销宣传正是我所不相信的。 \n, He slicked his hair back with gel. \n 他打了发胶将头发向后梳平整。 \n]\n','2020-02-27',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/uksle/uksleep019.mp3'),('slicked','熟练自如的，娴熟的油滑的，华而不实的浮油（同 oil slick）高级亮光纸印刷的杂志（同 glossy magazine）使（头发）光滑，使亮滑','uk :slɪk, us :slɪk','[Manilow gave the slick, polished performance that we ve come to expect. \n 正如我们所期望的那样，马尼洛的表演挥洒自如、技艺精湛。 \n, A slick pass from Eaves to Brinkworth set up the goal. \n 布林克沃斯接伊夫斯的妙传射门成功。 \n, It s that sort of slick sales talk that I mistrust. \n 那种油腔滑调的推销宣传正是我所不相信的。 \n, He slicked his hair back with gel. \n 他打了发胶将头发向后梳平整。 \n]\n','2020-03-25',2,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/uksle/uksleep019.mp3'),('slip','滑倒；失脚移出正确的位置，滑走溜走；迅速地做；悄悄地做变糟；下降，退步逃离，离开价值降低纸条；小纸片小错误，疏漏摔倒；滑跤（情况）变糟女式衬裙两座码头之间可停船的水面瘦小的逃离（某人），摆脱（某人）','uk :slɪp, us :slɪp','[She slipped on the ice. \n 她在冰上滑倒了。 \n, Careful you don t slip - there s water on the floor. \n 小心别滑倒了——地板上有水。 \n, The razor slipped while he was shaving and he cut himself. \n 他刮胡子时剃须刀一滑，把自己划伤了。 \n, Her hat had slipped over one eye. \n 她的一只眼睛被滑下的帽子盖住了。 \n, He could feel the rope slipping out of his grasp. \n 他能感觉到绳子正从他手中滑走。 \n, Just slip out of the room while nobody s looking. \n 趁没人注意时溜出房间。 \n, She slipped between the cool cotton sheets and was soon asleep. \n 她钻进凉爽的棉褥单里，很快就睡着了。 \n, He slipped a piece of paper into my hand with his address on it. \n 他偷偷把一张写有他地址的纸塞到我的手里。 \n, [ + two objects ] \n If you slip the waiter some money/slip some money to the waiter he ll give you the best table. \n 如果你偷偷塞点钱给侍者，他会为你安排最好的位置。 \n, Productivity in the factory has slipped noticeably in the last year. \n 工厂一年来生产率显著下降。 \n, The schedule has started to slip (= things are happening later than planned). \n 日程开始推迟。 \n, I don t know what went wrong, I must be slipping. \n 我不知道哪里出了问题，我一定是退步了。 \n, The ship slipped its moorings. \n 船漂离了停泊处。 \n, The dollar slipped against the Japanese yen. \n 美元对日元汇率下降。 \n, a slip of paper \n 一张纸条 \n, If you want to order a book fill out the green slip. \n 如果想订购书，就填写那张绿色单子。 \n, She s made one or two slips - mainly spelling errors - but it s basically well written. \n 她犯了一两个小错误——主要是拼写错误——不过基本上写得很不错。 \n, One slip meant a long tumble to the rocks below. \n 一旦滑倒就意味着一路摔滚到下面的石头上。 \n, A slip in the value of the U.S. dollar helped push prices higher. \n 美元下跌推高了价格。 \n, a slip in standards \n 水平下跌 \n, I knew her when she was a slip of a girl. \n 她还是个小女孩的时候我就认识她了。 \n]\n','2020-02-27',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/uksli/ukslimm010.mp3'),('slippery','湿滑的，容易打滑的狡猾的，滑头的','uk :ˈslɪp.ər.i, us :ˈslɪp.ɚ.i','[slippery soap \n 湿滑的肥皂 \n, a slippery floor \n 湿滑的地板 \n, The road was wet and slippery. \n 道路又湿又滑。 \n, He s as slippery as an eel - you can never get a straight answer out of him. \n 他非常滑头——你永远无法从他嘴里得到直率的回答。 \n, He s a slippery customer (= person), and I ve never felt comfortable with him. \n 他是个狡猾的家伙，和他在一起我总是感到不舒服。 \n]\n','2019-12-20',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/uksli/ukslimm016.mp3'),('slog-away','辛苦干活','','null\n','2020-02-13',0,0,0,'null'),('slogging','苦干，锲而不舍地做（尤指困难或乏味的工作）艰难行进，跋涉（不加控制地）猛击（球）一段时间的艰苦努力（不加控制的）猛击','uk :slɒɡ, us :slɑːɡ','[I ve been slogging away for days on this essay and I m still not finished. \n 我为了这篇文章已经埋头苦干好几天了，但还没有完成。 \n, Despite the rain, they slogged on for another six miles. \n 尽管下着雨，他们还是又艰难跋涉了6英里。 \n, They slogged up the trail in the rain. \n 他们在雨中沿着小道向上跋涉。 \n, The soldiers slogged through mud. \n 士兵们在泥泞中跋涉。 \n, This semester was a long hard slog; I m glad it s over. \n 这个学期非常艰苦，很高兴终于结束了。 \n, That last hill before the finishing line was a long slog! \n 终点线前的最后一座小山是一段漫长而艰难的赛程！ \n, And that was a real slog from Kumar. \n 那是库马尔的一次真正的大力击球。 \n]\n','2020-02-13',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/ukslo/ukslobb004.mp3'),('slot','狭缝；（尤指）投币口，狭槽（为某活动安排的）时段被（能）放于狭槽中','uk :slɒt, us :slɑːt','[I put my money in the slot and pressed the button but nothing came out. \n 我把钱放入投币口，按了按钮，但没有东西出来。 \n, The holder has slots for 100 CDs. \n 这个CD架的槽口可以放100张CD。 \n, The programme will occupy that half-hour slot before the six o clock news. \n 那个节目将在六点新闻前的半小时这一时段播出。 \n, The legs of the chair are meant to slot into the holes at the back. \n 椅子腿应该要插到后面的孔里。 \n, Do these two pieces slot together? \n 这两个部件能插在一起吗? \n, Slot piece A into piece B, taking care to keep the two pieces at right angles. \n 把 A 件插入 B 件，注意使二者保持正确的角度。 \n]\n','2019-12-24',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/ukslo/ukslobb018.mp3'),('smack','（尤指作为惩戒孩子的方式）掌掴，打撞；使劲摔（作为惩戒手段的）打巴掌，掴（用握成拳的手）打呯的一声，啪的一声响吻海洛因不偏不倚地，正好径直，猛地；砰然作声地','uk :smæk, us :smæk','[I never smack my children. \n 我从来不打孩子。 \n, I ll smack your bottom if you don t behave yourself. \n 如果你表现不好，我就打你屁股。 \n, I smacked my head on the corner of the shelf. \n 我的头撞在了架子角上。 \n, She smacked her books down on the table and stormed out of the room. \n 她啪地把书摔在桌子上，气冲冲地离开了房间。 \n, You re going to get a smack on the bottom if you don t stop throwing your toys. \n 如果你再乱扔玩具，就该打屁股了。 \n, I gave him a smack on the jaw. \n 我一拳头打在他下巴上。 \n, She slammed her briefcase down on the desk with a smack. \n 她啪的一声把她的皮箱放到桌子上。 \n, a big smack on the lips \n 在嘴唇上的响亮一吻 \n, How long has she been on smack? \n 她吸海洛因多长时间了？ \n, She lives smack in the middle of Shanghai. \n 她住在上海市的正中心。 \n, S \n The kids are smack dab in the middle of the fight between their parents. \n 父母吵架时，孩子们被夹在正中间。 \n, I wasn t looking where I was going and walked smack into a lamppost. \n 我没有看路，直愣愣地撞到了灯柱上。 \n]\n','2019-12-26',0,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/ukslu/ukslutt010.mp3'),('smolder','（smoulder 的美式拼写）','uk :ˈsməʊl.dər, us :ˈsmoʊl.dɚ','[]\n','2020-03-06',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/uksmo/uksmoke009.mp3'),('smoulder','无火焰地慢慢烧，闷燃（问题或不良局势）持续存在，维持（强烈的情绪）郁积，闷在心头欲火中烧；心驰神往','uk :ˈsməʊl.dər, us :ˈsmoʊl.dɚ','[a smouldering fire \n 闷燃的火 \n, smouldering embers \n 闷燃的余烬 \n, The fire was started by a smouldering cigarette. \n 大火是由闷燃的烟蒂引起的。 \n, The dispute is still smouldering, five years after the negotiations began. \n 谈判开始到现在都5年了，争端的暗火仍在燃烧。 \n, She was smouldering with rage as she explained how her son had been killed. \n 她强压着满腔的怒火，叙述了儿子被害的经过。 \n, He gazed at her with smouldering eyes, wishing she wasn t married. \n 他那双充满欲望的眼睛直勾勾地盯着她，心里希望她还没有结婚。 \n]\n','2020-03-06',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/uksmo/uksmoke009.mp3'),('smuggle','走私；（常指非法）偷运','uk :ˈsmʌɡ.əl, us :ˈsmʌɡ.əl','[She was caught trying to smuggle 26 kilos of heroin out of/into the country. \n 她在企图把26千克海洛因走私出境／入境时被抓获。 \n, They managed to smuggle a video of the captive journalists out of the prison. \n 他们设法把被俘记者的录像带偷偷带出了监狱。 \n]\n','2020-01-03',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/uksmo/uksmoke026.mp3'),('snap','突然折断，咔嚓一声折断突然无法控制情感，突然发作（尤指动怒）（使）啪地突然移动（到某位置）迅速恢复啪地关上；啪地合上咬，咬人厉声说，恶声恶气地说拍快照把（两片金属或塑料片）扣上咔嚓声；突然折断（或合上）的声音摁扣，子母扣快照，快相呼“同”牌游戏（一种纸牌游戏，玩家抢先看到有两张相同的牌时呼“同”）容易的事，好办的事（美式橄榄球）开球匆忙的；不加思索的；不做准备的（呼“同”牌游戏中的）“同！”（发现两件事物相同时所说）太巧了！','uk :snæp, us :snæp','[You ll snap that ruler if you bend it too far. \n 如果你把那把尺子弯得太厉害，它就会咔嚓一下折断。 \n, Some vandal s snapped off my car aerial again. \n 某个蓄意作恶的家伙又把我的汽车天线折断了。 \n, When she asked me to postpone my trip to help her move to her new house, I just snapped (= got angry). \n 她让我推迟旅行帮她搬家时，我一下子就火了。 \n, Tendons store elastic energy by stretching and then snapping back into shape like rubber bands. \n 腱通过橡皮筋似的拉伸和迅速缩回贮存了弹力。 \n, Simply snap the pieces into place. \n 把这些小片啪地一声推到位就行。 \n, After substantial losses last year, the company has snapped back to profitability (= started making profits again). \n 去年出现巨额亏损之后，这家公司的经济状况又迅速好转，开始盈利了。 \n, She snapped her book shut and got up to leave. \n 她啪地合上书，起身离开了。 \n, Her mouth snapped shut when she realized he d heard everything she d said about him. \n 意识到自己所说的一切关于他的话都被他听到了之后，她立刻闭上了嘴。 \n, The guard dog was snarling and snapping behind the fence. \n 那条看门狗正在篱笆后面吠咬。 \n, There s no need to snap at me - it s not my fault that you lost your wallet. \n 何必对我这样恶声恶气——你丢了钱包又不是我的错。 \n, [ + speech ] \n  Well, I hate you too!  she snapped. \n “哼，我也恨你！”她厉声说。 \n, He was arrested for snapping photos of a military parade. \n 他因拍摄了阅兵式的快照而被逮捕。 \n, She s very pleased with her new camera and was snapping away the whole time we were abroad. \n 她对自己的新相机十分满意，我们在国外时，她一直不停地拍照。 \n, He snapped up his jacket. \n 他把外套扣上了。 \n, She broke the stick over her knee with a loud snap. \n 她咔嚓一声用膝盖折断了棍子。 \n, holiday snaps \n 假期拍的快照 \n, Did you take many snaps while you were away? \n 你出游的时候拍了很多照片吗？ \n, a game of snap \n 呼“同”牌游戏 \n,  Will you finish on time?   Sure thing. It s a snap.  \n “你能按时完成吗？”“当然，太容易了。” \n, Talking to girls is a snap for him. \n 和女孩子交谈对他来说十分容易。 \n, He always makes snap decisions and never thinks about their consequences. \n 他总是匆忙作决定，从不考虑后果。 \n, Snap! We re wearing the same shirts! \n 太巧了！我们穿了同样的衬衫！ \n]\n','2020-03-05',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/uksmu/uksmut_011.mp3'),('snark','故意中傷的批評','','null\n','2020-02-27',0,0,0,'null'),('sneeze','打喷嚏喷嚏','uk :sniːz, us :sniːz','[Cats make him sneeze - I think he s allergic to them. \n 猫会使他打喷嚏——我想他对猫过敏。 \n, He has all the classic symptoms of a cold - the coughs and sneezes and the sore throat. \n 他具备感冒的所有典型症状——咳嗽、打喷嚏和嗓子疼。 \n]\n','2020-01-10',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/uksne/uksneak005.mp3'),('soapy','含有肥皂的；像肥皂的','uk :ˈsəʊ.pi, us :ˈsoʊ.pi','[I soaked it in some soapy water and the stains came out. \n 我把它浸泡在肥皂水中，污渍就被洗去了。 \n, I used to think avocados tasted soapy when I was a child. \n 我小时候曾认为鳄梨的味道像肥皂。 \n]\n','2019-12-26',0,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/uksno/uksnows025.mp3'),('sock','短袜，袜子重重的一击（用拳头）打，击（棒球运动中）猛击，狠打（球）','uk :sɒk, us :sɑːk','[a pair of socks \n 一双短袜 \n, nylon/woollen/cotton socks \n 尼龙／羊毛／纯棉短袜 \n, thermal socks \n 保暖袜 \n, ankle/knee socks \n 及脚踝／膝的袜子 \n, Put on your shoes and socks. \n 穿上你的鞋袜。 \n, The little boy was wearing odd socks (= socks of different colours). \n 小男孩穿着两只不配对的袜子。 \n, a sock on the jaw \n 下巴上挨的重重一拳 \n, He socked the policeman on the jaw/in the eye. \n 他冲着警察的下巴／眼睛就是一拳。 \n]\n','2020-01-03',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/uksob/uksober023.mp3'),('socket','插座；插槽（人体的）槽，臼','uk :ˈsɒk.ɪt, us :ˈsɑː.kɪt','[an electrical socket \n 电插座 \n, a light socket \n 灯头 \n, K \n He had forgotten to plug the television into the mains socket. \n 他忘了把电视机插头插进墙上的插座里。 \n, The air freshener plugs into a car s lighter socket. \n 空气清新器插头插在汽车点烟器插孔里。 \n, a tooth/eye socket \n 牙槽／眼窝 \n, a ball-and-socket joint like the hip joint \n 像髋关节似的球窝关节 \n]\n','2020-03-12',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/uksob/uksober024.mp3'),('soil','泥土，土壤国家；国土耕作，务农（尤指因大便）弄脏','uk :sɔɪl, us :sɔɪl','[light/heavy/fertile soil \n 轻质／黏重／肥沃土 \n, sandy or chalky soils \n 沙质或白垩质土壤 \n, It was the first time we had set foot on foreign/French/American soil (= gone to a foreign country/France/America). \n 那是我们第一次踏上异国／法国／美国的土地。 \n, Gardening is a way for city dwellers to return to the soil. \n 从事园艺是城市居民务农的一种方式。 \n, soiled nappies/underwear/sheets \n 弄脏的尿布／内衣／床单 \n]\n','2020-02-27',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/uksod/uksodiu019.mp3'),('solicitude','关怀','uk :səˈlɪs.ɪ.tʃuːd, us :səˈlɪs.ɪ.tuːd','[\'m touched by your solicitude.\n]\n','2020-03-06',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english/uk_pron/u/uks/uksol/uksoldi020.mp3'),('solid','坚固的；坚硬的实心的，无空隙的纯的，无杂质的固体的，固态的（尤指给婴儿或病人吃的食物）固体的确定的；扎实的；可信赖的持续的，不间断的立体；立体图形固体物质固体食物','uk :ˈsɒl.ɪd, us :ˈsɑː.lɪd','[solid ground \n 坚硬的地面 \n, a solid object \n 坚固的物体 \n, a solid structure \n 坚固的结构 \n, solid rock \n 实心的石头 \n, a solid oak table \n 质地坚实的橡木桌子 \n, solid doors/walls \n 实心门／墙 \n, a solid line of traffic \n 拥挤不堪的车流 \n, The lecture hall was packed solid (with students). \n 演讲大厅里挤满了（学生）。 \n, solid gold/silver candlesticks \n 纯金／银烛台 \n, a white rose on a solid blue background \n 纯蓝色背景下的一枝白玫瑰 \n, Liquid and solid waste is collected in the tank. \n 液体和固体废物集中在箱罐里。 \n, Freeze the mixture for about three hours or so until solid. \n 把混合物冷冻3小时左右，直到其变成固体。 \n, That rice pudding was the first solid food he s eaten since his operation. \n 那种大米布丁是他手术后吃的第一种固体食物。 \n, This provided solid evidence that he committed the crime. \n 这提供了确凿证据，证明他犯了罪。 \n, The drama course gives students a solid grounding in the basic techniques of acting. \n 戏剧课为学生们的表演基本功打下了扎实的基础。 \n, I slept for eleven solid hours. \n 我整整睡了11个小时。 \n, The hotel was booked solid all of December. \n 整个12月份该宾馆的客房都被预订出去了。 \n, A cube and a pyramid are both solids. \n 立方体和棱锥体都是立体图形。 \n]\n','2020-03-11',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/uksol/uksoldi021.mp3'),('soliloquy','（戏剧中的）独白','uk :səˈlɪl.ə.kwi, us :səˈlɪl.ə.kwi','[Hamlet s soliloquy starts  To be or not to be . \n 哈姆雷特的独白以“生存还是毁灭”开头。 \n]\n','2020-03-18',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/uksol/uksoldi029.mp3'),('sophisticated','精于世故的，老练的；见多识广的；很有品位的精密的，复杂的；高级的','uk :səˈfɪs.tɪ.keɪ.tɪd, us :səˈfɪs.tə.keɪ.t̬ɪd','[She was slim, svelte, and sophisticated. \n 她身材苗条，体态娇美，处事练达。 \n, I don t think I have any books that would suit your sophisticated tastes. \n 我认为我没有什么书能满足你那高雅的品位。 \n, He was older than me and from London and I thought him very sophisticated. \n 他比我大，而且来自伦敦，我觉得他为人很老练。 \n, I think a more sophisticated approach is needed to solve this problem. \n 我认为要解决这个问题需要更为高明的方法。 \n, These are among the most sophisticated weapons in the world. \n 这些属于世界上最尖端的武器。 \n]\n','2019-12-20',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/uksoo/uksoon_012.mp3'),('sophomore','（美国大学或高中的）二年级学生','uk :ˈsɒf.ə.mɔːr, us :ˈsɑː.fə.mɔːr','[]\n','2019-12-20',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/uksoo/uksoon_015.mp3'),('sought','搜寻','uk :sɔːt, us :sɑːt',NULL,'2021-03-08',7,9,1,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english/uk_pron/u/uks/uksor/uksorel011.mp3'),('sour','酸的，有酸味的不友好的；坏脾气的，没好气的（使）变酸；（使）酸腐（使）令人不快，（使）不友好酸味鸡尾酒','uk :saʊər, us :saʊr','[These plums are a bit sour. \n 这些李子有点酸。 \n, Overnight, it seemed, their relationship had turned sour. \n 他们的关系似乎在一夜之间变糟了。 \n, She gave me a sour look. \n 她没好气地瞪了我一眼。 \n, Hot weather sours milk. \n 热天会让牛奶变酸。 \n, Milk sours in hot weather. \n 牛奶在热天会变酸。 \n, Her whole attitude to life soured as a result of that experience. \n 那次经历过后，她对生活的整个态度变得很消极。 \n, This incident has soured relations between the two countries. \n 这一事件导致两国关系恶化。 \n, a whisky sour \n 威士忌酸味鸡尾酒 \n]\n','2020-01-03',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/uksou/uksound010.mp3'),('souvenir','纪念品；纪念物','uk :ˌsuː.vənˈɪər, us :ˌsuː.vəˈnɪr',NULL,'2021-03-08',7,9,1,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/uksou/uksouth007.mp3'),('spacious','宽敞的，空间大的','uk :ˈspeɪ.ʃəs, us :ˈspeɪ.ʃəs','[a spacious house/living room \n 宽敞的房子／起居室 \n, spacious accommodation \n 宽敞的住宿条件 \n]\n','2019-12-20',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/uksou/uksouth030.mp3'),('spade','铲，锹黑桃花色，一组黑桃（纸牌中的）黑桃（冒犯性用语）黑人，黑鬼','uk :speɪd, us :speɪd','[a garden spade \n 园艺铲 \n, K \n The kids took their buckets and spades to the beach. \n 孩子们带着他们的桶和铲子到海边去了。 \n, the ace/queen of spades \n 黑桃 A／皇后 \n, Don t you have any spades? \n 你手里有黑桃吗？ \n]\n','2020-03-12',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/ukspa/ukspaci003.mp3'),('spam','（斯帕姆）午餐肉垃圾邮件（通常指广告）给…发垃圾邮件','uk :spæm, us :spæm','[spam fritters \n 油炸午餐肉馅饼 \n, I get so much spam at work. \n 我的工作邮箱收到如此之多的垃圾邮件。 \n]\n','2020-01-15',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/ukspa/ukspaci009.mp3'),('span','一段时间长度；宽度；跨度（桥等的）跨度，跨距，墩距（spin 的过去式）（时间）持续，跨越横跨崭新的；极整洁的，极干净的','uk :spæn, us :spæn','[He has a short attention/concentration span. \n 他的注意力持续时间很短。 \n, an average life span of 70 years \n 平均寿命70岁 \n, Over a span of just three years, the new government has transformed the country s economic prospects. \n 仅仅3年的时间，新政府已经使该国的经济前景出现了改观。 \n, huge wings with a span of over a metre \n 翼展超过1米的巨型翅膀 \n, The bridge crosses the river in a single span. \n 河上的桥是单孔桥。 \n, Tennis has a history spanning several centuries. \n 网球的历史长达几个世纪。 \n, Her acting career spanned almost six decades. \n 她的演艺生涯持续了近60载。 \n, An old bridge spans the river just outside the town. \n 一座老桥横跨在镇外的河上。 \n]\n','2020-03-11',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/ukspa/ukspaci011.mp3'),('spare','额外的，备用的；多余的空闲时间瘦高的，瘦长的简朴的，未装饰的很恼火，很生气饶恕；不伤害；不毁坏使避免，使免遭不遗余力／不惜工本竭尽全力，全力以赴（尤指在自己困难的情况下）抽出，拨出，匀出替（某人）着想剩下，多余备用品（汽车或其他设备的）备件，配件','uk :speər, us :sper','[a spare key/tyre \n 备用钥匙／轮胎 \n, spare sheets and blankets \n 多余的床单和毛毯 \n, Do you have a spare pen? \n 你有多余的笔吗？ \n, We have a spare room if you want to stay overnight with us. \n 要是你想在我们这里过夜的话，我们有一个空房间。 \n, Could I have a word with you when you have a spare moment/minute? \n 如果你有时间，我能否和你谈两句？ \n, K informal \n  Do you want this cake?   Yes, if it s going spare (= if no one else wants it).  \n “你要这块蛋糕吗？”“如果没有别人要，就给我吧。” \n, I like to paint in my spare time. \n 我业余时间喜欢画画。 \n, He had the spare build of a runner. \n 他有着赛跑运动员的瘦长体型。 \n, The interior is spare, almost minimalist. \n 内部是简朴的，几乎是最简单的。 \n, She goes spare if I m so much as five minutes late. \n 如果我迟到5分钟，她就会很生气。 \n, They asked him to spare the women and children. \n 他们要他放过妇女和儿童。 \n, Luckily, I was spared the embarrassment of having to sing in front of everyone. \n 幸运的是，我躲过了在大家面前唱歌的尴尬。 \n, It was a nasty accident - but I ll spare you (= I won t tell you) the gruesome details. \n 那是一起严重的事故——我就不跟你讲那些令人毛骨悚然的细节了。 \n, [ + to infinitive ] \n We will spare no effort to find out who did this. \n 我们会不遗余力，一定查出是谁做了这件事。 \n, She never spared herself in the pursuit of excellence. \n 她竭尽全力追求卓越。 \n, [ + two objects ] \n Could you spare me £20? \n 你能匀给我20英镑吗？ \n, I d love to come, but I can t spare the time. \n 我很想来，但恐怕没时间。 \n, Spare a thought for me tomorrow, when you re lying on a beach, because I ll still be here in the office! \n 明天你躺在海滩上的时候，就想想我吧，因为我还在办公室里！ \n, If you have any woolyarn to spare when you ve finished the sweater, can you make me some gloves? \n 如果你织完毛衣还剩下毛线的话，可以给我织副手套吗？ \n, I caught the plane with only two minutes to spare. \n 我赶上飞机时距离起飞只剩两分钟了。 \n, There s no time/We have no time to spare if we want to get the article written by tomorrow. \n 如果我们想明天就把这篇文章写完，那么就没剩多少时间了。 \n]\n','2020-01-03',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/ukspa/ukspaci022.mp3'),('spawn','（鱼、青蛙等的）卵小动物；小孩（使）产生，（使）突然增长产卵','uk :spɔːn, us :spɑːn','[isapproving \n He looked at me as if I was a spawn of Satan because I was smoking a cigarette. \n 他看着我的样子，仿佛是看到了恶魔一般，就因为我抽烟。 \n, The new economic freedom has spawned hundreds of new small businesses. \n 新的经济自由催生了上百家新的小企业。 \n, Her death spawned countless films and books. \n 她的去世催生了无数电影和书籍。 \n, The frogs haven t spawned yet. \n 青蛙还未产卵。 \n]\n','2019-12-19',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/ukspa/uksparr017.mp3'),('speakeasy','（美国20世纪20至30年代）非法销售饮用酒精饮料的地方','uk :ˈspiːkˌiː.zi, us :ˈspiːkˌiː.zi','[]\n','2019-12-27',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/ukspa/uksparr020.mp3'),('species','（动植物的）种，物种','uk :ˈspiː.ʃiːz, us :ˈspiː.ʃiːz','[Mountain gorillas are an endangered species. \n 山地大猩猩属于濒危物种。 \n, Over a hundred species of insect are found in this area. \n 这一地区有上百种昆虫。 \n, igurative humorous \n Women film directors in Hollywood are a rare species. \n 女性电影导演在好莱坞属于稀有物种。 \n]\n','2019-12-26',0,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/ukspe/ukspeci007.mp3'),('speculate','猜测；推测，推断投机，做投机买卖','uk :ˈspek.jə.leɪt, us :ˈspek.jə.leɪt','[I don t know why she did it - I m just speculating. \n 我不知道她为什么那么做——我只是猜测。 \n, A spokesperson declined to speculate on the cause of the train crash. \n 一位发言人拒绝就火车相撞事件的原因作出推测。 \n, Journalists are speculating about whether interest rates will be cut. \n 记者们在猜测是否会降息。 \n, [ + that ] \n The newspapers have speculated that they will get married next year. \n 报纸猜测他们明年会结婚。 \n, He made his money speculating on the London gold and silver markets. \n 他在伦敦黄金市场和白银市场上做投机生意赚了钱。 \n, The company has been speculating in property for years. \n 这家公司做房地产投机生意已经有好几年了。 \n]\n','2019-12-24',0,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/ukspe/ukspect003.mp3'),('speculator','投机商，投机者','uk :ˈspek.jə.leɪ.tər, us :ˈspek.jə.leɪ.t̬ɚ','[]\n','2020-01-17',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/ukspe/ukspect007.mp3'),('splendid','极佳的，非常好的；华丽的；壮丽的','uk :ˈsplen.dɪd, us :ˈsplen.dɪd','[We had splendid food/a splendid holiday/splendid weather. \n 我们的食物／我们的假期／我们碰到的天气简直太棒了。 \n, You look splendid in that outfit. \n 你穿那一身衣服简直棒极了。 \n]\n','2020-04-03',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/ukspl/uksplee002.mp3'),('splintered','（木头、玻璃、塑料等的）尖细条，尖碎片裂成碎片','uk :ˈsplɪn.tər, us :ˈsplɪn.tɚ','[The girl had a splinter (of wood) in her toe. \n 女孩脚趾上扎进了一块（木头）碎片。 \n, The edges of the plastic cover had cracked and splintered. \n 塑料罩子的边缘裂成了碎片。 \n, igurative \n The danger is that the Conservative Party may splinter into several smaller political parties. \n 危险在于保守党可能会分裂成几个小的政党。 \n]\n','2019-12-19',0,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/ukspl/uksplee010.mp3'),('spoiler','（汽车的）气流偏导器；（机翼的）扰流器（某报刊或电视台抢先或同期推出的）试图抢风头的文章（或节目）,剧透·','uk :ˈspɔɪ.lər, us :ˈspɔɪ.lɚ','[]\n','2020-01-20',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/ukspl/uksplee021.mp3'),('spondulix','（幽默的说法）货币；钱，金钱；财产','uk :spɒnˈduː.lɪks, us :spɑːnˈduː.lɪks','[]\n','2019-12-20',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/ukspl/uksplee028.mp3'),('sponge','（擦洗物品用的）海绵（用海绵或布）擦拭，擦洗海绵蛋糕白吃，白要；（尤指）吃白饭用湿海绵（或湿布）擦，擦洗','uk :spʌndʒ, us :spʌndʒ','[Give it a sponge with a damp cloth - that will remove the blood stains. \n 用湿布擦一下——能把血迹擦掉。 \n, sponging off the state \n 靠国家来养活 \n, Most food stains will come off if you sponge the material with a little detergent. \n 用一点去污剂能去除布料上的大部分食物污渍。 \n, The doctor told me to sponge Erik down with cold water in order to lower his temperature. \n 医生告诉我用冷水给埃里克擦身，以帮他降低体温。 \n]\n','2020-01-23',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/ukspl/uksplee029.mp3'),('spreadsheet','（尤用于商务的）电子表格程序','uk :ˈspred.ʃiːt, us :ˈspred.ʃiːt','[]\n','2019-10-07',0,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/ukspo/ukspotl019.mp3'),('spur','激励，鞭策；促进，加速（用马刺）策（马）前行马刺，靴刺山嘴，尖坡刺激；激励','uk :spɜːr, us :spɝː','[Rising consumer sales have the effect of spurring the economy to faster growth. \n 消费的增长有刺激经济加速发展的作用。 \n, Spurred (on) by her early success, she went on to write four more novels in rapid succession. \n 受到之前成功的鼓励，她紧接着又连续写了4部小说。 \n, He spurred his horse on and shouted  Faster! Faster!  \n 他用马刺策马向前，嘴里喊着“驾！驾！” \n, The manager said that the team s win on Saturday would be a spur to even greater effort this season. \n 主教练说球队周六的胜利将会激励全队在本赛季中有更好的表现。 \n]\n','2020-02-19',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/ukspr/uksprin021.mp3'),('square','正方形，四方形正方形物，四方形物（城镇中的）广场（常包括周围的建筑）（游戏中棋盘的）格直角尺，丁字尺古板的人；老古董使成平方；使成二次幂正方形的，四方形的（与长度单位连用）平方的（紧接长度单位后）…见方正的；相等的；水平的两清的，互不欠账的平局的直线的，笔直的乏味的；古板守旧的使成平方；使成二次幂（表示决心已定）挺起胸膛，挺直身子','uk :skweər, us :skwer',NULL,'2020-03-25',0,5,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/uksqu/uksquab010.mp3'),('squeeze','（尤指从各方面）挤压，捏，挤，榨给…带来财务困难，使陷入财务困境（困难地）挤进，挤过挤压，捏；榨减少；削减；限制通货紧缩，银根紧缩拥挤；挤入','uk :skwiːz, us :skwiːz','[Cut the lemon in half and squeeze the juice into the bowl. \n 把柠檬一切为二，将汁挤到碗里。 \n, As she waited to go into the exam, he squeezed her hand (= pressed it affectionately with his hand) and wished her good luck. \n 在她候考时，他捏了捏她的手，祝她好运。 \n, Once he had finished cleaning the floor, he squeezed the cloth out. \n 他擦完地板之后，把抹布拧干。 \n, He reloaded the gun, took aim, and then squeezed (= pulled back) the trigger. \n 他重新上好子弹，瞄准目标，然后扣动了扳机。 \n, igurative \n The studio is using all sorts of marketing tricks to squeeze as much profit from the movie as they can. \n 该制片厂使出种种营销伎俩，从电影中榨取尽可能多的利润。 \n, Small businesses are being squeezed by heavy taxation. \n 重税使小企业在财务上捉襟见肘。 \n, She squeezed through the crowd and found a seat at the front. \n 她从人群中挤过去，在前面找了个座位。 \n, They managed to squeeze under the fence and get into the festival without paying. \n 他们没付钱，而是从围栏下硬挤过去，进入了庆祝会场。 \n, She gave the present a quick squeeze and tried to guess what was inside. \n 她捏了捏礼物，想猜猜里面是什么。 \n, Garnish the fish with some fresh parsley and a squeeze of lemon. \n 用新鲜西芹作鱼的饰菜，再挤上几滴柠檬汁。 \n, The squeeze on profits in the oil industry has led to thousands of redundancies. \n 石油产业利润的减少导致数千人失业。 \n, The squeeze on local spending means that many services will have to be cut. \n 地方支出的缩减意味着将不得不砍掉很多公共服务。 \n, The government has imposed a sharp credit squeeze in an attempt to hold down inflation. \n 为抑制通货膨胀，政府施行了严格的信贷紧缩政策。 \n, I can give you a lift, but it ll be a tight squeeze as I m taking four other people as well. \n 我可以开车捎你一程，不过我还要载4个人，所以会很挤。 \n]\n','2020-02-21',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/uksqu/uksquab029.mp3'),('squirm','（因紧张、尴尬或疼痛）动来动去，来回扭动','uk :skwɜːm, us :skwɝːm','[Nobody spoke for at least five minutes and Rachel squirmed in her chair with embarrassment. \n 至少有5分钟谁也没说话，雷切尔尴尬地在椅子上扭来扭去。 \n, The fish squirmed on the ground for a few moments and then lay still. \n 鱼在地上翻腾了一会儿就不动了。 \n]\n','2020-02-28',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/uksqu/uksquee015.mp3'),('squishy','软弱','uk :ˈskwɪʃ.i, us :ˈskwɪʃ.i','[ squishy banana\n, he whole idea of what constitutes a disability is squishy. \n, he definition of spam is squishy - a message that you delete I may think is a worthwhile offer.\n, hey feel he is too squishy on issues such as the rights of suspected terrorists.\n, he toy shop has a range of squishies for kids who love to squeeze, squish, and squash. \n, quishy white bread\n]\n','2019-12-13',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english/uk_pron/u/uks/uksqu/uksquee019.mp3'),('staircase','（建筑物内通常带有扶手的）楼梯','uk :ˈsteə.keɪs, us :ˈster.keɪs','[She descended the sweeping (= long and wide) staircase into the crowd of photographers and journalists. \n 她走下又长又宽的楼梯，来到摄影师和记者中间。 \n]\n','2019-12-20',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/uksta/ukstabl030.mp3'),('statistical','统计的；统计学的','uk :stəˈtɪs.tɪ.kəl, us :stəˈtɪs.tɪ.kəl','[statistical errors/evidence \n 统计错误／证据 \n]\n','2019-10-07',0,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/uksta/ukstate017.mp3'),('stereotype','','uk :ˈster.i.ə.taɪp, us :ˈster.i.ə.taɪp','[racial/sexual stereotypes \n 陈旧的种族偏见／性别成见 \n, He doesn t conform to/fit/fill the national stereotype of a Frenchman. \n 他不符合一般人头脑中法国人的形象。 \n, The characters in the book are just stereotypes. \n 书中的人物毫无新意。 \n, The study claims that British advertising stereotypes women. \n 这项研究声称英国的广告对女性抱有成见。 \n, We tried not to give the children sexually stereotyped toys. \n 我们尽量不给孩子们玩带有性别成见的玩具。 \n]\n','2021-03-26',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/ukste/ukstere004.mp3'),('sterile','（生物）不育的；（土地）贫瘠的，不长作物的缺乏想象力的；缺乏新意的；无生气的消过毒的，无菌的','uk :ˈster.aɪl, us :ˈster.əl','[Mules are usually sterile. \n 骡子通常无法生育。 \n, One of the side effects of the drug could be to make men sterile. \n 这种药物的副作用之一是可能会导致男性不育。 \n, a sterile argument \n 毫无新意的论点 \n, The operation must be carried out under sterile conditions. \n 手术必须在无菌条件下进行。 \n]\n','2020-01-23',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/ukste/ukstere007.mp3'),('stiff','硬的，挺的，坚实的不易弯曲的；不易活动的（人或身体部位）僵硬的，强直的拘谨的，局促的，生硬的严厉的，严格的；艰难的强风烈性酒／白兰地／杜松子酒（等等）（价格）高昂的，过高的十分，非常…的人死尸不付…欠下的钱','uk :stɪf, us :stɪf','[stiff cardboard \n 硬纸板 \n, a stiff collar \n 硬领 \n, His clothes were stiff with dried mud. \n 他的衣服上的泥干了，硬邦邦的。 \n, This hair spray has made my hair stiff. \n 这种发胶使我的头发变硬了。 \n, Mix the powder and water into a stiff paste. \n 把粉末和水混合成稠糊。 \n, The handle on this door is rather stiff. \n 这扇门的把手相当紧。 \n, The man s body was (as) stiff as a board when it was found in the snow. \n 在雪地里找到这名男子时，他的身体已经僵硬了。 \n, Sitting still at a computer terminal all day can give you a stiff neck. \n 在电脑前一动不动地坐上一整天会令人颈部发僵。 \n, The general is a tall man with steel spectacles and a stiff, pompous manner. \n 将军是个戴着金属框眼镜的高个男子，态度生硬，相当傲慢。 \n, The athlete was given a stiff punishment for using drugs. \n 这名运动员因服用违禁药物受到了严厉的惩罚。 \n, They are campaigning for stiffer penalties for people who drink and drive. \n 他们正在进行游说活动，要求对酒后驾车者处以更严厉的惩罚。 \n, There has been stiff opposition/resistance to the proposed tax increases. \n 增加税收的提案遭到了强烈的反对／抵制。 \n, It s a stiff climb to the top of the hill. \n 要爬上山顶很费劲。 \n, Some colleges have stiffer entry requirements than others. \n 有些大学比其他大学有更严格的入学资格要求。 \n, Both companies are worried about losing business in the face of stiff competition. \n 两家公司都担心在激烈的竞争中损失业务。 \n, A stiff whisky - that s what I need. \n 一杯烈性威士忌——这是我真正需要的。 \n, We had to pay a stiff membership fee to join the health club. \n 我们支付了一笔高昂的会费后才得以加入这家健康俱乐部。 \n, I got frozen stiff (= very cold) waiting at the bus stop. \n 我在公交车站等车时差点儿冻僵了。 \n, I was scared stiff when I heard someone moving around upstairs. \n 我听到楼上有人走来走去时吓坏了。 \n, a working stiff \n 工作狂 \n, you lucky stiff \n 你这个幸运的家伙 \n, They found a stiff in the river. \n 他们在河里发现了一具尸体。 \n, She stiffed the cab driver. \n 她没有付给出租车司机钱。 \n]\n','2019-12-27',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/uksti/ukstick006.mp3'),('stilt','（支撑建筑物高出地面或水面的）柱子，支材高跷','uk :stɪlts, us :stɪlts','[The houses are built on stilts to protect them from the annual floods. \n 房子建在柱桩上，以免遭受一年一度洪水的侵袭。 \n, to walk on stilts \n 踩高跷 \n]\n','2020-04-03',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukcld/ukcld01412.mp3'),('stimulating','（物）有启发性的（人）能激发热情的，激发灵感的（活动）增强活力的，促进身体机能的','uk :ˈstɪm.jə.leɪ.tɪŋ, us :ˈstɪm.jə.leɪ.t̬ɪŋ','[a stimulating discussion \n 具有启发性的讨论 \n, The classes look attractive and stimulating. \n 这些课程看起来既有吸引力又有启发性。 \n, a really stimulating teacher \n 真正循循善诱的老师 \n, Aerobics is one of the most stimulating forms of exercise. \n 有氧健身操是最能增强身体活力的锻炼之一。 \n]\n','2020-02-14',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/uksti/ukstick029.mp3'),('stockpile','储备物；囤积物（大量）储备，贮存；囤积','uk :ˈstɒk.paɪl, us :ˈstɑːk.paɪl','[They have a stockpile of weapons and ammunition that will last several months. \n 他们的武器和弹药储备足够支撑好几个月。 \n, The rebels have been stockpiling weapons. \n 叛乱分子一直在储备武器。 \n]\n','2020-03-31',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/uksto/ukstock011.mp3'),('stoic','克制感情的；（尤指面对逆境）坚忍的，隐忍的恬淡寡欲者；克制感情的人','uk :ˈstəʊ.ɪk, us :ˈstoʊ.ɪk','[We knew she must be in pain, despite her stoic attitude. \n 尽管她非常坚忍，但我们知道她一定很痛苦。 \n, He showed a stoic resignation towards his fate. \n 他在命运面前表现得听天由命，隐忍顺从。 \n, Local people were stoical about the damage caused by the hurricane. \n 当地居民默默承受了飓风造成的破坏。 \n, My father is a stoic by nature and found it hard to express his grief when my mother died. \n 我父亲天生隐忍克制，我母亲去世时他很难表露自己的悲伤之情。 \n]\n','2020-01-17',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/uksto/ukstock022.mp3'),('stomp','迈着重重的步子走；（尤指）怒气冲冲地走（常指为表示生气）跺（脚）；重踏，重踩','uk :stɒmp, us :stɑːmp','[She stomped up the stairs and slammed her bedroom door. \n 她噔噔噔地上了楼，重重地关上了卧室的门。 \n, He woke up in a bad mood and stomped off to the bathroom. \n 他一觉醒来心情不佳，噔噔地踩着重步走向浴室。 \n, The little boy was stomping his foot and refusing to take his medicine. \n 那个小男孩跺着脚不肯吃药。 \n, She stood by the road, stomping her feet to stay warm. \n 她站在路边，跺着脚让自己暖和些。 \n, I wish those people upstairs would stop stomping around. \n 我希望楼上那些人别再乱跺脚了。 \n, Why did you stomp on that insect? \n 你为什么要踩那只虫子？ \n]\n','2021-03-26',3,6,1,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/uksto/ukstoma003.mp3'),('stoned','（服用毒品后）神志恍惚的，飘飘然的去核的','uk :stəʊnd, us :stoʊnd','[They spent the evening getting stoned. \n 他们整个晚上都在吸食毒品，神志恍惚。 \n, stoned olives \n 去核橄榄 \n]\n','2020-02-21',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/uksto/ukstoma005.mp3'),('strain','压力；拉力，张力；作用力（肌肉等软组织的）损伤，拉伤，扭伤压力；紧张类型；品质；个性特点，禀性（动植物的）品系，株系，品种旋律；曲调滤，过滤（食物）（使）紧张，（使）承受压力；拉紧，绷紧；损伤（尤指金钱）过多使用','uk :streɪn, us :streɪn','[The hurricane put such a strain on the bridge that it collapsed. \n 在飓风强大的作用力下，桥塌了。 \n, As you get older, excess weight puts a lot of strain on the heart. \n 随着年龄的增长，体重过重会给心脏造成很大负担。 \n, Their constant arguments were putting a strain on their marriage. \n 他们持续不断的争吵使他们的婚姻关系非常紧张。 \n, The recent decline in the dollar has put a bigger strain on the economic system. \n 最近美元的贬值为经济体系带来了更大的压力。 \n, Migration into the cities is putting a strain on already stretched resources. \n 城市移民给已经过度紧张的资源带来了压力。 \n, a groin/hamstring strain \n 腹股沟／腘旁腱拉伤 \n, She s a lot better than she was but she s still not ready to face the stresses and strains of a job. \n 她比以前好多了，但仍然没有准备好应对工作的紧张和压力。 \n, He s been under a lot of strain recently. \n 他最近压力很大。 \n, A strain of puritanism runs through all her work. \n 她的所有作品都带有一种清教主义色彩。 \n, Scientists have discovered a new strain of the virus which is much more dangerous. \n 科学家们已经发现了一种危险得多的新病毒。 \n, I could hear the strains of Mozart in the background. \n 我听见背景音中有莫扎特的旋律。 \n, Could you strain the vegetables, please. \n 你能把菜滤一滤吗？ \n, The oil in which the fish is fried is strained off and used to cook potatoes. \n 煎鱼的油在过滤之后用来炸土豆了。 \n, I ve put on such a lot of weight recently - this dress is straining at the seams. \n 我最近胖了很多——这条裙子穿上后紧绷绷的。 \n, I strained a muscle in my back playing squash. \n 我打壁球拉伤了背肌。 \n, Don t watch TV in the dark - you ll strain your eyes! \n 不要在黑暗中看电视——会伤害你的眼睛！ \n, [ + to infinitive ] \n figurative \n I really had to strain (= try very hard) to reach those top notes. \n 我确实得铆足了劲儿才能唱出那些最高的音。 \n, igurative \n I was straining (my ears) (= listening hard) to hear what they were saying. \n 我竖起耳朵，拼命想听清他们在说什么。 \n, Increases in wholesale oil prices have strained the company s finances. \n 油料批发价的上涨让公司财务支出过多。 \n]\n','2020-04-03',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/ukstr/ukstrai004.mp3'),('strategies','战略；策略；计谋；行动计划；策划，部署','uk :ˈstræt.ə.dʒi, us :ˈstræt̬.ə.dʒi','[The president held an emergency meeting to discuss military strategy with the Pentagon yesterday. \n 总统昨天召开紧急会议，跟五角大楼商讨军事战略。 \n, Their marketing strategy for the product involves obtaining as much free publicity as possible. \n 他们对这一产品采取的市场策略包括尽可能去争取免费宣传的机会。 \n, [ + to infinitive ] \n We re working on new strategies to improve our share of the market. \n 我们正在制订新策略来增加我们的市场份额。 \n]\n','2020-01-23',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/ukstr/ukstrat003.mp3'),('strategy','战略；策略；计谋；行动计划；策划，部署','uk :ˈstræt.ə.dʒi, us :ˈstræt̬.ə.dʒi','[The president held an emergency meeting to discuss military strategy with the Pentagon yesterday. \n 总统昨天召开紧急会议，跟五角大楼商讨军事战略。 \n, Their marketing strategy for the product involves obtaining as much free publicity as possible. \n 他们对这一产品采取的市场策略包括尽可能去争取免费宣传的机会。 \n, [ + to infinitive ] \n We\'re working on new strategies to improve our share of the market. \n 我们正在制订新策略来增加我们的市场份额。 \n]\n','2019-10-07',0,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/ukstr/ukstrat003.mp3'),('stroke','中风（书写或绘画的）一笔，一画；笔画（用于口语中）斜杠，斜线击球（使用武器的）击，打泳姿；（游泳的）划水动作幸运／高明的举动(等等)一点儿工作果断之举；断然之举钟声，钟鸣；（尤指）整点报时声轻抚，抚摸轻抚，抚摸击球','uk :strəʊk, us :stroʊk','[She suffered/had a stroke that left her unable to speak. \n 她中风了，不能开口说话。 \n, a brush stroke \n 毛笔的笔触 \n, With a few bold strokes, she signed her name. \n 她粗粗几笔签下了名字。 \n, She returned the volley with a powerful stroke to win the game. \n 她奋力将凌空球击回，赢得了比赛的胜利。 \n, The punishment was 20 strokes of the lash. \n 惩罚是被抽20下鞭子。 \n, What s your best stroke when you re swimming? \n 你最擅长的泳姿是哪种？ \n, By a stroke of luck, someone else was walking along the trail and heard my shouts for help. \n 幸运的是，刚好有人从小路上经过，听到了我的呼救。 \n, She s been gossiping and hasn t done a stroke (of work) all morning. \n 她整个上午都在闲聊，一点儿活都没干。 \n, Ending negotiations was seen as a bold stroke by many commentators. \n 终止谈判被很多评论者视为大胆果断之举。 \n, By computerizing we could, at a (single)/in one stroke, improve efficiency and reduce costs. \n 计算机化能够使我们一下子既提高效率，又降低成本。 \n, How many strokes did you count? \n 你听见钟敲了几下？ \n, Don t be frightened, just give the horse a stroke. \n 别怕，你去摸一摸那匹马。 \n, Stroke the dog if you want, he won t bite. \n 想摸这条狗就摸，它不会咬人的。 \n, She lovingly stroked Chris s face with the tips of her fingers. \n 她深情地用指尖抚摸着克里斯的脸庞。 \n, The batsman stroked the ball effortlessly to the boundary. \n 击球手毫不费力地将球击到边线上。 \n]\n','2020-02-27',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/ukstr/ukstrik029.mp3'),('stuffy','（房间或建筑物）闷的，通风不畅的古板的，保守的，一本正经的','uk :ˈstʌf.i, us :ˈstʌf.i','[a stuffy office \n 空气污浊的办公室 \n, It s really hot and stuffy in here - let s open the window. \n 这里又热又闷——我们把窗户打开吧。 \n, The bedroom gets a little stuffy in the summer. \n 这个房间在夏天有点闷。 \n, Sir William had the ability to conduct proceedings in a dignified manner without ever becoming stuffy. \n 威廉爵士能够以庄重但毫不刻板的方式主持会议。 \n, She is trying to promote a less stuffy image of librarians. \n 他在努力提升图书管理员的形象，想使之显得不那么古板。 \n]\n','2020-01-20',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/ukstu/ukstubb024.mp3'),('sturdy','结实的，牢固的；强壮的坚决的，坚定的','uk :ˈstɜː.di, us :ˈstɝː.di','[sturdy walking boots \n 结实的徒步靴 \n, a sturdy table \n 结实的桌子 \n, sturdy little legs \n 结实的小腿 \n, They put up a sturdy defence of their proposal. \n 他们坚定地为自己的提议辩护。 \n]\n','2020-01-17',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/ukstu/ukstun_020.mp3'),('submission','提交；呈递顺从，屈服；不得以接受','uk :səbˈmɪʃ.ən, us :səbˈmɪʃ.ən','[No date has yet been set for the submission of applications. \n 申请的提交日期还未确定。 \n, The final deadline for submissions is 21 February. \n 提交的最后期限是2月21日。 \n, [ + that ] \n formal \n The judge will hear the defence s submission (= suggestion) that the case be dismissed. \n 法官将听取被告方撤销该案的意见。 \n, They thought the country could be bombed into submission. \n 他们认为轰炸可以使该国屈服。 \n, The teachers agreed to a special meeting, in submission to parents  demands. \n 在家长的要求下，老师们只得同意召开特别会议。 \n]\n','2020-01-24',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/uksub/uksubhe027.mp3'),('subscriber','订购者，订阅人；用户；定期捐款者','uk :səbˈskraɪ.bər, us :səbˈskraɪ.bɚ','[Cable television companies have launched major campaigns to increase their number of subscribers. \n 有线电视公司已开展大型促销活动以增加用户数。 \n]\n','2020-02-28',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/uksub/uksubmi009.mp3'),('substantially','在很大程度上大体上；基本上','uk :səbˈstæn.ʃəl.i, us :səbˈstæn.ʃəl.i','[The new rules will substantially change how we do things. \n 新规则会在很大程度上改变我们的行事方式。 \n, This model has leather seats, but the two cars are substantially the same. \n 这一型号有几个附加装置，但两款车大体上是一样的。 \n]\n','2020-03-05',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/uksub/uksubsp005.mp3'),('succor','帮助；（尤指）救助，救援帮助；（尤指）救助，救援','uk :ˈsʌk.ər, us :ˈsʌk.ɚ','[Her organization gave succour and strength to those who had been emotionally damaged. \n 她的机构向那些情感上受到过伤害的人提供帮助和支持。 \n, to succour the poor, help the helpless, support the weak \n 救助贫困者，帮助无助者，支持弱者 \n, Students should be encouraged, supported and succoured. \n 学生们应该受到鼓励、支持和帮助。 \n]\n','2020-01-20',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/uksub/uksubur021.mp3'),('succumb','屈从，屈服；放弃抵抗；承认失败病死；生病；受病痛折磨','uk :səˈkʌm, us :səˈkʌm','[The town finally succumbed last week after being pounded with heavy artillery for more than two months. \n 在遭受了两个多月的猛烈炮火轰击后，小镇最终在上星期放弃了抵抗。 \n, I m afraid I succumbed to temptation and had a piece of cheesecake. \n 我还是没顶住诱惑，吃了一块奶酪蛋糕。 \n, I felt sure it would only be a matter of time before he succumbed to my charms. \n 我确信他为我的魅力所倾倒只不过是个时间问题。 \n, Thousands of cows have succumbed to the disease in the past few months. \n 过去几个月里，几千头奶牛都得了这种病。 \n]\n','2020-01-20',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/uksub/uksubur024.mp3'),('suitable','适宜的，合适的','uk :ˈsuː.tə.bəl, us :ˈsuː.t̬ə.bəl','[The film is not suitable for children. \n 这部电影不适宜儿童观看。 \n, A conference was planned, but finding a suitable venue proved difficult. \n 已经拟定召开会议，但是要找到合适的会场却很困难。 \n, Each room has books, toys, and games that are suitable to that particular age group.  \n 每个房间里都放有适合特定年龄段的书籍、玩具和游戏。 \n, My mother doesn t like me to wear short skirts to church - she doesn t think they re suitable. \n 我妈妈不喜欢我穿着短裙去教堂——她认为这不太合适。 \n]\n','2020-02-21',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/uksug/uksugar011.mp3'),('summit','峰会，首脑会议，最高级会议山顶，顶峰顶峰，极点，巅峰','uk :ˈsʌm.ɪt, us :ˈsʌm.ɪt','[a summit meeting \n 首脑会议 \n, World leaders will meet next week for their annual economic summit. \n 世界各国领导人将在下周齐聚一堂，参加一年一度的经济峰会。 \n, On this day in 1784, Dr Michel Paccard and Jacques Balmat reached the summit of Mont Blanc. \n 1784年的今天，迈克尔‧帕卡德医生和雅克‧巴尔马特登上了勃朗峰的顶峰。 \n, I certainly haven\'t reached the summit of my career. \n 当然，我还没有达到事业的巅峰。 \n]\n','2019-10-08',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/uksul/uksulta014.mp3'),('superior','好于平均的，好过其他的，优越的（人）高傲的，傲慢的，有优越感的上司（的），上级（的）更靠近头，更远离脚的上司，上级','uk :suːˈpɪə.ri.ər, us :səˈpɪr.i.ɚ','[This is clearly the work of a superior artist. \n 这显然是一位优秀艺术家的作品。 \n, She was chosen for the job because she was the superior candidate. \n 因为她比其他应聘者更出色，所以她被选中做这份工作。 \n, For babies, breastfeeding is superior to bottle-feeding. \n 对婴儿来说，母乳喂养比奶瓶喂养好得多。 \n, The government troops were superior in numbers (= there were more of them). \n 政府军在人数上占优势。 \n, a superior manner/smile \n 傲慢的态度／微笑 \n, I can t stand Amanda - she s so superior. \n 我受不了阿曼达——她太高傲了。 \n, The soldier was reported to his superior officer for failing in his duties. \n 这个士兵失职之事被报告到了他的上级那里。 \n, The head is superior to the shoulder. \n 头比肩离脚更远。 \n, I will pass your complaint on to my superiors. \n 我会把您的投诉转达给我的上司。 \n]\n','2020-01-14',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/uksup/uksuper004.mp3'),('superiority','优越性，优势高傲自大，自觉优越优势；优越性','uk :suːˌpɪə.riˈɒr.ə.ti, us :səˌpɪr.iˈɔːr.ə.t̬i','[The Australian team soon demonstrated their superiority over the opposition. \n 澳大利亚队很快在对手面前显示出优势。 \n, Her sense of superiority makes her very unpopular. \n 她的优越感让她非常不受欢迎。 \n]\n','2020-03-18',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/uksup/uksuper005.mp3'),('supervised','监督，管理，指导','uk :ˈsuː.pə.vaɪz, us :ˈsuː.pɚ.vaɪz','[The UN is supervising the distribution of aid by local agencies in the disaster area. \n 联合国正在监督灾区的地方机构发放救援物资。 \n, The children play while two teachers supervise (= make certain that they behave correctly and are safe). \n 孩子们在两位教师的监管下玩耍。 \n]\n','2019-10-08',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/uksup/uksuper030.mp3'),('surfeit','过量，过剩','uk :ˈsɜː.fɪt, us :ˈsɝː.fɪt','[The country has a surfeit of cheap labour. \n 这个国家的廉价劳动力过剩。 \n]\n','2020-04-03',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/uksup/uksuppo027.mp3'),('surly','脾气坏的；不友好的，粗鲁无礼的','uk :ˈsɜː.li, us :ˈsɝː.li','[We were served by a very surly waiter. \n 为我们服务的侍者态度很差。 \n, He gave me a surly look. \n 他很不友好地看了我一眼。 \n]\n','2021-03-24',4,6,1,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/uksur/uksurge008.mp3'),('surrealism','超现实主义（20世纪的一个文艺流派）','uk :səˈrɪə.lɪ.zəm, us :','[]\n','2020-02-28',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/uksur/uksurge022.mp3'),('surrealistic','超现实的；离奇的；荒诞的','uk :səˌrɪəˈlɪs.tɪk, us :səˌriː.əˈlɪs.tɪk','[]\n','2020-02-28',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/uksur/uksurge024.mp3'),('suspend','停止，暂停，中止（因犯错而）暂令停职；暂令停学；暂令停止参加活动悬挂悬浮，漂浮','uk :səˈspend, us :səˈspend','[The ferry service has been suspended for the day because of bad weather. \n 因为天气恶劣，渡船已经停开了。 \n, The country\'s president has suspended the constitution and assumed total power. \n 总统废除了宪法，独揽大权。 \n, When you go to the theatre, you have to be willing to suspend disbelief (= to act as if you believe that what you are seeing is real or true, although you know that it is not). \n 去戏院看戏时你得对剧情深信不疑。 \n, I\'m suspending judgment (= not forming an opinion) on the book I\'m reading until I\'ve finished it. \n 把书读完之前我不会作任何评价。 \n, Mr Young was given a six-month jail sentence, suspended for two years (= if he commits another crime within two years, he will have to go to prison for six months for his original crime). \n 杨先生被判监禁6个月，缓期2年执行。 \n, She was suspended from school for fighting. \n 她因为打架而被勒令停学。 \n, He was suspended for four games after arguing with the referee. \n 跟裁判发生争执之后，他被停赛4场。 \n, The builders worked on wooden platforms, suspended by ropes from the roof of the building. \n 建筑工人站在用绳子从房顶上吊下来的木制平台上作业。 \n, It was very uncomfortable lying on the hospital bed with my legs suspended in the air. \n 我躺在医院的病床上，腿悬吊在半空，难受极了。 \n, The drug is suspended in a saline solution. \n 这种药悬浮在生理盐水中。 \n, A cloud of smoke was suspended in the air. \n 空中飘浮着一团烟雾。 \n]\n','2019-10-08',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/uksur/uksurro024.mp3'),('sustain','保持，维持，使持续，使继续维持…的生命，供养经历，遭受（尤指破坏或损失）（情感上）支持','uk :səˈsteɪn, us :səˈsteɪn','[The economy looks set to sustain its growth into next year. \n 看来经济的增长会持续到明年。 \n, He seems to find it difficult to sustain relationships with women. \n 他似乎觉得和女人维持关系并不容易。 \n, S \n The judge sustained (= accepted) the lawyer s objection. \n 法官接受了律师的反对意见。 \n, The soil in this part of the world is not rich enough to sustain a large population. \n 这里的土地不够肥沃，无法供养大量的人口。 \n, She sustained multiple injuries in the accident. \n 她在这次事故中多处受伤。 \n, Most buildings sustained only minimal damage in the earthquake. \n 在这次地震中，大多数建筑物受到的破坏都很小。 \n, The company has sustained heavy losses this year. \n 公司今年遭受了严重的亏损。 \n, She was sustained by the strength of her religious faith. \n 宗教信仰的力量支撑着她。 \n, The love of my family and friends sustained me through my ordeal. \n 家人和朋友的爱支撑着我渡过了难关。 \n]\n','2019-12-13',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/uksus/uksuspi003.mp3'),('swallow','吞咽，吞下，咽下（因为紧张、害怕或要开始说话而）做吞咽动作，咽口水吞掉；吞没大量使用，大量夺走（贵重之物）轻信；全盘接受不表露，不表现，抑制住吞，咽，吞咽燕子','uk :ˈswɒl.əʊ, us :ˈswɑː.loʊ','[My throat is so sore that it really hurts when I swallow. \n 我的喉咙很痛，吞咽起来很难受。 \n, He put a grape into his mouth and swallowed it whole. \n 他把一颗葡萄放进嘴里，整个儿吞了下去。 \n, He swallowed hard and said,  Dad, I have something to tell you.  \n 他狠劲儿咽了一下口水说：“爸，我有点事想告诉您。” \n, An increasing amount of the countryside is being swallowed (up) by the town. \n 越来越多的乡村被城镇吞没。 \n, Many small businesses have been swallowed (up) by large companies. \n 很多小企业已经被大公司吞并了。 \n, Taxes have swallowed up nearly half of my pay increase. \n 我的加薪有近一半都被税收抵消了。 \n, Not surprisingly, this excuse was too much for them to swallow. \n 不出所料，他们无法接受这个借口。 \n, He swallowed her story whole. \n 他对她的说法深信不疑。 \n, She swallowed his sales pitch hook, line, and sinker (= believed it completely). \n 她对他的推销之词深信不疑。 \n, She swallowed her disappointment, saying,  That s OK, it doesn t matter.  \n 她抑制住自己的失望说：“没事，没关系。” \n, He gave a swallow, then began speaking. \n 他咽了一下口水，然后开始说话。 \n]\n','2020-03-18',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/uksus/uksuspi018.mp3'),('swath','长条区域，大块区域；（尤指）长条田地，大块田地部分；范围绷带，布条，带子（用布）裹，绑，包，缠','uk :sweɪð, us :sweɪð','[Huge swathes of rainforest are being cleared for farming and mining. \n 为了耕种和采矿，大片大片的雨林被砍伐。 \n, These people represent a broad/wide swathe of public opinion. \n 这些人代表了广大人民的意见。 \n, His head was wrapped in swathes of bandages. \n 他的头上缠着绷带。 \n, He came out of the hospital swathed in bandages. \n 他从医院出来时身上缠满了绷带。 \n, I love to swathe (= dress) myself in silk. \n 我喜欢穿丝绸做的衣服。 \n]\n','2019-10-07',0,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/ukswa/ukswast004.mp3'),('swathe','长条区域，大块区域；（尤指）长条田地，大块田地部分；范围绷带，布条，带子（用布）裹，绑，包，缠','uk :sweɪð, us :sweɪð','[Huge swathes of rainforest are being cleared for farming and mining. \n 为了耕种和采矿，大片大片的雨林被砍伐。 \n, These people represent a broad/wide swathe of public opinion. \n 这些人代表了广大人民的意见。 \n, His head was wrapped in swathes of bandages. \n 他的头上缠着绷带。 \n, He came out of the hospital swathed in bandages. \n 他从医院出来时身上缠满了绷带。 \n, I love to swathe (= dress) myself in silk. \n 我喜欢穿丝绸做的衣服。 \n]\n','2019-10-07',0,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/ukswa/ukswast004.mp3'),('swear','诅咒，咒骂发（誓）；宣（誓）','uk :sweər, us :swer','[It was a real shock, the first time I heard my mother swear. \n 我第一次听见母亲骂脏话时觉得非常震惊。 \n, When the cab driver started to swear at him, he walked away. \n 当出租车司机开口对他骂脏话时，他走开了。 \n, I don t know anything about what happened, I swear (it). \n 我发誓我对所发生的事一无所知。 \n, [ + (that) ] \n You might find it difficult to believe, but I swear (that) the guy just came up to me and gave me the money. \n 你可能觉得这难以置信，但我发誓，那个人确实走过来把这些钱给了我。 \n, K informal \n She swore blind (= promised definitely) (that) she didn t know what had happened to the money. \n 她信誓旦旦地说她不知道钱哪儿去了。 \n, [ + to infinitive ] \n New gang members must swear to obey the gang leaders at all times. \n 新的帮会成员必须发誓在任何时候都服从帮会头目。 \n, In some countries, witnesses in court have to swear on the Bible. \n 在有些国家，出庭证人必须手按《圣经》宣誓。 \n, I swore an oath to tell the truth, the whole truth, and nothing but the truth. \n 我发誓要陈述实情，言无不尽，绝无半点虚言。 \n, A few of us knew what was going to happen, but we were sworn to secrecy (= we were made to promise to keep it a secret). \n 我们有几个人知道将要发生什么事，但我们已经发过誓要对此保密。 \n, I think his birthday is on the 5th, but I wouldn t/couldn t swear to it (= I am not completely certain about it). \n 我想他的生日是5号，但我并不完全肯定。 \n]\n','2020-02-26',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/ukswa/ukswast008.mp3'),('swell','肿胀，肿，膨胀（音乐声等）变大，增大，变响亮（缓慢的）波涛起伏（乐器）音量的变大极好的极好地','uk :swel, us :swel','[It was obvious she had broken her toe, because it immediately started to swell (up). \n 她的脚趾显然已经骨折，因为立刻肿起来了。 \n, The group recruited more members, swelling its ranks (= increasing its size) to more than 1.3 million. \n 这个团体招募了更多会员，总人数已超过130万人。 \n, iterary \n His heart/breast swelled with pride (= he felt very proud) as he stood watching his son graduate. \n 当他站在那里观看儿子的毕业典礼时，心中充满自豪。 \n, That s a swell idea! \n 那个主意好极了！ \n, Everything s going swell. \n 一切都很顺利。 \n]\n','2021-03-24',7,9,1,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/ukswe/uksweet002.mp3'),('swells','肿胀，肿，膨胀（音乐声等）变大，增大，变响亮（缓慢的）波涛起伏（乐器）音量的变大极好的极好地','uk :swel, us :swel','[It was obvious she had broken her toe, because it immediately started to swell (up). \n 她的脚趾显然已经骨折，因为立刻肿起来了。 \n, The group recruited more members, swelling its ranks (= increasing its size) to more than 1.3 million. \n 这个团体招募了更多会员，总人数已超过130万人。 \n, iterary \n His heart/breast swelled with pride (= he felt very proud) as he stood watching his son graduate. \n 当他站在那里观看儿子的毕业典礼时，心中充满自豪。 \n, That s a swell idea! \n 那个主意好极了！ \n, Everything s going swell. \n 一切都很顺利。 \n]\n','2021-03-23',3,6,1,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/ukswe/uksweet002.mp3'),('swift','迅速的，敏捷的，快的雨燕','uk :swɪft, us :swɪft','[The police took swift action against the rioters. \n 警方对暴动人员迅速采取了行动。 \n, Thank you for your swift reply. \n 感谢您的即时回复。 \n, The gazelle is one of the swiftest and most graceful of animals. \n 瞪羚是最敏捷、最优雅的动物之一。 \n]\n','2020-01-20',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/ukswe/uksweet010.mp3'),('swindle','诈骗，骗取（钱财）','uk :ˈswɪn.dəl, us :ˈswɪn.dəl','[They swindled local businesses out of thousands of dollars. \n 他们诈骗了当地企业几千美元。 \n]\n','2020-04-03',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/ukswe/uksweet022.mp3'),('swinging','令人兴奋的；时尚的','uk :ˈswɪŋ.ɪŋ, us :ˈswɪŋ.ɪŋ','[It s a nostalgia trip back into the youth culture of the swinging 60s. \n 这是一次感受风靡一时的60年代青年文化的怀旧之旅。 \n]\n','2020-01-03',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/ukswe/uksweet029.mp3'),('swivel','（使）转动，（使）旋转转动的，旋转的','uk :ˈswɪv.əl, us :ˈswɪv.əl','[She swivelled round to look out of the window. \n 她转过身看着窗外。 \n, The ostrich swivelled its head in our direction. \n 鸵鸟把头转向我们。 \n, a swivel chair \n 转椅 \n, a swivel lamp \n 旋转灯 \n]\n','2020-01-23',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/ukswi/ukswipe013.mp3'),('swollen','（swell的过去分词）肿大的；膨胀的；大于正常的','uk :ˈswəʊ.lən, us :ˈswoʊ.lən','[a bruised, swollen face \n 青肿的脸 \n, The stream is swollen because of the heavy rain. \n 天下了大雨，溪水涨了。 \n]\n','2020-02-19',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/ukswi/ukswipe018.mp3'),('symmetry','对称（性）；匀称（数学中的）对称（性）','uk :ˈsɪm.ə.tri, us :ˈsɪm.ə.tri','[The design of the house had a pleasing symmetry, its oblong shape being picked up in its elongated windows. \n 房子的设计透着一种赏心悦目的对称美，狭长的窗户使长方形的结构显得更加和谐。 \n]\n','2020-03-19',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/uksyb/uksybar026.mp3'),('sympathetic','有同情心的，同情的（书或电影中的人物）能引起共鸣的，让人同情的，让人有同感的支持的，赞同的','uk :ˌsɪm.pəˈθet.ɪk, us :ˌsɪm.pəˈθet̬.ɪk','[He suffers from back trouble too, so he was very sympathetic about my problem. \n 他自己也受到背痛的困扰，所以他对我的烦恼深表同情。 \n, She just needed someone who would lend a sympathetic ear to her (= listen to her in a kind and understanding way) once in a while. \n 她只是需要有个人能时不时以一种理解的态度听她倾诉。 \n, She comes across as a more sympathetic character in the movie. \n 她在影片中扮演的角色更能引起观众的共鸣。 \n, The party is considered to be sympathetic to/towards welfare reform. \n 这个政党被认为对福利改革抱赞同态度。 \n, Did he give your proposal/complaints a sympathetic hearing? \n 他是以赞同的态度倾听你的建议／投诉吗？ \n]\n','2020-03-19',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/uksyb/uksybar027.mp3'),('sympathy','同情（心），理解慰问，吊唁，吊慰支持，赞同支持参加罢工以支持（某人）','uk :ˈsɪm.pə.θi, us :ˈsɪm.pə.θi','[The president has sent a message of sympathy to the relatives of the dead soldiers. \n 总统已经向阵亡士兵的家属发去了唁电。 \n, I don t have much sympathy for her - I think she s brought her troubles on herself. \n 我不太同情她——我觉得她是在自找麻烦。 \n, I went along to the funeral in order to offer my sympathies. \n 我去参加了葬礼以表吊慰。 \n, I must confess I have some sympathy with his views. \n 我必须承认我比较赞同他的观点。 \n, Of those people questioned, 93 percent said their sympathies were with the teachers. \n 接受调查的人当中有93%表示支持教师。 \n, He is known to have right-wing sympathies. \n 大家都知道他支持右翼。 \n, The railway workers came out in sympathy with the miners. \n 铁路工人加入了罢工，声援煤矿工人。 \n]\n','2019-11-08',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/uksym/uksympa002.mp3'),('symptom','（疾病的）症状征兆，征候','uk :ˈsɪmp.təm, us :ˈsɪmp.təm','[He s complaining of all the usual flu symptoms - a high temperature, headache, and so on. \n 他说他出现了所有常见的感冒症状——高烧、头痛等。 \n, He s been HIV-positive for six years, but just recently he s started to develop the symptoms of AIDS. \n 他 HIV 病毒检测呈阳性已有6年时间，但直到最近才开始出现艾滋病的症状。 \n, It s her feeling that the recent outbreaks of violence are a symptom of the dissatisfaction that is currently affecting our society. \n 她觉得最近爆发的暴力事件表明目前不满情绪正在影响我们的社会。 \n]\n','2020-01-23',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/uksym/uksympa008.mp3'),('syncope','晕厥','uk :ˈsɪŋ.kə.pi, us :ˈsɪŋ.kə.pi','[Postural syncope occurs when the body cannot supply enough blood to the brain in the upright position because of low blood pressure. \n 直立时因血压过低导致大脑供血不足时会出现直立性晕厥。 \n]\n','2020-02-26',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/c/ces/cespu/cespuk001129.mp3'),('syndrome','综合征，征群，综合症状（用于多种病名中）综合征（特定情形下人的）典型负面特征，典型负面表现','uk :ˈsɪn.drəʊm, us :ˈsɪn.droʊm','[irritable bowel syndrome \n 肠易激综合征 \n, It s a classic case of the bored-housewife syndrome - she has nothing to do all day except eat and go shopping. \n 这是百无聊赖的家庭主妇的典型特征——她成天除了喝酒、购物，就没有什么事情可干了。 \n]\n','2020-01-23',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/uksym/uksympa022.mp3'),('synergistic','协同','uk :sɪn.əˈdʒɪs.tɪk, us :sɪn.ɚˈdʒɪs.tɪk','[he synergistic effect of two drugs given at the same time\n]\n','2020-02-21',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english/uk_pron/c/cal/cald4/cald4uk1527.mp3'),('synonym','同义词，近义词','uk :ˈsɪn.ə.nɪm, us :ˈsɪn.ə.nɪm',NULL,'2021-03-08',7,9,1,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/uksym/uksympa026.mp3'),('tactics','策略，手法战术','uk :ˈtæk.tɪk, us :ˈtæk.tɪk','[These bomb attacks represent a change of tactics by the terrorists. \n 这些炸弹袭击事件表明恐怖分子改变了策略。 \n]\n','2020-01-17',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukt/uktab/uktable029.mp3'),('talkative','爱说话的，健谈的；多嘴的','uk :ˈtɔː.kə.tɪv, us :ˈtɑː.kə.t̬ɪv','[She s a lively, talkative person. \n 她是个活泼健谈的人。 \n]\n','2019-12-27',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukt/uktaj/uktajik018.mp3'),('tangible','真实的；非想象的；可触摸的；可感知的','uk :ˈtæn.dʒə.bəl, us :ˈtæn.dʒə.bəl','[We need tangible evidence if we re going to take legal action. \n 如果我们要采取法律行动，就需要有实实在在的证据。 \n, Other tangible benefits include an increase in salary and shorter working hours. \n 其他实实在在的好处包括加薪和缩短工作时间。 \n]\n','2020-03-11',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukt/uktal/uktalmu021.mp3'),('tango','探戈舞；探戈舞曲','uk :ˈtæŋ.ɡəʊ, us :ˈtæŋ.ɡoʊ','[]\n','2019-12-20',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukt/uktal/uktalmu025.mp3'),('tariff','关税；关税表','uk :ˈtær.ɪf, us :ˈter.ɪf','[]\n','2019-10-08',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukt/uktar/uktarge002.mp3'),('teaser','有趣的难题；智力测验题','uk :ˈtiː.zər, us :ˈtiː.zɚ','[]\n','2020-01-10',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukt/uktea/ukteams012.mp3'),('temerity','鲁莽；冒失','uk :təˈmer.ə.ti, us :təˈmer.ə.t̬i',NULL,'2021-03-24',15,17,1,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukt/uktel/uktelex008.mp3'),('tendency','（思想、行为等的）倾向趋势（某事发展的）倾向','uk :ˈten.dən.si, us :ˈten.dən.si','[[ + to infinitive ] \n His tendency to exaggerate is well known. \n 他喜欢夸张是出了名的。 \n, There is a tendency for unemployment to rise in the summer. \n 夏季的失业率有上升的趋势。 \n, [ + to infinitive ] \n There is a growing tendency to regard money more highly than quality of life. \n 越来越多的人倾向于把金钱看得重于生活质量。 \n]\n','2020-03-05',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukt/uktem/uktempt013.mp3'),('tender','温柔的；温情的；关怀的；慈爱的（身体部位）疼痛的，一触即痛的（肉或蔬菜）嫩的，软的（植物）娇嫩的，不抗寒的年幼的；未成熟的投标出价购买（股票等）提出；提供投标（书）（期货交易中的）交割意向通知书对…招标（尤指挂在火车头后的）煤水车（用来在大船与陆地间运送人员或货物的）小船（通常裹有面包屑的）鸡胸脯肉；鸡里脊肉','uk :ˈten.dər, us :ˈten.dɚ','[a tender look/smile \n 温柔的眼神／微笑 \n, What you need is some tender loving care. \n 你需要的是体贴入微的关怀。 \n, My arm was very tender after the injection. \n 打针后我的胳膊一碰就疼。 \n, My steak was beautifully tender. \n 我的牛排做得很嫩，好极了。 \n, He was sent off to boarding school at the tender age of seven. \n 他在7岁就被送去上寄宿学校了。 \n, Five companies have tendered for the hospital contract. \n 已有5家公司投标承建该医院。 \n, Please tender the exact fare. \n 请如数交费。 \n, The health minister has tendered her resignation (= has offered to leave her job). \n 卫生部长已提交辞呈。 \n, The council has invited tenders for the building contract. \n 市政会已经为建筑工程招标。 \n, Education departments in all the prisons are being put out to tender. \n 现在正在对所有监狱的教管部门进行招标。 \n, The SS Nomadic was a tender to the ill-fated liner, Titanic. \n “漂流号”是后来遭受厄运的“泰坦尼克号”上搭载的一艘小艇。 \n, chicken tenders \n 鸡胸脯肉 \n]\n','2020-02-28',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukt/uktem/uktempt017.mp3'),('tenfold','十倍的有十个部分的（以）十倍（地)','uk :ˈten.fəʊld, us :ˈten.foʊld','[a tenfold increase \n 十倍的增长 \n, a tenfold classification \n 十部分的分类 \n, Membership grew more than tenfold this year.  \n 今年会员人数增长了十倍。 \n]\n','2020-01-24',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukb/ukb01/ukb01730.mp3'),('tenor','男高音（歌手）；次中音（乐器）大意；要旨；基调','uk :ˈten.ər, us :ˈten.ɚ','[a tenor saxophone \n 次中音萨克斯管 \n, What was the general tenor of his speech? \n 他演讲的主旨是什么？ \n]\n','2019-12-11',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukt/uktem/uktempt026.mp3'),('tense','（动词的）时态紧张的，焦虑的（局势）令人紧张的（身体或肌肉）僵直的，绷紧的（语音）紧的；紧张音的（使）（身体或肌肉）绷紧，（使）变得僵直紧张的，焦虑的','uk :tens, us :tens','[ I sing  is in the present tense and  I sang  is in the past tense. \n I sing是现在式，I sang是过去式。 \n, She was very tense as she waited for the interview. \n 在等待面试时她非常紧张。 \n, There were some tense moments in the second half of the game. \n 比赛的下半场有几次紧张的局面。 \n, Don t tense your shoulders, just relax. \n 别缩紧肩膀，放松点。 \n, I could feel myself tense up as he touched my neck. \n 他摸我脖子时，我能感觉到自己的身体绷紧了。 \n, You seem all tensed up. Are you still waiting for that call? \n 你好像很紧张。你还在等那个电话吗？ \n]\n','2020-02-28',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukt/ukten/uktense001.mp3'),('tension','（精神上的）紧张，焦虑，焦急（互不信任的人群之间的）紧张关系；紧张局势（铁丝或绳子的）拉力，张力','uk :ˈten.ʃən, us :ˈten.ʃən','[You could feel the tension in the room as we waited for our exam results. \n 我们等待考试结果出来的时候，你可以感觉到屋子里的紧张气氛。 \n, ethnic/racial tension \n 民族／种族间的紧张关系 \n, There are growing tensions between the two countries. \n 两国间的关系日益紧张。 \n]\n','2019-10-08',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukt/ukten/uktense006.mp3'),('tepid','（液体）温热的，微热的（反应）不热情的，不热烈的','uk :ˈtep.ɪd, us :ˈtep.ɪd','[I got a tepid response to my suggestion. \n 我的建议得到的反应很平淡。 \n]\n','2020-02-21',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukt/ukten/uktense016.mp3'),('territory','领土；领域；领地；活动范围（某一动物或人想控制的）领地；地盘（知识等的）领域，范围','uk :ˈter.ɪ.tər.i, us :ˈter.ə.tɔːr.i','[He was shot down in enemy territory. \n 他在敌方领土上被击落。 \n, The UN is sending aid to the occupied territories. \n 联合国正在向被占领地区提供援助。 \n, The robin keeps other birds off that part of the garden - that\'s his territory. \n 这只知更鸟不许其他鸟儿进入花园的那块地方，那是它的领地。 \n, The director is back on familiar territory with his latest film. \n 该导演的最新电影又转回到了他所熟悉的题材上。 \n]\n','2019-10-08',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukt/ukter/uktermi026.mp3'),('thaw','（使）融化；（使）解冻变得友好；变得放松（关系的）缓和，改善融雪期；化冰期；解冻期','uk :θɔː, us :θɑː',NULL,'2021-03-11',9,11,1,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukt/uktet/uktetch029.mp3'),('theft','盗窃；偷窃行为','uk :θeft, us :θeft','[Unfortunately, we have had several thefts in the building recently. \n 很不幸，我们楼里最近发生了几起盗窃案。 \n, Shoplifting is theft. \n 偷拿商店的商品是偷窃。 \n]\n','2020-01-03',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukt/ukthe/uktheat008.mp3'),('theorist','理论家','uk :ˈθɪə.rɪst, us :ˈθiː.ɚ.ɪst','[a political theorist \n 政治理论家 \n]\n','2020-03-06',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukt/ukthe/uktheat028.mp3'),('theory','理论；学说；意见理论上，从理论上讲','uk :ˈθɪə.ri, us :ˈθɪr.i','[economic theory \n 经济理论 \n, scientific theory \n 科学理论 \n, Darwin s theory of evolution \n 达尔文的进化论 \n, He has a theory that the hole was caused by a meteorite. \n 他认为那个洞是陨石坠落形成的。 \n, In theory, the journey should take three hours, but in practice it usually takes four because of roadworks. \n 按理说行程应该只要3小时，但由于道路施工，实际上通常会需要4小时。 \n]\n','2020-03-19',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukt/ukthe/uktheat030.mp3'),('thorn','（植物茎上的）刺，荆棘','uk :θɔːn, us :θɔːrn','[]\n','2020-03-13',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukt/ukthi/ukthirt014.mp3'),('thoroughly','非常仔细地','uk :ˈθʌr.ə.li, us :ˈθɝː.ə.li','[I thoroughly enjoyed the performance. \n 我非常喜欢这个演出。 \n, We went through the report thoroughly but couldn t find the information anywhere. \n 我们仔细查看了该报告，但没有找到我们需要的信息。 \n]\n','2020-02-28',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukt/ukthi/ukthirt020.mp3'),('thou','汝，尔，你（尤指钱数）一千（thousand 的非正式说法）','uk :ðaʊ, us :ðaʊ','[ How much do you think it cost him?   About thirty thou.  \n “你估计这个东西花了他多少钱？”“大约3万。” \n]\n','2020-04-03',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukt/ukthi/ukthirt023.mp3'),('thrive','茁壮成长；兴旺，繁荣','uk :θraɪv, us :θraɪv','[His business thrived in the years before the war. \n 战前那些年，他的生意很兴隆。 \n, She seems to thrive on stress. \n 她似乎很擅长在压力下工作。 \n]\n','2020-01-24',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukt/uktho/ukthoug026.mp3'),('throw-a-fit','大发脾气','','null\n','2020-03-06',0,0,0,'null'),('thrust','推挤；刺；戳；插入要点，要旨，中心点猛推；刺牵引力，驱动力','uk :θrʌst, us :θrʌst','[She thrust the money into his hand. \n 她把钱塞进他手中。 \n, They thrust a microphone in front of me and fired questions at me. \n 他们把麦克风推到我面前，不断向我发问。 \n, She thrust the papers at me (= towards me). \n 她把报纸塞给我。 \n, The bodyguards thrust past the crowd to get at the cameraman. \n 保镖挤过人群直扑摄影师。 \n, The main thrust of her argument was that women are compromised by the demands of childcare. \n 她的主要论点是妇女受到需要照看孩子的拖累。 \n]\n','2020-03-06',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukt/ukthr/ukthroa018.mp3'),('thump','嘭嘭敲打，（使）砰然作响重击，捶击（某人）头痛欲裂（某人）心怦怦直跳砰然落下；物体落下的声音重击，捶击','uk :θʌmp, us :θʌmp','[Someone was thumping on the door. \n 有人在使劲敲门。 \n, He thumped him in the face. \n 他一拳狠狠打在他的脸上。 \n, When I woke up my mouth was dry and my head was thumping. \n 我醒来时口干舌燥、头痛欲裂。 \n, She stood outside his room, her heart thumping. \n 她站在他的房门外，心怦怦直跳。 \n, She fell to the floor with a thump. \n 她重重地摔倒在地板上。 \n, If he does that again I m going to give him a thump (= hit him with my closed hand). \n 如果他再那样做，我要好好揍他一顿。 \n]\n','2020-03-25',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukt/ukthr/ukthroa026.mp3'),('thwart','反对；阻挠；挫败','uk :θwɔːt, us :θwɔːrt',NULL,'2021-03-26',11,10,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukt/ukthu/ukthund012.mp3'),('tingling','感到刺痛强烈地感到（激动或恐惧）刺痛引起刺痛的','uk :ˈtɪŋ.ɡəl, us :ˈtɪŋ.ɡəl','[My fingers and toes are tingling with the cold. \n 我的脚趾和手指冻得刺痛。 \n, There s a line in that poem that makes my spine tingle every time I read it. \n 每当我读起那首诗，里面有一行诗句总是让我感到激动不已。 \n, She tingled with fear as she entered the dark alleyway. \n 她走进那黑暗的小巷时，感到一阵阵恐惧。 \n, There s a slight tingle in my wrists. \n 我的手腕有微微的刺痛感。 \n, She stroked his head, sending tingles down his spine. \n 她抚摸着他的头，令他感到无比激动。 \n, The massage had left me with a pleasant tingly sensation. \n 按摩后我感到阵阵畅快。 \n]\n','2020-02-19',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukt/uktim/uktimin013.mp3'),('tiptoed','踮着脚尖用脚尖走，踮着脚走','uk :ˈtɪp.təʊ, us :ˈtɪp.toʊ','[The children stood on tiptoe in order to pick the apples from the tree. \n 为了摘到树上的苹果，孩子们踮起了脚尖。 \n, They walked across the room on tiptoe so as not to wake the baby. \n 他们蹑手蹑脚地穿过房间，生怕惊醒婴儿。 \n, He waited until his daughter was asleep, then tiptoed quietly out of the room. \n 他等女儿睡着后才蹑手蹑脚地悄悄走出了房间。 \n]\n','2020-03-05',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukt/uktip/uktippe008.mp3'),('tobacco-stained','烟草染色','Yāncǎo rǎnsè','\n','2019-12-20',0,0,0,'https://translate.google.cn/translate_tts?ie=UTF-8&q=tobacco-stained&tl=ja&tk=734078.853770&client=webapp&prev=input'),('toggle','套索扣，栓扣钉切换键（点击同一按键来）切换','uk :ˈtɒɡ.əl, us :ˈtɑː.ɡəl','[Select the function you require by pointing to the toggle (= image of a button on the screen) with the mouse and then clicking. \n 将鼠标移向切换图标并点击，选择你所需要的功能。 \n, Use this key to toggle between the two typefaces. \n 用这个键在这两种字体间切换。 \n, By toggling this key, you can switch the italics on and off. \n 用这个键来切换，你能够打开和关闭斜体字。 \n]\n','2019-12-13',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukt/uktob/uktobyj018.mp3'),('tolerance','宽容；忍受；容忍忍耐力；忍受力（动植物对药物或毒药的）耐受性公差；容许偏差','uk :ˈtɒl.ər.əns, us :ˈtɑː.lɚ.əns',NULL,'2021-03-08',3,8,1,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukt/uktol/uktold_004.mp3'),('tolerate','宽容；容忍忍耐；忍受','uk :ˈtɒl.ər.eɪt, us :ˈtɑː.lə.reɪt','[I will not tolerate that kind of behaviour in my class. \n 在我的课堂上我不会容许那种行为。 \n, [ + -ing verb ] \n I won t tolerate lying. \n 我不会容忍说谎。 \n, These ants can tolerate temperatures that would kill other species. \n 这些蚂蚁能够忍受可以导致其他物种死亡的高温。 \n]\n','2020-02-13',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukt/uktol/uktold_007.mp3'),('toll','（道路、桥梁等的）通行费长途电话费伤亡；损失；破坏（使）缓慢而反复地鸣响','uk :təʊl, us :toʊl','[Tolls are now collected electronically on most motorways. \n 现在绝大部分高速公路采用电子收费。 \n, Is Bayonne a toll call (= a more expensive phone call) from New York? \n 从纽约打电话到贝约纳是长途吗？ \n, Independent sources say that the death toll from the earthquake runs into thousands. \n 独立消息人士称地震中的伤亡人数达到数千人。 \n, In the distance, a church bell tolled the hour (= showed the time by ringing). \n 远处传来教堂报时的钟声。 \n]\n','2020-01-24',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukt/uktol/uktold_009.mp3'),('tongue','舌头（用作食物的动物的）舌头，口条舌状物（尤指鞋舌）语言说话方式','uk :tʌŋ, us :tʌŋ','[I burned my tongue on some soup last night. \n 我昨晚喝汤时烫着了舌头。 \n, immigrants struggling to learn a foreign tongue \n 艰难学习外语的移民 \n, an ancient tongue \n 古老的语言 \n, She is a prolific writer with critical views and a sharp (= severe and critical) tongue. \n 她是一个多产的作家，观点尖锐，语言犀利。 \n]\n','2020-04-01',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukt/ukton/uktoned006.mp3'),('tormented','折磨；痛苦精神上的折磨与痛苦痛苦（或烦恼）之源折磨；使痛苦','uk :ˈtɔː.ment, us :ˈtɔːr.ment','[The family said they had endured years of torment and abuse at the hands of their neighbours. \n 这家人说多年来他们一直忍受着邻居们的欺凌羞辱。 \n, Waiting for the result of the medical tests was sheer torment. \n 等待医疗检查的结果简直就是一种折磨。 \n, He spent the night in torment, trying to decide what was the best thing to do. \n 他在痛苦中度过了那个晚上，思量着最好该怎么做。 \n, Nothing can describe the torments we went through while we were waiting for news. \n 我们在等待消息时所受的精神折磨是无法用语言描述的。 \n, Writing reports was a monthly torment to him. \n 写报告每个月都让他头疼。 \n, The animals are tormented mercilessly by flies and mosquitoes. \n 动物受到苍蝇和蚊子的无情折磨。 \n, The camera focused on a group of women whose faces were tormented by/with (= showed that they were suffering) grief. \n 照相机对准了一群满脸忧伤的女人。 \n, It tormented me all day - had I said the wrong thing and hurt her feelings? \n 这件事折磨了我一整天——我是不是说错了话伤了她的感情？ \n]\n','2020-03-19',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukt/uktor/uktorme001.mp3'),('torture','拷打；拷问；折磨；虐待折磨，煎熬拷打；拷问；折磨；虐待使精神上受到折磨；使痛苦；使苦恼','uk :ˈtɔː.tʃər, us :ˈtɔːr.tʃɚ','[Half of the prisoners died after torture and starvation. \n 半数的囚犯死于拷打和饥饿。 \n, He revealed the secret under torture. \n 在严刑拷打之下他吐露了秘密。 \n, The rush-hour traffic was sheer torture as usual. \n 交通高峰期像往常一样简直就是一种煎熬。 \n, It is claimed that the officers tortured a man to death in a city police station. \n 据称在一所市警察局里警察将一名男子拷打致死。 \n, He tortured himself for years with the thought that he could have stopped the boy from running into the road. \n 他本可以阻止那个男孩跑到马路上去的想法多年来一直折磨着他。 \n]\n','2019-11-13',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukt/uktor/uktorme030.mp3'),('tract','（尤指有关宗教或政治主题的）短文，传单大片土地（用于建房、采油等特定目的）丈量过的土地（人或动物体内的）管，道，束','uk :trækt, us :trækt','[a moral/religious/socialist tract \n 关于道德说教／宗教／社会主义者的短文 \n, Have you read John Milton s tracts on divorce? \n 你读过约翰‧弥尔顿论离婚的小册子吗？ \n, The house is surrounded by vast tracts of woodland. \n 这幢房子周围是大片的林地。 \n, a 132-acre tract in Irving \n 位于埃尔温的一块132英亩的土地 \n, the urinary/respiratory/digestive tract \n 尿道／呼吸道／消化道 \n]\n','2020-01-23',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukt/uktow/uktowni026.mp3'),('tragedy','悲剧性事件，灾难，不幸悲剧（作品）','uk :ˈtrædʒ.ə.di, us :ˈtrædʒ.ə.di','[The pilot averted a tragedy when he succeeded in preventing the plane from crashing. \n 飞行员成功阻止了飞机的坠毁，从而避免了一场悲剧。 \n, Hitler s invasion of Poland led to the tragedy of the Second World War. \n 希特勒入侵波兰引发了第二次世界大战这场浩劫。 \n, His life was touched by hardship and personal tragedy. \n 他的一生充满了艰辛和不幸。 \n, Not long after they moved, tragedy struck - their son was killed in an accident. \n 他们刚搬家不久就遭遇了不幸——儿子在一次交通事故中丧生。 \n, [ + (that) ] \n It s a tragedy (that) so many young people are unable to find jobs. \n 这么多的年轻人找不到工作，真是不幸。 \n, Shakespeare s tragedies include  Hamlet ,  King Lear , and  Othello . \n 莎士比亚的悲剧作品包括《哈姆雷特》、《李尔王》和《奥赛罗》。 \n, In Greek tragedy, the role of the chorus is to express the audience s reactions to what is happening in the play. \n 在希腊悲剧中，合唱队的作用是表达观众对剧情发展的反应。 \n]\n','2020-02-27',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukt/uktra/uktract020.mp3'),('trailer','拖车；挂车（大卡车的）挂车旅行拖车（影视节目、广播的）预告片','uk :ˈtreɪ.lər, us :ˈtreɪ.lɚ','[The car was pulling a trailer with a motorcycle on it. \n 这辆汽车拖着一辆挂车，挂车上面载着一辆摩托车。 \n, I saw a trailer for the new series of  Game of Thrones  last night. \n 我昨晚看了新一季《权力的游戏》的预告片。 \n]\n','2020-01-10',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukt/uktra/uktract026.mp3'),('tranquility','平静，宁静祥和','uk :træŋˈkwɪl.ə.ti, us :træŋˈkwɪl.ə.t̬i','[living in peace and tranquillity \n 生活在平静祥和之中 \n, I love the tranquillity of the countryside. \n 我喜欢乡村的恬静。 \n]\n','2020-03-18',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukt/uktra/uktrain016.mp3'),('transaction','交易','uk :trænˈzæk.ʃən, us :trænˈzæk.ʃən','[a business transaction \n 生意 \n, Each transaction at the foreign exchange counter seems to take forever. \n 外币兑换柜台的每笔交易似乎都要花很长时间。 \n, We need to monitor the transaction of smaller deals. \n 我们需要监控规模较小的交易。 \n]\n','2019-10-07',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukt/uktra/uktrain021.mp3'),('transatlantic','横越大西洋的；大西洋两岸国家的','uk :ˌtræn.zətˈlæn.tɪk, us :ˌtræn.zætˈlæn.t̬ɪk','[transatlantic flights \n 横越大西洋的飞行 \n, a transatlantic phone call \n 来自大西洋彼岸的电话 \n]\n','2019-10-07',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukt/uktra/uktrain022.mp3'),('transcend','超越，超过，超出（尤指界限）','uk :trænˈsend, us :trænˈsend','[The best films are those which transcend national or cultural barriers. \n 最优秀的影片是那些超越了民族或文化障碍的影片。 \n, The underlying message of the film is that love transcends everything else. \n 这部电影内在的中心意旨是爱超越一切。 \n]\n','2020-02-28',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukt/uktra/uktrain023.mp3'),('transmit','播送，发射，传送（信号）传递；传播','uk :trænzˈmɪt, us :trænsˈmɪt','[Radio Seven transmits on 201 medium wave (= uses those particular radio waves to broadcast on). \n 广播七台通过中波201千赫广播。 \n, The information is transmitted electronically to the central computer. \n 这些信息以电子化的方式传送到中央计算机。 \n, a sexually transmitted disease \n 性传播疾病 \n, Cholera is transmitted through contaminated water. \n 霍乱是通过受污染的水传播的。 \n, Some diseases are transmitted from one generation to the next. \n 有些疾病是世代遗传的。 \n, Somehow your panic and fear transmits itself to the horse that you re riding. \n 不知怎么的，你的恐惧会传染给你骑的马。 \n]\n','2020-01-24',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukt/uktra/uktrans105.mp3'),('transparency','透明性，透明幻灯片；透明正片（公开处理，非秘密进行的）透明度','uk :trænˈspær.ən.si, us :trænˈsper.ən.si','[The old-fashioned type of plastic lacked transparency. \n 老式塑料透明性不好。 \n, We want more transparency in government. \n 我们想要政府更透明。 \n]\n','2020-01-24',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukt/uktra/uktrans112.mp3'),('transparent','透明的清楚易懂的；显而易见的公开和诚实的，无秘密的','uk :trænˈspær.ənt, us :trænˈsper.ənt','[Grow the bulbs in a transparent plastic box, so the children can see the roots growing. \n 把球茎种在透明的塑料盒里，这样孩子们就能看到根的生长。 \n, Her blouse was practically transparent! \n 她的衬衫几乎是透明的！ \n, I think we should try to make the instructions more transparent. \n 我觉得我们应该尽可能使指令更清楚易懂些。 \n, We are committed to being totally transparent about our charges. \n 我们致力于让收费完全透明。 \n]\n','2020-03-06',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukt/uktra/uktrans113.mp3'),('treachery','背叛，背信弃义','uk :ˈtretʃ.ər.i, us :ˈtretʃ.ɚ.i','[From his cell on board ship, the captain wrote about the treachery of his crew. \n 在船上被关押的房间里，船长记录下了船员们的背叛行为。 \n]\n','2020-03-18',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukt/uktre/uktreac001.mp3'),('treaty','条约；协定','uk :ˈtriː.ti, us :ˈtriː.t̬i','[a peace treaty \n 和平条约 \n, the treaty on European union \n 欧盟条约 \n, [ + to infinitive ] \n We\'ve signed/concluded a treaty with neighbouring states to limit emissions of harmful gases. \n 我们和几个邻国签署／缔结了限制有害气体排放的条约。 \n]\n','2019-10-08',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukt/uktre/uktreac018.mp3'),('trend','趋势，趋向；倾向，动向时尚；新款式时尚的（某一时刻在社交媒体或网站上）被提及最多的词语（主题或名字）','uk :trend, us :','[Surveys show a trend away from home-ownership and toward rented accommodation. \n 调查表明，出现了一种从私人拥有住房转向租赁住房的趋势。 \n, There s been a downward/upward trend in sales in the last few years. \n 过去几年中销售额一直呈下降／上升趋势。 \n, Whatever the latest fashion trend, you can be sure Nicki will be wearing it. \n 不管是什么样的流行款式，尼基肯定会穿。 \n, The trend at the moment is for a more natural and less made-up look. \n 时下的潮流是多一分自然，少一些妆容。 \n, Her long skirt is right on trend this winter. \n 她的长半截裙今年冬季正流行。 \n, Within minutes of the incident her name was trending on Twitter. \n 事件发生几分钟后她的名字就在推特上传开了。 \n, Click here for a list of trending topics. \n 点击这里可以看到热门主题的名单。 \n]\n','2020-02-13',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukt/uktre/uktremu008.mp3'),('trial','审判，审理试验；试用惹麻烦的人；令人伤脑筋的事物；考验预试，模拟考试试验；试用','uk :traɪəl, us :traɪəl','[trial proceedings \n 审判程序 \n, Trial by jury is a fundamental right. \n 由陪审团审判是一项基本权利。 \n, It was a very complicated trial that went on for months. \n 该审判非常复杂，历时数月。 \n, She s going on/standing trial for fraud. \n 她将因诈骗而受审。 \n, They re doing clinical trials on a new drug. \n 他们正在对一种新药进行临床试验。 \n, They ve employed her for a six-month trial (period). \n 他们录用了她，试用期为6个月。 \n, You can have the equipment on a trial basis (UK also on trial), and if you don t like it you can give it back. \n 你可以采用试用方式购买设备，如果不喜欢可以退货。 \n, She was a real trial to her parents when she was younger. \n 她年轻时真令父母头疼。 \n, The book is all about the trials of growing up. \n 这本书讲的全是成长过程中经历的种种烦恼。 \n, Trials take place in July. \n 预试在七月举行。 \n, We will trial the new drug in several hospitals. \n 我们将在几家医院试用这种新药。 \n]\n','2020-02-13',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukt/uktre/uktremu018.mp3'),('tricky','难办的；难对付的欺骗性的；狡猾的；诡计多端的','uk :ˈtrɪk.i, us :ˈtrɪk.i',NULL,'2020-03-25',0,5,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukt/uktri/uktribu010.mp3'),('trivialize','使显得不重要','uk :ˈtrɪv.i.ə.laɪz, us :ˈtrɪv.i.ə.laɪz','[I don t want to trivialize the problem, but I do think there are more important matters to discuss. \n 我并不是要贬低这个问题的重要性，我确实认为有更重要的事情需要讨论。 \n]\n','2020-01-14',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukt/uktri/uktrium008.mp3'),('tropical','热带的（天气）极热的','uk :ˈtrɒp.ɪ.kəl, us :ˈtrɑː.pɪ.kəl','[tropical fish \n 热带鱼 \n, a tropical island/region/climate \n 热带岛屿／地区／气候 \n, Leprosy is one of the few tropical diseases which could soon be eradicated. \n 有几种热带病可以很快彻底根除，麻风病就是其中之一。 \n, She specializes in tropical medicine (= the treatment of diseases from the tropical areas of the world). \n 她专门医治热带病。 \n, The Amazon river basin contains the world s largest tropical rainforest. \n 亚马孙河流域有世界上最大的热带雨林。 \n, The hurricane was downgraded to a tropical storm when its speed dropped to 70mph. \n 当飓风的速度降为每小时70英里时，就减弱为热带风暴。 \n, The weather was positively tropical last summer. \n 去年夏天天气非常热。 \n]\n','2020-02-27',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukt/uktro/uktropi001.mp3'),('trumpet','小号；喇叭（尤指象等大型动物的）吼声吹嘘；鼓吹','uk :ˈtrʌm.pɪt, us :ˈtrʌm.pət','[We could hear the elephants trumpeting in the distance. \n 我们可以听见远处大象的吼声。 \n, The museum has been loudly trumpeting its reputation as one of the finest. \n 该博物馆一直在大肆吹嘘自己是世界上最好的博物馆之一。 \n, Their much-trumpeted  low low prices  affect only five percent of the goods that they sell. \n 他们极力吹嘘的“一降再降”活动只包括他们所卖商品的5%。 \n]\n','2020-01-03',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukt/uktru/uktruam018.mp3'),('trustee','受托人','uk :ˌtrʌsˈtiː, us :ˌtrʌsˈtiː','[the museum s board of trustees \n 博物馆的受托人理事会 \n]\n','2020-03-11',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukt/uktru/uktrust001.mp3'),('tub-thumping','暴言','Zhòng jī','\n','2021-03-08',6,8,1,'https://translate.google.cn/translate_tts?ie=UTF-8&q=tub-thumping&tl=ja&tk=143096.268940&client=webapp&prev=input'),('tumble','跌倒；滚下，坠落；倒塌（价值）暴跌，骤降跌跌撞撞地走摔倒，跌跤；跌落','uk :ˈtʌm.bəl, us :ˈtʌm.bəl','[I lost my footing and tumbled down the stairs. \n 我一失足从楼梯上滚了下来。 \n, At any moment the whole building could tumble down. \n 整幢建筑随时有可能坍塌。 \n, He lost his balance and tumbled over. \n 他失去平衡摔倒了。 \n, Share prices tumbled yesterday. \n 昨天股票大跌。 \n, An excited group of children tumbled out of school/the bus. \n 一群激动不已的孩子一窝蜂地跑出了学校／跑下了公共汽车。 \n, She took a nasty tumble on her way to work and grazed her arm. \n 她上班途中重重摔了一跤，擦伤了胳膊。 \n]\n','2020-01-03',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukt/uktub/uktube_023.mp3'),('tumbler','（无柄无脚的）杯子','uk :ˈtʌm.blər, us :-blɚ','[]\n','2020-01-03',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukt/uktub/uktube_025.mp3'),('turquoise','绿松石青绿色青绿色的','uk :ˈtɜː.kwɔɪz, us :ˈtɝː.kɔɪz','[the clear turquoise water of the bay \n 海湾清澈碧绿的海水 \n]\n','2020-03-19',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukt/uktur/ukturnk012.mp3'),('tweak','扭，拧稍稍改进','uk :twiːk, us :twiːk','[Standing in front of the mirror she tweaked a strand of hair into place. \n 她站在镜子前，把一缕头发捋好。 \n, The software is pretty much there - it just needs a little tweaking. \n 软件差不多好了——只需要一点点改进。 \n, You just need to tweak the last paragraph and then it\'s done. \n 你只需要把最后一段稍作修改就可以了。 \n]\n','2019-10-09',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukt/uktux/uktuxed007.mp3'),('tweed','（杂色的）粗花呢粗花呢服装；（尤指）粗花呢套装','uk :twiːd, us :twiːd','[a tweed jacket \n 花呢短上装 \n, a tweed skirt and sensible shoes \n 花呢裙子及舒适实用的鞋子 \n, He wore tweeds and smoked a pipe. \n 他身上穿着花呢衣服，嘴里叼着烟斗。 \n]\n','2021-03-11',9,11,1,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukt/uktux/uktuxed009.mp3'),('twerp','傻瓜，笨蛋','uk :twɜːp, us :twɝːp','[]\n','2020-01-10',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukt/uktux/uktuxed020.mp3'),('twitchiness','焦虑','null','null\n','2020-01-20',0,0,0,'null'),('tyranny','暴政，专制统治暴虐，专横','uk :ˈtɪr.ən.i, us :ˈtɪr.ən.i',NULL,'2020-03-25',0,5,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukt/uktyp/uktypho016.mp3'),('unanimous','（团体）意见一致的；（决定或裁决）一致通